INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('1','easy microwave breakfast bowls','## Ingredients\n### Base\n- 1½ cups shredded potatoes (bagged or freshly grated)\n- 2 large whole eggs or equivalent egg substitute\n- ¼ cup cottage cheese\n### Vegetables\n- 2 tablespoons chopped onion\n- 2 tablespoons chopped green pepper\n### Seasoning\n- ¼ teaspoon black pepper\n- Pinch of salt\n### Optional\n- ¼ cup shredded cheese\n- Precooked lean meat (e.g., deli ham, rotisserie chicken)\n- Salsa\n- Hot sauce\n- Fresh herbs','## Instructions\n### Base Preparation\n1. In a microwave-safe bowl, add 1½ cups of shredded potatoes.\n   - If using thicker-cut potatoes, microwave for 2 minutes before proceeding.\n### Combining Ingredients\n2. Add 2 large whole eggs (or equivalent egg substitute), ¼ cup cottage cheese, chopped onion, chopped green pepper, black pepper, and salt to the bowl.\n3. Mix all ingredients thoroughly.\n### Cooking\n4. Microwave the mixture for 2-3 minutes, or until the eggs are fully cooked.\n   - Cooking time may vary depending on microwave power; monitor to prevent overcooking.\n### Optional Toppings\n5. After cooking, top with shredded cheese, precooked lean meat, salsa, hot sauce, or fresh herbs as desired.','assets/recipe-thumbnails/00abb195-2813-46c8-838a-a70946666da5.png',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('2','protein french toast pancakes','## Ingredients\n### French Toast Pancakes\n- 3 slices bread of choice\n- ½ cup Greek yogurt (preferably high protein)\n- ½ cup milk or milk substitute\n- 1 scoop protein powder\n- 2 large whole eggs\n- 2 tablespoons light or sugar-free syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ½ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- ½ tablespoon butter, oil, or cooking spray (for cooking)','## Instructions\n### Preparing the Bread\n1. Cut each slice of bread into approximately 9 small pieces.\n### Making the Batter\n1. In a large mixing bowl, combine Greek yogurt, milk, and protein powder. Mix until smooth.\n2. Add eggs, syrup, vanilla extract, and ground cinnamon to the mixture. Stir until all ingredients are well combined.\n### Cooking the Pancakes\n1. Place the bread pieces into the batter, ensuring they are fully coated. Let them soak briefly, but avoid over-soaking to prevent sogginess.\n2. Heat a pan or griddle over medium heat and add butter, oil, or cooking spray.\n3. Once heated, place the soaked bread pieces onto the pan, forming pancakes of your desired size.\n4. Cook each side for approximately 2-3 minutes, or until golden brown.\n5. Repeat the process until all the bread pieces are cooked.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('3','cottage cheese mashed potatos','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 5 pounds potatoes (Idaho, russet, or sweet potatoes)\n- 1½ cups cottage cheese\n- ½ cup high-protein milk or milk substitute\n- 3 tablespoons butter\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 5 teaspoons minced garlic\n### Optional Add-ins\n- 1–2 scoops unflavored protein powder\n- Grated parmesan cheese\n- Taco seasoning\n- Fresh herbs (e.g., chives)\n- Additional garlic','## Instructions\n### Preparing the Potatoes\n1. **Wash the potatoes thoroughly**, even if peeling, to prevent cross-contamination.\n2. **Decide on peeling**: You can leave the skins on for added texture and nutrients or peel them based on your preference.\n3. **Choose a cooking method**:\n   - **Baking**: Poke each potato with a fork several times. Place them on a baking sheet and bake at 425°F (218°C) for 50–55 minutes.\n   - **Boiling**: Cut the potatoes in half and place them in a pot with enough salted water to cover them by about an inch. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, approximately 15–20 minutes.\n   - **Microwaving**: Poke each potato with a fork. Microwave 1–2 potatoes at a time for 5–6 minutes, depending on your microwave''s power.\n### Preparing the Cottage Cheese Mixture\n1. While the potatoes are cooking, **blend the cottage cheese** in a food processor or powerful blender until smooth.\n2. If using, **add the unflavored protein powder** to the cottage cheese and blend until fully incorporated.\n### Mashing the Potatoes\n1. Once the potatoes are cooked, **place them in a large bowl**.\n2. **Lightly mash the potatoes** using a potato masher or fork.\n3. **Add the following ingredients** to the mashed potatoes:\n   - Blended cottage cheese mixture\n   - High-protein milk or milk substitute\n   - Butter\n   - Black pepper\n   - Salt\n   - Minced garlic\n4. **Mash and mix** all ingredients until smooth and well combined. Adjust the consistency by adding more milk if desired.\n### Optional Add-ins\n1. For additional flavor, consider **mixing in**:\n   - Grated parmesan cheese\n   - Taco seasoning\n   - Fresh herbs\n   - Additional garlic\n2. **Top with chives** before serving, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('4','protein pancake mug cake','## Ingredients\n### Main Component\n- ½ cup just-add-water pancake mix\n- 1 scoop (approximately 30g) protein powder (your favorite flavor)\n- 3–4 ounces milk or milk substitute','## Instructions\n### Main Component\n1. In a microwave-safe bowl, combine ½ cup pancake mix, 1 scoop protein powder, and 3–4 ounces of milk or milk substitute.\n2. Mix until the batter is smooth. The consistency should be easily pourable; add more milk if necessary.\n3. Optionally, coat the microwave-safe bowl with cooking spray before pouring in the batter.\n4. Microwave on high for 1 minute. Cooking times may vary depending on microwave wattage; adjust accordingly.\n5. Carefully remove from microwave and let it cool slightly before enjoying.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('5','eggnog protein custard','## Ingredients\n### Custard\n- 1 large whole egg\n- 1 cup eggnog (regular, almond nog, or a mix of eggnog and high-protein milk)\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 2 ounces Greek yogurt (preferably eggnog flavored; vanilla or cinnamon can be used as alternatives)\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener (optional, adjust based on desired sweetness)\n### Topping\n- Ground cinnamon\n- Ground nutmeg','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n1. Preheat your oven to 350°F (176°C).\n2. In a mixing bowl, blender, or shaker bottle, combine the egg, eggnog, protein powder, Greek yogurt, and sweetener (if using). Mix until smooth.\n### Baking\n1. Pour the mixture into a baking dish with at least a 2-cup capacity.\n2. Sprinkle ground cinnamon and nutmeg on top.\n3. Place the baking dish into a larger pan filled halfway with water to create a water bath.\n4. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until the custard is set.\n### Serving\n1. Remove from the oven and let it cool.\n2. Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('6','easy protein pumpkin crisp','## Ingredients\n### Pumpkin Layer\n- 3 large whole eggs\n- 1 can pumpkin puree\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 tablespoon pumpkin pie spice\n- 3/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 3 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 4 tablespoons syrup or honey\n- 1/2 cup milk or milk substitute\n- 1 pinch salt\n### Crumble Topping\n- 1 1/2 cups rolled oats\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar substitute\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 3/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1 cup unsweetened apple sauce','## Instructions\n### Pumpkin Layer\n- Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until smooth.\n### Crumble Topping\n- Mix all ingredients in another bowl until well combined.\n### Assembly\n- Coat a 9-inch baking dish or skillet with cooking spray.\n- Pour in the pumpkin layer, then add the crumble topping (using hands).\n- Optionally top with crushed pecans.\n- Bake at 350°F (176°C) for 30-35 minutes, until edges are golden brown.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('7','slow cooker taco soup','## Ingredients\n### Meat Base\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound lean ground beef (93% lean)\n- 1/2 onion, chopped (optional) \n- 4 teaspoons minced garlic (optional) \n### Vegetables & Legumes\n- 1 (28-ounce) can diced tomatoes (fire-roasted preferred) utm_source=chatgpt.com)\n- 1 (8-ounce) can bone broth (low or no sodium) \n- 1 (8-ounce) jar salsa (your choice of flavor)\n- 1 (4-ounce) can diced green chiles \n- 1 (15.5-ounce) can dark red kidney beans, drained and rinsed \n- 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 (15.25-ounce) can corn (regular or Southwest style) \n### Seasonings\n- 1 ounce packet low-sodium taco seasoning mix \n- 1.5 tablespoons ranch seasoning mix ','## Instructions\n### Meat Preparation\n1. In a large skillet over medium heat, add olive oil. \n2. Once heated, add ground beef, breaking it up as it cooks.\n3. Add chopped onion and minced garlic; cook until beef is browned, approximately 5-10 minutes. \n4. Drain excess fat if necessary, then transfer the mixture to the slow cooker.\n### Soup Assembly\n1. To the slow cooker, add diced tomatoes, bone broth, salsa, green chiles, kidney beans, black beans, corn, taco seasoning, and ranch seasoning. \n2. Stir all ingredients thoroughly to combine.\n### Cooking\n1. Cover the slow cooker and cook on low heat for 7-8 hours or on high heat for 3-4 hours. ','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('8','pumpkin protein custard','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 3 large whole eggs\n- ¾ cup Greek yogurt (flavors like pumpkin or vanilla recommended)\n- 1 (15-ounce) can pumpkin puree\n- 2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n- 3 tablespoons sugar-free syrup\n- 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice\n- 2 scoops protein powder (vanilla flavor recommended)\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 1-2 tablespoons sweetener (optional, adjust based on sweetness preference)\n','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (176°C).\n2. In a large mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients.\n3. Mix until smooth, using a hand mixer or whisk.\n### Baking\n4. If your baking dish isn''t non-stick, lightly coat it with cooking spray.\n5. Pour the mixture into your chosen baking dish. For individual servings, use two 1½-cup ramekins; for a single serving, use a larger dish.\n6. Bake in the preheated oven:\n   - For 1½-cup ramekins: 50-55 minutes.\n   - For a larger dish: baking time may be longer; check for doneness.\n7. Once baked, allow the custard to cool. Refrigerate for a better flavor experience.\n**Note:** Topping with sugar-free whipped topping or a protein frosting is optional.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('9','protein cornbread cookies','## Ingredients\n### Cornbread Cookies\n- 100 grams cornbread mix (e.g., Jiffy Corn Muffin Mix)\n- 1½ scoops vanilla protein powder\n- ⅛ cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 3 ounces vanilla Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon melted butter\n- ½ tablespoon honey (or preferred sweetener)\n- ¼ teaspoon baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n### Buttercream Protein Frosting\n- 3 ounces cream cheese (e.g., fat-free)\n- 5 tablespoons whipped topping (e.g., Cool Whip)\n- 1 tablespoon melted butter\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener of choice','## Instructions\n### Cornbread Cookies\n1. **Prepare the Dough**: In a mixing bowl, combine the cornbread mix, vanilla protein powder, applesauce, Greek yogurt, melted butter, honey, baking soda, and a pinch of salt. Stir until the mixture reaches a smooth consistency.\n2. **Chill**: Place the bowl in the refrigerator and let the dough cool for 20-30 minutes.\n3. **Shape the Cookies**: After chilling, preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Scoop portions of the dough onto the prepared baking sheet, shaping them to your desired size.\n4. **Bake**: Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 6-8 minutes. For a doughier texture, opt for the shorter baking time; for a firmer texture, bake a bit longer.\n### Buttercream Protein Frosting\n1. **Prepare the Frosting**: In a bowl, mix together the softened cream cheese, whipped topping, melted butter, vanilla protein powder, and sweetener until a smooth frosting forms. \n2. **Frost the Cookies**: Once the cookies have cooled, spread the buttercream frosting on top of each cookie.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('10','greek yogurt cake','## Ingredients\n### Cake Batter\n- 3 large whole eggs\n- 1 cup high-protein Greek yogurt (low-fat preferred)\n- 1–2 tablespoons sweetener (optional, adjust to taste)\n- 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n- 3 tablespoons cornstarch\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n### Optional Toppings\n- Sugar-free chocolate chips \n- Ground cinnamon \n- Protein frosting\n','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (176°C).\n- Grease your chosen baking pan (bread pan, cake pan, or muffin tin) with cooking spray or line it with parchment paper.\n### Mixing the Batter\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the eggs, Greek yogurt, sweetener (if using), vanilla extract, cornstarch, and baking soda.\n- Mix until the batter reaches a smooth consistency.\n### Baking\n- Pour the batter into the prepared pan.\n- Bake at 350°F (176°C) for the following approximate times:\n  - Bread Pan: 25 minutes \n  - 6-inch Cake Pan: 30–35 minutes\n  - Muffin Tin: 10–15 minutes \n- The cake is done when a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n### Cooling and Serving\n- Allow the cake to cool before serving.\n- Optional: Top with sugar-free chocolate chips, a sprinkle of ground cinnamon, or your choice of protein frosting.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('11','steak & stout pie','## Ingredients\n### Filling\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 kilogram (about 2.2 pounds) beef brisket, trimmed and cut into 2-centimeter (1-inch) cubes \n- Kosher salt \n- Freshly ground black pepper \n- 4 tablespoons all-purpose flour \n- 1 tablespoon unsalted butter\n- 3 carrots, peeled and diced \n- 2 stalks celery, diced \n- 2 yellow onions, large diced \n- 4 cloves garlic, finely chopped \n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste \n- 1 tablespoon brown sugar \n- 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce \n- 2 teaspoons finely chopped thyme \n- 2 bay leaves \n- 1 1/2 cups stout \n- 2 cups beef stock \n- 2 medium potatoes, peeled and diced \n### Pastry\n- 3/4 cup unsalted butter \n- 3/4 cup water \n- 2 3/4 cups all-purpose flour, plus more for dusting \n- 1 teaspoon kosher salt \n- 1 egg \n- 1 tablespoon milk ','## Instructions\n### Filling Preparation\n1. Preheat your oven to 325°F (160°C). \n2. In a large heavy-bottomed pot, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Season beef brisket cubes with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. Working in batches, sear the beef until browned on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n3. In the same pot, melt butter over medium heat. Add carrots, celery, onions, and garlic; sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n4. Stir in tomato paste and cook for another 2 minutes. \n5. Add brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chopped thyme, and bay leaves; mix well. \n6. Return seared beef to the pot. Sprinkle flour over the mixture and stir to combine.\n7. Pour in stout and beef stock, stirring to deglaze the pot. Bring to a simmer.\n8. Add diced potatoes, cover, and transfer the pot to the preheated oven. Bake for 1 hour.\n9. After 1 hour, remove from the oven, discard bay leaves, and let the filling cool to room temperature. \n### Pastry Preparation\n1. In a saucepan, melt butter with water over medium heat. \n2. In a large bowl, combine flour and kosher salt.\n3. Pour the melted butter and water mixture into the flour mixture. Stir until a dough forms.\n4. Divide the dough into two equal portions, shape into discs, wrap in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.\n### Assembly\n1. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n2. On a lightly floured surface, roll out one disc of dough to fit a 9-inch pie dish.\n3. Place the rolled-out dough into the pie dish, trimming any excess overhang.\n4. Pour the cooled filling into the pastry-lined pie dish.\n5. Roll out the second disc of dough and place it over the filling. Trim excess dough, pinch edges to seal, and cut a few slits on top to allow steam to escape.\n6. In a small bowl, whisk together the egg and milk. Brush the egg wash over the top crust.\n7. Bake for 45-50 minutes, or until the pastry is golden brown.\n8. Let the pie rest for 10 minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('12','cottage cheese fritata','## Ingredients\n### Frittata Base\n- 6 large eggs (or 12 large egg whites)\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 3/4 cup grated cheese (e.g., Parmesan)\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n- Salt to taste\n### Vegetables\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 red onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1 cup mushrooms, sliced\n### Optional Protein Topping\n- 2 ounces cooked ham, sausage, or bacon','## Instructions\n### Prepare the Frittata Base\n1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (176°C).\n2. In a blender or food processor, combine the eggs, cottage cheese, grated cheese, black pepper, and salt. Blend until smooth.\n### Prepare the Vegetables\n1. Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a 10-inch oven-safe skillet over medium heat.\n2. Add the chopped green bell pepper, red onion, and minced garlic to the skillet. Sauté for a few minutes until tender.\n3. Add the chopped spinach and sliced mushrooms. Continue to sauté until the vegetables are softened.\n### Assemble and Cook\n1. Pour the frittata base mixture over the sautéed vegetables in the skillet. Stir gently to combine.\n2. If desired, top with the cooked ham, sausage, or bacon.\n3. Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the center is set and the top is lightly golden.\n4. Remove from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('13','pineapple whip','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 2 cups frozen pineapple\n- 1 small frozen banana\n- 2 ounces pineapple juice\n- 3 ounces Greek yogurt (vanilla, pineapple, or lemon)\n- 1½ scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 1–2 tablespoons sweetener (optional, depending on protein powder sweetness)','## Instructions\n1. **Blend Ingredients**: Combine the frozen pineapple, frozen banana, pineapple juice, Greek yogurt, and protein powder in a food processor or blender.\n2. **Blend Until Smooth**: Process until the mixture becomes creamy and increases in volume. Scrape down the sides as needed.\n3. **Serve**: Spoon the whip into bowls or use a pastry bag for a decorative touch.\n**Note**: For a homemade pastry bag, cut the corner off a sealable bag.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('14','mozarella stuffed meatballs','## Ingredients\n### Meatball Base\n- 1 ½ pounds ground meat (beef, turkey, or chicken)\n- 2 large whole eggs\n- ¾ cup bread crumbs (low sodium preferred)\n- ½ cup parmesan cheese (grated)\n- 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning\n- ½ teaspoon black pepper\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n### Mozzarella Stuffing\n- ½ cup mozzarella cheese (sticks, block, or pearls)\n### Optional Seasonings\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1 ½ teaspoons minced garlic\n- 1 small onion (chopped)\n- Hot sauce, crushed red pepper, or other seasoning for heat\n### Cooking (if using slow cooker)\n- 1 jar pasta sauce','## Instructions\n### Meatball Preparation\n- Mix all base ingredients (except mozzarella and pasta sauce) in a large bowl.\n- Roll mixture into balls and press a thumb into the center to create space.\n- Stuff each ball with mozzarella, then seal and roll it into a full ball.\n### Cooking\n- **Slow Cooker:** Place meatballs in slow cooker, cover with pasta sauce, and cook on high for 2 ½-3 hours or low for 5-6 hours until they reach 165°F.\n- **Air Fryer/Oven:** Cook at 400°F for 11-14 minutes in an air fryer or 20-25 minutes in the oven, flipping halfway.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('15','protein oat cups','## Ingredients\n### Oat Cup Mixture\n- 2 ½ scoops protein powder (your choice flavor)\n- 2 ounces Greek yogurt (your choice flavor)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 ripe banana\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n### Chocolate Layer\n- 4 tablespoons sugar-free chocolate chips\n','## Instructions\n### Oat Cup Base\n- Mix protein powder, Greek yogurt, vanilla extract, and mashed banana in a bowl.\n- Add rolled oats and mix until fully incorporated.\n### No Bake Method\n- Melt chocolate chips in the microwave and spread over the oat mixture.\n- Freeze for 20-30 minutes until chocolate hardens.\n### Baked Method\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (176°C).\n- Bake in a muffin pan for around 10 minutes.\n- Let cool, then add melted chocolate and freeze for 20-30 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('16','egg roal bowl','## Ingredients\n### Main dish\n- 1 lb ground meat (chicken, beef, turkey, or pork)\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp minced garlic\n- 1/2 sweet onion, chopped\n- Black pepper to taste\n### Egg roll filling\n- 16 oz coleslaw mix\n- 4 oz shredded carrots\n- 1 tbsp rice vinegar\n- 1 tbsp sesame oil\n- 2 oz low sodium soy sauce\n- 1 tsp ground ginger\n- Optional: 2 tbsp sweet & sour sauce, hoisin, teriyaki, or oyster sauce\n### Optional toppings\n- Chopped green onion\n- Sesame seeds\n- Hot sauce\n- Hard boiled eggs','## Instructions\n### Cooking the meat\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add ground meat and brown, breaking it up as it cooks.\n- Add garlic, onion, and black pepper, continuing to cook until browned.\n### Egg roll filling\n- Lower heat and add coleslaw mix, shredded carrots, rice vinegar, sesame oil, soy sauce, and ginger.\n- Stir and cook for 5-10 minutes until the desired tenderness is reached.\n### Serving\n- Optionally, add green onion, sesame seeds, hot sauce, or chopped hard-boiled eggs before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('17','greek yogurt pancakes','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 2 large whole eggs\n- 6 ounces Greek yogurt (highest protein you can find)\n- 2 ounces milk (or milk substitute)\n- ¾ cup all-purpose flour (or oat flour substitute)\n- ½ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1-2 tablespoons sweetener\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder','## Instructions\n### Pancake Preparation\n- Mix all ingredients in a bowl until smooth.\n- Heat a pan on medium and coat with non-stick spray.\n- Pour the mix into the pan and cook each side for 2-3 minutes.\n- Repeat until the mix is used up.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('18','chocolate cheese cake','## Ingredients\n### Optional Crust\n- 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs\n- 2 tbsp cocoa powder\n- 2 tbsp melted butter\n### Cheesecake Filling\n- 2 large whole eggs\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 4 oz flavored Greek yogurt\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 5 tbsp cocoa powder\n- 1 tbsp melted chocolate chips (sugar-free or semi-sweet)\n- 1-2 tbsp sweetener','## Instructions\n### Optional Crust\n- Mix graham cracker crumbs, cocoa powder, and melted butter.\n- Press mixture into the bottom of a greased or parchment-lined pan.\n- Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 10-15 minutes until edges are cooked.\n### Cheesecake Filling\n- Blend all cheesecake ingredients in a food processor until smooth.\n- Pour filling onto crust or directly into the pan.\n- Bake at 325°F (162°C) for 50-60 minutes.\n- Let cool, refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('19','peanut butter pie','## Ingredients\n### Peanut Butter Pie\n- 8 oz reduced-fat cream cheese\n- 7 oz Greek yogurt (complementing flavor)\n- 8 tbsp powdered peanut butter\n- 60g protein powder (vanilla or complementary flavor)\n- 1-2 tbsp sweetener (optional)\n- 8 tbsp peanut butter\n- ¼ tsp xanthan gum (optional, for texture)\n- 1 pre-made pie crust (or homemade)\n### Protein Topping\n- 3 oz reduced-fat cream cheese\n- 3 oz Greek yogurt\n- 20g chocolate protein powder\n- 3 tbsp cocoa powder\n### Crust (if homemade)\n- 6 graham cracker sheets\n- 3 tbsp melted butter (or coconut oil)','## Instructions\n### Peanut Butter Pie\n- Combine all pie ingredients in a bowl or food processor until smooth.\n- Add to your prepared pie crust.\n- Chill in the fridge for 20-30 minutes.\n- Optionally top with protein topping or any additional toppings like sugar-free peanut butter chips.\n### Protein Topping\n- Mix all topping ingredients until smooth and spread on the chilled pie.\n### Crust (if homemade)\n- Crush graham crackers into crumbs.\n- Mix with melted butter and press into a pie pan.\n- Bake at 375°F for 12-15 minutes or until golden.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('20','rocatta meat balls','## Ingredients\n### Meatball Mix\n- 2 pounds ground beef (or turkey, 93/7)\n- 2 cups ricotta cheese\n- 1 ½ cups bread crumbs (optional)\n- 3 large whole eggs\n- ¾ cup parmesan cheese\n- 5 teaspoons minced garlic\n- ½ onion (chopped)\n- 1 ½ tablespoons Italian seasoning\n- 1 tablespoon parsley\n- 1 tablespoon basil\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n### Cooking Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil (for stovetop method)\n- 1 jar pasta sauce (optional)','## Instructions\n### Meatball Mix\n- Combine ricotta cheese and optional bread crumbs in a large bowl.\n- Add remaining ingredients (except olive oil and sauce) and mix well (use hands or a hand mixer).\n- Shape meatballs into desired size and set aside.\n### Stovetop Method\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Brown meatballs on all sides, about 2 minutes.\n- Add pasta sauce, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes or until meatballs reach 165°F.\n### Oven Method\n- Place meatballs on a baking sheet or in a dish.\n- Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 30-40 minutes, flipping halfway if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('21','whipped greek yogurt','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 250 grams Greek yogurt (higher protein preferred)\n- 2 ounces heavy cream\n- 1 large pasteurized liquid egg white (about 3 tablespoons)\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder (or chocolate for variation)\n- Honey (optional, for sweetness)\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder (optional, for chocolate flavor)','## Instructions\n### Mixing\n- Mix all ingredients together using a hand mixer on low speed until fully combined.\n- Increase the speed to high and continue mixing for a couple of minutes or until the volume doubles and the yogurt becomes creamy.\n### Serving\n- Top with desired toppings such as chocolate chips, sprinkles, nuts, or fresh fruit.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('22','slow cooker meatloaf','## Ingredients\n### Meatloaf\n- 3 lbs ground beef (or turkey, lean preferred)\n- 2 large eggs\n- 2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs (your choice, Italian preferred)\n- 1 cup low-sodium beef broth\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tbsp parsley\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1 red onion (optional)\n- 1 green pepper (optional)\n### Glaze\n- 1 cup low-sugar ketchup\n- 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 2-3 tbsp brown sugar substitute (optional)','## Instructions\n### Meatloaf\n- Chop vegetables (onion and green pepper).\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine all meatloaf ingredients.\n- Mix thoroughly with hands or a utensil.\n- Shape the mixture to fit the size of your slow cooker.\n- Optionally line the slow cooker with aluminum foil or a liner.\n- Place the mixture in the slow cooker and flatten to level the top.\n- Evenly distribute half of the glaze over the meatloaf.\n- Cover and cook on low for 6-7 hours or high for 3-4 hours.\n- 20 minutes before the end, add the remaining glaze and parsley.\n### Glaze\n- In a small bowl, combine ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, and brown sugar substitute.\n- Mix until smooth.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('23','cottage cheese pizza toast','## Ingredients\n### Cottage Cheese Mixture\n- ½ cup cottage cheese (your choice of fat content)\n- 3 tablespoons parmesan cheese\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n### Pizza Base\n- 2 pieces of bread (choose your preferred type)\n- Olive oil or cooking spray\n### Toppings\n- ¼ cup pizza sauce\n- ¼ cup mozzarella cheese\n- Optional: pepperoni slices','## Instructions\n### Prep the Toast\n- Coat both sides of the bread with cooking spray and toast until crispy in a toaster or on a stove with oil.\n- If using an oven, preheat to 400°F (204°C) and toast bread until golden.\n### Assemble the Pizza Toast\n- Spread ¼ cup of pizza sauce on each piece of toast.\n- Evenly distribute the cottage cheese mixture and top with mozzarella and optional pepperoni.\n### Baking\n- Place the assembled toast in the oven at 400°F (204°C) for 10-12 minutes or until the cheese melts.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('24','acai bowl','## Ingredients\n### Base Recipe\n- 200g frozen acai\n- 100g frozen blueberries\n- 15g spinach\n- 2 ounces milk substitute\n- 75g Greek yogurt (flavor of choice)\n- 30g protein powder (flavor of choice)\n### Optional Toppings\n- 25g granola\n- 28g hemp seed hearts\n- Fruit (banana, kiwi, or your choice)','## Instructions\n### Base Recipe\n- Add all base ingredients into a blender or food processor.\n- Blend until smooth.\n### Assembly\n- Pour the mixture into a bowl.\n- Add your chosen toppings.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('25','egg muffins','## Ingredients\n### Hash Brown Crust\n- 10 ounces hash browns (½ bag)\n- ½ tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large whole egg\n- ¼ cup cheese (your choice)\n### Breakfast Muffins\n- 6 large whole eggs\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 2 teaspoons minced garlic\n- Pepper (to taste)\n- Salt (to taste)\n- ½ cup cheese (your choice)\n- 2 tablespoons bacon bits (optional)\n- Bell pepper (optional)\n- Chives (optional)','## Instructions\n### Hash Brown Crust\n- Mix all hash brown crust ingredients.\n- Coat a muffin pan with non-stick spray.\n- Evenly distribute and press down the hash brown mixture into the muffin spots.\n- Bake at 400°F (204°C) for about 20 minutes until crispy.\n### Breakfast Muffins\n- Blend eggs, cottage cheese, garlic, pepper, and salt until smooth.\n- Distribute the mixture evenly into the muffin pan.\n- Add desired toppings (cheese, bacon bits, bell peppers, chives).\n- Bake at 400°F (204°C) for 10-12 minutes or until just slightly jiggly in the center.\n','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('26','protein fluff','## Ingredients\n### Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup fruit (e.g., strawberries, bananas, blueberries, or pineapple)\n- 1 scoop protein powder (30g, any flavor)\n- 2 ounces milk or milk substitute\n- 1-2 teaspoons sweetener (optional)','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Add all ingredients to a mixing bowl, blender, or food processor.\n- Mix, blend, or process until creamy.\n### Fluffing\n- Use a hand mixer or whisk to mix until the desired fluffiness is achieved (2-5 minutes).','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('27','japanese pancakes','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 3 large egg yolks\n- 2 oz milk or milk substitute\n- 1 scoop protein powder (flavor of your choice)\n- 2 tbsp sweetener (e.g., erythritol)\n- ½ cup pancake mix\n### Egg Whites\n- 3 large egg whites\n','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- In a bowl, combine egg yolks, milk, protein powder, sweetener, and pancake mix. Mix until smooth.\n- In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.\n- Gently fold the egg whites into the pancake batter.\n### Cooking (Cake Pan Method)\n- Coat a cake pan with non-stick spray and evenly distribute the batter.\n- Bake at 325°F (162°C) for 20 minutes, removing when slightly jiggly.\n### Cooking (Stovetop Method)\n- Heat a non-stick pan with low heat. Coat with cooking spray.\n- Pour batter into the pan, cover, and cook for 1-2 minutes.\n- Add more batter, cover, and cook until done.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('28','omellete cheeseburgers','## Ingredients\n### Burgers\n- Ground beef (or turkey)\n- Garlic powder\n- Salt\n- Black pepper\n- Cheese slices (your favorite)\n### Omelette Bun\n- 4 large whole eggs\n- Chopped red onion\n- Bacon bits\n- Garlic powder\n- Cheese slices (your favorite)','## Instructions\n### Burgers\n- Shape the burgers and create a dimple in each.\n- Season both sides with garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.\n- Grill to your preferred temperature, adding cheese slices a few minutes before they''re done.\n### Omelette Bun\n- Whisk eggs and pour into a greased, heated pan.\n- Add chopped red onion, bacon bits, garlic powder, and cheese.\n- Fold and cook each side until done.\n- Cut in half and place the burger inside.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('29','slow cooker sweet pork salad','## Ingredients\n### Pork & Cooking Liquid\n- 3-4 lbs pork sirloin roast (or pork shoulder)\n- 1 can (12 oz) root beer\n- 1 jar (16 oz) green salsa\n### Sauce\n- 1 cup enchilada sauce\n- 1/2 cup brown sugar\n- 1 can (4 oz) green chilies\n- 1 cup salsa\n- Reserved spices from pork seasoning','## Instructions\n### Cook Pork\n- Season the pork roast with spices (salt, pepper, cumin, garlic powder, and onion powder).\n- Add pork to slow cooker with root beer and green salsa.\n- Cook on low for 6-8 hours until tender.\n### Shred & Make Sauce\n- Shred the pork and discard most of the liquid.\n- In a separate bowl, combine enchilada sauce, brown sugar, green chilies, salsa, and reserved spices.\n- Return shredded pork to the slow cooker with the sauce and cook for an additional 30 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('30','everything bagels','## Ingredients\n### Bagel Dough\n- 1 tsp granulated sugar\n- 2 tsp active dry yeast\n- 1 1/4 cups lukewarm water\n- 4 cups bread flour (or all-purpose flour)\n- 1 1/2 tsp fine-grain sea salt\n### Toppings\n- Everything bagel seasoning (or a mix of minced garlic, onion, sesame seeds, poppy seeds, coarse salt)\n','## Instructions\n### Preparing the Dough\n- Proof yeast by dissolving sugar and yeast in warm water, waiting 5 minutes for bubbles.\n- Mix the dough by hand or with a stand mixer on low, knead until smooth and elastic (about 5-6 minutes).\n  \n### Shaping the Bagels\n- Divide dough into 8 portions, roll into balls, and poke holes in the center to form bagel shapes.\n- Boil bagels for 1-2 minutes, then drain and place on a baking sheet.\n### Baking\n- Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C), bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('31','chicken cordon bleu','## Ingredients\n### Chicken\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 4 slices ham\n- 4 slices cheese (Swiss or Gruyère)\n### Crumb Coating\n- 2 tbsp mayonnaise\n- 2 tsp mustard\n- 1 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1 egg (for dredging)\n### Mustard Cream Sauce\n- 1/2 cup cream\n- 1 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n','## Instructions\n### Chicken Preparation\n- Cut a pocket in each chicken breast and stuff with ham and cheese.\n- Secure with toothpicks.\n### Crumbing Process\n- Option 1: Smear mayo and mustard, then coat with breadcrumbs.\n- Option 2: Dredge in egg mixture and breadcrumbs.\n- Toast breadcrumbs in the oven for 3 minutes for extra crunch (optional).\n### Cooking\n- Bake at 400°F (200°C) for 25-30 minutes until golden and cooked through.\n### Sauce\n- Combine cream and mustard in a pan, season, and simmer for 2-3 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('32','fish tacos','## Ingredients\n### fish\n- 1 pound tilapia (or your choice of white fish)\n### seasoning\n- Southwestern seasoning\n- Ground cumin\n- Salt\n- Fresh lime juice\n### other\n- Olive oil\n- Tortillas\n- Cheese (optional)\n- Guacamole (optional)\n- Salsa (optional)','## Instructions\n### preparing the fish\n- Coat one side of the fish with southwestern seasoning, ground cumin, salt, and fresh lime juice.\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat.\n- Place fish seasoned side down into the pan.\n- Coat the other side with the same seasoning mix.\n- Flip the fish after a few minutes and cook until fully done.\n### assembling tacos\n- Warm tortillas.\n- Place the cooked fish in the tortillas.\n- Add your choice of toppings like cheese, guacamole, and salsa.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('33','steel cut slow cooker cinamon buns','## Ingredients\n### main dish\n- 1 ½ cups steel cut oats\n- 3 tablespoons almond flour\n- 1 tablespoon ground cinnamon\n- 4 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- ¼ teaspoon baking powder\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- pinch of salt\n- 2 large whole eggs, beaten\n- 6 cups milk or milk substitute\n- 2 containers vanilla Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons melted butter\n### cinnamon buns\n- 2-3 pieces cinnamon bun dough\n- sugar-free syrup (for topping)','## Instructions\n### preparation\n- Optionally line your slow cooker for easy cleanup.\n- Add all ingredients (except cinnamon bun dough and syrup) to the slow cooker and mix well to remove clumps.\n### cooking\n- Break cinnamon bun dough into pieces and stir into the mixture.\n- Top with sugar-free syrup and cover the slow cooker.\n- Cook on low for 7-8 hours or high for 3-4 hours. Keep an eye to avoid burning.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('34','protein blueberry muffins','## Ingredients\n### Wet ingredients\n- 3 large whole eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar\n- 2 teaspoons lemon juice\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened apple sauce\n### Dry ingredients\n- 1/2 cup coconut flour\n- 1 1/2 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener (optional)\n### Add-ins\n- 1/2 cup fresh blueberries\n','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a bowl, combine all wet and dry ingredients and mix until smooth.\n- If the batter is too thick, add an extra egg white to adjust consistency.\n### Baking\n- Evenly distribute the mixture into a muffin pan (you can line it for easier cleanup).\n- Top each muffin with a couple of blueberries and gently press them in.\n- Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until muffins rise.\n### Final steps\n- Let the muffins cool before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('35','slow cooker jumbalaya','## Ingredients\n### Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb chicken breast, chopped\n- 12 oz smoked turkey sausage, low sodium, chopped\n- 2 cups green pepper, chopped\n- 2 cups celery, chopped\n- ¼ cup green onion, chopped\n- ¾ cup sweet onion, chopped\n- 2 ½ tsp minced garlic\n- 1 tbsp Cajun seasoning\n- 2-3 bay leaves\n- ½ tsp salt\n- 1-2 tbsp chili sauce or hot sauce\n- 20 oz low sodium bone broth\n- 1 can (28 oz) diced tomatoes, low sodium\n- 1 ½ cups uncooked brown rice\n- 12 oz frozen shrimp, peeled (remove tails)','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Chop chicken, sausage, and vegetables.\n- Mix everything (except rice and shrimp) in the slow cooker.\n### Cooking\n- Cook on high for 4-4.5 hours.\n- Remove shrimp tails and add shrimp and rice.\n- Stir and cook on high for an additional 30-45 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('36','spicy dutch oven enchiladas','## Ingredients\n### Filling\n- 2 lbs lean ground beef\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 11 oz can Mexicorn, drained (or substitute with corn and chilies)\n- 1 15 oz can black beans, drained\n- 1 cup black olives, chopped\n- 3 tablespoons fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 2 teaspoons chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n### Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, finely diced\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup green bell pepper, finely diced\n- 2 14 oz cans tomato sauce\n- 1 4 oz can diced green chilies\n- 2 tablespoons chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n### Additional\n- 2 lbs shredded cheddar cheese\n- 24 10\\ flour tortillas\n- 3 14 oz cans enchilada sauce','## Instructions\n### Prepare the Filling\n1. Heat a 12\\ Dutch oven with 20-22 briquettes at the bottom until hot.\n2. Add ground beef, onions, and garlic. Cook until beef is browned and onions are translucent.\n3. Spoon off excess grease and stir in Mexicorn, black beans, olives, cilantro, chili powder, paprika, and cumin.\n4. Salt and pepper to taste, then heat thoroughly. Remove the mixture from the Dutch oven.\n### Prepare the Sauce\n1. Heat a 10\\ Dutch oven with 12-14 briquettes at the bottom.\n2. Add olive oil, onion, garlic, and green bell pepper. Sauté until soft.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, green chilies (juice included), chili powder, paprika, cumin, and red pepper flakes.\n4. Bring the sauce to a boil, then simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.\n### Assemble Enchiladas\n1. Dip a tortilla in sauce to cover both sides, then place it on a plate.\n2. Fill with 1/4 - 1/3 cup of meat filling and sprinkle with cheese. Roll up the tortilla and place it seam-side down in the Dutch oven.\n3. Repeat with remaining tortillas, layering them in the Dutch oven.\n4. Cover the enchiladas with remaining meat filling, pour over the remaining sauce, and sprinkle with cheese.\n### Bake\n1. Cover and bake using 12-14 briquettes on the bottom and 12-14 on the top for 20 minutes or until the sauce bubbles and cheese melts. Alternatively, bake in the oven at 350°F until bubbly and cheese melts.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('37','sesame chicken','## Ingredients\n### Chicken\n- 3 chicken breast fillets (chopped into bite-size chunks)\n- 2 eggs (lightly beaten)\n- 3 tbsp cornflour (cornstarch)\n- 10 tbsp plain (all-purpose) flour\n- ½ tsp salt\n- ½ tsp pepper\n- ½ tsp garlic salt\n- 2 tsp paprika\n- 5 tbsp vegetable oil\n### Sauce\n- 1 tbsp sesame oil (optional)\n- 2 cloves garlic (minced)\n- 1 tbsp Chinese rice vinegar\n- 2 tbsp honey\n- 2 tbsp sweet chili sauce\n- 3 tbsp ketchup\n- 2 tbsp brown sugar\n- 4 tbsp soy sauce\n### To Serve\n- Boiled rice\n- 2 tbsp sesame seeds\n- Chopped spring onions/scallions\n','## Instructions\n### Prepare Chicken\n- Heat oil in a wok or large frying pan.\n- Dredge chicken pieces in cornflour, dip in egg, and coat with seasoned flour mixture.\n- Fry in batches for 6-7 minutes until golden brown. Remove from pan and place on paper towels.\n### Make Sauce\n- In the same pan, add sesame oil and garlic, then cook for 1 minute.\n- Stir in rice vinegar, honey, chili sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, and soy sauce. Simmer for 2-3 minutes.\n### Combine\n- Add chicken back into the pan with the sauce, toss to coat.\n- Serve with rice, sprinkle with sesame seeds, and garnish with spring onions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('38','avacado smoothie','## Ingredients\n### main components\n- 6 ounces unsweetened vanilla milk substitute (or regular milk)\n- 1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract\n- 1 ½ scoops vanilla protein powder\n- ½ avocado\n- 1 banana\n- 1 cup kale or spinach\n- 1-2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- Ice','## Instructions\n### preparation\n- Add all ingredients into a blender.\n- Blend until smooth.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('39','lemon chia cookies','## Ingredients\n### Dry Ingredients\n- 4 tablespoons coconut flour\n- 2 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- ¾ teaspoon baking powder\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon zest\n- ½ teaspoon xanthan gum\n### Wet Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil (melted)\n- 1 large egg\n- 1-2 tablespoons sweetener (your choice)\n- 2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- ¼ cup lemon juice','## Instructions\n### Preparing Dry Ingredients\n- In a large bowl, combine coconut flour, protein powder, chia seeds, baking powder, salt, lemon zest, and xanthan gum.\n- Lightly mix the dry ingredients together.\n### Preparing Wet Ingredients\n- In a smaller bowl, combine melted coconut oil, egg, sweetener, vanilla extract, honey, and lemon juice.\n- Mix the wet ingredients together.\n### Combining Ingredients\n- Gradually add the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, mixing until a cookie dough forms.\n- Optionally, refrigerate the dough for 20-30 minutes to reduce stickiness.\n### Shaping and Baking\n- Preheat the oven to 325°F (162°C).\n- Line a baking pan with parchment paper or a silicone mat.\n- Use a cookie scooper or your hands to shape the dough into cookies.\n- Bake for 10-12 minutes, depending on the size of your cookies.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('40','pf chang''s lettuce wraps','## Ingredients\n### Sauce\n- 3 Tbsp. hoisin sauce\n- 2 Tbsp. low-sodium soy sauce\n- 2 Tbsp. rice wine vinegar\n- 1 Tbsp. Sriracha (optional)\n- 1 tsp. sesame oil\n### Filling\n- 1 Tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 Tbsp. freshly grated ginger\n- 1 lb. ground chicken\n- 1/2 cup canned water chestnuts, drained and sliced\n- 2 green onions, thinly sliced\n- Kosher salt\n- Freshly ground black pepper\n- Large leafy lettuce (leaves separated), for serving\n- Cooked white rice, for serving (optional)','## Instructions\n### Sauce\n- In a small bowl, whisk together hoisin sauce, soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, Sriracha, and sesame oil.\n### Filling\n- In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat olive oil. Add onions and cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in garlic and ginger, cook for 1 minute more.\n- Add ground chicken and cook until opaque, breaking it up with a wooden spoon.\n- Pour in sauce and cook for 1-2 minutes, until the sauce reduces slightly and the chicken is cooked through.\n- Stir in water chestnuts and green onions. Season with salt and pepper.\n### Assembly\n- Spoon rice, if using, and a large scoop (about 1/4 cup) of the chicken mixture into each lettuce leaf. Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('41','apple kiwi green energy smoothie','## Ingredients\n### Main ingredients\n- 8 oz milk substitute (or milk)\n- 1 apple, chopped\n- ½ kiwi, peeled\n- 5.3 oz Greek yogurt (fat-free plain, or cottage cheese)\n- 1½ scoops vanilla protein powder (optional)\n- 2 tbsp flaxseed meal\n- 1 cup ice\n- 1 cup spinach (washed)','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Add all ingredients into a blender.\n- Blend until smooth.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('42','protein nutella iced coffee','## Ingredients\n### main components\n- 2 ounces milk substitute (or milk)\n- 8 ounces coffee\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n- 1 ½ tablespoons Nutella\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder\n- ½ cup cottage cheese\n- ½ cup ice','## Instructions\n### Preparation\n- Brew your coffee as desired (e.g., French press, espresso, or cold brew).\n- Add the brewed coffee, milk substitute, cocoa powder, Nutella, protein powder, cottage cheese, and ice into a blender.\n- Blend until smooth.\n### Serving\n- Pour into a glass and enjoy as is, or top with whipped cream, chocolate shavings, or other toppings of choice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('43','nutella protein bars','## Ingredients\n### Main mixture\n- 4 ounces milk substitute (or milk)\n- 6 tablespoons coconut flour\n- ½ cup rolled oats\n- 3 scoops chocolate protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon Nutella\n### Chocolate shell\n- 3 tablespoons dark chocolate chips\n','## Instructions\n### Main preparation\n- Combine all ingredients except the chocolate chips into a food processor or powerful blender.\n- Process or blend until the mixture starts to clump together.\n- Shape the mixture into bars.\n### Chocolate coating\n- Melt the dark chocolate chips in a pan over low heat, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.\n- Coat the bars with the melted chocolate using a spoon or by dipping the bars directly into it.\n- Refrigerate for 20 minutes or until the chocolate hardens.\n### Storage\n- Store the bars in the fridge or freezer. They can last for weeks.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('44','feijuada','## Ingredients\n### Main Dish\n- 1 pound dried black beans\n- 3 tablespoons cooking oil (e.g., avocado or canola oil)\n- 1 pound pork shoulder, left whole and shredded after cooking or cut into chunks\n- ½ pound thick-sliced bacon, cut into small pieces\n- 2 large onions, sliced\n- 5 cloves garlic, minced\n- ½ pound fresh Italian or other spicy sausage, casings removed and crumbled\n- ½ pound smoked sausage (e.g., linguica or kielbasa), sliced into rounds\n- 1 smoked ham hock\n- 4 bay leaves\n- 1 tablespoon beef bouillon base (e.g., Better Than Bouillon)\n- ½ teaspoon black pepper\n- Water, as needed\n- Salt, to taste\n- Hot sauce, according to heat preference\n### Garnish\n- 1 orange, washed and cut into slices','## Instructions\n### Preparing the Beans\n1. Soak the dried black beans in a large bowl of water overnight. Drain and rinse before use.\n### Cooking the Meats and Aromatics\n1. In a large Dutch oven or heavy-duty pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat.\n2. Brown the pork shoulder on all sides until generously browned. Remove and set aside.\n3. In the same pot, add the bacon and cook until slightly crispy. Optionally, drain some grease for a lighter dish.\n4. Add the sliced onions to the bacon and cook until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes.\n5. Stir in the minced garlic and cook for another minute.\n6. Add the crumbled Italian sausage and smoked sausage slices; cook until the crumbled sausage is no longer pink.\n### Combining Ingredients\n1. Return the browned pork shoulder and add the smoked ham hock to the pot.\n2. Add the soaked, drained black beans.\n3. Stir in the bay leaves, black pepper, and beef bouillon base.\n4. Pour in enough water to just barely cover the meat and beans, approximately 2 quarts.\n### Simmering the Stew\n1. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low.\n2. Cover and let it simmer for 2 hours, ensuring the beans become tender.\n3. After 2 hours, remove the pork shoulder, shred it, and return the shredded meat to the pot.\n4. Season with salt to taste and add hot sauce according to your heat preference.\n### Serving\n1. Remove the bay leaves before serving.\n2. Serve hot, garnished with orange slices on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('45','protein red velvet bites','## Ingredients\n- 2 ounces unsweetened milk substitute (or regular milk)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n- 2 ½ scoops chocolate protein powder\n- 1 teaspoon instant coffee (decaffeinated if preferred)\n- 2 tablespoons coconut flour (or oat flour)\n- 1 serving red velvet cake mix\n- 4 tablespoons chocolate peanut butter\n- 2-4 drops red food coloring (optional)','## Instructions\n1. In a mixing bowl, combine the unsweetened milk substitute, vanilla extract, cocoa powder, chocolate protein powder, instant coffee, coconut flour, red velvet cake mix, chocolate peanut butter, and red food coloring','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('46','lemon pie overnight oats','## Ingredients\n- **Overnight Oats:**\n  - ½ cup rolled oats\n  - 4 ounces (½ cup) unsweetened milk substitute or milk\n  - ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n  - ½ ripe banana\n  - 1 teaspoon lemon juice\n  - 1 tablespoon coconut flour\n  - 1½ scoops vanilla protein powder\n  - 1 serving lemon sugar-free, fat-free instant pudding mix\n  - 2.65 ounces (½ container) fat-free lemon Greek yogurt\n- **Topping:**\n  - Remaining ½ container fat-free lemon Greek yogurt','## Instructions\n- **Overnight Oats:**\n  1. In a mixing bowl or container, combine rolled oats, milk substitute, vanilla extract, ripe banana, lemon juice, coconut flour, vanilla protein powder, instant pudding mix, and ½ container of lemon Greek yogurt.\n  2. Mash the banana with a fork and mix all ingredients until well incorporated.\n  3. Cover the mixture and refrigerate overnight, or for at least a few hours, to allow it to thicken.\n- **Serving:**\n  1. Before serving, top the overnight oats with the remaining ½ container of lemon Greek yogurt.\n','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('47','microwave protein carot cake','## Ingredients\n### Carrot Cake\n- 1 ½ scoops vanilla protein powder\n- ¼ cup unsweetened milk substitute (e.g., almond milk)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ¼ teaspoon pumpkin pie spice\n- ½ teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 3 tablespoons coconut flour\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener of choice\n- 1 teaspoon light brown sugar\n- 1 ½ large egg whites (or 4 ½ tablespoons liquid egg whites)\n- ½ teaspoon baking powder\n- 4 ½ ounces carrots, chopped or shredded\n### Healthy Cream Cheese Frosting\n- ½ container vanilla Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener of choice\n- 4 tablespoons fat-free cream cheese','## Instructions\n### Carrot Cake\n1. In a mixing bowl, food processor, or blender, combine the vanilla protein powder, unsweetened milk substitute, vanilla extract, pumpkin pie spice, ground cinnamon, coconut flour, sweetener, light brown sugar, egg whites, and baking powder. Mix until smooth.\n2. Add the chopped or shredded carrots to the mixture. If using a food processor or blender, process until the carrots are shredded and well incorporated. If using a mixing bowl, ensure the carrots are finely chopped or shredded before adding.\n3. Lightly coat two microwave-safe dishes (each with at least a 2-cup capacity) with non-stick cooking spray. Evenly distribute the batter between the two dishes.\n4. Microwave each dish separately for 30 seconds. Lightly stir the contents, then microwave for an additional 60 to 90 seconds, depending on your microwave''s power. The cake should be set but moist.\n### Healthy Cream Cheese Frosting\n1. In a bowl, combine the vanilla Greek yogurt, sweetener, and fat-free cream cheese. Mix until smooth and creamy.\n### Assembly\n1. Once the cakes have cooled slightly, remove them from the dishes.\n2. Top each cake with the healthy cream cheese frosting.\n3. Optionally, garnish with additional chopped carrots or a sprinkle of cinnamon.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('48','coconut cream pie protein shake','## Ingredients\n### Protein Shake Base\n- 1 cup unsweetened coconut milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon coconut extract\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 tablespoon sweetener (e.g. stevia, erythritol, or sweetener of choice)\n- 1/4 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup rolled oats\n- 1 tablespoon unsweetened shredded coconut\n- 1/2 frozen banana\n- 1/2 cup ice','## Instructions\n### Protein Shake Base\n- Add all ingredients to a blender.\n- Blend on high until smooth and creamy.\n- Taste and adjust sweetness or thickness as desired by adding more sweetener, ice, or milk.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('49','oatmeal cookie protein shake','## Ingredients\n### Shake Base\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1/2 cup rolled oats\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1 tablespoon peanut butter (or nut butter of choice)\n- 1/2 banana (frozen for better texture)\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 teaspoon honey or sweetener of choice (optional)\n- 1/2 cup ice (optional, for thicker texture)','## Instructions\n### Shake Base\n- Add all ingredients into a blender.\n- Blend on high speed for 30–60 seconds, or until smooth and creamy.\n- Pour into a glass and enjoy immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('50','beef stew','## Ingredients\n### Main Stew\n- 2 lbs beef chuck, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 3 tablespoons flour\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 cups beef broth\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 teaspoon dried rosemary\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 2 bay leaves\n### Vegetables\n- 4 carrots, cut into 1-inch chunks\n- 3 potatoes, peeled and cut into 1-inch chunks\n- 2 stalks celery, chopped\n- 1 cup frozen peas','## Instructions\n### Prepare the Beef\n- Toss beef cubes with flour, salt, and pepper to coat.\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.\n- Brown the beef in batches to avoid overcrowding the pan. Remove and set aside.\n### Build the Stew Base\n- In the same pot, add onions and cook until softened (about 5 minutes).\n- Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.\n- Stir in tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, rosemary, thyme, and bay leaves.\n- Return beef to the pot and pour in beef broth. Bring to a boil.\n### Simmer and Cook\n- Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 1.5 hours or until beef is tender.\n- Add carrots, potatoes, and celery to the pot.\n- Simmer for an additional 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.\n- Stir in frozen peas and cook for another 5–10 minutes.\n### Final Touches\n- Remove bay leaves before serving.\n- Adjust seasoning with additional salt and pepper if needed.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('51','siracha deviled eggs','## Ingredients\n### Hard Boiled Eggs\n- 12 large whole eggs\n### Filling\n- 10 tablespoons fat-free mayonnaise\n- 1 serving Dijon or yellow mustard\n- 80 grams Sriracha chili sauce\n- 1 tablespoon lime juice\n- ½ teaspoon kosher salt\n- ½ teaspoon black pepper','## Instructions\n### Hard Boiled Eggs\n1. Place 12 large eggs in a stovetop pan and add water until it covers the eggs by about 1 inch.\n2. Optionally, add a pinch of salt to the water to help with peeling.\n3. Heat the water on high until it reaches a boil, then let the eggs boil for 30-60 seconds.\n4. Remove the pan from heat, cover, and let the eggs sit for 10-15 minutes.\n5. Transfer the eggs to a container filled with ice water and let them cool completely.\n6. Once cooled, gently tap the nose ends of the eggs to crack the shells, then peel.\n### Filling and Assembly\n1. In a mixing bowl, combine the egg yolks (removed from the halved eggs), 10 tablespoons of fat-free mayonnaise, 1 serving of mustard, 80 grams of Sriracha chili sauce, 1 tablespoon of lime juice, ½ teaspoon of kosher salt, and ½ teaspoon of black pepper.\n2. Mix until smooth and well combined.\n3. Fill the egg white halves with the yolk mixture using a spoon or a dessert decorator.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('52','roast veg & feta puff pastry tart','## Ingredients\n- 1 sheet ready-to-roll puff pastry\n- 3 tbsp. green pesto\n- 1 zucchini (sliced)\n- 1 red onion (sliced)\n- 2 peppers (sliced)\n- Handful of cherry tomatoes (halved)\n- 100g low-fat feta cheese\n- Pinch of chili flakes (optional)','## Instructions\n1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).\n2. Roll out the puff pastry onto a lined baking tray. Fold up the edges to create a 1-inch border.\n3. Spread the green pesto evenly within the border of the pastry.\n4. Arrange the sliced zucchini, red onion, peppers, and halved cherry tomatoes over the pesto layer.\n5. Crumble the low-fat feta cheese over the top of the vegetables.\n6. Sprinkle a pinch of chili flakes over the tart, if desired.\n7. Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until the pastry is golden and crisp.\n8. Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly before slicing and serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('53','soya tika masala','## Ingredients\n### For the Chicken Marinade\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- ½ teaspoon ground cumin\n- ½ teaspoon paprika\n- ½ teaspoon salt\n- ¼ teaspoon black pepper\n### For the Spicy Garlic Sauce\n- ½ cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons mayonnaise\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon tahini (optional)\n- 2 teaspoons sriracha or to taste\n- ½ teaspoon lemon juice\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- Pinch of black pepper\n### For Assembly\n- 4 whole-grain flatbreads or whole-wheat tortillas\n- 1 cup arugula or mixed greens\n- 1 large tomato, sliced\n- ½ small red onion, thinly sliced','## Instructions\n### Marinate the Chicken\n1. In a mixing bowl, combine olive oil, minced garlic, lemon zest, lemon juice, dried oregano, ground cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper.\n2. Add the chicken pieces to the marinade, ensuring they are well-coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for enhanced flavor.\n### Prepare the Spicy Garlic Sauce\n1. In a separate bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, mayonnaise, minced garlic, tahini (if using), sriracha, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper until smooth. Adjust seasoning to taste. Refrigerate until ready to use.\n### Cook the Chicken\n1. Heat a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Lightly oil the pan.\n2. Add the marinated chicken pieces to the pan in a single layer. Cook for about 6-8 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is browned and cooked through. Remove from heat and set aside.\n### Assemble the Wraps\n1. Warm the flatbreads or tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave to make them pliable.\n2. Spread a generous amount of the spicy garlic sauce over each flatbread.\n3. Layer arugula or mixed greens, sliced tomatoes, and red onion on top of the sauce.\n4. Divide the cooked chicken evenly among the flatbreads, placing it over the vegetables.\n5. Drizzle additional spicy garlic sauce over the chicken if desired.\n6. Fold the sides of the flatbread over the filling, then roll tightly to form a wrap.\n### Serve\n1. Serve the wraps immediately, or wrap them in parchment paper for a portable meal option.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('54','beef bowl','## Ingredients\n### Seasoned Beef\n- 1 lb (450 g) 93/7 ground beef\n- 1 tbsp (7 g) tomato paste\n- 1 tsp (7 g) salt\n- 1 tsp (3 g) cumin\n- 1 tsp (3 g) smoked paprika\n- ½ tsp (2 g) cayenne pepper\n### Yogurt Sauce\n- 3 tbsp (50 g) non-fat plain yogurt\n- 1 tbsp (15 g) green chile sauce\n- A drizzle of lime juice\n### Bowl Components\n- ~10 tortilla chips\n- ¼ cup (30 g) Monterey Jack cheese, grated\n- Red onions, diced\n- Pickled jalapeños, diced\n- Romaine lettuce, chopped\n','## Instructions\n### Seasoned Beef\n1. In a pan over medium-high heat, add the ground beef, salt, cumin, smoked paprika, and cayenne pepper.\n2. Use a wooden spoon or potato masher to break up the beef as it cooks.\n3. Once the beef is well browned, add the tomato paste along with a splash of water and mix until the beef is glazed.\n### Yogurt Sauce\n1. In a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, green chile sauce, and lime juice until homogeneous. Adjust spice and acidity to taste.\n### Assemble the Bowl\n1. Chop the romaine lettuce, dice the red onions and pickled jalapeños, and grate the Monterey Jack cheese.\n2. To assemble, place the chopped lettuce as a base in each bowl.\n3. Top with one-third of the seasoned beef, grated cheese, diced red onions, and pickled jalapeños.\n4. Drizzle with the green chile yogurt sauce.\n5. Serve with tortilla chips on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('55','gochujang noodles','## Ingredients\n### Noodles & Egg\n- 1 pack Vite Ramen noodles (high-protein ramen)\n- 1 egg\n- Drizzle of cooking oil\n### Gochujang Sauce\n- 10 g gochujang (Korean red chili paste)\n- 5 g Kewpie mayo\n- 5 g Chinese black vinegar\n### For Serving\n- Thinly sliced scallions\n- Black sesame seeds','## Instructions\n### Noodles & Egg\n1. Boil the Vite Ramen noodles according to package directions, then drain.\n2. In a small bowl, mix together gochujang, Kewpie mayo, and Chinese black vinegar until smooth. Taste and adjust if needed.\n3. Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a pan over medium heat. Fry the egg sunny side up to your desired doneness and set aside.\n### Assemble & Serve\n1. In the same pot used for boiling, combine the drained noodles with the gochujang sauce, mixing until the noodles are well coated.\n2. Transfer the sauced noodles to a plate. Top with the fried egg, sliced scallions, and black sesame seeds. Enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('56','chicken flatbread wrap','## Ingredients\n### Chicken Marinade\n- 1 chicken breast, cubed\n- 5 g (1 tsp) neutral oil\n- Sprinkle of salt\n- Sprinkle of oregano\n- Red pepper flakes, to taste\n- Freshly cracked black pepper, to taste\n### Low-Calorie Yogurt Herb Sauce\n- 100 g plain nonfat yogurt (e.g., Siggi''s)\n- 20 g low-fat mayonnaise\n- Dried dill, to taste\n- Dried oregano, to taste\n- Black pepper, to taste\n- Lemon juice, to taste\n### Wrap Assembly\n- Lavash bread, or any flatbread\n- Pickled onions\n- Lettuce, thinly sliced\n- Tomato, thinly sliced\n- 10 g feta cheese, crumbled','## Instructions\n### Marinate & Cook Chicken\n1. In a bowl, combine the cubed chicken with neutral oil, salt, oregano, red pepper flakes, and freshly cracked black pepper. Mix until the chicken is well coated.\n2. Heat a pan over high heat. Add the chicken pieces and sear on one side for a couple of minutes until browned.\n3. Flip the chicken pieces and cook until fully cooked through.\n### Prepare the Yogurt Herb Sauce\n1. In a bowl, combine plain nonfat yogurt, low-fat mayonnaise, dried dill, dried oregano, black pepper, and lemon juice. Mix until smooth.\n2. Adjust acidity and seasoning to taste.\n### Assemble the Wrap\n1. Spread one-third of the yogurt herb sauce onto a piece of lavash bread.\n2. Layer 150 grams of the cooked chicken, sliced tomatoes, thinly sliced lettuce, and pickled onions on top.\n3. Crumble 10 grams of feta cheese over the fillings.\n4. Wrap the flatbread tightly around the fillings. Using aluminum foil can help keep the wrap secure and is useful for making ready-to-go extras for later.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('82','Banana Greek Yogurt Cake with Caramel Topping','## Cake\n- 2 medium ripe bananas, mashed\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 eggs\n- 1/4 cup arrowroot powder (or cornstarch)\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- 1/4 cup powdered sugar\n\n## Caramel Topping\n- 2 tbsp coconut oil\n- 2 tbsp maple syrup\n- 1 tbsp peanut butter\n- Pinch of salt','## Cake Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Prepare a 6-inch round cake pan by lining it with parchment paper.\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the mashed bananas, Greek yogurt, eggs, arrowroot powder, and a pinch of salt. Stir until the mixture is smooth and well combined.\n- Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan, spreading it evenly.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n- Remove the cake from the oven and let it cool completely on a wire rack.\n\n## Caramel Topping Preparation\n- In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine coconut oil, maple syrup, peanut butter, and a pinch of salt.\n- Stir the mixture continuously until it becomes smooth and thoroughly combined, about a few minutes.\n- Take the sauce off the heat and allow it to cool for 15-20 minutes. It will thicken and develop a caramel-like texture.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('83','Chicken with Mac & Cheese','## Chicken\n- 800g raw chicken breast, cut into cubes\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tsp chili flakes (optional)\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp onion powder\n- 1.5 tsp paprika or smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- 30g light butter (plus extra for finishing)\n- 2 tsp minced garlic\n- 30g honey (15g per batch)\n- Handful of fresh chopped parsley\n\n## Mac and Cheese\n- 1 tbsp minced garlic\n- 300ml skimmed milk\n- 160g light cream cheese\n- 1 tsp salt (or to taste)\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1/2 tsp nutmeg\n- 100g low-fat cheddar cheese\n- 220g uncooked macaroni pasta','## Prepare Chicken\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and add olive oil and butter. Allow the butter to melt and then add the chicken cubes, ensuring not to overcrowd the pan.\n- Cook the chicken for 4-5 minutes on one side until a golden-brown crust forms. Flip and cook for an additional 3-4 minutes on the other side.\n- Reduce the heat to low and add extra butter, minced garlic, and honey. Stir until the chicken is coated in the sticky glaze. Remove from heat and sprinkle with fresh parsley.\n\n## Mac & Cheese\n- In the same pan, cook the minced garlic over medium-low heat for about 2 minutes until fragrant.\n- Add skimmed milk and cream cheese, whisking until the mixture is smooth.\n- Lower the heat and stir in the cheddar cheese until melted.\n- Add cooked macaroni, season with salt, black pepper, smoked paprika, and nutmeg. Mix well until the pasta is fully coated with the cheese sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('84','Chicken with Caramelized Onion Creamy Sauce and Lemon Butter Herb Rice','## Chicken & Seasoning\n- 1000g raw chicken breast, cubed\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 2 tsp oregano\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp dried basil\n- 3 tsp olive oil\n- 10g reduced fat butter (for cooking)\n\n## Caramelized Onion Creamy Sauce\n- 20g reduced fat butter\n- 350g red or white onion, finely sliced\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 80g sun-dried tomatoes, drained and chopped\n- 10g minced garlic\n- 380g 1% milk or skimmed milk\n- 180g 50% fat cream cheese\n- 50g Parmigiano Reggiano, grated\n- 1 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Lemon Butter Herb Rice\n- 10g reduced fat butter\n- 15g minced garlic\n- 1/2 tsp salt or to taste\n- 2 tsp mixed herbs\n- 250g uncooked basmati rice (or 600g cooked)\n- 1.5 tsp lemon zest\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon','## Chicken\n- Season the chicken cubes with salt, pepper, garlic powder, oregano, smoked paprika, and basil.\n- Heat olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken in batches, cooking for about 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Caramelized Onion Creamy Sauce\n- In the same skillet, melt the butter over medium heat and add the sliced onions.\n- Cook onions for 10-12 minutes, stirring every 4-5 minutes, until they become soft and caramelized. Cook longer if needed.\n- Add minced garlic, sun-dried tomatoes, salt, pepper, smoked paprika, and chili flakes. Stir to combine.\n- Reduce the heat to low, then slowly pour in the milk and add the cream cheese.\n- Stir gently until the cheese melts and the sauce becomes smooth and creamy.\n- Mix in the grated Parmigiano Reggiano and fresh parsley.\n- Return the cooked chicken to the skillet, tossing it in the sauce to coat evenly.\n\n## Lemon Butter Herb Rice\n- While the chicken cooks, melt the butter in a saucepan over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté until fragrant.\n- Stir in salt, mixed herbs, and uncooked basmati rice.\n- Add water according to rice package instructions to cook the rice.\n- Once cooked, stir in lemon zest and lemon juice.\n- Fluff the rice with a fork and serve alongside the chicken.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('85','Cajun Steak Bites with Parmesan Crusted Potatoes and Cajun Creamy Sauce','## Cajun Steak Bites\n- 1000g Raw Topside/Top Sirloin Beef\n- 2 tsp Salt\n- 2 tsp Italian Herbs\n- 1.5 tsp Chilli Flakes\n- 2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 2 tsp Onion Powder\n- 2 tsp Parsley\n- 2 tsp Paprika\n- 3 tsp Olive Oil\n- 20g Reduced Fat Butter\n- 20g Minced Garlic\n- 1 tbsp Fresh Parsley, chopped\n\n## Parmesan Crusted Potatoes\n- 900g Raw White Potatoes, cubed\n- 250g Broccoli Florets, chopped\n- 200g Red Onion, chopped\n- 200g Red Bell Pepper, chopped\n- 1.5 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1.5 tsp Paprika\n- 1.5 tsp Italian Herbs\n- 1.5 tsp Parsley\n- 50g Parmesan, grated\n- 3 tsp Olive Oil\n\n## Cajun Creamy Sauce\n- 10g Reduced Fat Butter\n- 1/2 tsp Salt\n- 1/2 tsp Paprika\n- 1/2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1/2 tsp Onion Powder\n- 1/2 tsp Italian Herbs\n- 1/2 tsp Parsley\n- 250g 1% Milk\n- 150g Light Cream Cheese\n- 40g Parmesan, grated','## Cajun Steak Bites\n- Cut the beef into bite-sized pieces. In a bowl, combine the beef with salt, Italian herbs, chili flakes, garlic powder, onion powder, parsley, and paprika.\n- Heat the olive oil and butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the steak bites, cooking each side for 3-4 minutes until they are golden brown and nicely seared.\n- Reduce the heat to low, then mix in the minced garlic and fresh parsley. Stir to combine and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.\n\n## Parmesan Crusted Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven to 160°C (320°F) or set your air fryer to 160°C (320°F).\n- In a large bowl, toss the cubed potatoes, broccoli, red onion, and red bell pepper with garlic powder, paprika, Italian herbs, parsley, grated Parmesan, and olive oil.\n- Place the vegetable mixture on a baking tray or in the air fryer basket. Bake or air fry for 20-24 minutes. Stir halfway through to ensure even cooking, being careful not to overcook the broccoli.\n\n## Cajun Creamy Sauce\n- In a saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.\n- Stir in the salt, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, Italian herbs, and parsley.\n- Slowly whisk in the milk and cream cheese, cooking until the mixture begins to thicken.\n- Add the grated Parmesan and continue stirring until the cheese melts and the sauce is smooth.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('86','Orange Chicken with Toasted Sesame Garlic Rice and Cucumber Salad','## Orange Chicken\n- 1000g boneless skinless chicken thighs, cubed\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 20g minced garlic\n- 20g ginger paste\n- 2 tsp red pepper flakes\n- 30g honey\n- 30g sriracha\n- 100g freshly squeezed orange juice\n- 1.5 tsp orange zest\n- 25g dark soy sauce\n\n## Toasted Sesame Garlic Rice\n- 15g reduced fat butter\n- 25g sesame seeds\n- 20g minced garlic\n- 250g uncooked white rice or 690g cooked rice (preferably leftover or day-old cooked)\n- 50g green onion (green parts only), chopped\n- Sesame seeds for garnish\n\n## Cucumber Salad\n- 300g green cabbage, thinly sliced\n- 400g cucumber, thinly sliced\n- 200g red onion, thinly sliced\n- 200g carrots, grated\n- 150g green onion, finely chopped\n- 25g rice vinegar\n- 1-2 tsp red pepper flakes\n- 20g honey','## Orange Chicken\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (400°F).\n- In a large bowl, combine the chicken, minced garlic, ginger paste, black pepper, red pepper flakes, honey, sriracha, orange juice, orange zest, and dark soy sauce. Mix until the chicken is well-coated.\n- Arrange the chicken pieces in a single layer on a baking sheet or air fryer basket.\n- Cook for 19-22 minutes, turning halfway through, until the chicken is golden brown and the glaze is caramelized.\n\n## Toasted Sesame Garlic Rice\n- Melt the butter in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the sesame seeds and minced garlic, and cook until the sesame seeds are golden and fragrant.\n- Stir in the cooked rice until it''s well-mixed with the sesame and garlic flavors.\n- Mix in the chopped green onions, and remove from heat.\n- Garnish with additional sesame seeds before serving.\n\n## Cucumber Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the sliced cabbage, cucumber, red onion, and carrots.\n- In a separate small bowl, whisk together the rice vinegar, honey, and red pepper flakes.\n- Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss until everything is well-coated.\n- Sprinkle with the finely chopped green onions before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('87','Marinated Chicken with Butter Sauce and Masala Potatoes','## Chicken Marinade\n- 800g boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cubed\n- 1 Tbsp garlic paste\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp garam masala\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 1/2 tsp turmeric\n- 1 tsp chili powder\n- 80-100g low-fat yogurt\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n\n## Crispy Masala Potatoes\n- 800g white potatoes, cut into small cubes\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp paprika\n- 1 tsp garam masala\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- (Optional) 2 tsp olive oil\n\n## Butter Chicken Sauce\n- 40g light butter (plus extra for finishing)\n- 150g sliced white onion\n- 1/2 tsp each: salt, garam masala, paprika, turmeric\n- 1 tsp garlic paste\n- 60g raw cashew nuts\n- 600g canned tomatoes or fresh chopped tomatoes\n- 100g low-fat yogurt\n- 60ml light evaporated milk\n- Extra butter for finishing (optional)\n\n## White Sauce\n- 50g low-fat yogurt\n- 20-25ml milk (adjust to desired consistency)','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Use cubed chicken breast if preferred. Combine all marinade ingredients with the chicken. Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes or overnight for enhanced flavor.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Air fry or bake the marinated chicken at 200°C (400°F) for 18–20 minutes, or until fully cooked.\n- Alternatively, pan-fry over medium heat for 3–4 minutes on each side.\n\n## Make the Butter Chicken Sauce\n- In a pan, melt the butter and sauté the onions for 5 minutes.\n- Add the garlic paste and cashews, then incorporate the tomatoes.\n- Cover the pan and cook on low heat for 6–8 minutes, until the tomatoes are softened.\n- Allow the sauce to cool before blending to a smooth consistency.\n- Return the sauce to the pan, add yogurt, evaporated milk, and adjust seasonings if needed. Let it simmer briefly.\n\n## Prepare the Masala Potatoes\n- Toss the potato cubes with salt, paprika, garam masala, and garlic powder.\n- Spread onto a baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil if desired, and bake at the same temperature as the chicken for 25–30 minutes, until crispy.\n\n## Serve\n- Plate the chicken with the butter sauce and crispy masala potatoes.\n- Drizzle white sauce over the top or serve on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('88','Crispy Chicken Fajita with Creamy Fajita Mac n Cheese','## Crispy Chicken Fajita\n- 1000g (35oz) raw chicken breast, cubed\n- 2 tsp salt\n- 3 tsp oregano\n- 2.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 2.5 tsp onion powder\n- 1.5 tsp cumin\n- 15g (3 tsp) olive oil\n- 20g reduced fat butter (for cooking)\n- 30g honey (for all the chicken)\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Fajita Veggie Mix (Half for Chicken/Half for Mac)\n- 20g reduced fat butter (for cooking)\n- 100g white onion, finely chopped\n- 100g red onion, finely chopped\n- 100g green bell pepper, chopped\n- 100g red bell pepper, chopped\n- 100g yellow bell pepper, chopped\n- 2 tsp salt (adjust to taste)\n- 2 tsp oregano\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 30g minced garlic\n\n## Creamy Fajita Mac n Cheese\n- 300g 1% milk\n- 120g 50% fat cream cheese\n- 50g fat-free cottage cheese\n- 80g low-fat cheddar cheese, grated\n- 275g uncooked macaroni pasta','## Crispy Chicken Fajita\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter over medium-high heat. Season the chicken with salt, oregano, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, and cumin.\n- Cook the chicken for 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown and crispy.\n- Reduce the heat and add the fajita veggie mix, honey, and parsley. Stir until everything is coated and juicy.\n- Repeat this process for all the chicken pieces.\n\n## Fajita Veggie Mix (Half for Chicken/Half for Mac)\n- Melt the butter in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the onions and bell peppers, cooking for 5–6 minutes until they start to soften.\n- Mix in the salt, oregano, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, and minced garlic.\n- Cook for an additional 5 minutes until the spices are thoroughly mixed in and the vegetables are golden.\n- Divide the mix, using half for the chicken and the other half for the mac and cheese.\n\n## Creamy Fajita Mac n Cheese\n- Blend the milk, cream cheese, and cottage cheese in a blender until smooth.\n- In a saucepan over low heat, warm the reserved half of the fajita veggie mix for about 2 minutes.\n- Pour the blended sauce over the mix, stirring continuously until it becomes smooth and starts to thicken slightly.\n- Add the grated cheddar cheese and cooked macaroni, stirring gently.\n- Continue cooking for 3–4 minutes until the mac and cheese is heated through and creamy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('89','Chicken Shawarma with Golden Yellow Rice and Special Garlic White Sauce','## Chicken Shawarma\n- 1000g Boneless Skinless Chicken Thighs\n- 30g Minced Garlic\n- 2 Tsp Salt\n- 2 Tsp Black Pepper\n- 2 Tsp Smoked Paprika (or regular paprika)\n- 2 Tsp Onion Powder\n- 1.5 Tsp Cumin\n- 1.5 Tsp Cinnamon\n- 1.5 Tsp Sumac\n- 3 Tsp Olive Oil\n- Juice of 3/4 Lemon\n\n## Fragrant Golden Yellow Rice\n- 20g Reduced Fat Butter\n- 35g Minced Garlic\n- 200g White Onion, finely chopped\n- 1 Tsp Turmeric\n- 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 1 Tsp Salt\n- 250g Uncooked Basmati Rice\n- 600g Water\n\n## Special Garlic White Sauce (big batch, store in bottle)\n- 150g Fat Free Yogurt\n- 75g Light Mayo\n- 25g Honey\n- 1/2 Tsp each Salt & Black Pepper\n- 1 Tsp Garlic Powder\n- 25g Pickle Juice (adjust to desired consistency)\n\n## Fresh Crunchy Slaw (big batch, store separately)\n- 250g Red Onion, thinly sliced\n- 300g Cherry Tomatoes, chopped\n- 200g Pickled Gherkins, thinly sliced\n- 2 Tbsp Fresh Parsley, chopped\n- 1 Tsp each Salt & Black Pepper\n- 1 Tsp Sumac','## Chicken Shawarma\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (400°F).\n- Mix the chicken thighs with garlic, salt, black pepper, smoked paprika, onion powder, cumin, cinnamon, sumac, olive oil, and lemon juice.\n- Spread the mixture on a baking tray or air fryer basket.\n- Cook for 20 minutes. For a charred finish, broil for an additional 3-4 minutes.\n- Allow the chicken to rest for 4-5 minutes, then chop into cubes. Incorporate the pan juices for extra flavor.\n\n## Fragrant Golden Yellow Rice\n- In a pot, melt the butter over medium-low heat.\n- Add minced garlic and chopped onion, cooking until softened and aromatic (about 5-6 minutes).\n- Stir in turmeric, smoked paprika, salt, and the basmati rice. Toast the rice for 2-3 minutes.\n- Pour in the water and bring to a gentle simmer.\n- Cover with a lid and let it cook for 10-12 minutes until the rice is done, stirring halfway to prevent sticking.\n\n## Special Garlic White Sauce\n- Combine the yogurt, mayo, honey, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and pickle juice in a bowl.\n- Adjust the pickle juice to reach the desired consistency.\n- Store in a sealed bottle in the refrigerator.\n\n## Fresh Crunchy Slaw\n- Mix together the sliced red onion, cherry tomatoes, pickled gherkins, and chopped parsley.\n- Season with salt, black pepper, and sumac.\n- Store separately in the refrigerator.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('90','Garlic Steak Bites with Creamy Mashed Potatoes and Garlicky Alfredo Sauce','## Garlic Steak Bites\n- 1000g Topside/Top Sirloin Beef, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 2 tsp Salt\n- 2 tsp Black Pepper\n- 2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 2 tsp Parsley\n- 3 tsp Olive Oil\n- 30g Light Butter, plus extra for cooking\n- 20g Minced Garlic\n- Pinch of Chili Flakes (optional for no spice)\n- Fresh Parsley, chopped\n\n## Creamy Mashed Potatoes\n- 1100g Raw Potatoes, cut into chunks\n- 20g Light Butter\n- 80g Light Cream Cheese\n- 100g 1% Milk\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Black Pepper\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n\n## Garlicky Alfredo Sauce\n- 15g Light Butter\n- 1 tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 1/2 tsp Salt, or to taste\n- 1/2 tsp Chili Flakes (optional for no spice)\n- 1 tbsp Dijon Mustard\n- 20g Minced Garlic\n- 1 tbsp Fresh Parsley\n- 200g Blended Cottage Cheese\n- 200-250g 1% Milk','## Garlic Steak Bites\n- Season the beef cubes with salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and parsley.\n- Heat olive oil and a bit of butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the beef cubes and sear for 2-3 minutes on each side until a brown crust forms.\n- Add minced garlic and a pinch of chili flakes, if using, and cook for an additional 30 seconds.\n- Finish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.\n\n## Creamy Mashed Potatoes\n- Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water.\n- Bring to a boil and cook for 12-14 minutes until fork-tender.\n- Drain the potatoes and allow them to steam dry for about 5 minutes.\n- Mash the potatoes with butter, cream cheese, milk, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder until smooth and creamy.\n\n## Garlicky Alfredo Sauce\n- In a blender, blend cottage cheese with milk until completely smooth.\n- In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat and add minced garlic, cooking until fragrant.\n- Pour in the blended cottage cheese mixture along with smoked paprika, salt, chili flakes, Dijon mustard, and fresh parsley.\n- Simmer gently on low heat, stirring frequently, to prevent the sauce from splitting.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('91','Low Calorie Chicken with Bang Bang Sauce and Lemon Garlic Herb Coconut Rice','## Chicken Marinade\n- 1000g boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cut into cubes\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- 2.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 2.5 tsp onion powder\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp ginger powder\n- 3 tsp olive oil\n\n## Low Calorie Bang Bang Sauce\n- 100g light mayonnaise\n- 60g fat-free yogurt\n- 50g reduced sugar sweet chili sauce\n- 50g sriracha\n- 20g rice vinegar\n- 1 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Lemon Garlic Herb Coconut Rice\n- 260g uncooked white rice (cooked or leftover rice recommended)\n- 20g reduced-fat butter\n- 35g garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 170g white onion, finely chopped\n- Extra seasoning: 1 tsp salt, oregano, parsley, chili flakes\n- 35g shredded or desiccated coconut\n- 2 tsp lemon zest\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon','## Chicken Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F).\n- In a large bowl, combine the chicken with salt, black pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, ginger powder, and olive oil. Mix well to ensure all pieces are evenly coated.\n- Place the chicken pieces on a baking tray lined with parchment paper.\n- Spread a thin layer of the prepared Bang Bang sauce over the chicken cubes.\n- Bake in the oven for 22-25 minutes or until crispy and golden brown, ensuring the chicken is thoroughly cooked.\n\n## Final Touch for Bang Bang Chicken\n- After cooking, apply an additional layer of the Bang Bang sauce to the chicken for extra flavor.\n\n## Lemon Garlic Herb Coconut Rice\n- In a large skillet, melt the reduced-fat butter over medium heat.\n- Add the finely chopped onion and garlic, cooking for 5-6 minutes until they become fragrant and slightly translucent.\n- Add the shredded coconut, salt, oregano, parsley, chili flakes, and lemon zest to the onion mixture. Stir well and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes.\n- Incorporate the cooked rice into the skillet. Stir continuously until everything is well combined and the rice is fluffy.\n- Squeeze the juice of half a lemon over the rice, mix well, and serve alongside the chicken.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('92','Honey BBQ Chicken with Garlic Parmesan Potatoes and Creamy Sauce','## Honey BBQ Chicken\n- 1000g raw chicken breast, cubed\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1.5 tsp cumin\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- 30g light butter (for cooking all batches)\n- 60g honey (to coat all batches)\n- 160g sugar-free BBQ sauce (Brand: G Hughes)\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Garlic Parmesan Potatoes\n- 1000g uncooked potatoes, cubed\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp Italian herbs\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp onion powder\n- 30g grated Parmigiano Reggiano\n- 2 tsp olive oil (optional)\n\n## Creamy Sauce\n- 200g fat-free cottage cheese, blended\n- 300ml 1% milk\n- 1 tsp Italian herbs\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 40g grated Parmesan','## Honey BBQ Chicken\n- Season the chicken cubes with garlic powder, smoked paprika, cumin, salt, and black pepper.\n- Heat the olive oil and light butter in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the chicken for about 5 minutes on each side, ensuring each piece is golden and crispy.\n- Reduce the heat to low and stir in the honey and BBQ sauce.\n- Mix everything thoroughly to coat the chicken well, for about 1 minute.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.\n\n## Garlic Parmesan Potatoes\n- Preheat the oven to 200°C (400°F) or prepare your air fryer.\n- Combine potatoes with salt, Italian herbs, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, and olive oil.\n- Spread the potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet or air fryer basket.\n- Bake or air fry for 20-22 minutes, or until golden and crispy.\n- Sprinkle with grated Parmigiano Reggiano before serving.\n\n## Creamy Sauce\n- Blend the cottage cheese until smooth, then combine it with milk, Italian herbs, garlic powder, and grated Parmesan.\n- Gently heat the sauce in a pan on low heat, but do not bring it to a boil. Stir until slightly warm and well-mixed.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('93','Crispy Garlic Chicken with Onion Butter Fried Rice and Garlic Yum Yum Sauce','## Crispy Garlic Chicken\n- 1000g Boneless Skinless Chicken Thighs\n- 2 Tsp Black Pepper\n- 1.5 Tsp Chilli Flakes\n- 2 Tsp Garlic Powder\n- 2 Tsp Onion Powder\n- 25g Dark Soy Sauce\n- 25g Light Soy Sauce\n- 2 Tsp Olive Oil (optional)\n- 20g Reduced Fat Butter for cooking\n- 1 Tbsp Fresh Parsley finely chopped\n\n## Onion Butter Fried Rice\n- 280g Uncooked White Rice (cook to 620g weight or use cold leftover cooked rice)\n- 30g Reduced Fat Butter\n- 150g White Onion finely chopped\n- 100g Spring Onion (white part chopped)\n- 100g Carrots chopped\n- 1 Tsp each Black Pepper, Onion Powder, Parsley (Extra Seasoning)\n- 20g Dark Soy Sauce (add more if needed)\n- 20g Light Soy Sauce\n- 40g Oyster Sauce\n- Big Handful Chopped Spring Onion\n\n## Garlic Yum Yum Sauce\n- 150g Light Mayo\n- 75g Reduced Sugar Ketchup\n- 75g Sriracha\n- 1 Tsp Minced Garlic\n- 1/2 Tsp Ginger Powder\n- 1 Tbsp Rice Vinegar\n- Dash of Milk or Water for desired consistency\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh Parsley chopped\n- Chilli & Garlic grinder mix\n- Sesame Seeds','## Crispy Garlic Chicken\n- Preheat oven to 200°C (392°F).\n- In a large bowl, mix black pepper, chilli flakes, garlic powder, onion powder, dark soy sauce, and light soy sauce.\n- Add chicken thighs to the bowl, ensuring they are well-coated with the marinade. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Heat a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat and add olive oil and butter.\n- Once butter is melted, add chicken thighs skin-side down and sear for 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown.\n- Transfer skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes or until chicken is completely cooked through and juices run clear.\n- Remove from oven, let rest for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with fresh parsley before serving.\n\n## Onion Butter Fried Rice\n- Heat a large pan over medium heat and add butter.\n- Add chopped white onion and carrots, sautéing until the onion becomes translucent and the carrots soften.\n- Add the chopped white part of the spring onion. Stir and cook for an additional 2 minutes.\n- Add cooked rice to the pan and increase heat to medium-high. Stir well to combine with vegetables.\n- Stir in black pepper, onion powder, parsley, dark soy sauce, light soy sauce, and oyster sauce.\n- Cook while stirring for another 3-5 minutes or until the rice is heated through and evenly coated with sauce.\n- Garnish with a handful of chopped spring onion before serving.\n\n## Garlic Yum Yum Sauce\n- In a small bowl, combine light mayo, reduced sugar ketchup, sriracha, minced garlic, ginger powder, and rice vinegar.\n- Stir well to combine, adding a dash of milk or water to reach your desired consistency.\n- Store in an airtight container in the fridge until ready to use.\n\n## Serving\n- Plate the chicken and fried rice.\n- Drizzle Garlic Yum Yum Sauce over the top or serve on the side.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley, chilli & garlic grinder mix, and sesame seeds.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('94','High-Protein Taco Bowl','## Taco Seasoning Mix (1 Serving)\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Black Pepper\n- 1 tsp Onion Powder\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1 tsp Cumin\n- 1 tsp Paprika\n- 1 tsp Chili Powder\n- 1 tsp Oregano\n\n## Potatoes\n- 800g Raw Cubed Potatoes\n- 1 Serving Taco Seasoning Mix\n- 2 tsp Olive Oil\n\n## Chipotle Spicy Sauce\n- 100g Fat-Free Yogurt\n- 80g Light Mayo (Brand: Hellmann''s)\n- 50g Chipotle Chili Paste (Brand: Waitrose)\n- 20g Hot Sauce\n- 20g Honey\n- Salt, Paprika, Garlic Powder to taste\n\n## Pico de Gallo\n- 2 Large Tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 Large Red Onion, chopped\n- 1/2 Red Bell Pepper, chopped\n- 1/2 Green Bell Pepper, chopped\n- Large handful of Coriander, chopped\n- Salt, Pepper, Garlic, Cumin, Paprika to taste\n- Juice of 1 Whole Lime\n\n## Taco Beef\n- 800g Raw Lean Minced Beef (Topside Beef)\n- 20-30g Tomato Paste\n- 1.5 Serving Taco Seasoning Mix\n- Grated Mozzarella or any low-fat cheese\n- 15g Grass-Fed Butter for cooking','## Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven to 200°C (392°F).\n- In a bowl, toss the cubed potatoes with olive oil and the taco seasoning mix until well coated.\n- Spread the potatoes out onto a baking sheet.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until they are golden and tender, taking care not to overcook them.\n\n## Chipotle Spicy Sauce\n- Combine yogurt, light mayo, chipotle chili paste, hot sauce, and honey in a bowl.\n- Season with salt, paprika, and garlic powder to taste.\n- Mix well until smooth.\n- Store in the refrigerator until ready to use.\n\n## Pico de Gallo\n- In a mixing bowl, combine chopped tomatoes, red onion, red and green bell peppers, and coriander.\n- Season with salt, pepper, garlic, cumin, and paprika.\n- Stir in the lime juice.\n- Mix well and store in a separate container in the refrigerator.\n\n## Taco Beef\n- Heat the butter in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add the minced beef and cook until browned.\n- Stir in the tomato paste and taco seasoning mix.\n- If the mixture is too dry, add a little water to maintain moisture.\n- Cook until everything is well combined and heated through.\n\n## Assembly\n- Reheat the potatoes and beef if they have cooled.\n- Spoon the beef and potatoes into bowls.\n- Top with your prepared pico de gallo and chipotle spicy sauce.\n- Garnish with grated mozzarella or any low-fat cheese before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('95','Creamy Chicken Alfredo Pasta','## Grilled Chicken\n- 800g Raw Cubed Chicken Breast\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 2 tsp Italian Herbs\n- 1.5 tsp Parsley\n- 1 tsp Chilli Flakes (optional for spice)\n- 1.5 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1.5 tsp Paprika\n- 2 tsp Olive Oil\n- 20g Light Butter (for cooking + after cooking)\n\n## Creamy Alfredo Pasta\n- 210g Uncooked / 520g Cooked Pasta (preferably fettuccine)\n- 80g Chopped White Onion\n- 4 Garlic Cloves, chopped\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Italian Herbs\n- 1 tsp Parsley\n- 0.5 tsp Chilli Flakes (optional for spice)\n- 1 tsp Paprika\n- 150g Tomato Sauce / Passata\n- 300ml Light Evaporated Milk\n- 130g Light Cream Cheese\n- 30g Grated Parmesan Cheese\n- Optional: Pasta Water (to adjust sauce thickness)','## Grill Chicken\n- Season the chicken cubes with salt, Italian herbs, parsley, chilli flakes, garlic powder, and paprika. Toss in olive oil.\n- In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook the chicken pieces for 3-4 minutes. Flip and cook for another 3 minutes until fully cooked.\n- Reduce the heat, add a little more butter, coat the chicken, then set aside.\n\n## Prepare Alfredo Sauce\n- In the same skillet, cook the chopped onion over medium heat for 5-6 minutes until softened.\n- Add the garlic and spices; stir for 1 minute.\n- Add the tomato sauce and let it simmer on low heat for at least 5 minutes until it bubbles and slightly separates.\n\n## Combine and Finish\n- Stir in the evaporated milk and light cream cheese, maintaining a low heat, until the mixture combines and thickens.\n- Add the grated Parmesan cheese, stirring until melted into the sauce.\n- If the sauce is too thick, incorporate some reserved pasta water.\n\n## Reheat and Serve\n- To serve, reheat the chicken and pasta together in a pan over low heat. Cover with a lid for about 5 minutes.\n- If the sauce has thickened too much upon reheating, add a splash of milk to adjust consistency before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('96','High-Protein Beef Mac & Cheese','## Main Ingredients\n- 800g raw beef mince (topside/top round)\n- 20g grass-fed butter or lighter butter\n- 1 tbsp minced garlic\n- 100g white onion, chopped\n- 75g each of red, green, and yellow bell peppers\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 140g light cream cheese\n- 50g shredded mozzarella\n- 3-4 light cheese slices (19g each)\n- 240g uncooked macaroni or 560g cooked macaroni\n\n## To Finish\n- 125ml reserved pasta water\n- Garnish with parsley','## Cooking Instructions\n- Begin by cooking the macaroni in boiling water until tender. Reserve 125ml of the pasta water, then drain and set aside.\n- In a large pan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the onions and bell peppers, cooking for 5-6 minutes until they become soft and aromatic.\n- Push the vegetables to the side or remove them from the pan. Increase the heat to high and add the beef mince along with the garlic. Cook for about 8 minutes, stirring in the salt, black pepper, paprika, and chili flakes, until the beef is golden brown and fully cooked.\n- Reduce the heat to low, then stir in the cream cheese until well combined. Add the reserved pasta water to create a smooth sauce.\n- Mix in the cooked macaroni and shredded mozzarella, allowing the cheese to melt into the sauce evenly.\n- Layer the light cheese slices over the mixture and let them melt down gently.\n- Garnish with chopped parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('97','Lemon Garlic Chicken with Crispy Seasoned Potatoes','## Lemon Garlic Chicken Marinade\n- 1100g raw boneless skinless chicken thighs (trim excess fat)\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2.5 tsp mixed herbs\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1.5 tsp chili flakes\n- 2 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- Juice of 1 large lemon\n- 4 tsp olive oil\n\n## Crispy Seasoned Potatoes\n- 1100g raw yellow or white potatoes, cubed\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp mixed herbs\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1.5 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- 3-4 tsp olive oil','## Lemon Garlic Chicken Marinade\n- Combine chicken thighs with salt, mixed herbs, garlic powder, smoked paprika, chili flakes, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, and olive oil in a large bowl or resealable bag.\n- Marinate for a few hours or overnight for optimal flavor, although cooking immediately is also an option if time is short.\n- Preheat oven or air fryer to 200°C / 400°F.\n- Arrange the marinated chicken on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, ensuring an even layer for efficient cooking.\n- Bake for 25 minutes, or up to 30 minutes for a crispier texture.\n- Reserve the flavorful juices from the pan to drizzle over the chicken when serving.\n- Allow the chicken to rest for 4-5 minutes before slicing into cubes.\n\n## Crispy Seasoned Potatoes\n- Toss potato cubes with salt, mixed herbs, garlic powder, smoked paprika, chili flakes, Dijon mustard, and olive oil until well coated.\n- Spread evenly on a parchment-lined baking sheet.\n- Bake or air fry at 200°C / 400°F for 25-28 minutes until crispy.\n- You can cook the potatoes alongside the chicken to save time.\n- To reheat, warm in a pan over low heat for 5 minutes or use the air fryer to restore crispiness.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('98','Steak Bites with Chipotle Creamy Potatoes','## Steak\n- 800g beef steaks, cut into cubes (Topside/Top Round preferred)\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp parsley\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- Juice of 1 whole lime\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- 20g light butter (for cooking and additional use)\n- Fresh garlic paste\n\n## Chipotle Creamy Potatoes\n- 800g raw white potatoes, cubed\n- 2 tsp Italian herbs\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp olive oil (optional)\n- 3-4 garlic cloves, chopped\n- 100g red onion, chopped\n- 1 tsp Italian herbs\n- 50g chipotle chili paste (Brand: @waitrose)\n- 250ml light evaporated milk\n- 100g light cream cheese\n- 30g grated Parmesan cheese\n- Freshly chopped parsley','## Steak Preparation\n- Season your steak cubes with salt, garlic powder, parsley, cumin, smoked paprika, lime juice, and olive oil. Allow them to marinate for a minimum of 30 minutes to enhance the flavor.\n\n## Cooking the Steak Bites\n- Heat light butter in a pan over medium-high heat. Sear the steak bites for 2-3 minutes on each side until they develop a rich brown crust. Avoid overcrowding the pan to ensure even cooking.\n\n## Cooking Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (400°F). Toss the cubed potatoes with Italian herbs, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and olive oil (if using). Bake or air fry for 20-22 minutes until golden and cooked through.\n\n## Preparing the Sauce\n- In a separate pan, sauté the chopped garlic and onion over medium heat for about 5 minutes until softened. Stir in the Italian herbs and chipotle chili paste, mixing thoroughly before adding the evaporated milk.\n- Lower the heat and incorporate the cream cheese, stirring to form a smooth mixture. Once ready, fold in the cooked potatoes, ensuring they are well-coated with the sauce.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish the steak bites and chipotle creamy potatoes with freshly chopped parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('99','Korean BBQ Chicken with Crunchy Cucumber Salad','## Korean BBQ Chicken Marinade\n- 900g raw chicken thighs, boneless skinless\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tbsp garlic paste\n- 1 tbsp ginger paste\n- 40g gochujang paste\n- 25g sriracha\n- 1 tbsp sesame seeds\n- 40ml light soy sauce\n\n## Crunchy & Tangy Cucumber Salad\n- 400g cucumbers, thinly sliced\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp fresh garlic, minced\n- 15g gochujang\n- 15g honey\n- 30ml rice vinegar\n- 1 tbsp sesame seeds\n- 1 tsp red pepper flakes or chili flakes\n- 25ml light soy sauce','## Preparation\n- If using chicken breast, cut into thinner fillets before marinating.\n- For optimal flavor, marinate the chicken overnight, though it can be cooked immediately after marinating if needed.\n\n## Making the Marinade\n- In a bowl, combine black pepper, garlic paste, ginger paste, gochujang paste, sriracha, sesame seeds, and light soy sauce.\n- Add the chicken thighs to the mixture, ensuring they are fully coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate to marinate.\n\n## Making the Cucumber Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the salt, minced garlic, gochujang, honey, rice vinegar, sesame seeds, red pepper flakes, and light soy sauce.\n- Add the sliced cucumbers and toss until evenly coated.\n- Store in the refrigerator. Flavors will enhance over time.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Preheat an air fryer to 200°C (390°F).\n- Place the chicken on the air fryer''s sheet pan in a single layer.\n- Cook for approximately 12-15 minutes, adjusting based on the amount of chicken, until you achieve a nice char.\n- Check frequently to avoid overcooking.\n\n## Serving\n- Warm the chicken and rice in a pan over low heat if needed.\n- Serve the chicken alongside the chilled cucumber salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('100','Buffalo Chicken with Crispy Potatoes and Side Salad','## Buffalo Chicken\n- 800g Raw Chicken Breast, Cut Into Small Cubes\n- 1.5 tsp Salt\n- 1.5 tsp Dried Parsley\n- 1.5 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1 tsp Cumin\n- 1.5 tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 2 tsp Olive Oil\n- 100g Buffalo Hot Sauce (For Cooking)\n- 30g Light Butter (For Cooking)\n\n## Crispy Potatoes\n- 800g Raw White Potatoes, Cut Into Cubes\n- 1.5 tsp Salt\n- 1.5 tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 1.5 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1.5 tsp Dried Parsley\n- 1 tsp Cumin\n- Optional: 2 tsp Olive Oil or Use Cooking Spray for Lower Calories\n\n## Tangy Creamy Buffalo Sauce\n- 150g Buffalo Hot Sauce (e.g., Frank’s Red Hot)\n- 100g Low Fat Yogurt (e.g., Milbona)\n- 100g Light Mayonnaise (e.g., Hellmann’s)\n- 25g Honey\n\n## Fresh Side Salad\n- 150g Fresh Tomatoes, Chopped\n- 100g Red Onion, Finely Chopped\n- 100g Cucumber, Deseeded and Chopped\n- 50g Green Onion/Scallion, Chopped\n- 25g Fresh Parsley, Chopped\n- 1/2 tsp Each: Salt, Black Pepper, Garlic Powder, Cumin\n- Juice of 1/2 Lemon','## Crispy Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (400°F).\n- Toss potatoes with salt, smoked paprika, garlic powder, parsley, and cumin.\n- Lightly coat with olive oil or a cooking spray.\n- Spread out on a baking sheet and bake or air fry for 18-20 minutes until golden and crispy.\n\n## Buffalo Chicken\n- Season the chicken cubes with salt, parsley, garlic powder, cumin, and smoked paprika.\n- In a pan, heat olive oil and butter over medium-high heat.\n- Add chicken and cook until golden and slightly charred.\n- Reduce the heat to low, and stir in the buffalo hot sauce until well-coated.\n\n## Tangy Creamy Buffalo Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine buffalo hot sauce, yogurt, mayonnaise, and honey.\n- Mix well until smooth and creamy. Store in a bottle and refrigerate if prepared in advance.\n\n## Fresh Side Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, red onion, cucumber, green onion, and parsley.\n- Season with salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and cumin.\n- Drizzle with lemon juice and toss gently to combine.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('101','Honey Garlic Steak Bites with Creamy Gochujang Noodles and Marinated Cucumber Salad','## Honey Garlic Steak Bites\n- 1000g / 35oz Beef Topside Steaks, cubed\n- 1.5 tsp Salt\n- 2 tsp Black Pepper\n- 1.5 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1.5 tsp Onion Powder\n- 1.5 tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 3 tsp Olive Oil\n- 40g / 1.4oz Light Butter\n- 25g or 1 tbsp Minced Garlic\n- 35g Honey\n- A good handful of Chopped Parsley\n\n## Creamy Gochujang Noodles\n- 300g / 10.6oz Dry Medium Egg Noodles\n- 30g or 1.5 tbsp Minced Garlic\n- 80g / 2.8oz Gochujang Paste\n- 300ml / 1.2 Cups Milk or Evaporated Milk\n- 110g / 3.8oz Light Cream Cheese\n- 40g / 1.4oz Grated Parmesan Cheese\n- 125ml or 1/2 Cup Noodle/Pasta Water\n- Green Onion, Sesame Seeds, Parmesan Cheese for garnish\n\n## Marinated Cucumber Salad\n- 2 Cucumbers, sliced\n- 2 tbsp Soy Sauce\n- 2 tbsp Rice Vinegar\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1 tbsp Sesame Seeds','## Honey Garlic Steak Bites\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and add butter and olive oil.\n- Season the steak bites with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, and smoked paprika.\n- Cook the steak bites for 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown and charred.\n- Reduce the heat and add additional butter, minced garlic, honey, and chopped parsley.\n- Stir for 1 minute, ensuring each piece is well coated and juicy.\n\n## Creamy Gochujang Noodles\n- Boil the noodles according to package instructions and reserve 125ml or 1/2 cup of the pasta water.\n- In the leftover butter from the steak, cook the minced garlic on low heat for 2 minutes.\n- Add the gochujang paste and cook for another 1-2 minutes, mixing well.\n- Pour in the milk and stir until combined.\n- Add the cream cheese and allow it to melt, stirring to combine.\n- Slowly add the reserved noodle water to achieve the desired sauce consistency.\n- Toss the cooked noodles in the sauce and garnish with green onions, sesame seeds, and Parmesan cheese.\n\n## Marinated Cucumber Salad\n- In a bowl, combine sliced cucumbers with soy sauce, rice vinegar, garlic powder, and sesame seeds.\n- Mix well and let marinate for at least 10 minutes before serving for better flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('102','Honey Chipotle Chicken with Cilantro Lime Rice and Chipotle Sauce','## Honey Chipotle Chicken Marinade\n- 1000g raw boneless skinless chicken thighs\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp oregano\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1.5 tsp cumin\n- 70g chipotle paste or chipotle peppers in adobo\n- 50g honey\n- Juice of 3/4 lime\n\n## Cilantro Lime Rice\n- 20g light butter\n- 100g chopped white onion\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp turmeric\n- 3/4 tsp garlic powder\n- 3/4 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1/2 tsp cumin\n- 280g raw basmati rice (cooked)\n- Chopped cilantro/coriander (a large handful)\n- Juice of 1 lime\n\n## Chipotle Sauce\n- 100g low-fat yogurt\n- 50g light mayo\n- 20-30g chipotle paste\n- 50g pineapple chunks (preferably fresh)\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1/2 tsp onion powder\n- Squeeze of lime juice','## Cooking the Chicken\n- Preheat your oven to 200C / 400F.\n- Mix the chicken thighs with salt, oregano, garlic powder, smoked paprika, cumin, chipotle paste, honey, and lime juice until evenly coated.\n- Place the coated chicken on a baking tray lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake in the oven for 20-23 minutes or until cooked through, then broil for an additional 2-3 minutes to crisp and char the surface.\n\n## Preparing the Cilantro Lime Rice\n- In a large pan, melt the light butter over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped white onion and cook until soft and translucent.\n- Stir in salt, turmeric, garlic powder, smoked paprika, and cumin until the spices are fragrant.\n- Add the cooked basmati rice and stir until evenly coated with the spice mixture.\n- Fold in the chopped cilantro and lime juice just before serving.\n\n## Making the Chipotle Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine low-fat yogurt, light mayo, chipotle paste, pineapple chunks, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, and a squeeze of lime juice.\n- Mix until smooth and adjust seasoning according to taste.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('103','Garlic Steak Bites with Spicy Sauce, Seasoned Potatoes, and Fluffy Scrambled Eggs','## Garlic Steak Bites\n- 800g Raw Topside Beef Steak, cut into cubes\n- 2 tsp Himalayan Pink Salt\n- 2 tsp Black Pepper\n- 2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 2 tsp Dried Parsley\n- 2 tsp Olive Oil\n- 15-20g Grass-Fed Butter for cooking\n\n## Seasoned Potatoes\n- 700g Cubed Raw Potatoes\n- 1 tsp Pink Salt\n- 1 tsp Black Pepper\n- 1 tsp Cumin\n- 1 tsp Paprika\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n- Optional: Olive Oil or Cooking Spray\n\n## Spicy Sauce\n- 100g Natural Yogurt\n- 50g Light Mayo\n- 50g Chipotle Chili Paste\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Smoked Paprika\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n\n## Scrambled Eggs\n- 8 Whole Eggs (preferably pasture-raised)\n- Pinch of Salt & Pepper','## Preparation\n- Start by marinating the steak cubes in olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and dried parsley. Allow the steak to marinate for as long as possible to enhance flavor.\n\n## Spicy Sauce\n- Combine natural yogurt, light mayo, chipotle chili paste, salt, smoked paprika, and garlic powder in a bowl. Make extra sauce to store in the refrigerator for future use.\n\n## Garlic Steak Bites\n- Preheat a pan over medium-high heat. Add butter and allow it to melt completely.\n- Add the marinated steak cubes to the pan in a single layer, cooking for 2-3 minutes on each side until a crust forms.\n- Reduce the heat, add extra garlic and parsley, and stir gently for 1-2 minutes.\n- Remove the steak bites from the pan and set aside.\n\n## Seasoned Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (392°F).\n- In a bowl, toss the cubed potatoes with pink salt, black pepper, cumin, paprika, garlic powder, and a drizzle of olive oil or a few sprays of cooking spray.\n- Cook the potatoes for 20-22 minutes until they are crisp and tender.\n\n## Scrambled Eggs\n- Crack the eggs into a bowl, add a pinch of salt and pepper, and whisk until well combined.\n- Heat a pan over medium heat, add the eggs, and continuously stir until the eggs are fluffy and fully cooked.\n\n## Serving\n- To reheat, place all components in a pan over low heat for 5 minutes.\n- Serve the spicy sauce fresh, pouring it over the steak bites just before eating.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('104','Chicken with Creamy Sauce and Crispy Potatoes','## Chicken Marinade and Creamy Sauce\n- 1000g raw chicken breast, cut into cubes\n- 1 tbsp (30g) minced garlic or garlic paste\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp mixed herbs (oregano, parsley, basil)\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp onion powder\n- 1.5 tsp chili flakes (optional)\n- 3 tsp olive oil\n- 20g light butter for cooking\n- 300ml skimmed milk\n- 160g garlic & herb cream cheese (e.g., Philadelphia)\n- 80g shredded mozzarella or any low-fat cheese\n\n## Crispy Potatoes\n- 1100g raw yellow or white potatoes, cut into small cubes\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp mixed herbs\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 2 tsp olive oil (optional)','## Chicken Marinade and Creamy Sauce\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and melt the light butter.\n- Add the chicken cubes and cook for 5 minutes on one side until a golden brown crust forms; flip and cook for an additional 4-5 minutes until fully cooked.\n- Remove chicken from the pan and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add minced garlic, salt, mixed herbs, smoked paprika, onion powder, chili flakes, and olive oil; sauté until fragrant.\n- Stir in the skimmed milk and allow it to heat through.\n- Add the garlic & herb cream cheese and shredded mozzarella, stirring until the sauce is smooth and creamy.\n- Return the cooked chicken to the pan, coating it with the creamy sauce; keep warm.\n\n## Crispy Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven or air fryer to 200°C (400°F).\n- Toss the potato cubes with salt, mixed herbs, garlic powder, paprika, and olive oil if desired, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Spread the potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet or air fryer basket.\n- Bake or air fry for 22-25 minutes, until the potatoes are golden brown and crispy, shaking halfway through cooking for even crisping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('105','Garlic Herb Cajun Chicken with Light & Fluffy Mash and Creamy Cajun Sauce','## Garlic Herb Cajun Chicken\n- 800g boneless skinless chicken thighs\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp Italian herbs\n- 1.5 tsp chili flakes\n- 1.5 tsp parsley\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp onion powder\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n\n## Light & Fluffy Mash\n- 800g white potatoes, peeled and diced into 1-inch chunks\n- 20g room temperature light butter\n- 125ml (1/2 cup) warm skimmed milk\n- 1.5 tsp salt, or to taste\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n\n## Creamy Cajun Sauce\n- 10g light butter\n- 3/4 tsp each of salt, Italian herbs, chili flakes, garlic powder, onion powder, parsley, paprika\n- 250ml (1 cup) skimmed milk\n- 40g grated Parmigiano cheese\n- A good handful of chopped spinach','## Garlic Herb Cajun Chicken\n- Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F).\n- Mix together the salt, Italian herbs, chili flakes, parsley, garlic powder, onion powder, and paprika.\n- Coat the chicken thighs with olive oil and rub the spice mix evenly onto them.\n- Arrange the chicken on a baking sheet and bake in the oven or air fry for 22-25 minutes, or until fully cooked. Alternatively, pan-fry in some butter for 4-5 minutes on each side over medium heat until golden and cooked through.\n\n## Light & Fluffy Mash\n- Place the diced potatoes in a pot and cover with cold water.\n- Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for 12-14 minutes until the potatoes are fork-tender.\n- Drain the water, cover the pot with a lid, and let the potatoes steam for about 5 minutes.\n- Uncover, then mash the potatoes using a ricer or masher.\n- Incorporate room temperature butter and warm milk, mixing until the mash is smooth and creamy. Season with salt and garlic powder.\n\n## Creamy Cajun Sauce\n- Melt the butter in a saucepan over low heat.\n- Add the spices and toast for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.\n- Slowly whisk in the milk and then add the cream cheese and parmesan.\n- Continue stirring until the sauce is smooth, creamy, and slightly thickened.\n- Add the spinach and gently warm the sauce for an additional 3-4 minutes, until the spinach is wilted.\n\n## Serving\n- Slice the chicken into cubes and serve alongside the fluffy mashed potatoes.\n- Pour the creamy sauce over the chicken and potatoes just before serving, or store it separately and add when ready to eat.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('106','Garlic Teriyaki Beef with Garlic Fried Rice and Low-Cal Yum Yum Sauce','## Garlic Teriyaki Beef\n- 800g (28oz) Beef Mince\n- 30g (2 Tbsp) Light Soy Sauce\n- 20g (2 Tbsp) Dark Soy Sauce\n- 30g (2.5 Tbsp) Honey or Maple Syrup\n- 25g (2 Tbsp) Rice Vinegar\n- 20g (1.5 Tbsp) Minced Garlic or Garlic Paste\n- 1 Cup Chopped Green Onion (Green part)\n- 1.5 Tbsp Sesame Seeds\n- 20g Light Butter (for cooking)\n\n## Garlic Fried Rice\n- 10g Light Butter (for cooking)\n- 1 Tbsp Chopped Garlic\n- 80g Chopped White Onion\n- 80g Chopped Green Onion (white part)\n- 2 Whole Eggs + 2 Egg Whites (whisked)\n- 200g Dry Weight / ~520g Cooked White Rice (Basmati or short grain)\n- 15g Dark Soy Sauce\n- 15g Light Soy Sauce\n- 60g Chili Garlic Sauce\n- Good Handful of Chopped Green Onion\n- 1/2 Cup Chopped Coriander\n- 1 Tbsp Sesame Seeds\n\n## Low-Cal Yum Yum Sauce\n- 50g Fat-Free Yogurt (Greek or Skyr)\n- 50g Light Mayo\n- 25g Reduced Sugar Ketchup\n- 25g Sriracha\n- 1 Tsp Garlic Powder\n- Dash of Milk for desired consistency','## Garlic Teriyaki Beef\n- Heat a large pan over high heat and add the butter. Once melted, add the beef mince and cook for 6-8 minutes until it''s well-browned.\n- Reduce the heat to medium. Stir in the minced garlic, light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, and honey or maple syrup.\n- Continue cooking the beef for another 5 minutes, allowing it to become crispy. Set aside after cooking.\n- Sprinkle the chopped green onions and sesame seeds over the cooked beef as garnish.\n\n## Garlic Fried Rice\n- In a large pan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic, and cook for about 5 minutes until the vegetables are softened.\n- Move the vegetables to one side of the pan and pour in the whisked eggs and egg whites. Stir gently over low heat until scrambled.\n- Add the cooked rice along with light and dark soy sauces. Mix thoroughly to ensure the rice is fully coated. Adjust with extra soy sauce if needed.\n- Stir in the chili garlic sauce, chopped green onions, coriander, and sesame seeds. Heat through and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Low-Cal Yum Yum Sauce\n- In a bowl, whisk together yogurt, light mayo, reduced sugar ketchup, sriracha, and garlic powder.\n- Add a dash of milk to thin out the sauce to your desired consistency. Mix until smooth.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('107','Spicy Chicken Wraps','## Chicken\n- 600g raw chicken breast, cut into thin strips\n- 3-4 garlic cloves, minced or 1 tbsp garlic paste\n- 1.5 tsp oregano\n- 1.5 tsp paprika\n- 1.5 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 3/4 lemon, juiced\n- 2 tsp olive oil (for cooking)\n- 3 low-calorie tortilla wraps\n- Shredded lettuce\n- Chopped red onion and tomato\n\n## Spicy Sauce\n- 100g low-fat yogurt\n- 20g sriracha or any preferred hot sauce\n- 1 tsp minced garlic\n- A handful of fresh chopped parsley\n- 1/2 tsp each salt and pepper\n- 1/2 lemon, juiced','## Chicken Preparation\n- Slice the chicken into thin strips and marinate it with minced garlic, oregano, paprika, onion powder, chili flakes, salt, black pepper, and lemon juice for 15-30 minutes to enhance the flavor.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Cook the chicken strips for 3-4 minutes on each side until they are golden brown and fully cooked through.\n- Avoid overcrowding the pan to prevent the chicken from steaming in its own juices.\n\n## Spicy Sauce Preparation\n- Mix the low-fat yogurt, sriracha, minced garlic, chopped parsley, salt, pepper, and lemon juice in a bowl. Adjust seasoning to taste.\n- You can prepare this sauce in batches and store it in the fridge for later use.\n\n## Assembling the Wraps\n- Warm the tortilla wraps slightly. Fill each wrap with cooked chicken strips, shredded lettuce, chopped red onion, and tomato.\n- Drizzle with spicy sauce, wrap tightly, and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('108','Marinated Chicken with Chilli Peanut Noodles','## Marinated Chicken\n- 800g raw chicken breasts, cut into cubes\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tbsp garlic paste\n- 1 tbsp ginger paste\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1.5 tsp onion powder\n- 25g sriracha\n- 30ml soy sauce (15ml light soy sauce + 15ml dark soy sauce)\n- 20g light butter\n- Handful chopped coriander/cilantro\n\n## Chilli Peanut Noodles\n- 100g natural peanut butter (without palm oil)\n- 75g soy sauce (45g light soy sauce + 30g dark soy sauce)\n- 50g sriracha\n- 30g rice vinegar\n- 1 tsp chili flakes (optional if you don''t like spicy)\n- 125ml - 150ml hot noodle water (reserved from boiled noodles)\n- 250g uncooked/570g cooked medium egg noodles\n- 1/2 cup chopped green onion/scallion\n- Handful chopped coriander\n- Handful sesame seeds','## Marinated Chicken\n- Preheat a skillet over medium heat. Cook the chicken cubes for 3-4 minutes on each side until they develop a golden brown crust. Avoid overcrowding the pan.\n- Once cooked, reduce the heat and add extra butter along with chopped coriander. Cook for an additional minute to meld flavors.\n\n## Chilli Peanut Noodles\n- Boil the medium egg noodles for 4-5 minutes over medium heat until tender. Drain and rinse under cold water to halt cooking.\n- In a pan over low heat, combine peanut butter, soy sauce, sriracha, rice vinegar, and chili flakes. Gradually mix in the reserved hot noodle water until the sauce is smooth and silky.\n- Toss the cooked noodles in the prepared sauce. Garnish with chopped green onion, chopped coriander, and sesame seeds.\n\n## Notes\n- Marinate chicken for at least 30 minutes or ideally overnight to enhance flavor.\n- To reheat, place the noodles in a pan over low heat for 5-10 minutes. Add a little water to loosen if necessary.\n- Boil noodles before making the peanut sauce to have the noodle water ready for use.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('109','Garlic Parmesan Steak Bites with Alfredo Pasta','## Garlic Parmesan Steak Bites\n- 800g raw steaks, cut into cubes\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp Italian herbs\n- 1.5 tsp parsley\n- 1.5 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- 30-40g light butter (for cooking and extra after cooking)\n- 2 tsp garlic paste or minced garlic\n- 20g grated Parmigiano Reggiano\n\n## Alfredo Pasta\n- 80g white onion, chopped\n- 1 tbsp chopped garlic\n- 1 tsp each of salt, pepper, Italian herbs, parsley, and smoked paprika (extra seasoning)\n- 250-300ml light evaporated milk or regular milk\n- 130g light cream cheese\n- 40g grated Parmigiano Reggiano\n- 210g uncooked or 520g cooked pasta\n- 50-60ml pasta water (if sauce is too thick)','## Steak Preparation\n- Combine the steak cubes with salt, pepper, Italian herbs, parsley, garlic powder, smoked paprika, and olive oil in a bowl.\n- Marinate for 30 minutes to enhance the flavor.\n\n## Cooking the Steak Bites\n- In a pan over medium-high heat, melt some butter.\n- Sear the steak bites for about 2 minutes on each side until they form a beautiful golden crust.\n- Reduce the heat, add extra butter, garlic, and half of the grated Parmigiano Reggiano.\n- Stir for one minute until well-coated, then remove and set aside.\n\n## Preparing the Alfredo Sauce\n- In the same pan, sauté the onion and garlic over medium-low heat for 5-6 minutes until soft and translucent.\n- Stir in additional seasoning spices, and cook for another minute.\n- Reduce the heat and add milk and cream cheese, stirring until smooth.\n- Allow it to bubble gently until thickened.\n- Stir in the remaining grated Parmigiano Reggiano.\n\n## Final Assembly\n- Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and mix well. If the sauce is too thick, add some reserved pasta water.\n- Serve the pasta with the garlic parmesan steak bites on top.\n\n## Reheating Instructions\n- This dish freezes well. Reheat by placing in a pan or microwave on low for 5 minutes with a splash of milk to keep the pasta creamy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('110','Marinated Chicken with Spicy Red Rice and Side Salad','## Chicken Marinade\n- 800g chicken breast, cut into small cubes\n- 1 tbsp garlic paste\n- 1.5 tsp salt\n- 1.5 tsp oregano\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- 20g light butter (for cooking + extra)\n- Handful of fresh chopped coriander/cilantro\n\n## White Sauce\n- 100g low-fat yogurt\n- 80g light mayonnaise\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp pepper\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon\n- Optional: Drizzle of sriracha when serving\n\n## Spicy Red Rice\n- 4-5 garlic cloves, chopped\n- 50g harissa or tomato paste\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp oregano\n- 1 tsp paprika\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 20-25ml water\n- 560g cooked basmati rice\n\n## Side Salad\n- 200g shredded lettuce\n- 250g chopped tomatoes\n- 200g chopped cucumbers\n- Dash of chili flakes','## Chicken Preparation\n- Marinate the chicken cubes with garlic paste, salt, oregano, smoked paprika, chili flakes, cumin, olive oil, and lemon juice. Allow it to marinate for a minimum of 30 minutes, or refrigerate overnight for optimal flavor.\n- In a skillet, melt a portion of the light butter over medium-high heat. Cook the marinated chicken for 3-4 minutes on each side until it turns golden brown.\n- Reduce the heat when adding extra butter and fresh coriander. Stir well to coat the chicken thoroughly.\n\n## White Sauce\n- Combine the yogurt, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and lemon juice in a bowl. Mix until smooth. Drizzle sriracha for an optional spicy kick.\n- Store in a bottle and refrigerate for use with other dishes. Feel free to make a larger batch.\n\n## Spicy Red Rice\n- In a large pan, sauté chopped garlic in a little olive oil until aromatic.\n- Add harissa or tomato paste, salt, oregano, paprika, chili flakes, cumin, and water, stirring to combine.\n- Fold in the cooked basmati rice, ensuring the mixture is well incorporated and heated through.\n\n## Side Salad\n- In a salad bowl, combine shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, and cucumbers.\n- Sprinkle with a dash of chili flakes. Store the salad separately or freshly prepare when serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('111','Spicy Beef and Cheesy Nacho Fries with Fresh Side Salad','## Taco Seasoning Mix (1 Serving)\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp paprika\n- 1/2 or 1 tsp chili powder\n- 1 tsp oregano\n- 1 tsp cumin\n\n## Crispy Taco Fries\n- 900g white potatoes, cut into thin fries\n- 1 serving taco seasoning mix\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n\n## Juicy Spicy Beef\n- 800g minced beef\n- 1 serving taco seasoning\n- 20g tomato paste\n- 25g chopped jalapeños (from the jar)\n- 20-25ml jalapeño juice\n- 20g light butter (for cooking)\n\n## Nacho Cheese Sauce\n- 180ml light evaporated milk\n- 5 cheese slices (20g each slice)\n- 50g light cheddar or sharp cheddar\n- 15-20ml jalapeño juice (optional)\n\n## Fresh Side Salad\n- 150g tomatoes, chopped\n- 100g red onion, chopped\n- 150g red & green bell peppers, chopped\n- 200g avocados, cubed\n- 25g fresh coriander, chopped\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 15g honey\n- 1 tsp salt & black pepper','## Juicy Spicy Beef\n- In a large skillet, melt the light butter over high heat. Add the minced beef, breaking it up with a spatula, and cook for 5-7 minutes until fully browned.\n- Mix in the taco seasoning, tomato paste, chopped jalapeños, and jalapeño juice. Continue to cook for 2-3 more minutes until everything is well combined and golden brown.\n\n## Crispy Taco Fries\n- Preheat your oven to 220°C (428°F) or air fryer to recommended settings.\n- In a large bowl, toss the cut potatoes with olive oil and taco seasoning mix until evenly coated.\n- Spread the fries in a single layer on a baking sheet or air fryer basket.\n- Bake or air fry for 25-30 minutes, turning occasionally, until crispy and golden brown.\n\n## Nacho Cheese Sauce\n- In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the evaporated milk and cheese slices. Stir continuously until the cheese melts and the sauce thickens.\n- Add the grated cheddar and, if desired, the jalapeño juice. Continue stirring until smooth and cheesy.\n- Store any unused sauce in a bottle. Reheat gently before use as it will thicken when cooled.\n\n## Fresh Side Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the chopped tomatoes, red onion, bell peppers, avocados, and coriander.\n- Dress the salad with lime juice, honey, salt, and black pepper. Toss to coat evenly.\n- Store the salad in a separate container. It can be kept fresh for 4-5 days.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Reheat the beef and fries in a pan or re-crisp fries in an air fryer for 4-5 minutes before serving.\n- Arrange the fries on a serving dish, top with the beef mixture, and drizzle with nacho cheese sauce.\n- Serve with the side salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('112','Honey BBQ Chicken with Creamy Macaroni','## Chicken\n- 800g Raw Chicken Breast, cut into cubes\n- 1 Tbsp Minced Garlic (4-5 cloves)\n- 1 Tsp Black Pepper\n- 1.5 Tsp Paprika\n- 1.5 Tsp Onion Powder\n- 1 Tsp Salt\n- 1-2 Tsp Olive Oil\n- 15g Light Butter or Cooking Spray for cooking\n- 25g Honey\n- 90g Sugar-Free BBQ Sauce (G Hughes or reduced sugar variety)\n\n## Macaroni and Cheese Sauce\n- 220g Uncooked Macaroni (540g when cooked)\n- 300ml Fat-Free or Light Evaporated Milk (Carnations)\n- 60g Hot Sauce (like buffalo sauce or any preferred type)\n- 100g Light Cream Cheese, softened to room temperature\n- 50g Grated Light Cheddar Cheese\n- 1 Tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1 Tsp Onion Powder\n- Salt to taste (optional)','## Cooking the Chicken\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat.\n- Add the cubed chicken breast, minced garlic, black pepper, paprika, onion powder, and salt to the pan.\n- Cook each side for 3-4 minutes until the chicken has a golden-brown crust.\n- Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat, then stir in the honey and BBQ sauce until the chicken is evenly coated.\n\n## Preparing the Macaroni and Sauce\n- Cook the macaroni according to package instructions, drain, and set aside.\n- In a separate saucepan, heat evaporated milk over low-medium heat.\n- Add the softened cream cheese and stir until melted and smooth.\n- Mix in the hot sauce, grated cheddar cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt to taste.\n- Continue stirring until the sauce is well combined and has a creamy consistency.\n\n## Combining and Serving\n- Combine the cooked macaroni with the cheese sauce.\n- Serve the macaroni alongside or beneath the honey BBQ chicken.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('113','Sweet Potato and Beef Bowl with Special Sauce and Pickle Salad','## Sweet Potatoes\n- 800g raw sweet potatoes, cut into small cubes\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n\n## Beef\n- 800g 5% fat ground beef\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 30g light butter (for cooking and extra once cooked)\n- 80g light cheddar cheese, grated\n\n## Special Sauce\n- 100g light mayonnaise\n- 80g reduced sugar ketchup\n- 20-30g yellow mustard\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n- 1/2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 15-20ml pickle juice\n\n## Pickle Salad\n- 1 whole iceberg lettuce, thinly sliced\n- 2 medium red onions, chopped\n- 2 large tomatoes, chopped\n- 4-5 medium pickles, chopped','## Sweet Potatoes\n- Toss the sweet potato cubes with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, and olive oil until evenly coated.\n- Spread the cubes on a baking sheet in a single layer.\n- Bake or air fry at 200°C (400°F) for 25-30 minutes, or until golden and crispy.\n\n## Special Sauce\n- Combine mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard, onion powder, black pepper, smoked paprika, and pickle juice in a bowl.\n- Mix thoroughly until smooth.\n- Bottle the sauce and store it in the fridge.\n\n## Pickle Salad\n- Mix chopped red onions, tomatoes, and pickles separately.\n- Keep the sliced lettuce separate from the other vegetables to maintain crispness.\n- Combine just before serving.\n\n## Beef\n- Season the ground beef with salt and pepper.\n- Cook in a pan over medium heat with 30g of light butter until browned and thoroughly cooked.\n- Add grated cheese and let it melt over the beef.\n- Reheat with the sweet potatoes if needed by cooking together in a pan over low heat or air frying for 5 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('114','High Protein Yogurt Parfait','## Main Ingredients\n- 200g fat-free or low-fat yogurt\n- 10-15g honey\n- 80-100g blueberries\n- 20g protein granola\n\n## Toppings\n- 1 tsp chia seeds\n- 1 tbsp goji berries\n- 1 tbsp cacao nibs\n- 1 tsp cocoa powder\n- 1 tsp maca powder','## Preparation Steps\n- In a medium-sized bowl, combine the yogurt and honey. Mix well until smooth.\n- Layer the yogurt mixture in a serving glass or bowl, followed by a layer of blueberries.\n- Sprinkle the protein granola on top of the blueberries.\n- Evenly distribute the chia seeds, goji berries, and cacao nibs over the granola.\n- Finally, dust the top with cocoa powder and maca powder.\n\n## Serving Instructions\n- Serve immediately to enjoy the crunch and freshness.\n- Optionally, chill in the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes if a colder texture is preferred.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('115','Black Pepper Beef with Garlic Fried Rice','## Beef Marinade\n- 800g thinly sliced beef\n- 20ml dark soy sauce\n- 20ml light soy sauce\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 25g cornflour/cornstarch\n- 3 tsp olive oil\n\n## Black Pepper Sauce\n- 200ml beef broth\n- 20ml dark soy sauce\n- 30ml light soy sauce\n- 25g hoisin sauce\n- 20ml rice vinegar\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 10g cornflour/cornstarch\n- 150g sliced white onion\n- 200g sliced bell peppers\n\n## Garlic Fried Rice\n- 20g light butter\n- 50g chopped garlic\n- 540g cooked basmati rice\n- 20ml light soy sauce\n- 1 tsp red pepper flakes (for garnish)','## Beef Preparation\n- Combine beef with dark soy sauce, light soy sauce, black pepper, garlic powder, baking soda, cornflour, and olive oil in a bowl. Mix until the beef is evenly coated.\n- Let the beef marinate for at least 20 minutes to tenderize.\n\n## Cooking the Beef\n- Melt light butter in a pan over high heat. Sear the marinated beef slices for 1-2 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside.\n\n## Black Pepper Sauce\n- In a bowl, whisk together beef broth, dark soy sauce, light soy sauce, hoisin sauce, rice vinegar, black pepper, and cornflour until smooth.\n- In the pan, cook the sliced onions and bell peppers over medium heat until soft.\n- Pour in the sauce, stirring continuously until it thickens.\n- Add the cooked beef back into the pan, ensuring every piece is well coated with the sauce.\n\n## Garlic Fried Rice\n- Melt butter in a pan over medium-low heat. Sauté the chopped garlic until golden and fragrant.\n- Add the leftover basmati rice into the pan, mixing thoroughly with the garlic and butter.\n- Pour in the soy sauce and stir well until heated through.\n\n## Final Steps and Reheating\n- Serve the beef with sauce over the garlic fried rice. Garnish with red pepper flakes if desired.\n- To reheat, microwave the dish for 3-4 minutes or warm it in a pan over low heat until hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('116','Crispy Beef & Veggie Noodles','## Main Ingredients\n- 800g Lean Beef Mince\n- 20g Light Butter for cooking\n- 100g Chopped Green Onion\n- 1 Tbsp Chopped Garlic\n- 1 Tbsp Chopped Ginger\n- 1 Medium Red Onion, Sliced\n- 1 Medium Red Bell Pepper, Sliced\n- 220g Medium Egg Noodles (Raw Weight)\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 50ml Light Soy Sauce\n- 20ml Dark Soy Sauce\n- 30g Honey\n- 35g Sweet Chilli Sauce\n- 25g Rice Vinegar\n- 60g Chilli Garlic Paste\n- 1 Tsp Red Pepper Flakes\n- 1 Tsp Sesame Seeds\n- 20ml Water','## Prepare the Beef\n- In a pan, melt the light butter over medium-high heat.\n- Add the lean beef mince and cook for 6–8 minutes, ensuring most of the liquid evaporates before adding the sauce.\n- Combine the sauce ingredients: light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, honey, sweet chilli sauce, rice vinegar, chilli garlic paste, red pepper flakes, sesame seeds, and water.\n- Pour the sauce over the beef and cook for an additional 5 minutes until the beef is golden brown and crispy.\n- Transfer the crispy beef into a bowl and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Noodles and Vegetables\n- Boil a pot of water and cook the egg noodles for about 5 minutes until al dente. Drain the noodles to halt the cooking process.\n- In the same pan, sauté the chopped green onion, garlic, ginger, red onion, and red bell pepper for about 5 minutes until the vegetables are soft.\n- Add the cooked noodles to the pan with the vegetables and pour in any remaining sauce.\n- Mix everything over low heat until the noodles are fully coated.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Gently fold the crispy beef into the noodle and vegetable mixture.\n- Serve immediately, or refrigerate to enhance the flavor. This dish tastes even better after a day in the fridge.\n- Reheat in a microwave or a pan with a splash of water to maintain moisture.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('117','Creamy Basil Chicken with Spinach and Tomatoes','## Main Ingredients\n- 700g chicken breast, cubed\n- 4 garlic cloves, minced or 1 tbsp garlic powder\n- 2 tsp dried basil\n- 1 tsp chilli flakes\n- 2 tsp salt\n- 2 tsp smoked paprika\n- 3 tsp olive oil\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes\n- 1 cup spinach\n\n## Creamy Sauce\n- 350ml low-fat milk\n- 150g light cream cheese\n- 40g grated Parmesan\n- 60-70g tomato paste\n- 1 tsp dried basil\n- Salt to taste (optional)','## Preparation\n- Season the cubed chicken breast with garlic, dried basil, chilli flakes, salt, and smoked paprika.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the seasoned chicken cubes and cook for about 4 minutes, until slightly browned.\n\n## Creamy Sauce\n- Reduce the heat to low to prevent the sauce from splitting.\n- Add the low-fat milk, light cream cheese, grated Parmesan, tomato paste, and basil to the skillet.\n- Stir well to combine all the sauce ingredients.\n\n## Simmer and Finish\n- Cover and allow the mixture to simmer for 5 to 7 minutes.\n- Add the cherry tomatoes and spinach during the last 2 minutes of cooking.\n- Simmer until the sauce thickens, the spinach wilts, and the tomatoes soften.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve with 140g of cooked basmati rice per serving, seasoned with mixed herbs and salt.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('118','Peri Peri Chicken with Spicy Rice and Perinaise Sauce','## Peri Peri Seasoning Mix\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili powder\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp oregano\n\n## Peri Peri Chicken\n- 800g boneless skinless chicken thighs\n- 1.5x Peri Peri Seasoning Mix\n- 100g Nando’s marinade\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon\n- 20g light butter for cooking\n\n## Perinaise Sauce\n- 100g light mayonnaise\n- 80g Nando’s hot sauce\n- 1/2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1/2 tsp smoked paprika\n\n## Spicy Rice\n- 1 tbsp chopped garlic\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili powder\n- 1 tsp turmeric\n- 50g tomato paste\n- 560g cooked basmati rice\n- Fresh parsley, chopped','## Peri Peri Chicken\n- Marinate the chicken thighs by combining them with 1.5 times the Peri Peri Seasoning Mix, Nando’s marinade, and lemon juice. Mix well, cover, and refrigerate overnight for maximum flavor infusion.\n- Melt the light butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Sear the marinated chicken thighs, cooking them for about 5 minutes on each side until they achieve a golden-brown color.\n\n## Spicy Rice\n- In the same skillet used for the chicken, sauté the chopped onion and red bell pepper for about 5 minutes until they start to soften.\n- Add the garlic and cook for another minute.\n- Stir in the seasonings and tomato paste, and continue cooking for 2 more minutes to blend the flavors.\n- Gently fold in the cooked basmati rice and fresh parsley, stirring until the rice is evenly coated and takes on a bright orange hue.\n\n## Perinaise Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine the light mayonnaise, Nando’s hot sauce, garlic powder, and smoked paprika. Mix thoroughly.\n- Transfer the sauce to a bottle or airtight container and refrigerate until ready to serve.\n\n## Serving and Reheating\n- Serve the chicken with a side of spicy rice and a drizzle of Perinaise sauce.\n- For reheating, place the dish in a microwave or warm in a pan for about 5 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('119','Spicy Beef and Kimchi Fried Rice','## Beef Marinade\n- 900g lean beef, cut into thin strips\n- 30ml soy sauce\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- 1.5 tsp chili flakes\n- 1.5 tsp chili powder\n- 1 tbsp minced garlic\n- 1 tbsp ginger paste\n- 1 tbsp sesame seeds\n- 2 tsp olive oil\n- 20g light butter for cooking\n\n## Kimchi Fried Rice\n- 1 tbsp chopped garlic\n- 20g gochujang paste\n- 50-80g chopped green onion\n- 50-80g grated carrots\n- 560g cooked jasmine rice\n- 100g chopped kimchi with its juice\n- Extra chopped green onion\n- 10-15ml soy sauce\n- Sesame seeds for garnish','## Marinate the Beef\n- Combine all marinade ingredients in a large bowl. Add beef strips, ensuring they are well coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or overnight for optimal flavor.\n\n## Cook the Beef\n- Heat a pan over high heat and melt the light butter. Cook the marinated beef strips for 2-3 minutes on each side until a crust forms.\n\n## Prepare the Kimchi Fried Rice\n- In the same pan, add chopped garlic, gochujang paste, green onion, and carrots. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.\n- Stir in the cooked jasmine rice and chopped kimchi with its juice, mixing well.\n- Add soy sauce and extra chopped green onions, continuing to stir until everything is well combined and heated through.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds before serving.\n\n## Storage\n- Divide the dish into portions and store in the refrigerator or freezer. Reheat in the microwave or on a pan for a few minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('120','Chicken Gyros with Seasoned Fries and Tzatziki','## Gyros Seasoning\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Black Pepper\n- 1 tsp Oregano\n- 1 tsp Cumin\n- 1 tsp Coriander Powder\n- 1 tsp Paprika\n\n## Chicken Marinade\n- 400g Chicken Breast\n- 400g Skinless Chicken Thighs\n- 4-5 Garlic Cloves, minced\n- 1.5 tbsp Gyros Seasoning\n- 2 tsp Olive Oil\n- 100g Yogurt\n- Juice and zest of 1 whole lemon\n\n## Seasoned Fries\n- 700g Raw Potatoes, cut into fries\n- Salt, Pepper, Garlic Powder, Paprika (to taste)\n- 2 tbsp Olive Oil\n\n## Garlic Naan (Makes 4)\n- 180g Plain Flour\n- 200g Yogurt\n- 1 tsp Salt\n- 1 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1 tsp Baking Powder\n\n## Tzatziki Sauce\n- 200g Plain Yogurt\n- 1/2 Grated Cucumber\n- Salt to taste\n- Juice of 1/2 Lemon','## Prepare the Gyros Seasoning\n- In a small bowl, mix salt, black pepper, oregano, cumin, coriander powder, and paprika.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken\n- Slice chicken breast and thighs into strips.\n- In a large bowl, combine minced garlic, 1.5 tbsp of the gyros seasoning, olive oil, yogurt, lemon juice, and zest.\n- Add chicken strips to the marinade and mix well to coat.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.\n\n## Prepare the Seasoned Fries\n- Preheat oven to 220°C (430°F).\n- Toss the potato fries with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika until evenly coated.\n- Spread on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake for 25-30 minutes or until golden and crispy, flipping halfway through.\n\n## Prepare the Garlic Naan\n- In a bowl, mix flour, yogurt, salt, garlic powder, and baking powder until a dough forms.\n- Divide into 4 equal parts and roll out each to a flatbread shape.\n- In a skillet over medium heat, cook each naan for 2-3 minutes on each side until golden and puffed.\n- Keep warm by wrapping in a clean towel.\n\n## Make the Tzatziki Sauce\n- In a bowl, mix plain yogurt, grated cucumber, salt, and lemon juice until combined.\n- Refrigerate until ready to use.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook marinated chicken strips for 5-7 minutes, turning occasionally, until cooked through and slightly charred.\n\n## Assemble the Gyros\n- On each naan, spread a layer of tzatziki sauce.\n- Add cooked chicken strips and top with seasoned fries.\n- Serve immediately with additional tzatziki for dipping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('121','Glazed Chicken with Pickled Cucumbers','## Main Ingredients\n- 700-800g cubed chicken breast\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 1.5 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp paprika\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 30g cornflour\n\n## Glaze\n- 50ml light soy sauce\n- 50ml water\n- 25g honey\n- 40g gochujang paste\n\n## Pickled Cucumbers\n- Thinly sliced cucumber\n- 20ml light soy sauce\n- 10ml rice vinegar\n- Chili flakes\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp sesame seeds','## Chicken Preparation\n- Coat the cubed chicken breast evenly with cornflour, ensuring each piece is well covered. If cornflour is unavailable, you may proceed without it.\n- Season with garlic powder, black pepper, paprika, and salt, mixing thoroughly to coat the chicken.\n\n## Glaze\n- In a saucepan, combine light soy sauce, water, honey, and gochujang paste over low heat.\n- Stir continuously until the mixture lightly bubbles, then let it simmer for 3-4 minutes until it thickens.\n\n## Pickled Cucumbers\n- In a bowl, combine thinly sliced cucumber with light soy sauce, rice vinegar, chili flakes, garlic powder, and sesame seeds.\n- Mix well and set aside. These are best served cold, so store them separately.\n\n## Cooking and Serving\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and cook the chicken until it''s golden brown and cooked through.\n- Pour the glaze over the chicken, stirring to coat each piece evenly.\n- Serve the glazed chicken with the pickled cucumbers on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('122','Tender Beef Stir-Fry with Egg Noodles','## Beef Marinade\n- 700-800g lean beef steak, cut into thin strips\n- 20-30ml light soy sauce\n- 2 tsp garlic powder\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- 1/2 tsp baking soda\n\n## Stir-Fry\n- 2-3 tsp olive oil or cooking spray\n- 220g uncooked egg noodles\n- 1/2 red onion, sliced\n- 4-5 garlic cloves, chopped\n- Green onion/scallion, white and green parts separated\n- 20g cornflour/cornstarch (optional, for added crispiness)\n\n## Sauce\n- 20ml dark soy sauce\n- 20ml light soy sauce\n- 50g oyster sauce\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 5-10g cornflour/cornstarch mixed with 15ml water\n\n## Garnish\n- Chili flakes\n- Sesame seeds','## Marinate the Beef\n- Combine the beef strips with light soy sauce, garlic powder, black pepper, and baking soda in a bowl.\n- Let the beef marinate for 30 minutes to enhance tenderness.\n\n## Prepare the Noodles\n- Cook the egg noodles according to package instructions, usually 5-6 minutes in boiling water over low heat.\n- Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Beef\n- Heat olive oil or use cooking spray in a pan over medium-high heat.\n- Add the marinated beef and cook for 2-3 minutes. Avoid overcooking.\n- Remove the beef and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same pan, combine dark soy sauce, light soy sauce, oyster sauce, and water.\n- Bring the mixture to a simmer.\n- Stir in the cornflour/cornstarch slurry, cooking until the sauce thickens, about 2-3 minutes.\n\n## Combine and Finish\n- Reintroduce the beef to the pan with the sauce, mixing well.\n- Add the sliced red onion, chopped garlic, and the white parts of the green onion.\n- Toss in the prepared egg noodles and stir-fry briefly until everything is well coated and heated through.\n- Garnish with green onion tops, chili flakes, and sesame seeds before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('123','Creamy Garlic Shrimp Pasta','## Marinade\n- 800g Raw Argentinian Shrimp (frozen)\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced (or garlic powder)\n- 2 tsp Italian herbs\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1.5 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 3/4 lemon juice\n- 2-3 tsp olive oil (optional)\n\n## Sauce and Additional Ingredients\n- 40g light butter\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- 250ml milk\n- 120g light cream cheese\n- 40g parmesan, grated\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 25ml pasta water\n- 500g cooked linguine pasta\n- Handful of spinach','## Shrimp Preparation\n- In a bowl, combine shrimp, garlic, Italian herbs, chili flakes, smoked paprika, salt, lemon juice, and olive oil if using. Mix well and let marinate for 15-20 minutes.\n\n## Cooking Shrimp\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium-high heat. Add marinated shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until pink and opaque. Remove shrimp and set aside.\n\n## Making the Sauce\n- Reduce heat to low. Add butter to the pan, along with parsley and lemon juice.\n- Pour in milk and add cream cheese, stirring slowly until the sauce thickens.\n- Stir in the grated parmesan, ensuring it incorporates smoothly into the sauce.\n\n## Combining Ingredients\n- Add the cooked pasta to the sauce, gently tossing to coat.\n- If sauce is too thick, add some reserved pasta water to reach the desired consistency.\n- Return the cooked shrimp to the pan, along with a handful of spinach. Toss until combined.\n\n## Final Seasoning\n- Adjust seasoning with additional garlic, paprika, chili flakes, salt, and herbs if needed.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with more parsley and a squeeze of lemon juice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('124','Creamy Fajita Steak Pasta','## Steak Marinade\n- 700g topside beef, cut into steaks\n- Garlic powder\n- Chili powder\n- Salt\n- Pepper\n- Olive oil\n- 20g light butter for cooking\n\n## Creamy Fajita Sauce\n- 300ml low-fat milk\n- 150g light cream cheese\n- 40g Parmesan cheese\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp oregano\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 tsp chili flakes\n- 1/3 cup pasta water\n\n## For Cooking\n- 243g uncooked penne pasta (approximately 540g when cooked)\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 white onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, thinly sliced\n- 1 green bell pepper, thinly sliced\n- Fresh parsley for garnish\n- Additional seasoning to taste','## Preparation\n- Marinate the steaks with garlic powder, chilli powder, salt, pepper, and a drizzle of olive oil. Let them sit for as long as possible to enhance tenderness and flavour.\n\n## Cooking the Steak\n- Heat a pan over medium-high heat and add light butter. Cook the steaks to your desired doneness, considering thickness. Once done, set aside to rest.\n\n## Cooking the Pasta\n- Cook penne pasta according to package instructions. Drain and reserve 1/3 cup of the pasta water.\n\n## Preparing the Sauce\n- In the same pan, add onions and bell peppers. Cook until softened.\n- Then, reduce the heat and add low-fat milk, cream cheese, Parmesan, garlic powder, oregano, salt, and chilli flakes.\n- Stir continuously until the cheese is fully melted and everything is combined.\n\n## Combining and Serving\n- Add the pasta and reserved pasta water to the sauce mixture.\n- Let it simmer for a few minutes, allowing the sauce to thicken.\n- Thinly slice the rested steaks.\n- Serve the steak slices over the creamy pasta, garnished with fresh parsley. Adjust seasoning if necessary.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('125','Salmon with Coconut Noodle Bowl','## Salmon\n- 4 skinless salmon fillets (180-190g each)\n- Garlic powder\n- Smoked paprika\n- Salt\n- Pepper\n- 2 tsp olive oil or cooking spray\n\n## Noodles and Sauce\n- 2 garlic cloves, chopped\n- 20g chili paste (e.g., Lee Kum Kee)\n- 500ml light coconut milk (e.g., Sainsbury''s)\n- 1 tsp salt\n- Pepper\n- Paprika or ramen packet seasoning\n- 3.5 nests (220g) uncooked medium egg noodles (e.g., Sainsbury''s)\n- Green onions, chopped\n- 20ml soy sauce','## Cook the Salmon\n- Season the salmon fillets with garlic powder, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a non-stick pan over medium-low heat.\n- Cook the salmon for 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown and cooked through.\n\n## Prepare the Noodles and Sauce\n- Cook the egg noodles according to the package instructions (usually simmer for 5 minutes) and drain.\n- In a large pan, heat a little olive oil and sauté the chopped garlic for about 1 minute.\n- Add the chili paste and light coconut milk to the pan; stir to combine.\n- Bring the mixture to a gentle bubble.\n- Add the cooked noodles to the sauce and stir well, allowing the sauce to thicken slightly by simmering for a few minutes.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add soy sauce and adjust seasoning with salt, pepper, and paprika or ramen seasoning according to taste.\n- Place the salmon fillets on top of the noodles.\n- Garnish with chopped green onions.\n- Serve immediately. For meal prep, store the salmon and noodles separately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('126','High Protein Turkey Egg Wraps with Creamy Chipotle Sauce','## Main Filling\n- 2 lbs lean ground turkey (93/7 or leaner)\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 small yellow onion, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 green bell pepper, diced\n- 1 tbsp tomato paste\n- 1 tbsp adobo (chipotle) sauce\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- 2 tsp chili powder\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Egg Mixture\n- 10 large eggs\n- 1 cup liquid egg whites\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: pinch of turmeric for color\n\n## Extras\n- 3/4 cup reduced-fat Mexican blend cheese\n- 8 Ole Xtreme Wellness 10” wraps (or similar high-protein wraps)\n\n## Creamy Chipotle Greek Yogurt Sauce\n- 1/2 cup nonfat Greek yogurt\n- 1 tbsp light mayo (optional, for richness)\n- 1 chipotle pepper in adobo sauce\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- Salt and garlic powder to taste','## Main Filling Preparation\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and cook for 2-3 minutes until translucent.\n- Add the red and green bell peppers and cook for another 3-4 minutes until they begin to soften.\n- Add the lean ground turkey to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spatula. Cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the tomato paste, adobo sauce, and lime juice.\n- Add the chili powder, smoked paprika, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix thoroughly and cook for another 2 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Egg Mixture Preparation\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, liquid egg whites, salt, pepper, and turmeric, if using.\n- Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat and pour in the egg mixture.\n- Gently stir with a spatula as the eggs cook, forming soft curds. Cook until just set, about 3-5 minutes.\n- Remove from heat.\n\n## Wrap Assembly\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lay each wrap on a clean surface.\n- Divide the turkey mixture evenly among the wraps.\n- Top with scrambled eggs, followed by a sprinkle of cheese.\n- Roll each wrap tightly, folding in the sides as you roll.\n- Place the wraps seam side down on a baking sheet.\n- Bake in preheated oven for about 10 minutes, until heated through and cheese is melted.\n\n## Creamy Chipotle Greek Yogurt Sauce\n- In a blender or food processor, combine the Greek yogurt, light mayo, chipotle pepper, lime juice, salt, and garlic powder.\n- Blend until smooth. Adjust seasoning to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the wraps warm with the creamy chipotle Greek yogurt sauce on the side for dipping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('127','Spicy Chicken and Protein Mac & Cheese','## For the Chicken\n- 24 oz Chicken Breast (680g), cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 1 Cup All Purpose Flour (120g)\n- 2 Tbsps Garlic Salt (30g)\n- 1 Tbsp Smoked Paprika (8g)\n- 1 Tbsp Onion Powder (8g)\n- 1 Cup Egg Whites (240g) or 3 Beaten Eggs\n- 4 Tbsps Pickle Juice (60g)\n- 2 Tbsps Hot Sauce (30g)\n- 1 Cup Corn Flakes (40g), crushed\n\n## For the Mac & Cheese\n- 8 oz Dry Protein Pasta (225g)\n- 1 1/2 Cups Cottage Cheese (335g), 0% Fat\n- 1/2 Cup Fat Free Cheddar Cheese (56g), grated\n- 1 Mac & Cheese Powder Packet (30g)\n- 1/2 Cup Fat Free Milk (120g)\n\n## For the Buffalo Sauce Glaze\n- 6 Tbsps Buffalo Sauce (90g)\n- 2 Tbsps Honey (40g)\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh Chives (20g), chopped','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- In a bowl, mix flour, garlic salt, smoked paprika, and onion powder.\n- In another bowl, whisk together egg whites, pickle juice, and hot sauce.\n- Place crushed corn flakes on a plate for coating.\n- Dip each chicken piece into the flour mixture, then into the egg mixture, and finally coat with corn flakes.\n- Place the coated chicken pieces on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden and cooked through.\n\n## Make the Mac & Cheese\n- Cook the protein pasta according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n- In a saucepan, combine cottage cheese, cheddar cheese, mac & cheese powder, and milk.\n- Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, until smooth and creamy.\n- Add the cooked pasta to the cheese sauce and stir until well combined.\n\n## Prepare the Buffalo Sauce Glaze\n- In a small saucepan, combine buffalo sauce and honey.\n- Heat over low heat, stirring until well combined.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Drizzle the buffalo sauce glaze over the baked chicken pieces.\n- Serve the buffalo chicken with a side of the protein mac & cheese.\n- Garnish with fresh chopped chives before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('128','Lemon Garlic Chicken Thighs','## Marinate the Chicken\n- 3 boneless chicken thighs with skin\n- Salt and pepper\n- Cornstarch\n\n## Lemon Garlic Sauce\n- 2 tbsp of butter\n- 6 cloves of minced garlic\n- 1 shallot, diced\n- ½ cup of chicken broth\n- ½ cup of heavy cream\n- 2 tbsp of lemon juice\n- 1 cup of grated Parmesan cheese\n\n## Seasoning\n- 1 tsp of garlic powder\n- 1 tsp of paprika\n- 1 tsp of Italian seasoning\n- 1 tsp of red pepper flakes\n\n## Garnish\n- Chopped chives\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper.\n- Lightly coat the chicken with cornstarch, shaking off any excess.\n- Set the coated chicken aside.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium-high heat.\n- Place the chicken skin side down in the pan and cook each side for about 7 minutes until it turns golden brown.\n- Once cooked, remove the chicken and set it aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, reduce the heat to medium and melt the butter.\n- Add the minced garlic and diced shallots, stirring for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Mix in the garlic powder, Italian seasoning, chili flakes, and paprika; sauté for another 30 seconds.\n- Pour in the chicken broth and heavy cream, cooking until the sauce thickens.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Turn off the heat and stir in the lemon juice and Parmesan cheese, mixing until the cheese is fully melted.\n- Return the chicken to the pan and generously coat it with the sauce.\n- Serve with hot steamed rice, garnished with chopped chives and extra Parmesan cheese. Enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('129','Shrimp Pad Thai','## Main Ingredients\n- 120g dried Pad Thai rice stick noodles\n- 100g shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 1 shallot, thinly sliced\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 100g fried tofu, diced\n- 1 cup mung bean sprouts\n- 2 stalks scallions, chopped\n- 3 tbsp cooking oil\n- 2 eggs\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 2 tbsp tamarind paste\n- 2 tbsp palm sugar\n- 2 tbsp fish sauce\n- 1.5 tbsp oyster sauce\n- 1 tbsp dark soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup water\n\n## For Garnish\n- Fresh bean sprouts\n- Lime wedge\n- Crushed peanuts\n- Chili powder','## Prepare the Noodles\n- Soak 120g of dried Pad Thai rice stick noodles in boiling water for 5 minutes. Do not exceed 6-8 minutes to avoid mushiness.\n- Rinse noodles under cold water to halt cooking and set them aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup water, 2 tbsp tamarind paste, 2 tbsp palm sugar, 2 tbsp fish sauce, 1.5 tbsp oyster sauce, and 1 tbsp dark soy sauce. Stir well and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Shrimp\n- Heat 1 tbsp of cooking oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Cook the shrimp until pink and opaque for a few minutes. Remove and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Base\n- Add 2 tbsp of oil to the same pan over high heat. Sauté shallots, garlic, and diced tofu for about a minute until fragrant and golden.\n- Crack 2 eggs into the pan, scramble, and mix thoroughly.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- Add the soaked noodles to the pan along with the sautéed ingredients. Pour the prepared Pad Thai sauce and toss until noodles are well-coated and glossy.\n- Add cooked shrimp, scallions, mung bean sprouts, and crushed peanuts. Stir everything together for another 1-2 minutes to ensure even mixing.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Plate the Pad Thai and garnish with fresh bean sprouts, lime wedges, more crushed peanuts, and chili powder to taste.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if needed. Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('130','Tuna Melt Sandwich','## For the Tuna Mixture\n- 80g / 1/3 cup full-fat Mayo\n- 2 tsp Lemon Juice\n- 1 tsp Dijon Mustard\n- 1/8 – 1/4 tsp Salt & Black Pepper\n- 2 tbsp finely diced Gherkins/Pickles\n- 1 heaped tbsp very finely diced Fresh Parsley\n- 2 Spring Onions, finely diced\n- 2x 150g/5oz cans of Tuna Chunks (drained)\n\n## For the Sandwiches\n- 6 medium-large slices of Bread (such as Sourdough)\n- 120g / 4oz Cheddar, grated\n- 120g / 4oz Red Leicester, grated (or more Cheddar as a substitute)\n- Butter, for spreading\n- Hot Sauce, to serve (optional)','## Prepare Tuna Mixture\n- In a small bowl, mix together the mayo, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, parsley, pickles, spring onions, salt, and pepper.\n- Thoroughly drain the tuna and add it to the mixture. Stir until well combined. Adjust seasoning according to taste.\n\n## Assemble Sandwiches\n- Spread butter on one side of each slice of bread and place butter-side down.\n- Layer with grated cheddar, followed by the tuna mixture, then top with grated Red Leicester.\n- Place a second slice of bread on top, buttered side facing up.\n\n## Cook the Sandwiches\n- Heat a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the sandwiches (2-3 at a time) and cook until the bread is golden brown and crisp, and the cheese has melted, flipping once. Reduce the heat if the bread browns too quickly.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut the sandwiches in half and serve with hot sauce, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('131','Koobideh Kebabs with Herbed Yogurt Sauce','## Kebab Ingredients\n- 3 lbs 80/20 Ground Beef\n- 2 Yellow Onions\n- Pinch of Saffron (Optional)\n- 3 Tbsp Turmeric\n- 4 Tbsp Paprika\n- 3 Tbsp Sumac\n- 2 Tbsp Salt\n- 2 Tbsp Pepper\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 1/2 Cup Yogurt\n- Juice of 1 Lemon\n- 1 Bunch Fresh Mint\n- 1 Bunch Fresh Parsley\n- 2 Cloves Garlic\n- 1 Jalapeño, seeded','## Kebab Preparation\n- Grate the onions and use a paper towel to thoroughly remove excess moisture.\n- In a large bowl, combine the onions with ground beef, saffron, turmeric, paprika, sumac, salt, and pepper. Knead the mixture until all ingredients are well incorporated.\n- Take a portion of the mixture, about the size of a tennis ball. Dip your hands in warm water and shape the meat evenly around a skewer.\n- Using your index and middle fingers, create indentations along the length of each kebab.\n- Place the skewers on a rack and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to let them firm up.\n- Preheat your grill or heat source. Cook the kebabs, turning them every minute, until they are fully cooked through.\n\n## Sauce Preparation\n- Place all the sauce ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth.\n- If the sauce is too thick, slowly add olive oil until you reach the desired consistency.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('132','Stir-Fried Noodles with Pork Belly and Shrimp','## Main Ingredients\n- 10 oz cabbage, chopped\n- 10 oz gai lan (Chinese broccoli), chopped\n- 1 onion, sliced\n- 2/3 lb pork belly, sliced\n- 10 shrimp, deveined and cleaned\n- 1 pack 12 oz egg noodles\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 2 Tbsp dark soy sauce\n- 1 Tbsp soy sauce\n- 1/2 Tbsp oyster sauce\n- 1 tsp MSG (optional)\n- 1 Tbsp honey or sugar\n- 1/2 Tbsp corn starch\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 1/2 Tbsp sesame seeds\n- 1 tsp red chili flakes\n- 1 tsp black pepper','## Preparation\n- Wash and prepare your vegetables: chop the cabbage and gai lan, and slice the onion.\n- Gently separate the noodles to prevent sticking and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- Combine dark soy sauce, regular soy sauce, oyster sauce, optional MSG, honey (or sugar), corn starch, water, sesame seeds, red chili flakes, and black pepper in a bowl. Whisk until smooth.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and sauté the sliced onion until it becomes translucent.\n- Add the pork belly and cook until it is browned, crispy, and the fat is rendered.\n- Introduce the shrimp to the pan and cook until nearly done, about 80%.\n- Mix in the noodles and pour the sauce over the top. Gently toss everything together, cooking until the sauce thickens and coats the noodles.\n\n## Final Touches\n- Taste and adjust the seasoning if necessary. Serve hot and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('133','Korean BBQ Meatballs with Spicy Sesame Mayo','## Meatballs\n- 1 lb ground beef\n- ½ cup panko breadcrumbs\n- 1 large egg\n- 5 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp minced ginger\n- 2 tbsp gochujang\n- 2 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tsp sesame oil\n- 2 tbsp brown sugar\n- 3 green onions, thinly sliced\n\n## BBQ Sauce\n- ¼ cup soy sauce\n- 1 tbsp honey\n- 1 tbsp brown sugar\n- 1 tbsp gochujang\n- 1 tbsp rice vinegar\n- 1 tsp sesame oil\n- 1 tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 tbsp water (slurry)\n\n## Spicy Sesame Mayo\n- ½ cup mayonnaise\n- 1 tsp gochujang\n- 1 tsp sesame oil\n- Juice of ½ lime','## Preparation\n- Begin by preparing your ingredients: mince the garlic and ginger, and slice the green onions thinly.\n\n## Meatballs\n- In a bowl, combine the ground beef, panko, egg, minced garlic, ginger, gochujang, soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, and two-thirds of the green onions. Mix gently until combined; avoid over-mixing to keep meatballs tender.\n- Shape the mixture into meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.\n\n## Cooking the Meatballs\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and cook the meatballs, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides and cooked through, about 12-15 minutes. Remove them from the pan and set aside.\n\n## BBQ Sauce\n- In the same pan, combine the soy sauce, honey, brown sugar, gochujang, rice vinegar, and sesame oil. Stir and bring to a gentle simmer.\n- Add the cornstarch slurry to the sauce, stirring continuously until the sauce thickens.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Turn off the heat and return the meatballs to the pan, coating them thoroughly in the sauce.\n\n## Spicy Sesame Mayo\n- In a small bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, gochujang, sesame oil, and lime juice until smooth.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the meatballs with your preferred side, topped with the remaining green onions, sesame seeds, and the spicy sesame mayo on the side. Enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('134','Air Fryer Korean-Style Chicken Skewers with Garlic Lime Aioli','## Chicken\n- 1.5 lbs (680 g) chicken thighs, boneless & skinless\n- 1 tbsp fresh ginger, finely grated\n- 5 garlic cloves, minced\n- 2 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tsp sesame oil\n- 1 tbsp rice vinegar\n- 2 tbsp gochujang\n- 1 tbsp mayonnaise\n- 1 tbsp honey (+ extra for drizzling)\n- 2 tsp chili powder\n- 2 tsp paprika\n- 2 tsp black pepper\n- Green onions, chopped for garnish\n- Fresh lime, for garnish\n\n## Garlic Lime Aioli\n- Juice of 1/2 lime\n- 5 tbsp mayonnaise\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 tsp each: salt & black pepper\n- 1 tbsp gochujang\n\n## Additional Items\n- Wooden skewers, soaked in water for 30 minutes','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Dice the chicken thighs into 1-inch pieces.\n- In a large bowl, combine the ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sesame oil, rice vinegar, gochujang, mayonnaise, honey, chili powder, paprika, and black pepper.\n- Add the chicken pieces to the marinade, ensuring they are thoroughly coated. Let it sit for at least 30 minutes to marinate.\n\n## Prepare the Skewers\n- Thread the marinated chicken pieces onto the soaked wooden skewers.\n- Preheat your air fryer to 400°F (200°C).\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Place the skewers in the air fryer basket in a single layer.\n- Cook for 15-20 minutes, flipping halfway through, until chicken is cooked through and golden brown.\n\n## Make the Garlic Lime Aioli\n- In a small bowl, mix the lime juice, mayonnaise, minced garlic, salt, black pepper, and gochujang until smooth.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove the skewers from the air fryer, and drizzle with extra honey if desired.\n- Sprinkle chopped green onions over the skewers and serve with lime wedges.\n- Serve with garlic lime aioli on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('135','Air Fryer Shrimp Tacos with Bang Bang Sauce','## For the Shrimp\n- 1.25 lbs raw shrimp, peeled and deveined (41/50 count size)\n- 1 large egg\n- 1/2 cup (60g) panko breadcrumbs\n- 1/4 cup (30g) oat flour or any light flour for coating\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Spray oil for air fryer\n\n## For the Tacos\n- 8 low-calorie tortillas (e.g., Mission Carb Balance or Ole Extreme Wellness)\n- 1 cup slaw salad mix (for crunch and color)\n- Fresh cilantro or green onion, chopped, for garnish\n- Optional: squeeze of lime\n\n## For the Bang Bang Sauce (High-Protein Version)\n- 1/2 cup (113g) non-fat Greek yogurt\n- 2 tbsp (30g) light mayonnaise\n- 2 tbsp (32g) Thai sweet chili sauce\n- 1 tsp Sriracha (adjust to spice preference)\n- 1 tbsp honey','## Preparing the Shrimp\n- Preheat the air fryer to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a bowl, beat the egg and set aside.\n- In another bowl, mix panko breadcrumbs, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Lightly coat the shrimp in oat flour. Shake to remove any excess flour.\n- Dip each shrimp in the beaten egg, then coat with the breadcrumb mixture. Press lightly to adhere.\n- Place the shrimp in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Spray lightly with oil.\n- Air fry for 7-9 minutes, or until golden and cooked through, shaking halfway for even cooking.\n\n## Making the Bang Bang Sauce\n- In a small bowl, combine Greek yogurt, light mayonnaise, Thai sweet chili sauce, Sriracha, and honey.\n- Mix well until smooth and set aside.\n\n## Assembling the Tacos\n- Warm the tortillas in a skillet over medium heat for 30 seconds on each side or until soft.\n- Fill each tortilla with a portion of slaw salad.\n- Add 3-4 shrimp to each taco.\n- Drizzle generously with the Bang Bang Sauce.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro or green onion and a squeeze of lime if desired.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('136','Mint Chocolate Protein Cheesecake','## Base Ingredients\n- 3/4 cup vanilla Greek yogurt (170g)\n- 1/4 cup whipped cream cheese (40g)\n- 1 scoop vanilla whey protein (30g)\n- 1 tbsp zero calorie powdered sweetener\n- 1 tbsp sugar-free cheesecake pudding mix (8g)\n- 1/4 tsp peppermint extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- Few drops of natural green food coloring\n\n## Topping Ingredients\n- 2 crushed thin mint cookies (15g)\n- 2 tsp mini chocolate chips (10g)','## Prepare the Mixture\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the vanilla Greek yogurt, whipped cream cheese, and vanilla whey protein. Blend until smooth.\n- Add the zero calorie powdered sweetener, sugar-free cheesecake pudding mix, peppermint extract, pinch of salt, and green food coloring to the mixture. Stir until fully incorporated.\n\n## Chill the Mixture\n- Transfer the mixture into serving glasses or bowls.\n- Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to let the flavors meld and the mixture firm up.\n\n## Adding the Toppings\n- Before serving, evenly distribute the crushed thin mint cookies over the chilled mixture.\n- Sprinkle the mini chocolate chips on top for added texture and flavor.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve cold from the refrigerator. Enjoy your refreshing, protein-packed mint chocolate cheesecake!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('137','Korean-Style Ramen Carbonara','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 packs of Shin Ramyun\n- 1 pack of ramen seasoning\n- 4 cloves of garlic, minced\n- 4 strips of bacon, thinly sliced\n\n## Carbonara Sauce\n- 1 whole egg\n- 2 egg yolks\n- 60g of parmesan cheese, finely grated\n- 1.5 tbsp of Gochujang (Korean Chili Paste)\n- ½ tsp of black pepper\n\n## Garnish\n- Chives, chopped\n- Egg yolk (optional)\n- Sesame seeds','## Preparation\n- Finely grate the parmesan cheese and thinly slice the bacon. Set these aside.\n- In a bowl, mix together the whole egg, egg yolks, grated parmesan, Gochujang, and black pepper until a smooth paste forms.\n\n## Cooking\n- Prepare the ramen according to the package instructions, slightly undercooking by 1 minute. Drain, reserving about 1 cup of the cooking liquid.\n- In a large pan over medium-high heat, cook the bacon for about 5 minutes, or until it is crispy on the outside and still a bit chewy inside.\n- Add the minced garlic to the bacon and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add the cooked ramen to the pan along with the carbonara paste and ramen seasoning. Turn off the heat.\n- Mix everything thoroughly, adding reserved ramen water one tablespoon at a time until the sauce reaches a creamy, silky consistency.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the ramen to serving plates.\n- Top with additional parmesan cheese, chopped chives, and a sprinkle of sesame seeds.\n- Optionally, add an egg yolk on top for richness.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('138','High-Protein Beef and Spanish Rice Wraps','## Spanish Rice\n- 1.5 Cups Dry White Rice (270g)\n- 1 Cup Tomato Sauce (240g)\n- 1.5 Cups Chicken Bone Broth or Water (360g)\n- 1 Tbsp Garlic Salt (15g)\n- 0.5 Tbsp Cumin (3g)\n- 0.5 Tbsp Chili Powder (3g)\n- 0.5 Tbsp Oregano (3g)\n\n## Beef Filling\n- 60oz Lean Ground Beef (96/4) (1700g)\n- 1 White Onion, chopped (200g)\n- 2 Taco Seasoning Packets (2oz) (57g)\n- 0.5 Cup Red Enchilada Sauce (120g)\n- 2 Tbsps Minced Garlic (20g)\n\n## Cheese and Wraps\n- 4.5 Cups Fat Free Cheddar Cheese (500g)\n- 1.25 Cups Nacho Cheese Sauce (250g)\n- 10 Low Calorie Tortillas','## Cooking Spanish Rice\n- In a large pot, combine the rice, tomato sauce, garlic salt, cumin, chili powder, oregano, and chicken bone broth.\n- Stir well, cover with a lid, and bring to a light simmer over medium heat.\n- Cook for around 20 minutes, until the rice is tender and has absorbed most of the liquid. Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Preparing Beef Filling\n- In a large pan over medium-high heat, brown the ground beef until no longer pink, breaking it apart with a spoon as it cooks.\n- Add the chopped onion and minced garlic, cooking until the onion becomes translucent.\n- Mix in the taco seasoning and red enchilada sauce, stirring continuously until well combined.\n- Allow the mixture to simmer for 5-7 minutes, then remove from heat.\n\n## Assembling Wraps\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lay out the tortillas on a clean surface.\n- Evenly distribute the Spanish rice and beef mixture onto each tortilla.\n- Sprinkle the fat-free cheddar cheese over the filling.\n- Roll each tortilla tightly and place them in a baking dish.\n- Pour nacho cheese sauce evenly over the wraps.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10-15 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.\n- Serve hot and enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('139','High Protein Blueberry Cheesecake','## Cheesecake Filling\n- 150g light cream cheese\n- 400g low fat Greek yoghurt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 15g stevia\n- 40g protein powder\n- 200g frozen blueberries\n- 10g cornflour mixed with water\n\n## Base and Topping\n- 1 crushed biscuit/Graham cracker\n- 20g melted white chocolate','## Preparation\n- Preheat oven to 160°C (320°F).\n\n## Making the Base\n- Spread the crushed biscuit/Graham cracker evenly on the bottom of a small springform pan.\n\n## Preparing the Filling\n- In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth.\n- Add the Greek yoghurt, egg, vanilla extract, and stevia. Mix well.\n- Fold in the protein powder and mix until fully combined.\n- In a small saucepan, heat the frozen blueberries over medium heat until they release their juices.\n- Add the cornflour mixed with water to the blueberries, stirring continuously until the mixture thickens slightly.\n- Fold the blueberry mixture into the cream cheese mixture until well combined.\n\n## Baking\n- Pour the filling over the biscuit base in the springform pan.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 30-35 minutes, or until the center is set but still slightly jiggly.\n- Let the cheesecake cool at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight until set.\n\n## Serving\n- Once set, drizzle the melted white chocolate over the cheesecake before serving.\n- Slice and serve chilled.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('140','Chocolate Peanut Butter Banana Protein Smoothie','## Ingredients\n- 1 cup frozen banana\n- 1 1/2 cups Greek yogurt\n- 4 tbsp peanut butter powder\n- 2 scoops chocolate protein powder\n- 1/2 cup Fairlife milk\n- Ice cubes (optional)\n- Honey or maple syrup, to taste (optional)','## Instructions\n- Place the frozen banana, Greek yogurt, peanut butter powder, chocolate protein powder, and Fairlife milk in a blender.\n- Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy, stopping to scrape down the sides if necessary.\n- If the smoothie is too thick, add a little more milk until you reach your desired consistency.\n- Add ice cubes and blend again for a colder, thicker smoothie.\n- Taste and add honey or maple syrup if additional sweetness is desired.\n- Pour into a glass and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('141','Lazy Biryani','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups basmati rice\n- 400g skinless chicken breast, cut into chunks\n- 1 large onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 cup plain yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 3 whole cloves\n- 2 green cardamom pods\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 tablespoon ginger garlic paste\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Fried onions (optional)\n- Lemon wedges\n\n## Additional\n- 3.5 cups water\n- 1 tablespoon butter or ghee','## Preparation\n- Rinse the basmati rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Soak the rice in water for 15-20 minutes, then drain.\n- Marinate the chicken with yogurt, ginger garlic paste, turmeric, red chili powder, and salt. Let it sit for at least 15 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large pot, heat oil over medium heat. Add cumin seeds, cloves, cardamom, and cinnamon. Sauté until fragrant.\n- Add sliced onions and cook until golden brown.\n- Stir in the chopped tomatoes and cook until they soften.\n- Add the marinated chicken and cook until the chicken is sealed and begins to brown.\n- Add soaked and drained rice to the pot and gently mix with the chicken and spices.\n- Pour in 3.5 cups of water and salt to taste. Bring it to a boil.\n- Reduce the heat and cover with a tight-fitting lid. Let it cook on low heat for about 20 minutes, or until the rice is fully cooked and fluffy.\n\n## Final Touch\n- Turn off the heat and add butter or ghee. Let it sit covered for 5 minutes.\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro, fried onions, and serve with lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('142','Iced Tiramisu Latte Protein Shake','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup cold brewed coffee\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1/2 cup ice\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Cocoa powder for dusting\n- Whipped cream (optional)','## Preparation Steps\n- In a blender, combine the cold brewed coffee, almond milk, vanilla protein powder, cocoa powder, maple syrup, vanilla extract, cinnamon, and ice.\n- Blend until smooth and frothy.\n- Pour into a glass over additional ice cubes if desired.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Dust with a bit of cocoa powder on top.\n- Add a dollop of whipped cream if desired for a more indulgent treat.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('143','Pork Lumpia','## Filling\n- 1 lb ground pork\n- 1/2 cup carrots, finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup green beans, finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup onions, finely chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce\n- 1 teaspoon ground black pepper\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n## For wrapping and frying\n- 25-30 lumpia wrappers\n- 1 egg, beaten (for sealing)\n- Vegetable oil (for frying)','## Prepare the filling\n- In a large bowl, combine ground pork, carrots, green beans, onions, and garlic.\n- Add soy sauce, oyster sauce, black pepper, and salt. Mix thoroughly until well combined.\n- Let the mixture marinate for about 15 minutes for flavors to meld.\n\n## Wrap the lumpia\n- Place a lumpia wrapper on a flat surface, with one corner pointing towards you (like a diamond shape).\n- Spoon about 1-2 tablespoons of the pork mixture onto the wrapper near the corner closest to you.\n- Roll the corner over the filling tightly, fold in the sides, and continue rolling. Brush the end corner with a bit of beaten egg to seal the lumpia.\n- Repeat the process for the remaining wrappers and filling.\n\n## Fry the lumpia\n- In a deep frying pan, heat vegetable oil over medium heat.\n- Once the oil is hot, carefully add the lumpia in batches, frying until they are golden brown and crispy, about 3-5 minutes per batch.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.\n- Serve warm with your choice of dipping sauce, such as sweet chili sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('144','High-Protein Roast Beef Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 slices whole-grain bread\n- 12 oz roast beef, thinly sliced\n- 4 slices cheddar cheese (optional)\n- 1 cup arugula leaves\n- 1 medium tomato, sliced\n- 1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n\n## Spread\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- 1 tsp horseradish sauce\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Spread\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, Dijon mustard, horseradish sauce, salt, and pepper until smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Lay out the slices of bread. Spread the yogurt mixture evenly over one side of each slice.\n- Layer the roast beef evenly on four slices of bread.\n- Add a slice of cheddar cheese on top of the roast beef if desired.\n- Top with arugula leaves, tomato slices, and red onion slices.\n- Close the sandwiches with the remaining bread slices, spread side down.\n\n## Toast the Sandwich\n- Preheat a skillet or pan over medium heat.\n- Place the sandwiches in the hot skillet and toast each side for 3-4 minutes or until golden brown and the cheese has melted.\n- Press down gently with a spatula to ensure even cooking.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from the skillet and let cool slightly.\n- Cut each sandwich in half and serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('145','High-Protein Ricotta Pancakes','## Pancakes\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/2 cup whole wheat flour\n- 2 eggs\n- 1/4 cup milk (or almond milk for dairy-free option)\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- Fresh berries\n- Greek yogurt\n- Nuts or seeds\n- Honey or maple syrup','## Prepare the Batter\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the ricotta cheese, eggs, milk, honey, and vanilla extract. Whisk until well combined.\n- In another bowl, mix whole wheat flour, baking powder, and salt.\n- Slowly add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, stirring gently until just combined. Be careful not to over-mix.\n\n## Cook the Pancakes\n- Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat and lightly grease it with a little oil or butter.\n- Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.\n- Cook until bubbles start to form on the surface and the edges look set, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Flip the pancakes and cook for another 2-3 minutes, or until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Repeat with the remaining batter.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Serve the pancakes warm with your choice of toppings such as fresh berries, a dollop of Greek yogurt, a sprinkle of nuts or seeds, and a drizzle of honey or maple syrup.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('146','High-Protein Egg Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon Greek yogurt (optional for extra creaminess)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 4 slices of whole grain bread\n- 2 tablespoons cottage cheese\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 small tomato, sliced\n- Handful of spinach leaves\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil or butter\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Red pepper flakes\n- Chopped chives\n- Hot sauce','## Prepare the Eggs\n- Crack the eggs into a mixing bowl and add 1 tablespoon of Greek yogurt (optional), salt, and pepper. Beat the mixture until smooth.\n- In a non-stick skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil or butter over medium heat.\n- Pour in the egg mixture and let it sit for about 30 seconds. Use a spatula to gently stir and fold the eggs until just set and creamy. Remove from heat.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Toast the whole grain bread slices until golden brown.\n- Spread 1 tablespoon of cottage cheese on each slice of toast.\n- Layer sliced avocado and tomato on two pieces of toast.\n- Place a handful of spinach leaves on top of the avocado and tomato.\n- Divide the scrambled eggs evenly between the two sandwiches, placing them on top of the spinach leaves.\n- Top each sandwich with the remaining slices of toast.\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Sprinkle with red pepper flakes or chopped chives for extra flavor, if desired.\n- Serve immediately with hot sauce on the side, if preferred.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('147','Lettuce Burgers','## For the Patties\n- 1 lb ground turkey or lean beef\n- 1/2 cup finely chopped onion\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n\n## For the Assembly\n- Large lettuce leaves (such as romaine or iceberg)\n- 1 tomato, sliced\n- 1 red onion, sliced\n- Pickles\n- Avocado slices\n- Cheese slices (optional)\n- Condiments of choice (mustard, ketchup, etc.)','## Prepare the Patties\n- In a large bowl, combine the ground turkey or beef with the chopped onion, garlic, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until just combined, being careful not to overwork the meat.\n- Divide the mixture into 4 equal portions and form each into a patty about 3/4 inch thick.\n\n## Cook the Patties\n- Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the patties for about 5-6 minutes per side, or until fully cooked and the internal temperature reaches 165°F for turkey or 160°F for beef.\n- If using cheese, place a slice on each patty during the last minute of cooking to melt.\n\n## Assemble the Lettuce Burgers\n- Lay a large lettuce leaf on a plate and place a cooked patty on top.\n- Top the patty with tomato slices, red onion, pickles, avocado, and any other desired toppings.\n- Drizzle with condiments of choice.\n- Wrap the lettuce around the fillings to enclose the burger.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('148','King Prawn Madras','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g king prawns, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 inch ginger, grated\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n\n## Spices\n- 1 tablespoon Madras curry powder\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon chili powder (adjust for spice preference)\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n\n## Optional\n- 1 tablespoon coconut milk or yogurt for a creamy texture','## Preparation\n- Heat the vegetable oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the garlic and ginger, cooking for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the chopped tomatoes and tomato paste; cook until the tomatoes soften.\n- Mix in the Madras curry powder, cumin, coriander, turmeric, chili powder, and salt.\n- Cook the spice mixture for 2-3 minutes, adding a splash of water if it becomes too dry.\n- Add the king prawns and cook until they turn pink and are fully cooked, about 4-5 minutes.\n- Optional: Add coconut milk or yogurt to achieve a creamy consistency.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve with lemon wedges.\n- Pair with steamed rice or naan for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('149','Healthy High-Protein Chicken Parmesan','## Chicken & Coating\n- 2 large chicken breasts\n- 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Sauce & Topping\n- 1 cup marinara sauce (low-sodium)\n- 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese (part-skim)\n- Fresh basil leaves (optional)','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Slice the chicken breasts in half horizontally to create four thin cutlets.\n- Season the chicken cutlets with salt and pepper on both sides.\n\n## Coating\n- In a shallow bowl, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, and garlic powder.\n- Dredge each chicken cutlet in the breadcrumb mixture, pressing to adhere.\n\n## Baking\n- Place the coated chicken cutlets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes.\n\n## Adding Sauce & Cheese\n- Remove the chicken from the oven and spoon marinara sauce over each cutlet.\n- Sprinkle mozzarella cheese evenly over the top of each cutlet.\n\n## Final Baking\n- Return the chicken to the oven and bake for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is bubbly and the chicken is cooked through.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh basil leaves if desired.\n- Serve hot with a side of steamed vegetables or a fresh salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('150','High-Protein Osso Buco','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 pieces veal shanks, about 1.5 inches thick\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 carrots, chopped\n- 2 celery stalks, chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup white wine\n- 2 cups beef or chicken stock\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n- 2 teaspoons dried thyme\n- 2 bay leaves\n\n## Gremolata\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 clove garlic, minced','## Preparation Steps\n- Season the veal shanks with salt and pepper.\n- In a large oven-safe pot, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Brown the veal shanks on all sides, about 10 minutes, then remove and set aside.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- In the same pot, add chopped onions, carrots, and celery. Sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add minced garlic and cook for another minute.\n- Deglaze the pot with white wine, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom.\n- Return the veal shanks to the pot.\n- Add beef or chicken stock, diced tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, and bay leaves.\n- Bring to a simmer, cover, and cook over low heat for 1.5 to 2 hours until the meat is tender.\n- Alternatively, place the pot in a preheated oven at 350°F (175°C) for the same time duration.\n\n## Final Touches\n- Mix the lemon zest, parsley, and minced garlic to create the gremolata.\n- Sprinkle gremolata over the osso buco just before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('151','Chicken Saltimbocca','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 8 thin slices of prosciutto\n- 8 large fresh sage leaves\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 1/2 cup dry white wine\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Lemon wedges\n- Chopped fresh parsley','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Place each chicken breast between two pieces of plastic wrap and pound them to an even thickness of about 1/4 inch.\n- Season both sides of the chicken with salt and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Saltimbocca\n- Place two sage leaves on top of each piece of chicken, followed by two slices of prosciutto. Press down gently to adhere.\n\n## Coat the Chicken\n- Spread the flour on a shallow plate. Lightly dredge each chicken piece in the flour, shaking off excess.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken, prosciutto-side down, and cook for about 3 minutes until the prosciutto is golden and crispy.\n- Carefully flip the chicken and add butter to the skillet. Cook for another 2-3 minutes until chicken is cooked through.\n- Remove chicken from the skillet and keep warm.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, pour in the wine and chicken broth. Scrape up any brown bits from the bottom of the pan.\n- Bring to a simmer and cook until the liquid is reduced by half.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet and spoon the sauce over the top.\n\n## Serve\n- Transfer chicken to a serving platter, pour sauce over the top.\n- Garnish with lemon wedges and chopped parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('152','High-Protein Braciole','## For the Braciole\n- 1.5 pounds beef top round, sliced into thin cutlets\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/2 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted\n- 8 slices prosciutto\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (28 ounces) crushed tomatoes\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Filling\n- In a bowl, combine Parmesan cheese, parsley, minced garlic, and pine nuts.\n\n## Prepare the Beef\n- Lay out the beef slices and season with salt and pepper.\n- Place a slice of prosciutto on each beef slice.\n- Spread a thin layer of the filling mixture over the prosciutto.\n\n## Roll the Braciole\n- Carefully roll up each beef slice from one end to the other, securing with toothpicks or kitchen twine.\n\n## Brown the Braciole\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Add the rolls and brown on all sides for about 6-8 minutes.\n- Remove from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, add chopped onion and cook until translucent.\n- Add minced garlic and cook for 1 more minute.\n- Pour in the crushed tomatoes and add oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Bring the sauce to a simmer.\n\n## Cook the Braciole in Sauce\n- Return the browned beef rolls to the skillet, submerging them in the sauce.\n- Cover and simmer on low heat for 1.5 to 2 hours until the meat is tender.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('153','Pork Tenderloin with Rosemary & Garlic','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 pounds pork tenderloin\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil, divided\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh rosemary, chopped\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste\n\n## Optional\n- Lemon wedges for serving','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Pat the pork tenderloin dry with paper towels.\n- In a small bowl, combine 2 tablespoons of olive oil, minced garlic, and chopped rosemary.\n\n## Cooking\n- Season the pork tenderloin with salt and pepper on all sides.\n- Rub the garlic-rosemary mixture evenly over the pork.\n- Heat the remaining tablespoon of olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Once the oil is hot, add the pork and sear for 3-4 minutes on each side until browned.\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and roast for 15-20 minutes, or until the internal temperature of the pork reaches 145°F (63°C).\n\n## Finishing and Serving\n- Remove the tenderloin from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n- Serve with optional lemon wedges for extra flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('154','Chicken Cacciatore','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 chicken thighs (bone-in, skinless)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, sliced\n- 8 ounces mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 can (14.5 ounces) diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 1/4 cup dry white wine (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredients for Serving\n- Whole grain pasta, cooked (optional)\n- Steamed vegetables (optional)','## Preparation\n- Season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper on both sides.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, add olive oil and brown the chicken thighs on both sides, about 5 minutes per side. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add the chopped onion and garlic. Sauté for 2-3 minutes until the onion is translucent.\n- Add the sliced bell peppers and mushrooms. Cook for another 5 minutes until the vegetables are soft.\n- Stir in the diced tomatoes, chicken broth, and wine (if using). Add oregano, basil, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet. Cover and simmer on low heat for 30-35 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and tender.\n- Sprinkle with fresh parsley before serving.\n\n## Serving Suggestion\n- Serve over cooked whole grain pasta or with steamed vegetables for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('155','Stuffed Bell Peppers with Ground Turkey','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers (any color)\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes, drained\n- 1 cup black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup corn kernels (fresh, frozen, or canned)\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or mozzarella)\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n\n## Garnish (Optional)\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Sour cream or Greek yogurt\n- Sliced avocado','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes. Lightly oil a baking dish and arrange the peppers upright.\n\n## Cooking the Filling\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.\n- Add the ground turkey to the skillet, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until it’s browned and fully cooked, about 7-10 minutes.\n- Stir in the diced tomatoes, black beans, corn, cooked quinoa, cumin, smoked paprika, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Mix well and cook for another 5 minutes to blend the flavors.\n\n## Stuffing the Peppers\n- Evenly divide the turkey mixture among the prepared bell peppers, pressing down gently to fill them well.\n- Top each pepper with a generous amount of shredded cheese.\n\n## Baking\n- Cover the baking dish with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the peppers are tender.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving.\n- Garnish with freshly chopped cilantro, a dollop of sour cream or Greek yogurt, and sliced avocado if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('156','Italian Grilled Chicken Skewers','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Skewers\n- 1.5 pounds chicken breast, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 2 bell peppers (red and yellow), cut into 1-inch squares\n- 1 red onion, cut into wedges\n- Wooden or metal skewers','## Preparation\n- In a bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and black pepper to create the marinade.\n- Add the chicken cubes to the bowl and mix well to ensure all pieces are coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for more flavor.\n- If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for 30 minutes to prevent burning.\n\n## Assembly\n- Preheat grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the chicken, bell peppers, and red onion alternately onto the skewers, leaving a little space between each piece for even cooking.\n\n## Grilling\n- Place the skewers on the grill and cook for 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and has nice grill marks.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the grill and let rest for a few minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('157','Ricotta-Stuffed Shells with Protein Pasta','## For the Ricotta Filling\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/2 cup cottage cheese\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Protein Pasta Shells\n- 20 large protein pasta shells\n\n## For the Tomato Sauce\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Topping\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese','## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, mozzarella cheese, egg, basil, parsley, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until smooth and well combined.\n\n## Prepare the Pasta Shells\n- Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.\n- Add pasta shells and cook according to the package instructions until al dente.\n- Drain and set aside to cool slightly.\n\n## Prepare the Tomato Sauce\n- In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add marinara sauce, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer for about 5 minutes to combine flavors.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce at the bottom of a baking dish.\n- Stuff each shell with the ricotta filling and place in the dish.\n- Cover the stuffed shells with remaining tomato sauce.\n- Sprinkle mozzarella and Parmesan cheese on top.\n\n## Bake\n- Cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes.\n- Remove foil and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('158','Eggs in Purgatory','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 1 can (28 ounces) crushed tomatoes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- Crusty bread for serving\n- Chopped parsley for garnish','## Prepare the Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes to the oil, sauté until garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute.\n- Pour in the crushed tomatoes and stir in salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning.\n- Simmer the sauce for 10-15 minutes, allowing it to thicken slightly.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- Using a spoon, make small wells in the tomato sauce.\n- Crack an egg into each well.\n- Cover the skillet and cook for about 5-7 minutes, until the egg whites are set but yolks remain runny.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese and fresh basil over the top.\n- Serve immediately with crusty bread if desired, garnished with chopped parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('159','Cottage Cheese Lasagna','## Main Ingredients\n- 9 lasagna noodles\n- 1 1/2 pounds lean ground beef\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 1 can (15 ounces) tomato sauce\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Cottage Cheese Mixture\n- 2 cups cottage cheese\n- 1 egg, beaten\n- 1 teaspoon dried parsley\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n\n## Cheese Layer\n- 2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese for topping','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cook the lasagna noodles according to package instructions, then drain and set aside.\n\n## Meat Sauce\n- In a large skillet, cook the ground beef over medium heat until browned. Drain excess fat.\n- Add marinara sauce, tomato sauce, garlic powder, onion powder, dried basil, salt, and pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n## Cottage Cheese Mixture\n- In a medium bowl, mix together cottage cheese, egg, dried parsley, and Parmesan cheese.\n\n## Assembly\n- Spread a thin layer of meat sauce in the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish.\n- Place three lasagna noodles over the sauce.\n- Spread half of the cottage cheese mixture over the noodles.\n- Add a layer of mozzarella cheese.\n- Repeat layers: meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese mixture, mozzarella cheese.\n- Top with remaining noodles and the rest of the meat sauce.\n- Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.\n\n## Baking\n- Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes.\n- Remove foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly and golden brown.\n- Let rest for 10 minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('160','Mushroom & Cheese Arancini with Quinoa','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa, cooked\n- 1 cup mushrooms, finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, diced\n- 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/4 cup breadcrumbs\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 eggs, beaten\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Coating Ingredients\n- 1 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1/2 cup flour\n- 2 eggs, beaten\n\n## Cooking Oil\n- Vegetable oil for frying','## Preparing the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add onions and garlic, sauté until translucent.\n- Add mushrooms, cook until soft and moisture has evaporated.\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, sautéed mushrooms, mozzarella, Parmesan, breadcrumbs, and eggs.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n- Mix well to form a sticky mixture.\n\n## Forming the Arancini\n- With damp hands, take a spoonful of the mixture and form into small balls (about the size of a golf ball).\n\n## Coating the Arancini\n- Place flour, beaten eggs, and breadcrumbs each into separate bowls.\n- Roll each ball first in flour, then dip in beaten eggs, and finally coat thoroughly with breadcrumbs.\n\n## Cooking the Arancini\n- Heat vegetable oil in a deep frying pan or pot over medium-high heat.\n- Fry the arancini in batches, turning occasionally, until they are golden brown and heated through, about 4-5 minutes per batch.\n- Drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('161','Caprese Salad with Mozzarella & Grilled Chicken','## Salad Ingredients\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 8 ounces fresh mozzarella, sliced\n- 3 large ripe tomatoes, sliced\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 2 tablespoons balsamic glaze\n\n## Marinade\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a small bowl, mix together 2 tablespoons of olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken\n- Place the chicken breasts in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over them.\n- Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours.\n\n## Grill the Chicken\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the chicken from the marinade and brush with 1 tablespoon olive oil.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n- Grill the chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked.\n- Allow the chicken to rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- On a large platter, alternate slices of mozzarella and tomato.\n- Tuck whole basil leaves between the slices.\n- Place the sliced grilled chicken on top.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Drizzle with balsamic glaze.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('162','Baked Polenta with Ricotta & Spinach','## Polenta Base\n- 1 cup polenta (coarse cornmeal)\n- 4 cups water\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Toppings\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, roughly chopped\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg (optional)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil','## Prepare the Polenta\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a medium-sized saucepan, bring the water to a boil, then add the salt.\n- Gradually whisk in the polenta, reducing the heat to low and stirring constantly.\n- Cook the polenta until thick and creamy, about 15-20 minutes.\n- Stir in the olive oil, then remove from heat.\n- Pour the cooked polenta into a greased baking dish and spread it evenly.\n\n## Prepare the Toppings\n- In a skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.\n- Add the spinach and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.\n- In a bowl, combine the ricotta cheese, cooked spinach, salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Mix well.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Spread the ricotta and spinach mixture evenly over the top of the polenta.\n- Sprinkle the grated Parmesan cheese over the ricotta topping.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, until the cheese is golden and bubbly.\n- Let cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('163','Cauliflower Gnocchi Alfredo','## Cauliflower Gnocchi\n- 1 medium head cauliflower, cut into florets\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 large egg\n\n## Alfredo Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/2 cup parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley','## Cauliflower Gnocchi\n- Steam the cauliflower florets until tender, about 5-7 minutes. Drain well and let them cool slightly.\n- Transfer cauliflower to a food processor and pulse until creamy and smooth.\n- In a large bowl, combine cauliflower puree, almond flour, parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, and egg. Mix until dough forms.\n- On a floured surface, roll dough into long ropes and cut into 1-inch pieces to form gnocchi.\n- Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook gnocchi in batches for 2-3 minutes or until they float to the top. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.\n\n## Alfredo Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add minced garlic and sauté until fragrant.\n- Pour in almond milk and bring to a simmer. Stir in parmesan cheese until melted and the sauce thickens.\n- Add nutmeg, salt, and pepper to taste.\n- Toss the cooked gnocchi in the sauce until well coated.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('164','Three-Cheese Manicotti with Added Tofu','## For the Cheese Filling\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 200g firm tofu, drained and crumbled\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Manicotti\n- 12 manicotti shells\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded (for topping)\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (for topping)','## Preparing the Cheese Filling\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a large bowl, combine ricotta, cottage cheese, shredded mozzarella, crumbled tofu, Parmesan, and egg.\n- Add minced garlic, chopped basil, salt, and pepper. Mix thoroughly until well combined.\n\n## Assembling the Manicotti\n- Cook manicotti shells according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and lay them on a baking sheet to cool slightly.\n- Using a spoon or piping bag, fill each manicotti shell with the cheese and tofu mixture.\n- Spread 1 cup of marinara sauce in the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish.\n- Arrange the filled shells in a single layer over the sauce.\n- Pour the remaining marinara sauce evenly over the top of the manicotti.\n\n## Baking\n- Sprinkle the remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over the marinara sauce.\n- Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes, until the cheese on top is melted and bubbly.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('165','Pasta e Fagioli','## Produce\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced\n\n## Canned or Jarred\n- 1 (14 oz) can of diced tomatoes\n- 1 (15 oz) can of cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 (15 oz) can of kidney beans, drained and rinsed\n\n## Dry Goods\n- 1 cup ditalini pasta or small pasta of choice\n- 4 cups low-sodium vegetable broth\n\n## Spices & Herbs\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Oils & Vinegars\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Freshly grated Parmesan cheese\n- Chopped fresh parsley','## Preparation\n- In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the onion, carrots, and celery. Sauté for 5-7 minutes until the vegetables are softened.\n- Add the garlic and cook for another 1 minute until fragrant.\n\n## Cooking\n- Stir in the diced tomatoes, vegetable broth, oregano, basil, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n- Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.\n- Add the cannellini beans and kidney beans.\n- Allow the soup to simmer for around 10 minutes.\n- Add the pasta and cook until al dente, about 10-12 minutes.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Serving\n- Ladle the soup into bowls.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and Parmesan cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('166','Spaghetti Carbonara with Turkey Bacon','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz whole wheat spaghetti\n- 6 slices turkey bacon, diced\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Pecorino Romano cheese\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredient\n- 1/4 tsp red pepper flakes for heat','## Cooking Pasta\n- Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.\n- Add the spaghetti and cook until al dente, according to package instructions.\n- Reserve 1 cup of pasta water and then drain the spaghetti.\n\n## Preparing Sauce and Bacon\n- In a mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, Parmesan cheese, Pecorino Romano cheese, salt, and pepper. Set aside.\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, cook turkey bacon until crispy, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add minced garlic to the skillet and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n\n## Combining Ingredients\n- Reduce the heat to low and add the drained spaghetti to the skillet with the turkey bacon and garlic. Toss to combine.\n- Remove the skillet from heat and quickly pour the egg and cheese mixture into the pasta, stirring quickly to create a creamy sauce. Add reserved pasta water as needed to reach your desired consistency.\n- Season with red pepper flakes, if using, and additional salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh parsley.\n- Serve immediately, with additional grated cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('167','Protein Banana Bread','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup whole wheat flour\n- 1 scoop (about 30g) vanilla protein powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 3 ripe bananas, mashed\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 large eggs\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (walnuts or almonds)\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan or line it with parchment paper.\n\n## Mixing\n- In a large bowl, combine the whole wheat flour, protein powder, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon.\n- In another bowl, mix the mashed bananas, honey or maple syrup, Greek yogurt, vanilla extract, and eggs until well combined.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Do not overmix.\n- Fold in any optional add-ins like nuts or chocolate chips if using.\n\n## Baking\n- Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and spread it evenly.\n- Bake for 40-50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n- Let the bread cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, then remove it to a wire rack to cool completely before slicing.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('168','Cottage Cheese Lava Cakes','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup maple syrup or honey\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Filling\n- 2 oz dark chocolate, chopped','## Prepare Batter\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a bowl, mix almond flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt.\n- In a blender, blend cottage cheese until smooth.\n- Add eggs, maple syrup, and vanilla extract to the blender and blend until well combined.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.\n\n## Prepare and Fill Ramekins\n- Grease 4 ramekins with cooking spray or butter.\n- Fill each ramekin halfway with batter.\n- Place 0.5 oz of chopped dark chocolate in the center of each ramekin.\n- Cover the chocolate with the remaining batter until the ramekin is 3/4 full.\n\n## Bake\n- Place the ramekins on a baking sheet and bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the edges are set but the center is still soft.\n\n## Serve\n- Let the cakes cool for 5 minutes.\n- Run a knife around the edges to loosen them.\n- Carefully invert the cakes onto plates.\n- Serve warm to enjoy the molten chocolate center.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('169','Lemon Chicken Cutlets with Basil Sauce','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb thinly sliced chicken breasts\n- 1/3 cup half and half\n- 1 1/2 cups seasoned breadcrumbs (Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt, and pepper)\n- Olive oil (to coat the pan)\n- 3 tbsp butter\n- 4 slices of lemon\n\n## Lemon Sauce\n- Juice of 2 large lemons\n- Equal part olive oil (equivalent to lemon juice)\n- 2 cloves of garlic, grated\n- A handful of fresh basil, roughly chopped\n- Salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, and a dash of paprika','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 325°F (163°C).\n- Thinly slice the chicken breasts and season them with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning.\n- Place the chicken in a bowl and coat with half and half, ensuring even coverage to help breadcrumbs adhere.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Dredge the chicken slices in the seasoned breadcrumbs, making sure they are thoroughly coated.\n- Heat an oven-safe skillet over medium heat, adding olive oil and butter.\n- Sear the chicken for 3-4 minutes on each side, until golden brown (it does not need to be fully cooked).\n- Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and repeat until all chicken pieces are browned.\n\n## Sauce and Baking\n- Return all browned chicken to the hot skillet.\n- Top with lemon slices and pour the lemon sauce over the chicken.\n- Allow to simmer for 2 minutes.\n- Place the skillet in the oven, baking for 12-18 minutes until the chicken is fully cooked and golden.\n\n## Service\n- Keep warm at 200°F until serving.\n- Plate the chicken, drizzling with the remaining lemon sauce from the pan.\n\n## Lemon Sauce Preparation\n- In a measuring cup, combine the juice of two lemons, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, grated garlic, and paprika.\n- Slowly whisk in olive oil, matching the quantity of lemon juice, until emulsified.\n- Stir in chopped fresh basil and set aside.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('170','BBQ Chicken Pizza','## For the Pizza Dough\n- 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 packet (2 1/4 tsp) active dry yeast\n- 1 cup warm water (110°F)\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n\n## For the Toppings\n- 1 cup cooked chicken breast, shredded or diced\n- 1/2 cup BBQ sauce\n- 1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1/2 cup red bell pepper, thinly sliced (optional)\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese (optional)','## Prepare the Pizza Dough\n- In a small bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water and add the yeast. Let it sit for about 5 minutes until frothy.\n- In a large bowl, combine the flour and salt. Make a well in the middle and add the yeast mixture and olive oil.\n- Mix until a dough forms, then knead on a floured surface for about 5-7 minutes until smooth and elastic.\n- Place the dough in a lightly oiled bowl, cover it with a cloth, and let it rise in a warm area for 1 hour or until it doubles in size.\n\n## Prepare the Toppings\n- Mix the shredded or diced chicken with 1/4 cup of BBQ sauce to coat well.\n- Preheat your oven to 475°F (245°C).\n\n## Assemble the Pizza\n- Punch down the risen dough and roll it out onto a floured surface to form your pizza crust.\n- Lay the dough on a pizza stone or a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Spread the remaining BBQ sauce over the pizza crust, leaving a border for the crust.\n- Top with the coated chicken, shredded mozzarella cheese, red onion slices, and red bell pepper if using.\n- Sprinkle the optional feta cheese over the top for extra flavor.\n\n## Bake and Serve\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.\n- Remove from the oven and sprinkle with fresh cilantro before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('171','High Protein Hamburger Pizza','## For the Dough\n- 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 packet (2 1/4 teaspoons) active dry yeast\n- 3/4 cup warm water\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n\n## For the Toppings\n- 1/2 pound lean ground beef\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 cup pizza sauce\n- 1 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1/4 cup parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 small red onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons pickles, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- Fresh basil leaves for garnish','## Prepare the Dough\n- In a large bowl, combine the whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour, and salt.\n- In a small bowl, mix the warm water with the yeast until dissolved.\n- Add dissolved yeast and olive oil to the flour mixture. Stir until a dough forms.\n- Knead dough on a floured surface for about 5-7 minutes until smooth and elastic.\n- Place dough in a lightly oiled bowl, cover, and let rise for 1 hour or until doubled in size.\n\n## Cook the Beef\n- In a skillet over medium heat, cook the ground beef until browned. Drain excess fat.\n- Season with garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Stir well.\n\n## Assemble the Pizza\n- Preheat the oven to 475°F (245°C).\n- Punch down the dough and roll out on a floured surface to form a pizza crust.\n- Transfer the crust to a baking sheet or pizza stone.\n- Spread the pizza sauce evenly over the crust.\n- Sprinkle the cooked beef over the sauce.\n- Top with mozzarella cheese, parmesan cheese, cherry tomatoes, red onion, pickles, and sesame seeds.\n\n## Bake the Pizza\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes until the crust is golden and cheese is bubbly.\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly.\n- Sprinkle fresh basil leaves before slicing and serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('172','High Protein Hummus with Sautéed Sirloin and Pine Nuts','## Hummus\n- 1 can garbanzo beans, rinsed\n- Salt, to taste\n- 2 tbsp lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic (optional)\n- 1/3 cup tahini\n- 1-2 ice cubes\n- Cold water, as needed\n\n## Pine Nuts\n- 1 tbsp avocado oil\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts\n\n## Meat\n- 6 oz top sirloin, cut into cubes\n- 1 tbsp avocado oil\n- Salt, to taste\n- Pepper, to taste\n- Smoked paprika, to taste\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts (from above)\n\n## Topping\n- Pomegranate molasses, for drizzling\n- Olive oil, for drizzling','## Hummus\n- Combine garbanzo beans, salt, lemon juice, garlic, tahini, and ice cubes in a food processor or blender.\n- Blend until thick and creamy, adding cold water 1 tbsp at a time if needed for consistency.\n- Taste and adjust the seasoning with more salt or lemon juice if desired.\n\n## Pine Nuts\n- Heat 1 tbsp of avocado oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add pine nuts and cook for 4-5 minutes until golden brown, stirring constantly to prevent burning.\n- Remove from pan and set aside.\n\n## Meat\n- Heat 1 tbsp of avocado oil in a pan over high heat.\n- Add sirloin cubes and sear for 5-6 minutes, seasoning with salt, pepper, and smoked paprika to taste.\n- Mix in a handful of the toasted pine nuts during the last 2 minutes of cooking.\n\n## Assembly\n- Spread hummus on a serving dish.\n- Top with the seared sirloin and pine nuts.\n- Drizzle with pomegranate molasses and olive oil before serving.\n- Enjoy immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('173','High-Protein Chocolate Brownie Bites','## Dry Ingredients\n- 2 scoops chocolate whey casein protein (30g)\n- 1/4 cup zero sugar brownie mix (30g)\n- 1/4 cup zero calorie sweetener\n- 2 tbsp cocoa powder (10g)\n- 2 tbsp almond flour (15g)\n- 1/2 tsp baking powder\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 egg\n- 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (110g)\n- 1 tbsp melted light butter (15ml)\n- 1 tbsp sugar-free pancake syrup (15ml)\n- 1/4 tsp vanilla extract\n\n## Topping\n- 1 tsp rainbow sprinkles\n- 2 tsp mini chocolate chips (10g)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lightly grease a muffin tin or line with paper liners.\n\n## Mix Dry Ingredients\n- In a large bowl, combine the chocolate whey casein protein, brownie mix, sweetener, cocoa powder, almond flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir until well mixed.\n\n## Combine Wet Ingredients\n- In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg, Greek yogurt, melted butter, sugar-free syrup, and vanilla extract.\n\n## Combine Wet and Dry Ingredients\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix gently until just combined. Avoid over-mixing.\n\n## Bake\n- Divide the batter evenly into the prepared muffin tin.\n- Top each with a sprinkle of rainbow sprinkles and mini chocolate chips.\n- Bake in the oven for 15-18 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out mostly clean.\n\n## Serve\n- Let the brownie bites cool in the pan for about 5 minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n- Enjoy your healthy, high-protein chocolate brownie bites.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('174','High Protein Sloppy Joes','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb lean ground turkey or lean ground beef\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1 small green bell pepper, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup tomato sauce\n- 2 tbsp tomato paste\n- 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- 1 tbsp apple cider vinegar\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- Whole wheat burger buns or lettuce leaves for serving\n- Sliced pickles for garnish\n- 1 tbsp olive oil','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and bell pepper. Sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add ground turkey (or beef) to the skillet. Cook until browned, breaking up the meat with a spoon, about 8-10 minutes.\n- Stir in the tomato sauce, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, and apple cider vinegar.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Simmer the mixture for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the sloppy joe mixture on whole wheat buns or wrapped in lettuce leaves for a low-carb option.\n- Top with sliced pickles if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('175','High Protein Peanut Butter Biscoff Dessert','## Ingredients\n- 15g powdered peanut butter (PB2)\n- 5g natural sweetener\n- Dash of salt\n- 200ml unsweetened almond milk (adjust based on protein powder consistency)\n- 10g melted Biscoff spread\n- 10g chocolate chips\n- 1 crushed Biscoff biscuit (half mixed in, half for topping)\n- 45g vegan protein powder','## Instructions\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the powdered peanut butter, natural sweetener, vegan protein powder, and a dash of salt.\n- Slowly add the almond milk, stirring continuously, until the desired consistency is achieved.\n- Mix in the melted Biscoff spread and half of the crushed Biscoff biscuit.\n- Fold in the chocolate chips.\n- Cover the mixture and place it in the refrigerator for 15 to 25 minutes to thicken.\n- Once set, sprinkle the remaining crushed Biscoff biscuit on top before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('176','Protein-Packed Baked Breakfast Bowl','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 egg\n- 50 g yogurt (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 70 ml milk (soy, almond, or any preferred milk)\n- 35 g all-purpose flour\n- 25 g protein powder (vanilla or white chocolate; adjust liquid if using whey)\n- 5 g zero calorie granulated sweetener or sweetener of choice (1 tsp)\n- 1/2 tsp baking powder','## Preparation Steps\n- Preheat your oven to 180°C (356°F).\n- In an oven-safe glass bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix thoroughly.\n- For meal prep with multiple bowls, ensure each ingredient is added separately to each bowl.\n- Top with your choice of fresh fruit, sugar-free chocolate chips, shredded carrots, or keep it simple.\n- Bake the mixture for 20-22 minutes until set.\n- Once baked, allow it to cool for 5-10 minutes before serving.\n- Enhance your bowl by serving it with extra yogurt, peanut butter, maple syrup, or butter.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('177','High Protein Crab Cakes','## Crab Cakes\n- 1 lb lump crab meat\n- 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs\n- 1/4 cup mayonnaise\n- 1 large egg, beaten\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon Old Bay seasoning\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## For Cooking\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Optional Sauce\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Crab Cakes\n- In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, egg, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, parsley, Old Bay seasoning, salt, and pepper.\n- Gently fold in the crab meat and panko breadcrumbs, being careful not to break up the crab meat too much. Mix until just combined.\n- Form the mixture into 8 patties, about 1/2 inch thick. Place them on a baking sheet and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to help them hold their shape.\n\n## Cook the Crab Cakes\n- Heat olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the crab cakes and cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and cooked through. Be careful when flipping to maintain the shape.\n- Remove from heat and let rest for a couple of minutes before serving.\n\n## Prepare the Optional Sauce\n- In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, honey, salt, and pepper.\n- Serve the sauce alongside the crab cakes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('178','Classic Charmer Omelette','## Omelette Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons milk\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil or butter\n- 1/2 cup diced bell peppers\n- 1/2 cup diced onions\n- 1/2 cup sliced mushrooms\n- 1/2 cup diced cooked chicken breast\n- 1/4 cup grated cheddar cheese\n- Fresh parsley for garnish','## Preparation\n- In a mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, and pepper until well combined.\n- Heat olive oil or butter in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n\n## Cooking the Omelette\n- Add the diced bell peppers, onions, and mushrooms to the skillet. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are soft.\n- Stir in the diced chicken breast and cook for another 2 minutes until heated through.\n- Pour the egg mixture over the vegetable and chicken mixture in the skillet.\n- Cook the eggs without stirring until they begin to set around the edges.\n- Gently lift the edges of the omelette with a spatula, allowing the uncooked eggs to flow to the edges of the pan.\n- When the eggs are mostly set, sprinkle the cheddar cheese over one half of the omelette.\n- Carefully fold the omelette in half and cook for another minute, allowing the cheese to melt.\n- Slide the omelette onto a plate and garnish with fresh parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('179','Chorizo Stuffed Avocados','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 ripe avocados\n- 4 oz chorizo, crumbled\n- 1/2 cup pepper jack cheese, shredded\n- 1 jalapeño, finely chopped\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Lime wedges','## Preparing the Ingredients\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the avocados in half and remove the pits. Scoop out a small portion of the flesh to create a larger cavity. Reserve the scooped avocado flesh in a bowl.\n- Slice the jalapeño and cilantro finely.\n\n## Cooking the Chorizo\n- In a skillet over medium heat, cook the crumbled chorizo until fully cooked and slightly crispy. This should take about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add the jalapeños to the skillet and sauté for an additional 2 minutes until softened.\n- Remove the skillet from heat and let it cool slightly.\n\n## Assembling the Avocados\n- Mix the cooked chorizo and jalapeños with the reserved avocado flesh. Stir in half of the shredded pepper jack cheese.\n- Season the mixture with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Fill each avocado half with the chorizo mixture.\n\n## Baking\n- Place the stuffed avocados on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Sprinkle the remaining pepper jack cheese on top of the stuffed avocados.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('180','High Protein Mushroom Gruyère Quiche','## Crust\n- 1 1/4 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 cup cold unsalted butter, cubed\n- 3-4 tablespoons ice water\n\n## Filling\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 cups wild mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 cup caramelized onions\n- 1 teaspoon fresh thyme leaves, chopped\n- 3/4 cup grated Gruyère cheese\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 cup milk (or half-and-half for creaminess)\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Crust\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a bowl, mix flour and salt. Add butter and blend with a pastry cutter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\n- Add ice water gradually, mixing until the dough comes together. Form into a disc, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Roll out the dough on a floured surface, fit it into a 9-inch pie pan, and trim any overhang. Prick the base with a fork.\n\n## Pre-bake the Crust\n- Place parchment paper over the crust and fill with pie weights or beans.\n- Bake for 15 minutes, then remove weights and parchment. Bake for another 5 minutes until lightly golden.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add mushrooms, cooking until golden brown and moisture is evaporated, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in caramelized onions and thyme. Season with salt and pepper, then remove from heat.\n\n## Assemble the Quiche\n- Spread the mushroom and onion mixture evenly over the pre-baked crust.\n- Sprinkle Gruyère cheese on top.\n- In a bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper. Pour over filling in crust.\n\n## Bake the Quiche\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 35-40 minutes until the filling is set and the top is golden brown.\n- Let cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('181','Spinach and Cheese Stuffed Chicken Breast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup crumbled goat cheese\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika','## Preparation\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Butterfly each chicken breast by cutting it horizontally, being careful not to cut all the way through.\n- Season the inside of the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika.\n\n## Filling Preparation\n- In a bowl, mix together mozzarella, Parmesan, goat cheese, and chopped spinach until well combined.\n\n## Stuffing the Chicken\n- Divide the cheese and spinach mixture into four portions.\n- Stuff each chicken breast with one portion of the cheese mixture and secure the edges with toothpicks.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium heat.\n- Sear the stuffed chicken breasts for 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown.\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).\n\n## Serving\n- Remove chicken from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before serving.\n- Carefully remove toothpicks, slice and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('182','Avocado, Sun-Dried Tomato, and Feta Salad with Grilled Chicken','## Salad\n- 1 ripe avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes, chopped\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 cups fresh arugula\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n\n## Grilled Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Grilled Chicken\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush the chicken breasts with olive oil and season with garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Grill the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\n- Remove from the grill and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Prepare the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine diced avocado, sun-dried tomatoes, crumbled feta, arugula, and sliced red onion.\n- Toss gently to combine.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, balsamic vinegar, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper until emulsified.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- Drizzle the dressing over the salad and toss gently to coat all ingredients evenly.\n- Top the salad with sliced grilled chicken.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('183','Smoked Salmon and Dill Cream Cheese Spread','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz cream cheese, softened\n- 4 oz smoked salmon, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons fresh dill, chopped\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely diced\n- 2 teaspoons lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- Whole grain bread or crackers\n- Capers (optional)\n- Sliced cucumber (optional)','## Preparation\n- In a medium bowl, combine the softened cream cheese, smoked salmon, fresh dill, red onion, and lemon juice.\n- Mix everything together until well combined, making sure the ingredients are evenly distributed.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste, and adjust the lemon juice as desired.\n\n## Serving\n- Spread the mixture on whole grain bread or crackers.\n- Top with capers or sliced cucumber if desired for added flavor and texture.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('184','Roasted Sweet Potato and Black Bean Bowls with Chipotle Aioli','## For the Bowls\n- 2 large sweet potatoes, peeled and diced\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, rinsed and drained\n- 2 green onions, chopped\n\n## For the Chipotle Aioli\n- 1/2 cup mayonnaise (or Greek yogurt for a healthier option)\n- 1-2 chipotles in adobo sauce, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lime juice\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- Salt to taste','## Roast the Sweet Potatoes\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a bowl, toss the diced sweet potatoes with olive oil, paprika, salt, and pepper until well-coated.\n- Spread the sweet potatoes on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Roast for 25-30 minutes, or until tender and slightly browned, stirring halfway through.\n\n## Prepare the Chipotle Aioli\n- In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise (or Greek yogurt), minced chipotles, lime juice, minced garlic, and salt.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well incorporated and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Bowls\n- Divide the roasted sweet potatoes and black beans evenly among 4 bowls.\n- Top each bowl with a drizzle of the chipotle aioli.\n- Garnish with chopped green onions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('185','Garlic Spinach and Asiago Chicken','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 6 cloves garlic, roasted\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, washed and dried\n- 1/2 cup grated Asiago cheese\n- 1/4 teaspoon red chili flakes\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Place the chicken breasts on a cutting board and pat dry with paper towels.\n- Season both sides of the chicken breasts with salt and pepper.\n\n## Roasting Garlic\n- Place the garlic cloves in a small oven-safe dish.\n- Drizzle with a little olive oil and cover with foil.\n- Roast in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes or until soft.\n\n## Chicken Preparation\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken breasts and sear for 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Spinach and Asiago Mixture\n- In the same skillet, add the roasted garlic and mash into a paste using the back of a spoon.\n- Add the fresh spinach and cook until wilted, about 2 minutes.\n- Stir in the red chili flakes and half of the Asiago cheese.\n\n## Combining and Baking\n- Return the chicken to the skillet, spooning the spinach mixture over each piece.\n- Sprinkle the remaining Asiago cheese on top.\n- Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake for 15-20 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and the cheese is melted and bubbly.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove the skillet from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes.\n- Serve the chicken hot, garnished with chopped parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('186','Maple Glazed Chicken with Bacon, Brie, and Apple','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 8 slices of bacon\n- 4 slices of brie cheese\n- 1 large apple, thinly sliced (such as Granny Smith or Honeycrisp)\n\n## Maple Glaze\n- 1/4 cup pure maple syrup\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the maple syrup, Dijon mustard, soy sauce, apple cider vinegar, and garlic powder to make the glaze. Set aside.\n\n## Cook the Bacon\n- In a skillet over medium heat, cook the bacon until crispy. Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n## Prepare the Chicken\n- Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper on both sides.\n- In the same skillet with bacon drippings, sear the chicken breasts on each side for about 3-4 minutes until golden brown.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Place the seared chicken breasts in a baking dish.\n- Top each chicken breast with 2 slices of bacon, a slice of brie cheese, and several apple slices.\n- Drizzle the maple glaze evenly over each piece.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and the cheese is melted.\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.\n- Enjoy your Maple Glazed Chicken with Bacon, Brie, and Apple with a side of your choice, such as a salad or steamed vegetables.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('187','Zucchini Noodles with Basil Pesto, Cherry Tomatoes, and Goat Cheese','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium zucchinis, spiralized into noodles\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup goat cheese, crumbled\n\n## Basil Pesto\n- 2 cups fresh basil leaves\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Zucchini Noodles\n- Spiralize the zucchinis to make zucchini noodles. You can use a spiralizer or a julienne peeler.\n- Lightly salt the zucchini noodles and let them sit for about 10 minutes to release excess moisture. Blot with a paper towel to dry.\n\n## Make the Basil Pesto\n- In a food processor, combine the basil leaves, Parmesan cheese, pine nuts, and garlic.\n- Pulse until the mixture is finely chopped.\n- With the processor running, slowly pour in the olive oil until the mixture is smooth and creamy.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Cook the Dish\n- In a large pan, heat a tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the zucchini noodles and sauté for 2-3 minutes until just tender.\n- Add the cherry tomatoes to the pan and cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and mix in the basil pesto, ensuring the noodles are well coated.\n\n## Assemble and Serve\n- Transfer the zucchini noodles to serving plates.\n- Sprinkle with crumbled goat cheese.\n- Serve immediately, garnished with extra basil leaves if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('188','Bacon, Fried Egg, Toasted Bagel, and Cream Cheese Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of turkey bacon (for a leaner option)\n- 2 large eggs\n- 2 whole wheat bagels\n- 4 tablespoons reduced-fat cream cheese\n\n## Optional Add-ons\n- 1 ripe avocado, sliced\n- Handful of spinach leaves\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon olive oil','## Preparations\n- Preheat a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Slice the bagels in half and set aside.\n- If using, slice the avocado and rinse the spinach leaves.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Cook the turkey bacon in the skillet until crisp, about 4-5 minutes per side. Remove and set aside on a paper towel to drain excess fat.\n- In the same skillet, add 1 teaspoon of olive oil. Crack the eggs into the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook to your preferred doneness (sunny-side-up or over-easy), about 3-4 minutes.\n- While the eggs are cooking, toast the bagels to your liking.\n- Spread 1 tablespoon of cream cheese on each half of the toasted bagels.\n- Place the cooked bacon slices on the bottom halves of each bagel.\n- Place the fried eggs on top of the bacon, then add spinach leaves and avocado slices if desired.\n- Top with the other half of the bagel to make a sandwich.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve immediately while warm.\n- Optional: Serve with fresh fruit on the side for a balanced meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('189','Protein-Packed Breakfast Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 12 eggs\n- 1 cup (250g) high-protein Greek yogurt or blended cottage cheese\n- Pinch of salt & pepper\n- Chives, to taste\n- 1 bell pepper or banana pepper, chopped\n- Handful of spinach, chopped\n\n## Fillings\n- 3.5 oz. (100g) lactose-free sliced cheese\n- 3.5 oz. (100g) deli turkey\n- Bread of choice (e.g., oat bread made entirely of oats)','## Prepare the Egg Mixture\n- Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, Greek yogurt or cottage cheese, salt, pepper, and chives until well combined.\n\n## Bake the Egg Base\n- Line a baking dish with parchment paper and pour in the egg mixture.\n- Sprinkle the chopped bell pepper and spinach evenly over the top.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes or until the egg mixture is set.\n- Remove from the oven and let it cool slightly.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwiches\n- Once cooled, cut the baked egg into pieces that match the size of your bread slices.\n- Place a slice of turkey and a piece of the egg bake on one slice of bread, then top with a slice of cheese and another slice of bread.\n\n## Storage and Serving\n- Store the sandwiches in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 3-4 days, or freeze for longer storage.\n- To serve, microwave the sandwiches in the morning until the cheese melts, and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('190','High-Protein Blueberry Banana Smoothie Bowl','## Base Ingredients\n- 250ml whole milk\n- 100g 5% Greek yoghurt\n- 30g rolled oats\n- 1 medium banana\n- 100g frozen blueberries\n- 30g peanut butter\n- 15g honey\n- 30g vanilla protein powder\n\n## Toppings\n- 1 tbsp chia seeds','## Prepare the Base\n- In a blender, combine the whole milk, Greek yogurt, and rolled oats, and let the oats soak for a few minutes to soften.\n- Add the banana, frozen blueberries, peanut butter, honey, and vanilla protein powder to the blender.\n- Blend the mixture on high speed until it is smooth and creamy.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Pour the smoothie into a bowl.\n- Sprinkle the chia seeds on top as a garnish.\n- Optional: Add sliced bananas, fresh blueberries, or granola on top for added texture and flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('191','Grilled Chicken Ranch Wrap','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 2 cups romaine lettuce, chopped\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/3 cup ranch dressing\n- 4 large flour tortillas\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Sliced avocado\n- Diced tomatoes','## Preparation\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- In a small bowl, mix together the olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika.\n- Brush the chicken breasts with the olive oil mixture.\n\n## Grilling the Chicken\n- Place the chicken on the grill and cook for 6-7 minutes on each side or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\n- Remove the chicken from the grill and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing into thin strips.\n\n## Assembling the Wraps\n- Warm the flour tortillas on a skillet or in the microwave for a few seconds until pliable.\n- Layer the chopped romaine, sliced grilled chicken, shredded cheddar, and a drizzle of ranch dressing on each tortilla.\n- Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll tightly from the bottom up to form a wrap.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve immediately with optional garnishes such as fresh parsley, avocado slices, or diced tomatoes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('192','Spicy Grilled Chicken Wrap with Pepper Jack and Buffalo Sauce','## For the Chicken Marinade\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Wrap\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas\n- 4 slices pepper jack cheese\n- 1/4 cup buffalo sauce\n- 4 leaves romaine or butter lettuce\n- 1/2 cup pickled red onions\n- 1 fresh jalapeño, thinly sliced','## Chicken Preparation\n- In a bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the chicken breasts to the marinade, ensuring they are well-coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for more flavor.\n\n## Grilling the Chicken\n- Preheat your grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the chicken from the marinade and grill for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and a thermometer reads 165°F (74°C).\n- Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes before slicing into thin strips.\n\n## Assembling the Wraps\n- Warm the tortillas in a skillet for 10-15 seconds on each side until pliable.\n- Place a slice of pepper jack cheese in the center of each tortilla.\n- Layer the sliced grilled chicken over the cheese.\n- Drizzle with buffalo sauce.\n- Add a leaf of lettuce, pickled onions, and jalapeño slices.\n- Roll up the tortillas tightly, folding in the sides to secure the filling.\n\n## Serving\n- Cut the wraps in half and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('193','Herbed Chicken and Hummus Wrap','## For the Herbed Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Wrap\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas or wraps\n- 1 cup hummus\n- 1 cucumber, thinly sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 cup fresh spinach leaves\n- 1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese','## Prepare the Herbed Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper.\n- Place chicken breasts in the mixture, ensuring they are well coated. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Preheat a grill pan or skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the chicken for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked. The internal temperature should be 165°F (75°C).\n- Remove the chicken from the heat, let it rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Spread 1/4 cup of hummus on each tortilla.\n- Layer the sliced chicken, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, spinach, and feta cheese on top of the hummus.\n- Roll the tortilla tightly into a wrap.\n- Secure with a toothpick if necessary and slice in half to serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('194','Crispy Chicken Bacon Cheddar Wrap with BBQ Ranch','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 4 slices of bacon\n- 4 large tomato basil wraps\n- 1 cup cheddar cheese, shredded\n- 1 cup lettuce, shredded\n- 2 tomatoes, sliced\n\n## Coating for Chicken\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## BBQ Ranch Sauce\n- 1/2 cup ranch dressing\n- 1/4 cup BBQ sauce\n\n## For Frying\n- Vegetable oil','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Slice the chicken breasts into strips.\n- In a shallow dish, mix the flour, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Coat the chicken strips with the flour mixture, ensuring they are evenly covered.\n\n## Cook the Chicken and Bacon\n- In a large skillet, heat vegetable oil over medium heat.\n- Fry the coated chicken strips until golden brown and cooked through, about 4-5 minutes per side. Remove and drain on paper towels.\n- In the same skillet, cook bacon until crispy. Drain on paper towels.\n\n## Make the BBQ Ranch Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix together the ranch dressing and BBQ sauce until well combined.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Lay a tomato basil wrap on a flat surface.\n- Spread a spoonful of BBQ ranch sauce over the wrap.\n- Place a few chicken strips in the center of the wrap.\n- Sprinkle cheddar cheese over the chicken.\n- Add crispy bacon, shredded lettuce, and tomato slices.\n- Drizzle more BBQ ranch sauce if desired.\n\n## Roll the Wraps\n- Fold in the sides of the wrap and then roll it tightly from the bottom to the top.\n- Repeat with the remaining wraps and ingredients.\n\n## Serve\n- Slice the wraps in half, if desired, and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('195','Chipotle Chicken Wrap with Corn Salsa and Lime Crema','## Chipotle Chicken\n- 1 lb chicken breasts, diced\n- 1 tbsp chipotle powder\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Corn Salsa\n- 1 cup corn kernels (fresh or frozen)\n- 1/2 red onion, finely diced\n- 1/2 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Lime Crema\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 1 tsp lime zest\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Other Ingredients\n- 1 can black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 4 spinach tortillas','## Chipotle Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix diced chicken with chipotle powder, garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and cook the chicken for 7-8 minutes until fully cooked and slightly charred.\n\n## Corn Salsa\n- In a bowl, combine corn, red onion, red bell pepper, cilantro, lime juice, and salt.\n- Mix well and set aside to allow flavors to meld.\n\n## Lime Crema\n- In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lime juice, lime zest, and salt.\n- Set aside for the flavors to develop.\n\n## Assembly\n- Warm the spinach tortillas on a dry skillet for about 30 seconds on each side.\n- Spread a tablespoon of lime crema on each tortilla.\n- Layer the cooked chipotle chicken, corn salsa, black beans, and sliced avocado on each tortilla.\n- Carefully roll each tortilla into a wrap, folding in the sides as you go.\n- Serve immediately, with additional lime crema on the side if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('196','Jerk Chicken Wrap with Mango Salsa and Cilantro-Lime Yogurt','## For the Jerk Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons jerk seasoning\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## For the Mango Salsa\n- 1 ripe mango, diced\n- 1/2 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 small red onion, finely chopped\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and finely chopped\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- Salt to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh chopped cilantro\n\n## For the Cilantro-Lime Yogurt\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh cilantro\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Wrap\n- 4 coconut wraps\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce','## Prepare the Jerk Chicken\n- Rub the chicken breasts with jerk seasoning and olive oil.\n- Preheat the grill or a grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Grill the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and juices run clear.\n- Remove from the grill and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing it thinly.\n\n## Make the Mango Salsa\n- In a bowl, combine the diced mango, red bell pepper, red onion, jalapeño, lime juice, salt, and cilantro.\n- Mix well and taste for seasoning, adding more salt or lime as needed.\n\n## Prepare the Cilantro-Lime Yogurt\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, lime juice, cilantro, salt, and pepper until smooth.\n- Adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Spread a tablespoon of cilantro-lime yogurt onto each coconut wrap.\n- Layer with shredded lettuce, sliced jerk chicken, and mango salsa.\n- Fold the sides of the wrap inward, then roll it up tightly from the bottom.\n- Secure with a toothpick if needed.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('197','High Protein Chicken & Cheddar Breakfast Wrap','## For the Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## For the Scrambled Eggs\n- 4 large eggs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon butter\n\n## For the Sriracha Mayo\n- 1/4 cup mayonnaise\n- 1 tablespoon Sriracha sauce\n\n## For the Wrap\n- 4 flour tortillas (large)\n- 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 2 cups hash browns\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil for frying\n- Chopped fresh cilantro (optional)','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat, add the chicken, and cook for 6-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.\n- Remove from the skillet, let it rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n## Prepare the Hash Browns\n- In the same skillet, add olive oil and cook the hash browns according to package instructions until golden brown and crispy.\n- Remove from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Scrambled Eggs\n- In a bowl, whisk the eggs with salt and pepper.\n- Melt butter in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the eggs, stirring gently until cooked through but still soft.\n\n## Make the Sriracha Mayo\n- In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise and Sriracha sauce until well combined.\n\n## Assemble the Wrap\n- Lay a tortilla flat and spread a tablespoon of Sriracha mayo over it.\n- Place slices of chicken in the center, add a portion of scrambled eggs on top.\n- Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and add a spoonful of hash browns.\n- Sprinkle with fresh cilantro for extra flavor (optional).\n- Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll up tightly.\n\n## Grill the Wraps\n- Heat a clean skillet over medium heat.\n- Place the wrap seam side down on the skillet.\n- Grill for 2-3 minutes on each side until the tortillas are crispy and golden brown.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('198','Chicken Caesar Wrap','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 4 whole wheat tortilla wraps\n- 2 cups romaine lettuce, chopped\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n\n## Caesar Dressing\n- 1/3 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Croutons\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat the grill or a grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Rub the chicken breasts with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika.\n- Grill the chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side, until cooked through and juices run clear.\n- Let the chicken rest for a few minutes, then slice into strips.\n\n## Make the Caesar Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, minced garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Lay out a tortilla wrap on a flat surface.\n- Spread a tablespoon of Caesar dressing over the wrap.\n- Layer slices of grilled chicken, chopped romaine lettuce, and Parmesan cheese.\n- Add optional toppings like croutons or cherry tomatoes, if desired.\n- Fold in the sides of the wrap and roll it up tightly.\n- Repeat with the remaining wraps.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('199','High-Protein Chicken BLT Sandwich','## Sandwich Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 8 slices whole grain bread\n- 8 slices turkey bacon\n- 8 leaves of romaine lettuce\n- 2 large tomatoes, sliced\n- 4 slices reduced-fat cheddar cheese\n\n## Avocado Spread\n- 2 ripe avocados\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Rub the chicken breasts with olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n- Place chicken on a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\n- Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n## Cook the Turkey Bacon\n- In a skillet, cook the turkey bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 8 minutes.\n- Set aside on paper towels to drain excess oil.\n\n## Make the Avocado Spread\n- In a bowl, mash the avocados.\n- Add lemon juice, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.\n- Mix until smooth and creamy.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Toast the whole grain bread slices.\n- Spread the avocado mixture on one side of each slice.\n- Layer each sandwich with 1 slice of cheddar cheese, 1 breast of sliced chicken, 2 slices of turkey bacon, 2 romaine leaves, and several slices of tomato.\n- Top with another slice of bread to complete the sandwich.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('200','Buffalo Chicken Sourdough Melt','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of sourdough bread\n- 1/2 cup blue cheese, crumbled\n- 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1 cup shredded buffalo chicken\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt ranch dressing\n\n## Optional Add-ons\n- Butter or olive oil, for toasting\n- Fresh arugula or spinach, for serving','## Preparation\n- Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat.\n- If using butter or oil, lightly spread on one side of each slice of sourdough bread.\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the shredded buffalo chicken with Greek yogurt ranch dressing. Mix well to ensure the chicken is evenly coated.\n\n## Assembling the Sandwich\n- Place two slices of sourdough bread, buttered side down, on a clean surface.\n- Evenly distribute the shredded buffalo chicken mixture on top of each slice of bread.\n- Sprinkle blue cheese and mozzarella evenly over the chicken mixture.\n- Top with the remaining slices of sourdough bread, buttered side up.\n\n## Cooking\n- Carefully place the assembled sandwiches on the preheated skillet or griddle.\n- Cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until the bread is golden brown and crispy, and the cheese has melted.\n- Press down gently with a spatula to ensure even cooking.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove the sandwiches from the skillet and let them cool slightly before slicing in half.\n- Serve with fresh arugula or spinach on the side, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('201','Spicy Tempeh Grilled Cheese Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices multigrain bread\n- 2 slices sharp cheddar cheese\n- 2 slices Gouda cheese\n- 4-6 strips crispy tempeh\n- 2 tablespoons spicy peanut butter\n- 2 tablespoons chili jam\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro leaves','## Preparation\n- Preheat a skillet or grill pan over medium heat.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwiches\n- Spread 1 tablespoon of spicy peanut butter on one side of each bread slice.\n- Spread 1 tablespoon of chili jam on the other side of each bread slice.\n- Place a slice of sharp cheddar and a slice of Gouda on two of the slices.\n- Arrange 2-3 strips of crispy tempeh over the cheese on each sandwich.\n- Top with the remaining bread slices, ensuring the peanut butter side faces inward.\n\n## Cooking\n- Lightly grease the skillet with cooking spray or a little butter.\n- Place the sandwiches in the skillet, pressing down gently with a spatula.\n- Cook for about 3–4 minutes on each side, until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is melted.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the skillet and cut each sandwich in half.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves, if desired.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('202','Steak and Cheese Ciabatta Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 Ciabatta rolls\n- 8 slices Provolone cheese\n- 8 slices Pepper Jack cheese\n- 1 lb sliced grilled steak\n- 2 large onions, thinly sliced\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n\n## Horseradish Cream\n- 1/2 cup sour cream\n- 2 tbsp prepared horseradish\n- 1 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Caramelize Onions\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add sliced onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until they become golden brown and caramelized, about 20-25 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Prepare Horseradish Cream\n- In a bowl, mix sour cream, prepared horseradish, Dijon mustard, and lemon juice.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Refrigerate until ready to use.\n\n## Assemble Sandwiches\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Slice Ciabatta rolls in half horizontally.\n- Spread horseradish cream on both halves of each roll.\n- Layer slices of grilled steak, caramelized onions, Provolone, and Pepper Jack cheese on the bottom half of each roll.\n- Top with the other half of the roll.\n\n## Cook Sandwiches\n- Wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil and place on a baking sheet.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the sandwiches are heated through.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove sandwiches from the oven and carefully unwrap from the foil.\n- Serve warm and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('203','High-Protein Edamame Avocado Toast','## For the Toast\n- 4 slices sprouted grain bread\n- 1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1/2 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese\n- 1 cup smashed edamame (shelled and cooked)\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n\n## For the Pesto Spread\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup walnuts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Pesto Spread\n- In a food processor, combine basil leaves, Parmesan cheese, walnuts, olive oil, and minced garlic.\n- Blend until smooth, adding salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Toast\n- Toast the slices of sprouted grain bread until golden brown.\n- Spread a generous layer of the pesto on each slice of toast.\n- In a bowl, mix the smashed edamame with the crumbled feta cheese.\n- Top the toast evenly with the edamame and feta mixture.\n- Sprinkle the shredded Monterey Jack cheese over the edamame.\n- Place the toast under a broiler until the cheese is melted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Top with avocado slices before serving.\n- Optionally, drizzle a small amount of olive oil on top for added flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('204','High-Protein Open-Faced Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of rye bread\n- 4 slices of Havarti cheese\n- 4 slices of cheddar cheese\n- 4 hard-boiled eggs, sliced\n- 8 slices of crispy turkey bacon\n\n## Condiments and Seasoning\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparation\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Place the rye bread slices on a baking sheet.\n- Spread 1/2 tablespoon of Dijon mustard on each slice of bread.\n\n## Assembling the Sandwich\n- Layer one slice of Havarti cheese and one slice of cheddar cheese on each piece of bread.\n- Arrange the hard-boiled egg slices evenly over the cheese on each slice of bread.\n- Top each with 2 slices of crispy turkey bacon.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Baking\n- Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven.\n- Bake for 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from oven and let cool for a minute.\n- Serve warm and enjoy your high-protein open-faced sandwich.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('205','Tandoori Chicken and Paneer Naan Pizza','## Ingredients\n- 2 pieces naan bread\n- 1 cup shredded tandoori chicken\n- 1/2 cup paneer, crumbled\n- 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup mint chutney (plus extra for serving)\n- Fresh cilantro leaves for garnish (optional)','## Instructions\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Place the naan breads on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Spread a thin layer of mint chutney over each naan.\n- Evenly distribute the shredded tandoori chicken over the naan.\n- Sprinkle the crumbled paneer and shredded mozzarella cheese on top.\n- Add the thinly sliced red onions evenly over the pizzas.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly and the edges of the naan are golden brown.\n- Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves, if desired, and serve with extra mint chutney on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('206','High-Protein Breakfast Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 whole grain English muffin, split\n- 1 slice American cheese\n- 1 slice Swiss cheese\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 slices smoked ham\n\n## Sriracha Mayo\n- 2 tablespoons mayonnaise\n- 1 teaspoon sriracha sauce','## Preparing the Sriracha Mayo\n- In a small bowl, mix 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise with 1 teaspoon of sriracha sauce until well combined.\n\n## Cooking the Egg and Ham\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Crack the egg into the skillet and fry to your desired doneness (about 3-4 minutes for a slightly runny yolk).\n- Remove the egg and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, lightly brown the ham slices for about 1-2 minutes per side.\n\n## Assembling the Sandwich\n- Toast the English muffin halves until golden brown.\n- Spread the sriracha mayo evenly over the inside of each half of the muffin.\n- On the bottom half of the muffin, place the slice of American cheese, followed by smoked ham, fried egg, and Swiss cheese.\n- Top with the other half of the muffin to form a sandwich.\n\n## Melting the Cheese and Serving\n- Place the assembled sandwich back in the skillet and cover with a lid for about 1-2 minutes on low heat to melt the cheese.\n- Serve immediately while hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('207','Spicy Black Bean Grilled Cheese','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices whole wheat bread\n- 1/2 cup pepper jack cheese, shredded\n- 1/2 cup cheddar cheese, shredded\n- 1 cup smashed black beans\n- 1/4 cup pickled jalapeños, sliced\n\n## Chipotle Yogurt\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon chipotle in adobo sauce, minced\n- 1 teaspoon lime juice\n- Salt to taste','## Prepare the Chipotle Yogurt\n- In a small bowl, combine Greek yogurt, chipotle in adobo sauce, lime juice, and a pinch of salt. Mix well until smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Lay out two slices of whole wheat bread.\n- Spread a layer of smashed black beans on each slice.\n- Sprinkle shredded pepper jack and cheddar cheeses evenly over the black beans.\n- Add pickled jalapeños to each slice.\n- Spread a thin layer of chipotle yogurt on the other two slices of bread, then place on top to assemble the sandwiches.\n\n## Cook the Sandwich\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Place sandwiches in the skillet and press gently with a spatula.\n- Cook for 3-4 minutes on each side or until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is melted.\n- Remove sandwiches from skillet and allow to cool for a minute before slicing.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve warm, with extra chipotle yogurt on the side for dipping, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('208','Grilled Portobello and Cheese Sandwich with Miso Tahini Spread','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices country bread\n- 2 slices fontina cheese\n- 2 slices muenster cheese\n- 2 large portobello mushrooms, stemmed and gills removed\n- 1 cup fresh arugula\n\n## Miso Tahini Spread\n- 2 tablespoons white miso paste\n- 2 tablespoons tahini\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon water\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Miso Tahini Spread\n- In a small bowl, combine white miso paste, tahini, lemon juice, water, and honey.\n- Mix until smooth and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Prepare the Portobello Mushrooms\n- Preheat a grill pan over medium heat.\n- Brush the portobello mushrooms with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Grill the mushrooms for about 5 minutes on each side until tender and slightly charred.\n- Remove from heat and slice into thick strips.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Spread the miso tahini on one side of each slice of country bread.\n- On two slices of bread, layer fontina cheese, muenster cheese, grilled portobello strips, and fresh arugula.\n- Top with the remaining slices of bread, spread side down, to create two sandwiches.\n\n## Grill the Sandwich\n- Preheat a skillet over medium heat.\n- Place the sandwiches in the skillet and cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is melted.\n- Press down slightly with a spatula for even grilling.\n- Remove from heat and let cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('209','Mediterranean Lamb Flatbread','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 pita breads or flatbreads\n- 1/2 cup goat cheese, crumbled\n- 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1 cup sliced grilled lamb\n\n## Toppings\n- 1/2 cup tzatziki sauce\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomato spread','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n\n## Assembly\n- Place the pita breads on a baking sheet.\n- Spread 2 tablespoons of sun-dried tomato spread evenly over each flatbread.\n- Sprinkle goat cheese and mozzarella evenly over the flatbreads.\n- Distribute the sliced grilled lamb evenly on top.\n\n## Baking\n- Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven.\n- Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the edges of the flatbread are crispy.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly.\n- Drizzle with tzatziki sauce before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('210','Spicy Chicken and Cheese Texas Toast Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices Texas toast\n- 2 slices cheddar cheese\n- 2 slices pepper jack cheese\n- 4 crispy chicken tenders\n\n## Jalapeño Slaw\n- 1 cup shredded cabbage\n- 1 medium carrot, grated\n- 1 jalapeño, finely sliced\n- 2 tablespoons mayonnaise\n- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Honey Mustard Sauce\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard','## Prepare Jalapeño Slaw\n- In a bowl, combine shredded cabbage, grated carrot, and sliced jalapeño.\n- Add mayonnaise and apple cider vinegar.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Mix well until fully combined and set aside.\n\n## Make Honey Mustard Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix honey and Dijon mustard until smooth.\n- Set aside.\n\n## Assemble Sandwiches\n- Preheat a griddle or skillet over medium heat.\n- Place a slice of cheddar cheese on one piece of Texas toast and a slice of pepper jack on another.\n- Place two chicken tenders on each pair of cheesy toast slices.\n- Add a generous spoonful of jalapeño slaw on top of the chicken tenders.\n- Drizzle honey mustard sauce over the slaw.\n- Top with the other slice of toast.\n\n## Cook Sandwiches\n- Place sandwiches on the preheated skillet.\n- Grill each side for 3-4 minutes or until the bread is golden brown and the cheese has melted.\n- Remove from the skillet and let cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('211','Scotch Eggs','## For the eggs\n- 6 large eggs\n\n## For the meat layer\n- 500g ground sausage meat (lean)\n- 1/4 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1 tablespoon chopped parsley\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## For coating\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 beaten egg\n- 1 cup breadcrumbs (whole wheat)\n- 1/4 teaspoon paprika (optional)\n\n## For frying and serving\n- Vegetable oil (for frying)\n- Mixed greens or salad (optional, for serving)','## Prepare the eggs\n- Place 6 eggs in a saucepan and cover with water.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 6 minutes for soft-boiled, or 10 minutes for hard-boiled.\n- Immediately transfer eggs to a bowl of ice water to stop cooking.\n- Peel the eggs once they are cool enough to handle.\n\n## Prepare the sausage mix\n- In a large bowl, combine ground sausage meat, breadcrumbs, parsley, Dijon mustard, black pepper, and salt.\n- Divide the mixture into six equal parts.\n\n## Wrap the eggs\n- Flatten a portion of sausage mix in your hand and wrap it around a peeled egg, making sure to seal any gaps.\n- Repeat for all eggs.\n\n## Coat the eggs\n- Spread flour on a plate.\n- Roll each sausage-wrapped egg in the flour, shaking off excess.\n- Dip into the beaten egg, then roll in the whole wheat breadcrumbs mixed with paprika (if using).\n\n## Fry the eggs\n- Heat oil in a deep pan to 350°F (175°C).\n- Carefully lower each egg into the oil using a slotted spoon.\n- Fry for 6-8 minutes, turning occasionally, until golden and crispy.\n- Remove and drain on a paper towel.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve warm with mixed greens or a salad for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('212','Chicken Tortilla Soup','## Soup Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 green bell pepper, diced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and minced\n- 1 1/2 teaspoons ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 6 cups chicken broth\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 can (14 oz) black beans, rinsed and drained\n- 2 cups cooked, shredded chicken breast\n- 1 cup frozen corn\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Toppings\n- Tortilla strips or crushed tortilla chips\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Mexican blend)\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges','## Prepare the Soup\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add diced onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in garlic, red bell pepper, green bell pepper, and jalapeño, cooking for another 3-4 minutes.\n- Mix in cumin, chili powder, and smoked paprika, cooking for another minute until fragrant.\n- Pour in chicken broth and bring to a simmer.\n- Add diced tomatoes, black beans, shredded chicken, and corn.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Simmer for 20 minutes to combine flavors.\n\n## Serve the Soup\n- Ladle soup into bowls.\n- Top with tortilla strips, avocado slices, shredded cheese, fresh cilantro, and a squeeze of lime.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('213','Beef & Barley Soup','## Ingredients\n- 1 lb beef chuck, cut into 1/2-inch cubes\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 carrots, sliced\n- 2 stalks celery, sliced\n- 8 cups beef broth\n- 1 cup pearl barley\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped (optional)','## Instructions\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the beef cubes and brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add the onion and garlic. Sauté until the onion is translucent.\n- Add the carrots and celery, and cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Return the beef to the pot. Pour in the beef broth and bring to a boil.\n- Stir in the barley, bay leaves, thyme, and season with salt and pepper.\n- Reduce heat to low, cover, and let simmer for about 45 minutes, or until barley is tender.\n- Remove the bay leaves before serving.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('214','Turkey & White Bean Chili','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 can (15 ounces) white beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (15 ounces) diced tomatoes\n- 2 cups chicken broth\n- 1 tablespoon chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Sliced avocado\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Lime wedges\n- Greek yogurt or sour cream','## Prepare Ingredients\n- Chop the onion, mince the garlic, and dice the red bell pepper.\n\n## Cook the Turkey\n- In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the ground turkey and cook until browned, breaking it apart with a spoon.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Cook Vegetables\n- Add the chopped onion, minced garlic, and diced bell pepper to the pot.\n- Cook until the vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Add Remaining Ingredients\n- Stir in the white beans, diced tomatoes, and chicken broth.\n- Mix in the chili powder, cumin, and paprika.\n- Bring to a simmer.\n\n## Simmer the Chili\n- Reduce the heat to low and let the chili simmer for 20–25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n- Adjust seasoning with more salt and pepper if needed.\n\n## Serve\n- Ladle the chili into bowls.\n- Top with optional toppings like sliced avocado, chopped cilantro, lime wedges, or a dollop of Greek yogurt.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('215','High-Protein Lentil Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric\n- 1 cup dry green or brown lentils, rinsed and drained\n- 8 cups vegetable broth\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste\n- 2 cups chopped kale or spinach\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n- Red pepper flakes','## Preparation and Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté for about 4-5 minutes until translucent.\n- Stir in the garlic, carrots, and celery, and continue to cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Add cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, and turmeric, and sauté for an additional 1-2 minutes until the spices are fragrant.\n- Add the lentils, vegetable broth, and diced tomatoes to the pot. Stir well and bring the mixture to a boil.\n- Once boiling, reduce the heat to low, cover the pot, and let it simmer for about 25-30 minutes until the lentils are tender.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Add the chopped kale or spinach and cook for another 5 minutes until the greens are wilted.\n- Remove from heat and let the soup sit for a few minutes before serving.\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a sprinkle of red pepper flakes if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('216','Italian Wedding Soup','## Meatballs\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Soup\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 cup chopped onion\n- 1 cup chopped carrots\n- 1 cup chopped celery\n- 10 cups low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1 cup acini di pepe pasta\n- 3 cups baby spinach leaves\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Grated Parmesan cheese for serving','## Prepare the Meatballs\n- In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, Parmesan cheese, breadcrumbs, parsley, egg, garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until well combined.\n- Form into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter, and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Soup\n- In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add onion, carrots, and celery. Cook until vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Pour in the chicken broth and bring to a boil.\n- Add the meatballs to the broth and reduce heat to a simmer.\n- Cook for 7-8 minutes until meatballs are cooked through.\n- Add the acini di pepe pasta and cook until tender, about 6-8 minutes.\n- Stir in the spinach leaves and cook until just wilted, about 2 minutes.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serve\n- Ladle soup into bowls and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('217','High-Protein Chicken Pho','## Pho Broth\n- 8 cups chicken broth (low sodium)\n- 1 large onion, peeled and halved\n- 3-inch piece of ginger, sliced\n- 2 star anise pods\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 1 tablespoon coriander seeds\n- 2 tablespoons fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Chicken and Noodles\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast\n- 8 oz rice noodles\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n\n## Garnishes\n- 1 cup bean sprouts\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 1 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n- 2 green onions, sliced\n- 1 fresh chili pepper, sliced (optional)','## Prepare the Broth\n- In a large pot, add the chicken broth, onion, ginger, star anise, cinnamon stick, and coriander seeds.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 30 minutes.\n- Strain the broth to remove solids, then return the liquid to the pot.\n- Stir in fish sauce and soy sauce, and season with salt to taste.\n\n## Cook the Chicken and Noodles\n- While the broth is simmering, heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add chicken breasts and cook until browned on both sides and fully cooked, about 6-7 minutes per side.\n- Remove from heat and let the chicken rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly.\n- Cook rice noodles according to package instructions, drain and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Pho\n- Divide cooked noodles among bowls.\n- Top with sliced chicken.\n- Pour hot broth over the chicken and noodles.\n- Add bean sprouts, basil, cilantro, green onions, and chili slices as desired.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over the pho.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('218','Lamb & Chickpea Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g lamb shoulder, trimmed and cut into small cubes\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- 1 can (400g) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (400g) diced tomatoes\n- 4 cups chicken or vegetable broth\n- 1 bay leaf\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Lemon wedges\n- Fresh cilantro','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the lamb cubes and brown on all sides, approximately 5 minutes.\n- Remove lamb and set aside.\n\n## Cooking Instructions\n- In the same pot, add the onion, garlic, carrots, and celery. Sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in the cumin, coriander, cinnamon, and cayenne pepper. Cook for another minute until fragrant.\n- Return lamb to the pot and add chickpeas, diced tomatoes, broth, and bay leaf.\n- Bring to a simmer, cover, and let cook for 45-60 minutes, or until the lamb is tender.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Remove bay leaf, stir in fresh parsley before serving.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with lemon wedges and fresh cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('219','Ham & Split Pea Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound dried split peas, rinsed\n- 2 cups diced cooked ham\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 8 cups chicken or vegetable broth\n- 1 bay leaf\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Croutons\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Preparation\n- Rinse the split peas under cold water and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large pot, add a splash of oil over medium heat.\n- Add the onion, carrots, and celery, and sauté for 5-7 minutes until softened.\n- Stir in the garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\n- Add the ham, split peas, broth, bay leaf, and thyme to the pot.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and cover the pot.\n- Simmer for 45-60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until peas are tender and soup is thickened.\n- Remove the bay leaf, and season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Ladle the soup into bowls.\n- Garnish with chopped parsley, croutons, or Parmesan cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('220','Black Bean Soup with Ham','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 4 cups cooked black beans (or 2 cans, drained and rinsed)\n- 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1 cup diced cooked ham\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh cilantro\n- Sliced green onions\n- Lime wedges','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and minced garlic, sauté until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the diced red bell pepper, cumin, and smoked paprika. Cook for another 2 minutes, stirring frequently.\n\n## Cooking\n- Stir in the black beans, chicken broth, diced ham, and oregano.\n- Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat and let it simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n- Use an immersion blender to partially blend the soup, leaving some of the beans whole for texture.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Ladle the soup into bowls.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro, sliced green onions, and a wedge of lime.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('221','Tofu & Miso Soup','## Soup Base\n- 4 cups water\n- 4 tablespoons miso paste (red or white)\n\n## Tofu and Vegetables\n- 8 oz firm tofu, cubed\n- 1 cup sliced mushrooms (shiitake or cremini)\n- 1 cup chopped baby spinach\n- 1/2 cup sliced green onions\n\n## Garnish\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh cilantro (optional)','## Prepare the Soup Base\n- In a medium pot, bring 4 cups of water to a gentle simmer.\n- Place the miso paste in a small bowl. Add a ladleful of the simmering water to the bowl and whisk until smooth.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- Add the miso mixture back into the pot of simmering water, stirring well.\n- Add the cubed tofu and sliced mushrooms to the pot. Simmer for about 5 minutes until the mushrooms are tender.\n\n## Add Vegetables\n- Stir in the baby spinach and green onions. Simmer for an additional 3 minutes until the spinach is wilted.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Serve\n- Ladle the soup into bowls.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds and fresh cilantro, if using, before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('222','Shrimp & Corn Chowder','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 cups fresh or frozen corn kernels\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 ribs celery, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 4 cups chicken or vegetable broth\n- 1 cup milk (or coconut milk for a dairy-free option)\n- 2 medium potatoes, peeled and diced\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped green onions\n- Crumbled bacon\n- Grated cheese (such as cheddar or Monterey Jack)','## Preparation\n- In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add diced onion, garlic, celery, and bell pepper. Sauté until the vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the smoked paprika, corn, and potatoes to the pot. Stir to combine.\n- Pour in the broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until the potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.\n- Add the milk and shrimp to the pot. Cook until the shrimp are pink and cooked through, about 3-5 minutes.\n- Season the chowder with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Remove from heat and stir in fresh parsley.\n- Serve hot with optional garnishes of your choice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('223','High Protein Chicken Noodle Soup with Homemade Noodles','## Homemade Noodles\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 cup semolina flour\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Chicken Soup\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 carrots, sliced\n- 3 celery stalks, sliced\n- 8 cups chicken broth\n- 2 cups cooked chicken breast, shredded\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 bay leaf\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Making the Homemade Noodles\n- In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, semolina flour, and salt.\n- Make a well in the center and add eggs and olive oil.\n- Mix until a rough dough forms, then knead on a floured surface for 8-10 minutes until smooth.\n- Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let rest for 30 minutes.\n- Roll the dough out to desired thickness and cut into thin strips.\n\n## Preparing the Chicken Soup\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add onion, garlic, carrots, and celery. Cook until vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Pour in chicken broth and bring to a boil.\n- Add shredded chicken, thyme, and bay leaf. Simmer for 15 minutes.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Add homemade noodles to the soup and cook for 5-6 minutes until noodles are tender.\n- Remove bay leaf and stir in fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('224','Salmon Coconut Curry Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb salmon fillets, skinless and cut into cubes\n- 2 cups coconut milk\n- 2 cups vegetable or fish stock\n- 1 tbsp coconut oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 inch ginger, grated\n- 2 tbsp red curry paste\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 2 cups spinach or kale\n- 2 tbsp fish sauce\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh cilantro, for garnish\n- Lime wedges, for serving\n\n## Optional Side\n- Steamed jasmine rice','## Preparation\n- Cut salmon fillets into bite-sized cubes.\n- Chop the onion, mince the garlic, and grate the ginger.\n- Slice the red bell pepper.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat coconut oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the onion and sauté until translucent.\n- Stir in the garlic and ginger and sauté for another minute.\n- Add the red curry paste and cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\n- Pour in the coconut milk and vegetable or fish stock, and bring to a simmer.\n- Add the salmon cubes and cook for 5-7 minutes until opaque and cooked through.\n- Stir in the red bell pepper, spinach, fish sauce, lime juice, and salt.\n- Allow to simmer for another 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are tender.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Ladle the soup into bowls, garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side.\n- Optionally, serve with steamed jasmine rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('225','Chicken and Broccoli Stir Fry','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb (450g) boneless, skinless chicken breast, sliced thinly\n- 2 cups broccoli florets\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 cup snap peas\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon ginger, grated\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Sauce\n- 1/4 cup low-sodium soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 1 tablespoon Sriracha (optional, for heat)\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons sesame seeds\n- 2 green onions, sliced','## Preparation\n- Slice the chicken breast into thin strips.\n- Prepare the vegetables: cut broccoli into florets, slice the bell pepper, and trim the snap peas.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, honey, rice vinegar, cornstarch, chicken broth, sesame oil, and Sriracha.\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat.\n- Add sliced chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, about 5-6 minutes. Remove chicken from the pan and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil. Add minced garlic and grated ginger, stirring for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add broccoli, red bell pepper, and snap peas. Stir fry for about 5 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.\n- Return the cooked chicken to the pan.\n- Pour the sauce over the stir fry and stir well to combine. Allow the sauce to thicken slightly, cooking for another 2-3 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from heat and garnish with sesame seeds and sliced green onions.\n- Serve hot, ideally with a side of steamed brown rice or quinoa for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('226','Sriracha Egg Sandwich','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons milk\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon butter\n- 4 slices of whole-grain bread\n- 2 tablespoons mayonnaise\n- 1 tablespoon Sriracha sauce\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 4 leaves of lettuce\n- 1 medium tomato, sliced','## Prep the Ingredients\n- Crack the eggs into a bowl, add milk, salt, and pepper, and whisk until well combined.\n- Mix mayonnaise and Sriracha sauce in a small bowl.\n- Slice the avocado and tomato.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- Melt butter in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and cook, stirring gently to scramble, until the eggs are just set, about 3-4 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Lightly toast the bread slices.\n- Spread Sriracha mayo evenly on one side of each toasted bread slice.\n- Layer the avocado slices, lettuce, scrambled eggs, and tomato slices on two of the bread slices.\n- Top with the remaining bread slices, Sriracha mayo side down.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut the sandwiches in half and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('227','High-Protein Meatball Sub','## For the Meatballs\n- 1 lb lean ground beef (or a mix of beef and turkey)\n- 1/2 cup bread crumbs\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 egg\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## For the Sandwich\n- 4 whole grain sub rolls\n- 1 cup marinara sauce\n- 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Fresh basil leaves for garnish (optional)','## Making the Meatballs\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic, egg, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix gently until ingredients are just combined.\n- Shape the mixture into 16 meatballs and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes, or until fully cooked.\n\n## Assembling the Sandwich\n- While meatballs are baking, heat marinara sauce in a pan over medium heat.\n- When meatballs are done, add them to the marinara sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.\n- Preheat broiler on high.\n- Split sub rolls and brush the insides with olive oil.\n- Toast the rolls under the broiler until golden brown.\n- Place 4 meatballs inside each roll, spooning additional sauce on top.\n- Sprinkle shredded mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over the meatballs.\n- Return the assembled subs to the broiler. Broil until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 2 minutes.\n- Remove from oven and garnish with fresh basil leaves if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('228','Teriyaki Chicken Bowls','## Chicken and Marinade\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 1/4 cup low-sodium soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup mirin\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger\n\n## Rice\n- 1 cup uncooked brown rice\n- 2 cups water\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Vegetables\n- 1 cup broccoli florets\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 cup sugar snap peas\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Toppings\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- 2 green onions, chopped','## Marinate Chicken\n- In a bowl, whisk together soy sauce, mirin, honey, rice vinegar, sesame oil, garlic, and ginger.\n- Add chicken pieces to the bowl, mix to coat, and marinate for at least 30 minutes, preferably in the refrigerator.\n\n## Cook Rice\n- Rinse brown rice under cold water.\n- In a medium saucepan, combine the rice, water, and salt. Bring to a boil.\n- Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 45 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.\n- Fluff with a fork and set aside.\n\n## Cook Vegetables\n- In a large pan, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Add broccoli, bell pepper, and sugar snap peas.\n- Stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 5-7 minutes. Remove from pan and set aside.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- In the same pan used for vegetables, add marinated chicken over medium heat.\n- Cook until chicken is cooked through and caramelized, about 8-10 minutes.\n- Add vegetables back to the pan and toss to combine.\n\n## Assemble Bowls\n- Divide cooked rice into bowls.\n- Top with chicken and vegetable mixture.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds and chopped green onions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('229','Japanese BBQ Chicken Bowls','## For the Chicken Marinade\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken thighs\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce (low sodium)\n- 2 tablespoons mirin\n- 1 tablespoon sake\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon grated ginger\n\n## For the Bowls\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 2 cups broccoli florets\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 carrot, julienned\n- 2 green onions, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- 1 cup shredded cabbage (green or purple)\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon mirin\n- 1 teaspoon sake\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- 1/2 teaspoon sesame oil','## Prepare the Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine the soy sauce, mirin, sake, honey, garlic, and ginger.\n- Add the chicken thighs, cover, and marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to overnight in the refrigerator.\n\n## Cook the Quinoa\n- Rinse the quinoa under cold water.\n- In a saucepan, bring water to a boil and add the quinoa.\n- Reduce to a simmer, cover, and cook for 15 minutes until the water is absorbed.\n- Remove from heat and let sit, covered, for 5 minutes before fluffing with a fork.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Preheat a grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Remove chicken from marinade and grill for about 5-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked.\n- Let the chicken rest before slicing thinly.\n\n## Stir-fry the Vegetables\n- Heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add broccoli, bell pepper, and carrot, and stir-fry for about 5 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.\n\n## Assemble the Bowls\n- Divide the quinoa among four bowls.\n- Top with sliced chicken, stir-fried vegetables, shredded cabbage, and green onions.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce and Serve\n- In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, mirin, sake, honey, and sesame oil.\n- Drizzle over the prepared bowls.\n- Sprinkle with sesame seeds before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('230','Shish Tawook','## Marinade\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 5 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon ground paprika\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Chicken\n- 2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into cubes\n\n## For serving\n- Pita bread or rice\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine the Greek yogurt, olive oil, tomato paste, minced garlic, lemon juice, paprika, cumin, salt, and black pepper.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well combined.\n\n## Marinate Chicken\n- Add the chicken cubes to the marinade and toss until evenly coated.\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight for maximum flavor.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated chicken pieces onto skewers.\n- Grill the skewers for about 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and has nice grill marks.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the shish tawook hot with pita bread or rice.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('231','Kafta','## For the Kafta\n- 1 pound ground beef or lamb (or a mix of both)\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon allspice\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Olive oil for greasing\n\n## For Serving\n- Whole grain pita bread\n- Hummus or tzatziki\n- Tomato and cucumber salad','## Prepare the Kafta\n- In a large bowl, mix the ground meat, chopped onion, parsley, garlic, cumin, coriander, allspice, cinnamon, salt, and pepper until well combined.\n- Divide the mixture into 8 equal portions and shape each into an oval patty or a log.\n- If using skewers, insert each portion onto a skewer and flatten slightly.\n\n## Cook the Kafta\n- Heat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat. Lightly grease with olive oil.\n- Grill the kafta for about 4-5 minutes per side, or until fully cooked and browned on the outside.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the kafta with whole grain pita bread, a side of hummus or tzatziki, and a tomato and cucumber salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('232','Lamb Shawarma','## Marinade\n- 2 lbs lamb shoulder, thinly sliced\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tsp ground cumin\n- 2 tsp ground coriander\n- 1 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1 tsp ground allspice\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1/2 tsp cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Yogurt Sauce\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tbsp chopped fresh mint\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 4 whole wheat pita breads\n- 1 cup chopped tomatoes\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup sliced red onion\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine the minced garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, allspice, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the lamb slices to the marinade, ensuring each piece is well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.\n\n## Cook the Lamb\n- Preheat a large skillet or grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the marinated lamb slices in batches until browned and cooked through, about 4-5 minutes per batch.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Yogurt Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix together the Greek yogurt, lemon juice, minced garlic, salt, pepper, and fresh mint.\n- Refrigerate until ready to serve.\n\n## Assemble the Shawarma\n- Warm the pita breads in a dry skillet or in the oven.\n- Place a portion of the cooked lamb in the center of each pita.\n- Top with chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce, sliced red onion, and fresh parsley.\n- Drizzle with yogurt sauce.\n- Wrap and serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('233','Chicken Shawarma','## For the Chicken Marinade\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken thighs\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 tablespoon ground coriander\n- 1 tablespoon ground paprika\n- 1 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons tahini\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- 4 whole wheat pita breads\n- 1 cup chopped lettuce\n- 1/2 cup sliced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup sliced cucumbers\n- 1/4 cup sliced red onions\n- Fresh parsley, chopped (optional)','## Prepare the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, combine olive oil, minced garlic, cumin, coriander, paprika, turmeric, cinnamon, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the chicken thighs to the bowl and toss to coat well with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight for best results.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Preheat your grill or a skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the chicken thighs for 6-8 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and slightly charred.\n- Remove from heat and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing into thin strips.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, tahini, lemon juice, minced garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Shawarma\n- Warm the pita breads slightly on the grill or in a skillet.\n- Spread a generous amount of yogurt-tahini sauce over each pita.\n- Top with slices of chicken, lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, and onions.\n- Sprinkle with fresh parsley if desired.\n- Roll up the pita to enclose the fillings or serve open-faced as preferred.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('234','Baked Kibbeh','## Kibbeh Mix\n- 1 lb lean ground beef or lamb\n- 1 cup fine bulgur wheat\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground allspice\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Filling\n- 1/2 lb lean ground beef or lamb\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted\n- 1 teaspoon ground allspice\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil for brushing','## Prepare Bulgur\n- Rinse the bulgur under cold water.\n- Soak it in a bowl of water for about 15 minutes until it softens.\n- Drain well, pressing to remove excess water.\n\n## Make Kibbeh Mix\n- In a large bowl, combine soaked bulgur, 1 lb ground meat, chopped onion, cumin, allspice, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well until thoroughly combined and evenly textured.\n\n## Prepare Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add onion and sauté until soft and translucent.\n- Add 1/2 lb ground meat and cook until browned.\n- Stir in toasted pine nuts, allspice, salt, and pepper.\n- Remove from heat and allow to cool.\n\n## Assemble Kibbeh\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Lightly grease a baking dish with olive oil.\n- Divide kibbeh mix into two portions.\n- Spread one portion evenly in the baking dish to form a smooth base layer.\n- Spread the filling evenly over the base layer.\n- Cover with the remaining kibbeh mix, smoothing the top with wet hands.\n- Score the top layer into diamond shapes using a knife.\n- Brush with olive oil.\n\n## Bake Kibbeh\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 30-40 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and crispy.\n- Remove from oven and allow to cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('235','Grilled Lamb Chops','## Lamb Chops\n- 8 lamb chops, about 1 inch thick, trimmed of excess fat\n\n## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh rosemary, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh rosemary sprigs for garnish (optional)','## Preparation\n- In a bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the lamb chops in a resealable plastic bag or shallow dish and pour the marinade over them.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours, or overnight for best flavor.\n\n## Grilling\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the lamb chops from the marinade and let them come to room temperature.\n- Grill the lamb chops for about 4 minutes on each side, or until they reach an internal temperature of 145°F (63°C) for medium-rare.\n- Remove from grill and let rest for 5 minutes before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs if desired.\n- Serve with a side of grilled vegetables or a fresh salad for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('236','High-Protein Arayes','## For the Filling\n- 500g ground beef or lamb (choose lean for a healthier option)\n- 1/2 cup finely chopped parsley\n- 1/2 cup finely chopped onion\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts (optional)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon ground allspice\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## For the Arayes\n- 4 large pita breads, halved\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt','## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine ground meat, parsley, onion, pine nuts, olive oil, allspice, cumin, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well until all ingredients are evenly incorporated.\n\n## Assemble the Arayes\n- Carefully open each pita half to create a pocket.\n- Stuff each pita pocket with the meat mixture, pressing it flat to ensure even cooking.\n- Brush the outside of each filled pita with olive oil and sprinkle with a pinch of salt.\n\n## Cook the Arayes\n- Preheat a grill or skillet over medium heat.\n- Place the stuffed pita halves on the grill or skillet.\n- Cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side until the meat is cooked through and the pita is crispy and golden brown.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut each arayes into wedges and serve hot with a side of yogurt or tahini sauce for dipping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('237','High Protein Mansaf','## Main Ingredients\n- 1.5 lbs lamb, boneless and cut into 2-inch cubes\n- 2 cups plain Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup kefir\n- 1 egg\n- 4 cups chicken or lamb broth\n- 2 cups jasmine rice\n- 3 tablespoons ghee or clarified butter\n- 1/4 cup almonds, toasted\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted\n\n## Spices & Seasonings\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon allspice\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons chopped parsley','## Prepare the Yogurt Sauce\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the Greek yogurt, kefir, and egg until smooth.\n- Place the mixture in a pot over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent curdling.\n- Add a small amount of broth if the mixture is too thick and continue stirring for about 10 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Lamb\n- In a large pot, heat 1 tablespoon of ghee over medium-high heat.\n- Add lamb cubes and sear until browned on all sides.\n- Add turmeric, cinnamon, allspice, salt, and pepper to the lamb.\n- Pour in the broth, then cover and simmer on low heat for about 1.5 hours or until the lamb is tender.\n\n## Prepare the Rice\n- In a separate pot, melt 2 tablespoons of ghee over medium heat.\n- Add rice and sauté for a few minutes.\n- Pour in 3 cups of water and bring to a boil.\n- Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook for 15 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.\n\n## Assemble and Serve\n- Place a layer of rice on a large serving platter.\n- Top with the cooked lamb pieces.\n- Pour the yogurt sauce over the lamb.\n- Garnish with toasted almonds, pine nuts, and parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('238','High-Protein Chicken Makloubeh','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups basmati rice\n- 4 cups chicken broth\n- 2 lbs chicken thighs, skinless and boneless\n- 1 large eggplant, sliced into rounds\n- 2 medium potatoes, sliced into rounds\n- 1 medium cauliflower, cut into florets\n- 1 large onion, sliced\n- 3 tbsp olive oil\n\n## Spices and Seasoning\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1 tsp ground allspice\n- 1/2 tsp ground turmeric\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup slivered almonds, toasted\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped','## Prepare Vegetables\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Toss eggplant, potatoes, and cauliflower with 2 tbsp olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n- Lay vegetables on a baking tray and roast for 20-25 minutes until golden.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- In a large pot, heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add onion and sauté until soft.\n- Add chicken, cumin, cinnamon, allspice, turmeric, salt, and pepper.\n- Cook until chicken is browned on all sides.\n- Add chicken broth and bring to a simmer.\n\n## Assemble and Cook Makloubeh\n- In a large pot, layer roasted vegetables over the cooked chicken.\n- Rinse rice under cold water and spread evenly over the veggies.\n- Pour chicken broth over the rice until just covered.\n- Cover the pot tightly and cook on low heat for 30-40 minutes until rice is cooked.\n\n## Serving\n- Once cooked, let rest for 10 minutes, then invert the pot onto a large serving platter.\n- Garnish with slivered almonds and fresh parsley.\n- Serve with a side of Greek yogurt.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('239','Meat Sambousek','## Dough Ingredients\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 1/2 cup warm water\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n## Filling Ingredients\n- 1 pound ground beef or lamb\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons pine nuts (optional)\n- Cooking oil for frying','## Prepare the Dough\n- In a large bowl, combine the flour and salt.\n- Gradually add the olive oil and warm water, mixing until the dough comes together.\n- Knead the dough on a floured surface for about 5 minutes until smooth.\n- Cover with a damp cloth and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a skillet over medium heat, cook the ground beef or lamb until browned.\n- Add the chopped onion and minced garlic, cooking until the onion is soft.\n- Stir in the ground cumin, ground coriander, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.\n- Cook for another 2-3 minutes to let the spices infuse the meat.\n- If using, add the pine nuts and stir well.\n- Remove from heat and let it cool slightly.\n\n## Assemble the Sambousek\n- Divide the dough into small equal-sized balls.\n- Roll each ball into a thin circle, about 4 inches in diameter.\n- Place a heaping tablespoon of the meat filling onto one half of each circle.\n- Fold the dough over the filling, pressing the edges to seal.\n- Crimp edges with a fork for a decorative touch.\n\n## Cook the Sambousek\n- Heat cooking oil in a deep pan over medium heat.\n- Fry the sambousek in batches until golden brown on both sides, about 3-4 minutes per batch.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('240','Ful Medames','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup dried fava beans\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Toppings and Garnishes\n- 1/4 cup chopped parsley\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 1 tomato, diced\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Optional: boiled eggs for extra protein','## Prepare the Fava Beans\n- Soak the dried fava beans in water overnight or for at least 8 hours.\n- Drain and rinse the soaked beans.\n- Place the beans in a large pot, cover with water, and bring to a boil.\n- Reduce heat and simmer for about 1.5 hours or until the beans are tender.\n\n## Prepare the Ful Medames\n- Drain and slightly mash the cooked fava beans in the pot.\n- Stir in the olive oil, minced garlic, and lemon juice.\n- Season with salt to taste.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Transfer the fava bean mixture to a serving dish.\n- Top with chopped parsley, diced onion, and diced tomato.\n- Sprinkle with crumbled feta and ground cumin.\n- Drizzle a bit more olive oil if desired.\n- Optional: Add boiled eggs on top for extra protein.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('241','High-Protein Mujadara','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup brown or green lentils\n- 3/4 cup quinoa\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 large onions, thinly sliced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon cumin\n- 1 teaspoon coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Fresh chopped parsley\n- Plain Greek yogurt\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Lentils and Quinoa\n- Rinse the lentils and quinoa under cold water.\n- In a medium pot, add the lentils and cover with water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes until partially cooked. Drain and set aside.\n- In another pot, cook the quinoa according to the package instructions. Fluff and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Onions\n- While the lentils cook, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the sliced onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until they are caramelized (about 15–20 minutes).\n- In the last few minutes of cooking, stir in the minced garlic, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook for an additional 2–3 minutes until fragrant.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the partially cooked lentils to the onion mixture and cook for about 5–7 minutes, combining flavors.\n- Stir in the cooked quinoa, mixing well to combine all ingredients.\n- Adjust seasoning as needed.\n- Serve warm, garnished with fresh parsley, a dollop of Greek yogurt, and a squeeze of lemon juice, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('242','Chorizo & Egg Breakfast Burritos','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 ounces Mexican chorizo, casings removed if necessary\n- 6 large eggs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil (optional)\n- 4 large flour tortillas\n- 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Monterey Jack)\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- Salsa or hot sauce\n- Sour cream\n- Diced tomatoes\n- Chopped green onions','## Prepare the Chorizo\n- In a medium skillet over medium heat, cook the chorizo, crumbling it with a spatula, until fully cooked and browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Remove the cooked chorizo from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- In a bowl, whisk the eggs with a pinch of salt and pepper.\n- In the same skillet, reduce the heat to low and add olive oil if needed to prevent sticking.\n- Pour in the eggs and gently scramble them until just set. Be careful not to overcook.\n- Mix the cooked chorizo back into the eggs.\n\n## Assemble the Burritos\n- Warm the tortillas on a skillet or in the microwave to make them pliable.\n- Place a portion of the chorizo and egg mixture onto each tortilla.\n- Sprinkle with shredded cheese and add slices of avocado.\n- Top with fresh cilantro.\n- Roll each tortilla into a burrito by folding in the sides and then rolling from one end to the other.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately with optional toppings like salsa, sour cream, diced tomatoes, or chopped green onions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('243','Steak with Chimichurri Sauce','## Steak\n- 2 lbs ribeye or sirloin steak\n- Salt to taste\n- Pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Chimichurri Sauce\n- 1 cup fresh parsley leaves\n- 1/2 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 4 cloves garlic\n- 1/2 cup olive oil\n- 1/4 cup red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste','## Prepare the Chimichurri Sauce\n- Finely chop the parsley, cilantro, and garlic, or pulse them in a food processor until chopped.\n- In a bowl, combine the chopped herbs and garlic with olive oil, red wine vinegar, oregano, and red pepper flakes.\n- Season with salt and black pepper to taste.\n- Mix well and let the sauce sit at room temperature for at least 15 minutes to allow flavors to meld.\n\n## Cook the Steak\n- Heat the olive oil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Season the steak generously with salt and pepper on both sides.\n- Place the steak in the hot skillet and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.\n- Remove the steak from the skillet and let it rest for 5-10 minutes.\n\n## Serve\n- Slice the steak against the grain.\n- Serve the sliced steak with chimichurri sauce drizzled over the top.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('244','High-Protein Chana Salad','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup canned chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1/2 cup diced cucumber\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup diced red onion\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n\n## Dressing Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparation\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the chickpeas, cucumber, tomatoes, red onion, cilantro, and feta cheese.\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, honey, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n- Pour the dressing over the salad mixture and toss to combine thoroughly.\n- Adjust seasoning if necessary.\n- Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 hours to let the flavors meld.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('245','Coffee Protein Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup brewed coffee, chilled\n- 1 scoop chocolate or vanilla protein powder\n- 1 medium banana, frozen\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup almond milk or milk of choice\n- 1 tablespoon almond butter\n- 1 teaspoon honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Ice cubes (optional)','## Preparation Steps\n- Brew a cup of coffee and let it chill in the refrigerator.\n- In a blender, add the chilled coffee, protein powder, frozen banana, Greek yogurt, almond milk, almond butter, honey or maple syrup (if using), and vanilla extract.\n- Blend until smooth. If you prefer a thicker consistency, add a few ice cubes and blend again.\n- Taste and adjust sweetness, adding more honey or maple syrup if needed.\n- Pour into a glass and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('246','High Protein Salted Caramel Ice Cream','## Ice Cream Base\n- 2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup coconut sugar\n- 1 tablespoon vanilla extract\n\n## Salted Caramel Sauce\n- 1/2 cup coconut sugar\n- 1/4 cup water\n- 1/4 cup heavy cream\n- 1/4 teaspoon sea salt\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare the Salted Caramel Sauce\n- In a saucepan over medium heat, combine coconut sugar and water. Stir until the sugar dissolves.\n- Allow the mixture to come to a simmer. Do not stir, just swirl the pan occasionally until the caramel thickens (about 5-7 minutes).\n- Remove from heat and carefully stir in heavy cream, sea salt, and vanilla extract.\n- Let it cool completely.\n\n## Make the Ice Cream Base\n- In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the almond milk, Greek yogurt, protein powder, coconut sugar, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Pour the mixture into an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer''s instructions.\n\n## Combine and Freeze\n- Once the ice cream is partially churned and thick, slowly drizzle in the cooled salted caramel sauce.\n- Continue to churn until the ice cream reaches a soft-serve consistency.\n- Transfer the ice cream to an airtight container and freeze for at least 2-3 hours until firm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('247','Rice Paper Shrimp Rolls','## For the Shrimp Rolls\n- 12 large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 12 round rice papers\n- 1 cup shredded carrots\n- 1 cucumber, julienned\n- 1 red bell pepper, julienned\n- 1 cup fresh mint leaves\n- 1 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 1 cup cooked rice noodles (optional)\n\n## For the Dipping Sauce\n- 1/4 cup hoisin sauce\n- 2 tablespoons peanut butter\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon lime juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon sriracha sauce (optional)\n- 2 tablespoons water','## Prepare the Shrimp\n- Boil water in a saucepan and add shrimp.\n- Cook for 2-3 minutes until pink and cooked through.\n- Remove shrimp and immediately immerse in an ice bath to stop cooking.\n- Slice each shrimp in half lengthwise and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Rice Papers\n- Fill a shallow dish with warm water.\n- Dip each rice paper in the water for about 5 seconds until soft, then lay flat on a damp surface.\n\n## Assemble the Rolls\n- Place a few pieces of shrimp, some carrots, cucumber, bell pepper, mint, and cilantro in the center of each rice paper.\n- Add a small amount of rice noodles if using.\n- Fold the sides over the filling and roll tightly from the bottom to encase the filling.\n\n## Make the Dipping Sauce\n- In a bowl, whisk together hoisin sauce, peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, garlic, and sriracha.\n- Add water to achieve desired consistency.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the shrimp rolls with the dipping sauce on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('248','Creamy Salmon Pasta','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz whole wheat pasta (such as fettuccine or penne)\n- 12 oz salmon fillets, skinless\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Creamy Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon unsalted butter\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup low-fat milk\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon lemon zest\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh dill or parsley\n- Lemon wedges (optional)','## Prepare the Pasta\n- Cook pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Salmon\n- Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook salmon for 4-5 minutes on each side until fully cooked.\n- Remove from skillet and flake the salmon with a fork. Set aside.\n\n## Make the Creamy Sauce\n- In the same skillet, melt butter over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in Greek yogurt and milk, mixing until smooth.\n- Add Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, lemon zest, and red pepper flakes.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste, then cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring frequently until slightly thickened.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the cooked pasta and flaked salmon to the sauce.\n- Toss gently to combine and heat through.\n- Serve immediately, garnished with chopped dill or parsley and lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('249','High-Protein Papaya Oat Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons rolled oats\n- 1 cup papaya, diced\n- 1/2 cup almond milk\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon powder\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 2 almonds, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1 scoop protein powder (vanilla or unflavored) for additional protein\n- A few ice cubes for a chilled smoothie','## Preparation Instructions\n- 1. Place the rolled oats in a blender and pulse until they become a fine powder.\n- 2. Add the diced papaya, almond milk, cinnamon powder, honey, and chopped almonds to the blender.\n- 3. For extra protein, add a scoop of protein powder if desired.\n- 4. Blend until smooth and creamy. Adjust the consistency by adding more almond milk if needed.\n- 5. Taste and adjust sweetness with more honey, if required.\n- 6. Pour into a glass and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('250','Apple Oatmeal Power Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 apple, cored and diced\n- 3 tablespoons rolled oats\n- 1 tablespoon flax seeds\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 2 dates, pitted and chopped\n- 1 tablespoon cacao nibs\n\n## Optional\n- Honey or maple syrup, to taste\n- Almond milk or yogurt, as needed','## Preparation\n- In a small bowl, combine the rolled oats, flax seeds, and chia seeds.\n- Add 1/2 cup of hot water (or as needed) to the mixture and stir well. Let it sit for 5 minutes to allow the oats and seeds to absorb the liquid.\n- While the oats are soaking, dice the apple and chop the dates.\n- Once the oats have softened, add the diced apple and chopped dates to the bowl.\n- Sprinkle with cacao nibs and mix everything together gently.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the oatmeal in a bowl.\n- If desired, drizzle with a little honey or maple syrup for sweetness.\n- Add a splash of almond milk or a dollop of yogurt for extra creaminess, if preferred.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('251','Tropical Protein Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 3 Tbsp rolled oats\n- 1 cup pineapple, diced\n- 1 ripe banana\n- 1/4 inch ginger, peeled and grated\n- 2-3 mint leaves\n- 1/2 cup low-fat yogurt\n- 1 scoop protein powder (optional)\n- 1/2 cup almond milk or water\n- Ice cubes (optional)','## Preparation\n- Add the rolled oats to a blender and pulse until they form a fine powder.\n- Add the pineapple, banana, ginger, and mint leaves to the blender.\n- Pour in the low-fat yogurt and almond milk or water.\n- If using, add a scoop of your favorite protein powder for an extra protein boost.\n- Blend all the ingredients until smooth. Add ice cubes if desired for a colder smoothie.\n- Taste and adjust sweetness by adding a little honey or maple syrup if needed.\n\n## Serving\n- Pour the smoothie into a large glass.\n- Garnish with a few mint leaves or a slice of pineapple if desired.\n- Serve immediately for the best flavor and texture.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('252','High Protein Avocado Breakfast Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 avocado, peeled and pitted\n- 3 Tbsp rolled oats\n- 20 almonds\n- 1 Tbsp flax seeds\n- 1 Tbsp chia seeds\n- 2 Medjool dates, pitted and chopped\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh berries (e.g., blueberries, strawberries)\n- Honey or agave syrup for sweetness\n- A pinch of cinnamon','## Preparation\n- In a medium-sized bowl, mash the avocado until smooth.\n- Add the rolled oats, flax seeds, chia seeds, and chopped Medjool dates to the avocado and mix until well combined.\n\n## Adding Almonds\n- Roughly chop the almonds and add them to the mixture. Stir well to ensure they are evenly distributed.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Transfer the mixture into a serving bowl.\n- If desired, top with fresh berries and a drizzle of honey or agave syrup.\n- Sprinkle a pinch of cinnamon for extra flavor.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('253','High Protein Breakfast Hot Pockets','## Dough\n- 2 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n## Filling\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 cup cooked and crumbled turkey sausage\n- 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/2 cup chopped spinach\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Dough\n- In a large bowl, mix the whole wheat flour, Greek yogurt, baking powder, and salt until a dough forms.\n- Knead the dough on a floured surface for about 5 minutes until smooth.\n- Divide the dough into eight equal sections and roll each piece into a ball.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a skillet, scramble the eggs until just done. Season with salt and pepper.\n- Mix the scrambled eggs with the turkey sausage, shredded cheese, and chopped spinach.\n\n## Assemble the Hot Pockets\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Roll each dough ball out to about 6 inches in diameter.\n- Spoon 1/8 of the filling mixture onto the center of each dough circle.\n- Fold the dough over the filling and pinch the edges to seal them. Use a fork to crimp the edges securely.\n- Place the hot pockets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n\n## Bake\n- Bake the hot pockets in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until the dough is golden brown.\n- Allow them to cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('254','Chicken Satay with Peanut Sauce','## For the Chicken Satay\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into strips\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- Skewers (soaked in water if wooden)\n\n## For the Peanut Sauce\n- 1/2 cup creamy peanut butter\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 1 teaspoon sriracha or chili paste\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup coconut milk\n- Warm water (to thin, as needed)\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh cilantro\n- Crushed peanuts\n- Lime wedges','## Prepare the Marinade and Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine soy sauce, lime juice, olive oil, minced garlic, coriander, cumin, turmeric, and salt.\n- Add the chicken strips to the marinade and toss to coat.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for best flavor.\n\n## Make the Peanut Sauce\n- In a mixing bowl, combine peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, honey, sesame oil, sriracha, minced garlic, and coconut milk.\n- Whisk until smooth and well combined.\n- Add warm water gradually to reach the desired sauce consistency (should be pourable).\n\n## Cook the Chicken Satay\n- Preheat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated chicken strips onto skewers.\n- Grill the chicken skewers for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and slightly charred.\n\n## Serve\n- Arrange the chicken satay on a serving platter.\n- Drizzle with peanut sauce or serve the sauce on the side.\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro, crushed peanuts, and lime wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('255','Thai Basil Chicken (Pad Krapow Gai)','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb (450g) boneless, skinless chicken thighs, diced\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2-3 bird''s eye chili peppers, sliced (adjust for spice preference)\n- 1 cup fresh Thai basil leaves\n\n## Sauce\n- 3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon dark soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n\n## To Serve\n- 4 cups cooked jasmine rice\n- 4 fried eggs (optional)','## Preparation\n- Prepare and slice all vegetables, mince the garlic, and slice the chili peppers.\n- Mix all the sauce ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat.\n- Add the garlic and chili peppers, stir-fry for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add the diced chicken to the pan and stir-fry until cooked through, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add the sliced red bell pepper and continue to stir-fry for another 2-3 minutes.\n- Pour the sauce into the pan and mix well with the chicken and vegetables, ensuring everything is well coated.\n- Add the Thai basil leaves and stir until just wilted, about 1 minute.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the Thai basil chicken over freshly cooked jasmine rice.\n- Top each serving with a fried egg if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('256','Vietnamese Grilled Pork (Thịt Nướng)','## Marinade\n- 2 lbs pork shoulder, thinly sliced\n- 3 tablespoons fish sauce\n- 3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons sugar\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce\n- 1 tablespoon minced garlic\n- 1 tablespoon minced shallots\n- 1 teaspoon ground black pepper\n\n## Garnish and Serving\n- Fresh lettuce leaves\n- Cucumber slices\n- Carrot and daikon pickles (do chua)\n- Vietnamese herbs (mint, cilantro, basil)\n- Cooked rice or vermicelli noodles\n- Crushed peanuts (optional)','## Marinate the Pork\n- In a large bowl, combine fish sauce, soy sauce, sugar, honey, vegetable oil, oyster sauce, garlic, shallots, and black pepper to make the marinade.\n- Add the thinly sliced pork to the marinade, ensuring each piece is well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, preferably overnight for maximum flavor.\n\n## Grill the Pork\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush the grill with oil to prevent sticking.\n- Grill the marinated pork slices for about 3-4 minutes on each side, until fully cooked and slightly charred.\n\n## Assemble and Serve\n- Serve the grilled pork with fresh lettuce, herbs, and pickled vegetables on a plate.\n- Accompany with cooked rice or vermicelli noodles.\n- Top with crushed peanuts if desired.\n- For additional flavor, serve with a side of Vietnamese dipping sauce (nuoc cham).','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('257','Lemongrass Chicken Vermicelli Bowl','## Marinated Lemongrass Chicken\n- 500g (1 lb) boneless, skinless chicken thighs\n- 2 tablespoons lemongrass, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon brown sugar\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon ground black pepper\n\n## Vermicelli Bowl\n- 200g (7 oz) rice vermicelli noodles\n- 1 cup cucumber, julienned\n- 1 cup carrot, julienned\n- 1 cup bean sprouts\n- 1 cup fresh mint leaves\n- 1 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 1/2 cup chopped peanuts\n- 4 lime wedges\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons fish sauce\n- 3 tablespoons lime juice\n- 2 tablespoons water\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 red chili, sliced (optional)','## Prepare the Lemongrass Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix lemongrass, garlic, fish sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, vegetable oil, and black pepper.\n- Add the chicken thighs, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Marinate for at least 30 minutes in the refrigerator.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the chicken for about 5-7 minutes on each side, until fully cooked and nicely charred.\n- Remove from heat and let rest for 5 minutes. Then, slice into thin strips.\n\n## Prepare Vermicelli Noodles and Vegetables\n- Cook vermicelli noodles according to package instructions. Drain and rinse under cold water.\n- Arrange the noodles in serving bowls.\n- Top with cucumber, carrot, bean sprouts, mint, and cilantro.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together fish sauce, lime juice, water, sugar, garlic, and chili (if using) until sugar dissolves.\n\n## Assemble the Bowls\n- Place sliced chicken over the prepared noodle bowls.\n- Drizzle with the dressing.\n- Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and serve with lime wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('258','Yakitori Chicken Skewers','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken thighs\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Yakitori Sauce\n- 1/2 cup soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup mirin\n- 1/4 cup sake\n- 2 tablespoons sugar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ginger, grated\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped green onions\n- Sesame seeds','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Cut the chicken thighs into bite-sized pieces.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n- Thread the chicken pieces onto skewers.\n\n## Prepare the Yakitori Sauce\n- In a small saucepan, combine soy sauce, mirin, sake, sugar, garlic, and ginger.\n- Bring to a boil over medium heat, then reduce to a simmer.\n- Allow the sauce to thicken slightly, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Skewers\n- Preheat the grill or a grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Brush the skewers with vegetable oil.\n- Grill the skewers for about 5 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.\n\n## Glaze the Skewers\n- Brush the skewers with the yakitori sauce during the last few minutes of grilling, allowing the sauce to caramelize slightly.\n- Reserve some sauce for serving.\n\n## Serve\n- Arrange the skewers on a serving platter.\n- Garnish with chopped green onions and sesame seeds.\n- Serve with the reserved sauce on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('259','Japanese Miso Glazed Cod','## Marinade\n- 2 tablespoons white miso paste\n- 2 tablespoons mirin\n- 2 tablespoons sake\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 teaspoon grated ginger\n\n## Cod\n- 4 cod fillets (around 6 oz each)\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- Chopped green onions for garnish\n- Sesame seeds for garnish\n- Lemon wedges for serving','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a bowl, mix together white miso paste, mirin, sake, soy sauce, sugar, and grated ginger until smooth.\n\n## Marinate the Cod\n- Place the cod fillets in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over them, ensuring each fillet is well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or ideally overnight for better flavor absorption.\n\n## Cook the Cod\n- Preheat your oven''s broiler and place the oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source.\n- Carefully remove the cod from the marinade, letting excess marinade drip off.\n- Heat vegetable oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the cod fillets and sear for about 2-3 minutes on each side until lightly browned.\n- Transfer the skillet to the oven to broil for about 4-5 minutes, or until the cod is cooked through and the glaze is caramelized (internal temperature should reach 145°F).\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish the cod with chopped green onions and sesame seeds.\n- Serve with lemon wedges and enjoy with steamed rice or sautéed vegetables.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('260','Korean Spicy Pork (Jeyuk Bokkeum)','## Marinade\n- 1 lb pork belly, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons gochujang (Korean red pepper paste)\n- 2 tablespoons gochugaru (Korean red pepper flakes)\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1-inch piece ginger, minced\n- 1 tablespoon mirin\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n\n## Stir-fry\n- 1 medium onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 carrot, julienned\n- 1 green bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 4 green onions, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- Sesame seeds for garnish','## Marinate the Pork\n- In a large bowl, combine gochujang, gochugaru, soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, garlic, ginger, mirin, and rice vinegar.\n- Add pork slices to the marinade and mix well to coat evenly.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, ideally 1-2 hours, for better flavor absorption.\n\n## Cook the Pork\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.\n- Add marinated pork and stir-fry for 5-7 minutes until cooked through.\n- Add onions, carrots, and bell peppers to the pan.\n- Continue stirring and cooking for an additional 3-4 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.\n- Mix in chopped green onions and cook for another minute.\n\n## Serve\n- Transfer to a serving dish, sprinkle with sesame seeds.\n- Serve hot with steamed rice or lettuce leaves for wrapping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('261','Filipino Chicken Adobo','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 lbs chicken thighs or drumsticks\n- 1/2 cup soy sauce (preferably low sodium)\n- 1/2 cup apple cider vinegar\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 tsp whole black peppercorns\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, sliced\n- 1 cup water\n- 2 tbsp honey or brown sugar (optional)\n\n## Garnish\n- Chopped green onions\n- Cooked white rice for serving','## Marinade the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, combine soy sauce, apple cider vinegar, minced garlic, bay leaves, and whole black peppercorns.\n- Add the chicken pieces to the marinade, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or overnight for better flavor.\n\n## Cook the Chicken Adobo\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet or pot over medium heat.\n- Add the marinated chicken (reserve the marinade) and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.\n- Remove the chicken and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add sliced onions and sauté until translucent.\n- Return the chicken to the pot. Add the reserved marinade and 1 cup of water.\n- Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer.\n- Cover and cook for 25-30 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and tender.\n- If using, stir in the honey or brown sugar during the last 5 minutes of cooking to add a touch of sweetness.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the chicken hot, garnished with chopped green onions.\n- Pair with steamed white rice to soak up the flavorful sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('262','Thai Green Curry with Chicken','## Curry Paste\n- 2-3 green chilies, deseeded\n- 2 shallots, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic\n- 1-inch piece of ginger, peeled\n- 1 stalk lemongrass, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon shrimp paste\n- Zest of 1 lime\n- 1/2 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 3 tablespoons vegetable oil\n\n## Curry\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 pound boneless chicken breast, sliced into thin strips\n- 1 can (13.5 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 cup chicken broth\n- 2 tablespoons fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon brown sugar\n- 1 cup baby spinach\n- 1 cup sugar snap peas\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh Thai basil leaves\n\n## To Serve\n- Cooked jasmine rice\n- Lime wedges','## Prepare Curry Paste\n- Place green chilies, shallots, garlic, ginger, lemongrass, ground coriander, ground cumin, shrimp paste, lime zest, cilantro, and vegetable oil in a blender or food processor.\n- Blend until a smooth paste forms.\n\n## Cook Curry\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the chicken slices and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.\n- Remove chicken and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add the curry paste and sauté for 2-3 minutes until fragrant.\n- Pour in the coconut milk and chicken broth, stirring to combine with the paste.\n- Bring to a simmer and add fish sauce and brown sugar.\n- Add the cooked chicken back to the pan along with baby spinach, sugar snap peas, and red bell pepper.\n- Simmer for another 5-7 minutes or until the vegetables are tender and the chicken is cooked through.\n- Stir in Thai basil leaves just before serving.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve hot over cooked jasmine rice.\n- Garnish with lime wedges for an extra citrusy kick.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('263','Cambodian Beef Lok Lak','## Beef Marinade\n- 500g beef tenderloin, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Lok Lak Sauce\n- 3 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1 tablespoon sea salt\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Salad and Garnish\n- 1 small head of lettuce, leaves separated\n- 1 cucumber, sliced\n- 2 tomatoes, sliced\n- 1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n- Fresh cilantro leaves','## Marinate the Beef\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the beef slices with soy sauce, oyster sauce, fish sauce, sugar, and black pepper.\n- Mix well to ensure the beef is evenly coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to develop.\n\n## Prepare the Lok Lak Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix lime juice, sea salt, and black pepper.\n- Adjust seasoning according to taste and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Beef\n- Heat a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.\n- Once hot, add the marinated beef and stir-fry for about 5-7 minutes or until the beef is cooked to your liking.\n- Remove from heat.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Arrange lettuce leaves, cucumber slices, tomato slices, and red onion on a large serving platter.\n- Place the cooked beef on top of the salad.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the beef lok lak with the prepared lime-pepper sauce on the side for dipping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('264','Malaysian Beef Rendang','## Beef and Marinade\n- 2 lbs beef chuck, cut into 2-inch cubes\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- Salt, to taste\n\n## Spice Paste\n- 6 shallots, peeled and chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic, peeled\n- 2 inches galangal, peeled and sliced\n- 2 inches ginger, peeled and sliced\n- 3 stalks lemongrass, sliced (white part only)\n- 6 dried red chilies, soaked in warm water and drained\n\n## Cooking Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons cooking oil\n- 1 can (14 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 cup water\n- 2 teaspoons ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- 2 tablespoons palm sugar or brown sugar\n- 3 kaffir lime leaves, torn\n- 2 cinnamon sticks\n- 5 star anise\n- Salt, to taste','## Preparation\n- Marinate beef cubes with lime juice and salt for 30 minutes.\n- Blend shallots, garlic, galangal, ginger, lemongrass, and red chilies to form a smooth paste.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat oil in a pot over medium heat and sauté the spice paste until fragrant, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add beef and sear until lightly browned.\n- Pour in coconut milk and water. Stir in coriander, cumin, turmeric, and sugar.\n- Add kaffir lime leaves, cinnamon sticks, and star anise.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.\n- Cook until beef is tender and the sauce has thickened. This will take about 2 to 3 hours.\n- Season with additional salt to taste before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('265','Banh Mi with Lemongrass Tofu','## Lemongrass Tofu\n- 14 oz (400g) extra-firm tofu, pressed and sliced\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 teaspoons sugar\n- 2 stalks lemongrass, finely minced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 tablespoon lime juice\n\n## Pickled Vegetables\n- 1 cup shredded carrots\n- 1 cup daikon radish, julienned\n- 1/2 cup white vinegar\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 2 tablespoons sugar\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n\n## Banh Mi Assembly\n- 4 baguette rolls\n- 1/2 cup fresh cilantro\n- 1/2 cup sliced cucumbers\n- 1 jalapeño, thinly sliced\n- Mayonnaise, to taste','## Prepare the Lemongrass Tofu\n- In a bowl, mix soy sauce, sugar, lemongrass, garlic, vegetable oil, and lime juice.\n- Add tofu slices to the marinade, ensuring they are coated. Marinate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Preheat a grill or pan over medium heat. Cook the tofu for 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown.\n\n## Make the Pickled Vegetables\n- In a saucepan, combine vinegar, water, sugar, and salt. Bring to a simmer until sugar is dissolved.\n- Pour the vinegar mixture over the carrots and daikon in a heatproof container.\n- Let the vegetables pickle for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Banh Mi\n- Slice the baguette rolls open.\n- Spread mayonnaise on both sides of the rolls.\n- Layer the tofu, pickled vegetables, cucumbers, jalapeños, and cilantro in the baguette.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('266','Japanese Chicken Katsu','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt, to taste\n- Black pepper, to taste\n\n## Breading\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 large eggs, beaten\n- 1 cup panko breadcrumbs\n\n## Katsu Sauce\n- 1/4 cup ketchup\n- 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Shredded cabbage\n- Sliced lemon\n- Chopped parsley','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Slice each chicken breast in half horizontally to create four thin pieces.\n- Season both sides with salt and pepper.\n\n## Bread the Chicken\n- Place flour, beaten eggs, and panko breadcrumbs in three separate shallow dishes.\n- Dredge each chicken piece in flour, shaking off excess.\n- Dip into beaten eggs, ensuring full coverage.\n- Press into panko breadcrumbs, coating evenly.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the breaded chicken pieces for 3-4 minutes on each side, until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.\n\n## Make the Katsu Sauce\n- In a small bowl, whisk together ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, sugar, and Dijon mustard until smooth.\n- Adjust seasoning as needed.\n\n## Serve\n- Slice the chicken into strips.\n- Serve hot with katsu sauce on the side.\n- Optionally, garnish with shredded cabbage, lemon slices, and parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('267','Chinese Char Siu (BBQ Pork)','## Marinade\n- 2 lbs pork shoulder or pork tenderloin\n- 3 tablespoons hoisin sauce\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons oyster sauce\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons Chinese rice wine or dry sherry\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 1 teaspoon Chinese five-spice powder\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- A few drops of red food coloring (optional)','## Preparation\n- Place the pork in a large resealable bag or a shallow dish.\n- In a bowl, mix hoisin sauce, soy sauce, oyster sauce, honey, rice wine, brown sugar, sesame oil, Chinese five-spice powder, minced garlic, and the optional red food coloring.\n- Pour the marinade over the pork, ensuring it''s well-coated.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.\n\n## Cooking\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Line a baking tray with foil and place a wire rack on top.\n- Remove the pork from the marinade and place it on the wire rack. Reserve the marinade.\n- Roast the pork for 25-30 minutes, basting occasionally with the reserved marinade.\n- Increase the oven temperature to 425°F (220°C) and roast for an additional 10-15 minutes until the pork is glossy and slightly charred.\n- Remove the pork from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes.\n- Slice the pork thinly and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('268','Thai Larb Gai (Chicken Salad)','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb ground chicken\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1/4 cup chicken broth\n- 1/4 cup fish sauce\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 tablespoon toasted rice powder\n- 2 shallots, thinly sliced\n- 1-2 Thai chilies, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh mint leaves\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1/4 cup green onions, chopped\n\n## For Serving\n- Lettuce leaves (such as iceberg or romaine)\n- Lime wedges','## Cooking the Chicken\n- Heat the vegetable oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the ground chicken and cook until it''s no longer pink, breaking it apart with a spoon as it cooks.\n- Add the chicken broth and cook until the liquid reduces slightly.\n\n## Making the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, mix together the fish sauce, lime juice, and sugar until the sugar is dissolved.\n\n## Assembling Larb Gai\n- Pour the dressing over the cooked chicken and stir to combine.\n- Add the toasted rice powder and mix well.\n- Stir in the shallots, Thai chilies, mint leaves, cilantro, and green onions.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the larb in lettuce leaves, treating them as wraps.\n- Garnish with lime wedges on the side for extra zing.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('269','Bulgogi Chicken Lettuce Cups','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce (low-sodium)\n- 2 tablespoons sesame oil\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons rice vinegar\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ginger, grated\n- 1 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 2 green onions, finely chopped\n\n## Chicken\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast, thinly sliced\n\n## Lettuce Cups\n- 1 head of butter or bibb lettuce, leaves separated\n- 1/4 cup carrots, julienned\n- 1/2 cucumber, julienned\n- 1 red bell pepper, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons sesame seeds, toasted\n- Fresh cilantro for garnish\n\n## Optional Sauce\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon Sriracha\n- 1 teaspoon lime juice','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, mix together soy sauce, sesame oil, honey, rice vinegar, minced garlic, grated ginger, red pepper flakes, and green onions.\n- Add the sliced chicken breast to the marinade, ensuring all pieces are well coated.\n- Cover and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes (up to 2 hours for best results).\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the marinated chicken slices to the skillet, discarding excess marinade.\n- Cook the chicken for 5-7 minutes, or until fully cooked and slightly caramelized.\n- Remove from heat and let the chicken rest for a few minutes.\n\n## Prepare Lettuce Cups and Serve\n- Arrange lettuce leaves on a serving platter.\n- Place a few pieces of cooked chicken in each lettuce leaf.\n- Top with julienned carrots, cucumber, and red bell pepper slices.\n- Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds and garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Drizzle with optional sauce made by mixing Greek yogurt, Sriracha, and lime juice, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('270','Shrimp Pad Kee Mao (Drunken Noodles)','## Main Ingredients\n- 10 oz wide rice noodles\n- 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2-3 Thai bird chilies, sliced (adjust to taste)\n- 1 small onion, sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 cup broccoli florets\n- 1 cup Thai basil leaves\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons soy sauce (low sodium if preferred)\n- 2 tablespoons oyster sauce\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon dark soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n- 2 tablespoons water','## Preparation\n- Soak the rice noodles in warm water for about 30 minutes or until pliable, then drain.\n- Mix all the sauce ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large pan or wok, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat.\n- Add the garlic and Thai bird chilies, stir-frying for about 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add the onion, red bell pepper, and broccoli. Stir-fry for about 3 minutes until they start to soften.\n- Add the shrimp and stir-fry until they turn pink and are cooked through.\n- Add the drained noodles to the pan, pouring the sauce over the mixture.\n- Toss everything together for a few minutes until the noodles absorb the sauce and are well-coated.\n- Add the Thai basil leaves and stir-fry briefly until wilted.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with additional Thai basil or a wedge of lime, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('271','Cantonese Steamed Fish with Ginger & Scallions','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 whole white fish (such as sea bass or tilapia), about 1.5 pounds, cleaned and scaled\n- Salt, to taste\n- White pepper, to taste\n- 3 tablespoons light soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons rice wine or dry sherry\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n\n## Aromatics\n- 3 inches ginger, julienned\n- 2 scallions, julienned\n- 1/4 cup cilantro leaves\n- 1 red chili, thinly sliced (optional)\n\n## Steaming Equipment\n- A large shallow heatproof plate that fits inside your steamer\n- A steaming basket or setup','## Preparation\n- Rinse the fish under cold water and pat dry with paper towels.\n- Make diagonal slashes on both sides of the fish to help it cook evenly.\n- Rub the fish inside and out with salt and white pepper.\n- Place the fish on the heatproof plate, and stuff some ginger and scallions into the cavity of the fish.\n\n## Steaming\n- Set up a steamer or steaming basket over a pot of boiling water.\n- Place the plate with the fish inside the steamer and cover with a lid.\n- Steam the fish for about 8-10 minutes, depending on the thickness of the fish.\n\n## Sauce & Garnish\n- In a small saucepan, heat the soy sauce and rice wine until warm, but do not boil.\n- Once the fish is cooked, remove it from the steamer and carefully discard any accumulated liquid on the plate.\n- Pour the warm soy sauce mixture over the fish.\n- Heat sesame oil in a small pan until it is very hot, then pour it over the fish to release the aroma of the aromatics.\n- Garnish with the remaining ginger, scallions, cilantro leaves, and optional red chili.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('272','Egg Foo Young with Chicken','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 eggs\n- 1/2 cup cooked chicken, shredded (or substitute with shrimp)\n- 1/2 cup bean sprouts\n- 1/4 cup green onions, chopped\n- 1/4 cup bell pepper, chopped\n- 1/4 cup carrots, grated\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sesame oil\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n\n## Gravy\n- 1 cup chicken broth\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n- 1/4 teaspoon white pepper\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped green onions\n- Sesame seeds','## Prepare the Gravy\n- In a small saucepan, combine chicken broth, soy sauce, sugar, and white pepper.\n- Bring to a simmer over medium heat.\n- In a separate bowl, mix the cornstarch with a little water to make a slurry.\n- Gradually add the cornstarch slurry to the simmering broth, stirring continuously until thickened.\n- Set aside and keep warm.\n\n## Prepare the Egg Foo Young\n- In a large bowl, beat the eggs, then mix in cooked chicken, bean sprouts, green onions, bell pepper, carrots, soy sauce, and sesame oil.\n- Heat vegetable oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Pour a portion of the egg mixture into the skillet to form a small pancake-sized portion.\n- Cook for 3-4 minutes on each side or until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Repeat with the remaining mixture.\n\n## Assembly\n- Place the cooked egg foo young on a serving plate.\n- Spoon the gravy over the top.\n- Garnish with chopped green onions and sesame seeds if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('273','Korean Soy Garlic Chicken','## Chicken and Marinade\n- 1 pound chicken thighs, boneless and skinless\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon rice wine (mirin)\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper\n\n## Soy Garlic Sauce\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon minced garlic\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 2 tablespoons water\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil for frying\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- 2 green onions, chopped','## Prepare and Marinate Chicken\n- Cut chicken thighs into bite-sized pieces.\n- In a bowl, combine soy sauce, rice wine, garlic powder, and black pepper.\n- Add chicken pieces to the marinade and mix well.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Prepare Soy Garlic Sauce\n- In a small saucepan, combine soy sauce, honey, brown sugar, rice vinegar, and minced garlic.\n- Bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.\n- Add the cornstarch mixture and continue to stir until the sauce thickens.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.\n- Add marinated chicken pieces in batches, frying until they are golden brown and cooked through, about 6-8 minutes.\n- Remove and drain on a paper towel.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Reduce heat to low and add sesame oil to the pan.\n- Return the fried chicken to the pan and pour the soy garlic sauce over.\n- Toss chicken until evenly coated in the sauce.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds and chopped green onions.\n- Serve hot with steamed rice or vegetables.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('274','Teriyaki Salmon','## Salmon\n- 4 salmon fillets (about 6 oz each)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Teriyaki Sauce\n- 1/2 cup soy sauce (low sodium)\n- 1/4 cup mirin (sweet rice wine)\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh ginger, grated\n- 1 teaspoon sesame oil\n\n## Garnish (optional)\n- Sesame seeds\n- Chopped green onions','## Prepare the Sauce\n- In a small saucepan, combine soy sauce, mirin, honey, rice vinegar, garlic, ginger, and sesame oil.\n- Bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring until honey is dissolved.\n- Reduce the heat to low and let it reduce slightly, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Salmon\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper.\n- Place salmon fillets in a baking dish and pour teriyaki sauce over them, reserving some for serving.\n\n## Cook the Salmon\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 12-15 minutes, or until salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Serve\n- Drizzle the reserved teriyaki sauce over the cooked salmon.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds and chopped green onions if desired.\n- Serve hot with steamed vegetables or brown rice for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('275','Japanese Sukiyaki with Beef','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb (450g) thinly sliced beef ribeye or sirloin\n- 1 block (14 oz) firm tofu, cut into cubes\n- 1 bunch of enoki mushrooms, trimmed\n- 1/2 cup shiitake mushrooms, sliced\n- 1/2 cup shungiku (chrysanthemum leaves) or spinach\n- 1/2 cup napa cabbage, sliced\n- 1 small onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 cup shirataki noodles, rinsed and drained\n\n## Sukiyaki Sauce\n- 1/2 cup soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup mirin\n- 1/4 cup sake\n- 2 tbsp sugar\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- 2 green onions, thinly sliced\n- 4 raw egg yolks for dipping (optional)','## Prepare the Ingredients\n- Arrange all the vegetables, tofu, and noodles on a large serving platter.\n- Mix the soy sauce, mirin, sake, and sugar in a bowl to make the sukiyaki sauce.\n\n## Cooking the Sukiyaki\n- Heat a large skillet or shallow pot over medium heat.\n- Add a little bit of sukiyaki sauce to the skillet.\n- Once the sauce is hot, add the sliced onion and let it cook for a minute.\n- Add the beef slices and cook until they are browned.\n- Gradually add tofu, mushrooms, cabbage, enoki, and shirataki noodles to the skillet.\n- Pour the remaining sukiyaki sauce over the ingredients.\n- Cover and simmer the ingredients for about 5-7 minutes or until vegetables are tender.\n- Add the shungiku or spinach last and cook just until wilted.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with green onions.\n- For an authentic experience, provide egg yolks for dipping the cooked ingredients.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('276','Thai Panang Curry with Chicken','## Curry Paste\n- 2 tablespoons red curry paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/4 teaspoon cumin\n- 2 tablespoons peanut butter\n\n## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 pound chicken breast, sliced\n- 1 can (14 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 2 teaspoons sugar\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 cup green beans, trimmed\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh basil','## Prepare Curry Paste\n- In a small bowl, mix red curry paste, ground coriander, cumin, and peanut butter until smooth.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add sliced chicken and cook until no longer pink, about 5-7 minutes. Remove from pan and set aside.\n\n## Make Curry\n- In the same pan, add the blended curry paste and stir for a minute until fragrant.\n- Pour in coconut milk, fish sauce, sugar, and water. Stir to combine.\n- Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- Add bell pepper and green beans to the pan and cook for 3-4 minutes, until slightly tender.\n- Return cooked chicken to the pan and simmer for another 5 minutes.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Stir in fresh basil before serving.\n- Serve hot with steamed jasmine rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('277','Vietnamese Shaking Beef (Bò Lúc Lắc)','## Beef Marinade\n- 1 lb beef sirloin, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n\n## Stir Fry\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 medium onion, cut into wedges\n- 1 bell pepper (red or green), cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon lime juice\n- 1/2 teaspoon sugar\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Green onions, sliced\n- Lime wedges','## Marinating the Beef\n- In a bowl, combine soy sauce, oyster sauce, fish sauce, sugar, black pepper, vegetable oil, and garlic.\n- Add the beef cubes to the marinade, mixing well to coat all pieces.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, ideally 1-2 hours.\n\n## Cooking the Beef\n- Heat 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over high heat.\n- Add the marinated beef in a single layer, sear for 2-3 minutes until browned, then shake the pan to cook another side for 2-3 minutes. Remove beef and set aside.\n\n## Stir Fry Vegetables\n- In the same pan, add onion and bell pepper, stir fry for 2 minutes.\n- Add garlic, soy sauce, lime juice, and sugar, stir until the vegetables are just tender.\n- Return the beef to the pan, tossing everything together to coat with sauce.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro, sliced green onions, and lime wedges.\n- Serve immediately with steamed rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('278','Spicy Thai Glass Noodle Salad with Shrimp (Yum Woon Sen)','## Noodles and Shrimp\n- 100g glass noodles\n- 200g shrimp, peeled and deveined\n\n## Salad Ingredients\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup cucumber, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh mint leaves\n- 1/4 cup fresh coriander leaves\n- 2 tablespoons roasted peanuts, crushed\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons fish sauce\n- 3 tablespoons lime juice\n- 2 tablespoons palm sugar\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2-3 Thai bird''s eye chilies, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce (optional)','## Prepare Noodles and Shrimp\n- Soak glass noodles in warm water for 10 minutes until softened. Drain and set aside.\n- Bring a pot of water to boil. Add shrimp and cook until pink and opaque, about 2-3 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n\n## Make Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together fish sauce, lime juice, palm sugar, minced garlic, chilies, and soy sauce until the sugar is dissolved.\n\n## Assemble Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the softened noodles, cooked shrimp, cherry tomatoes, red onion, cucumber, cilantro, mint, and coriander.\n- Pour the dressing over the salad and toss until everything is well-coated.\n- Garnish with crushed roasted peanuts.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('279','Chinese Dan Dan Noodles with Ground Turkey','## Noodles and Sauce\n- 8 oz egg noodles or whole wheat noodles\n- 3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons tahini (or peanut butter)\n- 1 tablespoon rice vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon chili oil\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 1 tablespoon hoisin sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n\n## Turkey and Vegetables\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh ginger, minced\n- 4 green onions, chopped (reserve some for garnishing)\n- 1 tablespoon Sichuan peppercorns, ground (optional)\n- 1 cup bok choy, chopped\n- 1/2 cup carrots, julienned\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Noodles\n- Cook the noodles according to package instructions, drain, and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine soy sauce, tahini, rice vinegar, chili oil, sesame oil, hoisin sauce, sugar, and chicken broth.\n- Whisk until smooth and well combined. Set aside.\n\n## Cook the Turkey and Vegetables\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and ginger, sauté until fragrant.\n- Add ground turkey and cook until browned, breaking it apart with a spatula.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and ground Sichuan peppercorns (if using).\n- Add chopped bok choy, carrots, and half of the chopped green onions.\n- Stir-fry until vegetables are tender and turkey is cooked through.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the prepared sauce to the skillet with the cooked turkey and vegetables.\n- Stir until everything is well coated and heated through.\n- Add the cooked noodles and toss gently to combine.\n- Adjust seasoning if needed.\n- Serve hot, garnished with the remaining green onions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('280','Thai Chicken Coconut Soup (Tom Kha Gai)','## Soup Base\n- 4 cups chicken broth\n- 2 stalks lemongrass, trimmed and smashed\n- 4 kaffir lime leaves, torn into pieces\n- 3 slices galangal (or ginger if unavailable)\n\n## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast, sliced thinly\n- 1 can (13.5 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 cup mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n\n## Flavor Enhancers\n- 2-3 Thai bird chilies, smashed\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro leaves\n- Chopped green onions\n- Slices of lime','## Prepare the Broth\n- In a large pot, combine chicken broth, lemongrass, lime leaves, and galangal.\n- Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.\n\n## Cook Chicken and Mushrooms\n- Add sliced chicken and mushrooms to the broth.\n- Simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 10 minutes.\n\n## Add Coconut Milk and Seasonings\n- Stir in coconut milk, fish sauce, chilies, lime juice, and sugar.\n- Cook for another 5 minutes without letting it come to a full boil.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Ladle the soup into bowls.\n- Top with fresh cilantro, chopped green onions, and lime slices.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('281','Spicy Garlic Shrimp with Bok Choy','## For the Shrimp\n- 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp ginger, minced\n- 1 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tbsp sriracha sauce\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n\n## For the Bok Choy\n- 2 heads bok choy, cut into quarters\n- 1 tbsp sesame oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tsp sesame seeds','## Prepare the Shrimp\n- In a bowl, combine shrimp, garlic, ginger, soy sauce, and sriracha.\n- Marinate for at least 15 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Shrimp\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat.\n- Add the marinated shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until pink and cooked through.\n- Remove the shrimp from the pan and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Bok Choy\n- In the same pan, add sesame oil and minced garlic.\n- Sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Add the bok choy and soy sauce; stir-fry for about 4-5 minutes until the bok choy is tender-crisp.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Return the cooked shrimp to the pan, mixing with the bok choy.\n- Sprinkle sesame seeds over the top.\n- Serve hot, and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('282','Japanese Oyako Don (Chicken & Egg Bowl)','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 cups dashi stock (or substitute chicken stock)\n- 3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons mirin\n- 1 tablespoon sake\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 2 cups cooked Japanese short-grain rice\n- 2 green onions, finely chopped\n- Nori seaweed, cut into thin strips (optional)','## Preparation\n- Prepare the rice according to package instructions and keep warm.\n- In a bowl, lightly beat the eggs and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large skillet or donburi pan, combine the dashi stock, soy sauce, mirin, sake, and sugar. Bring to a simmer over medium heat.\n- Add the sliced onion to the simmering sauce and cook until tender, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add the chicken pieces to the onion and sauce, and cook until the chicken is just about cooked through, about 5-6 minutes.\n- Once the chicken is nearly done, pour the beaten eggs over the top of the chicken and onion mixture. Do not stir.\n- Cover the pan with a lid and allow the eggs to cook gently until they are just set, about 1-2 minutes.\n- Uncover and sprinkle the green onions over the top.\n\n## Serving\n- Scoop a generous portion of the cooked rice into individual bowls.\n- Gently slide the chicken and egg mixture over the rice, ensuring each bowl gets an even distribution of chicken and egg.\n- Garnish with nori strips, if using.\n- Serve hot and enjoy your homemade Oyako Don!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('283','Korean Tofu Stew (Sundubu Jjigae) with Ground Pork','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 200 grams ground pork\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 200 grams shiitake mushrooms, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons gochugaru (Korean red chili flakes)\n- 1 tablespoon gochujang (Korean red chili paste)\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 cups chicken or vegetable broth\n- 400 grams soft tofu, cut into large chunks\n- 2 green onions, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- 1 egg\n- Sesame seeds for garnish','## Preparation\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the ground pork to the pot and cook until browned.\n- Stir in the minced garlic, sliced onion, zucchini, and shiitake mushrooms. Cook until the vegetables are soft.\n\n## Spicing and Flavoring\n- Add the gochugaru and gochujang to the pot, stirring to combine and coat the vegetables and pork.\n- Pour in the soy sauce and broth, then bring to a simmer.\n\n## Simmer and Finish\n- Gently stir in the soft tofu, being careful not to break it apart. Let the stew simmer for about 10-15 minutes.\n- Add the chopped green onions and drizzle sesame oil over the top.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, optionally cracking an egg on top of the stew while it''s still steaming and stirring it in, allowing the heat to cook the egg.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds if desired.\n- Serve with steamed rice on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('284','Chicken Tikka','## Marinade\n- 1 cup plain yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- 1 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Chicken\n- 1.5 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces\n\n## To Cook & Serve\n- 1 tablespoon oil\n- Lemon wedges\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped, for garnish','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine the yogurt, lemon juice, ginger-garlic paste, cumin, coriander, paprika, cayenne pepper, turmeric, garam masala, and salt.\n- Mix well until all ingredients are fully combined.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken\n- Add the chicken pieces to the marinade, ensuring they are fully coated.\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, preferably overnight for best flavor.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Preheat your grill or oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- If using a grill, brush the grates with oil. If using an oven, line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and brush with oil.\n- Thread chicken pieces onto skewers, leaving a little space between each piece.\n- Grill or bake the chicken for about 15-20 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and slightly charred around the edges.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove the chicken from skewers and place on a serving plate.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve with lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('285','Paneer Bhurji','## Main Ingredients\n- 200g paneer, crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon oil or ghee\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 medium tomato, finely chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped, for garnish\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1 small bell pepper, finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup green peas\n- 1 teaspoon kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves)','## Preparation\n- Crumble the paneer and set aside.\n- Chop all vegetables as specified above.\n\n## Cooking Instructions\n- Heat oil or ghee in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until translucent.\n- Add green chili and ginger-garlic paste. Sauté for a minute until fragrant.\n- Add chopped tomato and cook until soft.\n- Stir in turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Mix well.\n- Add optional bell pepper and peas if using, and cook for 2-3 minutes.\n- Add crumbled paneer and mix well with spices. Cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and kasuri methi if using. Mix well.\n- Garnish with chopped coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('286','High-Protein Rajma','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup dried kidney beans (rajma)\n- 3 cups water (for soaking beans)\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, pureed\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 2 tablespoons cooking oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped, for garnish','## Preparation\n- Rinse the kidney beans thoroughly and soak them in 3 cups of water for at least 8 hours or overnight.\n- Drain and rinse the soaked beans.\n\n## Cooking the Beans\n- In a pressure cooker, add the soaked rajma and 3 cups of fresh water.\n- Cook under pressure for about 15-20 minutes or until the beans are soft and tender.\n\n## Making the Masala\n- Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste and green chilies, cooking for another 2 minutes.\n- Add tomato puree and cook until the oil starts separating from the mixture.\n- Mix in turmeric, coriander, and red chili powders and cook for an additional 2 minutes.\n\n## Final Assembly\n- Add the cooked rajma along with its cooking water to the pan with the masala.\n- Stir well and simmer for 10-15 minutes, adding more water if necessary to achieve desired consistency.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and adjust salt to taste.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('287','Methi Malai Chicken','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g boneless chicken pieces\n- 1 cup fresh methi (fenugreek) leaves, chopped\n- 1 cup cream (can use low-fat cream)\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 1 cup onions, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2-3 green chilies, slit\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Marinade\n- 1/2 cup yogurt\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix yogurt, red chili powder, and salt.\n- Add the chicken pieces and coat them well.\n- Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes in the refrigerator.\n\n## Prepare the Methi Malai Chicken\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add the onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\n- Add the ginger-garlic paste and green chilies, sauté for 2-3 minutes.\n- Add the turmeric powder, coriander powder, and salt, and mix well.\n- Add the marinated chicken and cook until the chicken is half-cooked.\n- Stir in the chopped methi leaves and cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Lower the heat and add the cream, ensuring to mix well.\n- Cook until the chicken is fully cooked and the sauce has thickened.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and mix well.\n\n## Garnishing and Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('288','Keema Matar','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g ground lamb or beef\n- 1 cup green peas (fresh or frozen)\n- 2 medium onions, finely chopped\n- 2 medium tomatoes, chopped\n- 4 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1-inch ginger, minced\n- 2 green chilies, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n\n## Spices\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 bay leaf\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 3-4 cloves\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds, bay leaf, cinnamon stick, and cloves. Sauté until fragrant.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger, garlic, and green chilies. Cook for 2-3 minutes.\n- Stir in chopped tomatoes; cook until they soften.\n- Add turmeric, coriander, cumin, and red chili powder. Mix well.\n- Add ground meat; cook until browned.\n- Add peas and salt. Mix well and cover the pan.\n- Lower the heat and let it cook for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n- Remove from heat once the peas are tender and the mixture is well-cooked.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped coriander leaves.\n- Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('289','High-Protein Egg Curry','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## For Serving\n- Cooked brown rice or whole grain naan','## Preparing the Eggs\n- Place eggs in a pot and cover with water.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for 10 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and transfer eggs to a bowl of cold water.\n- Peel the eggs and set aside.\n\n## Making the Curry Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in ginger-garlic paste, sautéing for another minute.\n- Add tomatoes and green chilies, cooking until tomatoes are soft.\n- Mix in turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt.\n- Cook the masala until the oil starts separating from the mixture.\n\n## Combining and Finishing\n- Gently add the boiled eggs to the curry sauce, stirring to coat them with the masala.\n- Sprinkle garam masala over the top.\n- Simmer for another 5 minutes to let the eggs absorb flavors.\n- Garnish with fresh chopped cilantro.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot with cooked brown rice or whole grain naan.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('290','Palak Paneer','## For the Paneer\n- 250g paneer, cubed\n\n## For the Spinach Gravy\n- 500g fresh spinach\n- 1 tablespoon oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, pureed\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- Salt, to taste\n- 2 tablespoons yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon cream (optional)\n\n## For Garnish\n- 1 tablespoon cream (optional)','## Preparing the Spinach\n- Wash and blanch the spinach in boiling water for 2-3 minutes.\n- Drain and immediately transfer to cold water to retain the green color.\n- Blend the spinach into a smooth puree and set aside.\n\n## Making the Gravy\n- Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds. Let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Cook for another minute.\n- Stir in the tomato puree and cook until the oil separates.\n- Add turmeric powder, garam masala, coriander powder, and salt.\n- Mix in the spinach puree and cook for 3-4 minutes.\n- Add yogurt and mix well. Cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Add the cream if using.\n\n## Final Assembly\n- Add the paneer cubes to the spinach gravy and gently mix.\n- Cook on a low flame for 5 minutes, allowing the paneer to absorb the flavors.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with a swirl of cream if desired.\n- Serve hot with roti, naan, or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('291','Moong Dal Tadka','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup yellow moong dal (split yellow gram)\n- 3 cups water\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Tempering Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon ghee or oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1/2 teaspoon mustard seeds\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- A pinch of asafoetida (hing)\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Dal\n- Rinse the moong dal thoroughly under running water to remove any dirt or impurities.\n- In a pot, add the rinsed dal and 3 cups of water. Bring it to a boil.\n- Reduce the heat and add salt to taste. Cook until the dal is soft and mushy, about 20 minutes.\n- Once cooked, mash the dal slightly with the back of a spoon.\n\n## Prepare the Tadka (Tempering)\n- In a pan, heat ghee or oil over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and mustard seeds; let them splutter.\n- Add asafoetida, then sauté onions until they become translucent.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste; cook until the raw smell disappears.\n- Add tomatoes, green chilies, turmeric powder, and red chili powder.\n- Cook until the tomatoes turn soft and the oil leaves the sides of the pan.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Mix the cooked dal with the prepared tempering.\n- Simmer everything together for 5-10 minutes to blend the flavors.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.\n- Serve hot with rice or roti, accompanied by lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('292','Fish Tikka','## Fish Marinade\n- 500g firm white fish fillets (such as cod, halibut, or haddock), cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 150g plain Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1-inch piece of ginger, grated\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## To Serve\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n- Red onion slices','## Marinade Preparation\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, red chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, and salt.\n- Mix the marinade until well blended.\n\n## Marinate the Fish\n- Add the fish pieces to the marinade and mix gently to coat all pieces evenly.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or up to 4 hours for richer flavor.\n\n## Cooking the Fish Tikka\n- Preheat your grill or oven to 200°C (400°F).\n- Line a baking tray with aluminum foil and lightly grease it.\n- Arrange the marinated fish pieces on the tray, ensuring they don''t overlap.\n- Grill or bake the fish for about 15-20 minutes, turning halfway, until cooked through and charred at the edges.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the fish tikka to a serving plate.\n- Garnish with chopped coriander leaves and serve with lemon wedges and red onion slices on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('293','Chicken Shami Kebab','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g boneless chicken thighs\n- 1/2 cup chana dal (split chickpeas)\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic\n- 1-inch ginger, chopped\n- 2-3 green chilies, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- Salt, to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh mint leaves, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons oil for frying\n\n## For Binding\n- 1 egg\n- 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs (optional)','## Prepare the Dal and Chicken\n- Soak the chana dal in water for 1-2 hours.\n- Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Mixture\n- In a large pot, add the chicken, soaked chana dal, onion, garlic, ginger, green chilies, cumin seeds, coriander powder, garam masala, turmeric, and salt.\n- Add water just to cover the ingredients.\n- Cook until the chicken is cooked through and dal is soft, about 15-20 minutes.\n- Once cooked, let it cool slightly.\n\n## Blend the Mixture\n- Transfer the mixture to a food processor.\n- Add fresh coriander and mint leaves.\n- Blend until smooth.\n\n## Shape the Kebabs\n- Transfer the blended mixture to a bowl.\n- Add the egg and breadcrumbs for binding (optional).\n- Mix well.\n- Shape into small, round patties.\n\n## Cook the Kebabs\n- Heat oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat.\n- Fry the kebabs until golden brown on both sides.\n- Serve hot with chutney or yogurt dip.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('294','Baingan Bharta with Soya','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 large eggplant (baingan)\n- 1 cup soya granules\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\n- 2 green chilies, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika (for extra smoky flavor)\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon','## Preparing the Eggplant\n- Roast the eggplant directly over a gas flame or in the oven until the skin is charred and the flesh is soft. Let it cool, then peel off the skin and mash the flesh.\n\n## Preparing the Soya Granules\n- Boil 2 cups of water and add the soya granules. Cook for 3-4 minutes until soft. Drain and squeeze out excess water.\n\n## Cooking the Baingan Bharta\n- In a pan, heat oil and add cumin seeds. Let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies, and cook for 2-3 minutes.\n- Add chopped tomatoes, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Cook until tomatoes are soft.\n- Stir in the mashed eggplant and soya granules. Mix well and cook for another 5-7 minutes.\n- Add garam masala and optional smoked paprika. Cook for an additional minute.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and a squeeze of lemon juice.\n- Serve hot with roti, naan, or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('295','Tandoori Salmon','## Salmon Marinade\n- 4 salmon fillets (about 6 oz each)\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons tandoori masala powder\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Marinade Preparation\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, lemon juice, olive oil, tandoori masala powder, ginger-garlic paste, ground cumin, and ground coriander.\n- Season with salt and mix until well combined.\n\n## Marinate Salmon\n- Place the salmon fillets in the marinade, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for more intense flavor.\n\n## Cooking\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or foil.\n- Place the marinated salmon fillets on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the tandoori salmon hot, garnished with fresh cilantro and lemon wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('296','Paneer Tikka','## Marinade\n- 200g paneer, cut into cubes\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- Salt, to taste\n\n## Vegetables\n- 1 large onion, cut into cubes\n- 1 bell pepper, cut into cubes\n- 1 tomato, seeds removed and cut into cubes\n\n## For Cooking\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- Skewers','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, cumin powder, coriander powder, lemon juice, and salt.\n- Mix well until all the spices are incorporated into the yogurt.\n\n## Marinate Paneer and Vegetables\n- Add the paneer cubes to the marinade and gently coat them.\n- Add the cubed onions, bell peppers, and tomatoes to the bowl and mix well.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours if time permits.\n\n## Skewer and Grill\n- Preheat the oven to 200°C (390°F) or heat a grill pan over medium heat.\n- Thread the marinated paneer and vegetables alternately onto skewers.\n- Brush the skewered pieces with vegetable oil to prevent sticking.\n\n## Cook the Paneer Tikka\n- Place skewers in the oven or on the grill.\n- Cook for about 15-20 minutes, turning occasionally, until the paneer and vegetables are cooked and slightly charred on the edges.\n- Baste with remaining oil occasionally for added flavor.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from oven or grill.\n- Serve hot with mint chutney or your choice of sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('297','Protein-Packed Masoor Dal','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup masoor dal (red lentils), rinsed\n- 3 cups water\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1-inch piece of ginger, grated\n- 1 green chili, slit (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Tempering Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon ghee or butter\n- 1/2 teaspoon mustard seeds\n- 2 dried red chilies\n- 8-10 curry leaves\n\n## Garnish Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n- Lemon wedges','## Cooking the Dal\n- In a large pot, combine the rinsed masoor dal and water. Bring to a boil.\n- Reduce the heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until the dal is soft and mushy.\n\n## Preparing the Base\n- In a separate pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the garlic, ginger, and green chili. Cook for another 2-3 minutes.\n- Add turmeric, coriander, and salt. Mix well.\n\n## Combining Dal and Base\n- Pour the cooked dal into the onion mixture.\n- Add garam masala and adjust salt if needed.\n- Simmer for another 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n## Tempering\n- In a small pan, heat ghee or butter.\n- Add mustard seeds, dried red chilies, and curry leaves. Let them splutter.\n- Pour the tempering over the cooked dal.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro.\n- Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('298','Chicken Chettinad','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g chicken, cut into pieces\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Curry leaves\n\n## Chettinad Masala\n- 2 tablespoons grated coconut\n- 1 tablespoon coriander seeds\n- 5-6 dried red chilies\n- 1 teaspoon fennel seeds\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon black peppercorns\n- 3-4 cloves\n- 2-3 cardamom pods\n- 1-inch cinnamon stick\n- 4-5 garlic cloves\n- 1-inch ginger piece','## Prepare Chettinad Masala\n- Dry roast coconut in a pan until golden brown. Set aside.\n- In the same pan, roast coriander seeds, dried red chilies, fennel seeds, cumin seeds, black peppercorns, cloves, cardamom, and cinnamon until aromatic.\n- Add garlic and ginger; roast for another minute.\n- Let the spices cool, then grind them to a fine paste with water.\n\n## Cook Chicken Chettinad\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add onions; sauté until golden brown.\n- Add tomatoes; cook until soft.\n- Stir in the ground Chettinad masala, turmeric powder, and salt.\n- Cook for 2-3 minutes until oil separates from the masala.\n- Add chicken pieces; mix well to coat with masala.\n- Cover and cook for 15-20 minutes until chicken is cooked through, stirring occasionally.\n- Garnish with curry leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('299','Mutton Rogan Josh','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 kg mutton, cut into pieces\n- 2 large onions, finely sliced\n- 2 cups yogurt\n- 1/2 cup ghee or vegetable oil\n- 1 cup water\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish\n\n## Spice Paste\n- 6-8 garlic cloves\n- 1 tablespoon ginger, freshly grated\n- 1 teaspoon fennel seeds\n- 2 teaspoons coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n\n## Whole Spices\n- 4 green cardamoms\n- 2 black cardamoms\n- 4 cloves\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 2 bay leaves','## Preparation\n- In a blender, combine garlic, ginger, fennel seeds, coriander powder, cumin seeds, red chili powder, and turmeric with a little water to form a smooth paste.\n- Whisk the yogurt and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat ghee or oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add whole spices (cardamoms, cloves, cinnamon, bay leaves) and sauté until fragrant.\n- Add sliced onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the spice paste and cook until the oil separates from the mixture.\n- Add mutton pieces and salt, cook until the meat is well-seared on all sides.\n- Add the whisked yogurt to the pot, mixing well to coat the meat.\n- Pour in water, bring the mixture to a boil, then lower the heat, cover, and simmer for about 1.5 to 2 hours until the mutton is tender and the sauce thickened.\n- Stir occasionally and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.\n- Serve hot with steamed rice or naan bread.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('300','Egg Bhurji','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil or ghee\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 green chilies, finely chopped\n- 1 medium tomato, finely chopped\n- 1 small bell pepper (any color), finely chopped\n- 2 tablespoons fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## Spices and Seasonings\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt, to taste','## Preparation\n- Crack the eggs into a bowl, add a pinch of salt, and whisk until well combined.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat oil or ghee in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\n- Add green chilies and sauté for about a minute.\n- Add tomatoes and cook until they soften.\n- Stir in the bell pepper and cook for another 2-3 minutes.\n- Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Stir well to combine.\n- Pour the whisked eggs into the pan and gently stir to scramble, ensuring the eggs cook through evenly.\n- Cook until the eggs are just set, ensuring they retain some moisture and are not overly dry.\n- Add chopped cilantro and mix well before removing from heat.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot with bread, roti, or as a filling for wraps.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('301','Sprouted Moong Salad','## Salad\n- 1 cup sprouted moong (mung beans)\n- 1 medium cucumber, diced\n- 1 small carrot, grated\n- 1 medium tomato, diced\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tablespoons coriander leaves, chopped\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped (optional)\n\n## Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon roasted cumin powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste','## Prepare the Moong Sprouts\n- Rinse the sprouted moong thoroughly under running water.\n- Drain and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the sprouted moong, cucumber, carrot, tomato, onion, coriander leaves, and green chili.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together lemon juice, olive oil, roasted cumin powder, salt, and black pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- Pour the dressing over the salad.\n- Toss well to combine all ingredients evenly.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately as a refreshing and healthy salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('302','Dhaba Style Chicken Curry','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 kg chicken, cut into pieces\n- 1 cup yogurt\n- 2 large onions, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, pureed\n- 2 tbsp ginger-garlic paste\n- 3-4 green chilies, slit\n- 1/4 cup mustard oil or cooking oil\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Spices\n- 1 tsp turmeric powder\n- 1 tbsp red chili powder\n- 1 tbsp coriander powder\n- 1 tsp cumin powder\n- 1 tsp garam masala\n- 2-3 bay leaves\n- 5-6 black peppercorns\n- 3-4 cloves\n- 1-inch cinnamon stick\n- 2-3 green cardamoms\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- In a large bowl, marinate chicken with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, and salt. Set aside for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat mustard oil in a large pan or wok until it begins to smoke slightly. Lower the heat and add bay leaves, peppercorns, cloves, cinnamon, and cardamoms.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\n- Add cumin powder, coriander powder, and red chili powder. Stir well and add tomato puree.\n- Cook the mixture until the oil separates from the masala.\n- Add marinated chicken pieces and green chilies. Combine well with the masala.\n- Cover and cook on low heat for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is tender.\n- Add garam masala and adjust seasoning with salt if needed. Mix well and cook for another 2-3 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped coriander leaves and serve hot with lemon wedges.\n- Pairs well with roti, naan, or steamed rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('303','Tofu Palak','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 block (14 oz) extra firm tofu, drained and cubed\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon ginger, grated\n- 2 tomatoes, pureed\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Spinach Base\n- 10 oz fresh spinach, washed and chopped\n- 1/4 cup water\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice','## Prepare Tofu\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cubed tofu and sauté until golden brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n\n## Cook Spinach\n- In the same pan, add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add onion, garlic, and ginger. Sauté until the onion is golden brown.\n- Stir in the pureed tomatoes, turmeric, garam masala, coriander, chili powder, and salt.\n- Cook until the oil separates from the mixture.\n- Add chopped spinach and water, cover, and simmer for 5-7 minutes until spinach is wilted.\n- Blend the spinach mixture into a smooth puree using an immersion blender.\n- Return the puree to the pan and stir in almond milk. Simmer for 5 minutes.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the tofu cubes to the spinach puree and gently mix to combine.\n- Simmer for another 3-4 minutes to allow flavors to meld.\n- Garnish with freshly chopped cilantro and a squeeze of lemon juice before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('304','Kala Chana Masala','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup dried kala chana (black chickpeas), soaked overnight\n- 2 tablespoons cooking oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, pureed\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)\n- 1 tablespoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped, for garnish\n\n## For Pressure Cooking\n- 1 bay leaf\n- 2-3 cups water','## Pressure Cook Kala Chana\n- Drain the soaked kala chana and place them in a pressure cooker.\n- Add bay leaf and 2-3 cups of water.\n- Pressure cook for about 15-20 minutes or until the kala chana is soft.\n- Release the pressure naturally and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Masala\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies; sauté for another minute.\n- Stir in the tomato puree and cook until the oil separates from the masala.\n\n## Combine and Cook\n- Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, and salt. Mix well.\n- Add the cooked kala chana along with the cooking liquid.\n- Simmer for 10-15 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.\n- Stir in garam masala and adjust seasoning if needed.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('305','Chicken Saagwala','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 teaspoons ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 2 teaspoons ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Saag (Spinach) Ingredients\n- 10 oz fresh spinach leaves, washed and chopped\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 1 medium tomato, chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon green chili, finely chopped (optional)\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Saag\n- In a large pot, bring 1/2 cup water to a boil.\n- Add the spinach leaves and cook for 3-4 minutes until wilted.\n- Blend the spinach and water mixture to a smooth paste. Set aside.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add the cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add the chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste and fry for 1-2 minutes.\n- Add the ground coriander, ground cumin, turmeric powder, and salt. Cook for another minute.\n- Add the chicken pieces and cook until they are browned on all sides.\n- Stir in the chopped tomato and green chili (if using), and cook until the tomato softens.\n- Pour in the blended spinach paste and mix well with the chicken.\n- Reduce the heat, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes until the chicken is cooked through.\n- Stir in the garam masala and let cook for an additional 2 minutes.\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.\n- Enjoy with steamed basmati rice or whole wheat naan.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('306','Grilled Tandoori Prawns','## Marinade\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon ginger paste\n- 1 tablespoon garlic paste\n- 2 teaspoons ground cumin\n- 2 teaspoons ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Prawns\n- 1 pound large prawns, peeled and deveined\n- Skewers (soaked in water if using wooden skewers)\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish\n- Lemon wedges for serving','## Marinade Preparation\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, lemon juice, ginger paste, garlic paste, ground cumin, ground coriander, turmeric powder, chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well until all ingredients are well incorporated.\n\n## Marinate Prawns\n- Add the prawns to the marinade, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to 1 hour to allow the flavors to absorb.\n\n## Grilling Prawns\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated prawns onto skewers.\n- Place the skewers on the grill and cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until the prawns are opaque and cooked through.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the grilled prawns to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and serve with lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('307','Protein-Packed Chole (Chickpea Curry)','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups canned or cooked chickpeas (garbanzo beans)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons chopped cilantro (coriander leaves)\n- Lemon wedges for serving\n- Optional: 1 tablespoon Greek yogurt for garnish','## Preparation\n- Rinse the canned chickpeas under cold water and drain them. If using dried chickpeas, soak them overnight and cook until tender.\n- Puree the tomatoes in a blender or food processor to make a smooth paste.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and allow them to sizzle.\n- Add the chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Cook for 1-2 minutes.\n- Add the tomato puree, coriander powder, cumin powder, turmeric powder, and red chili powder. Cook the mixture until the oil starts to separate from the masala.\n- Add the chickpeas and salt to the pan, stirring well to coat them with the spices.\n- Pour in 1 cup of water (or more for desired consistency) and let it simmer for 10-15 minutes.\n- Finally, mix in the garam masala and cook for another 2 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro and a squeeze of lemon juice.\n- Serve hot with rice, naan, or roti.\n- Optionally, add a dollop of Greek yogurt for extra creaminess and protein.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('308','Paneer Makhani','## Main Ingredients\n- 250g paneer, cubed\n- 2 tbsp ghee or oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tsp ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 large tomatoes, pureed\n- 1/2 cup cashew nuts, soaked and blended to a smooth paste\n- 1/2 cup milk or cream (optional for richer taste)\n- 1 tsp red chili powder\n- 1/2 tsp turmeric powder\n- 1 tsp garam masala\n- 1 tsp coriander powder\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tbsp fresh cream\n- 1 tbsp chopped coriander leaves','## Preparation\n- Cube the paneer and set aside.\n- Soak the cashews in water for 15 minutes and then blend into a smooth paste.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat ghee or oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add finely chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste and cook for another minute until fragrant.\n- Add the tomato puree and cook until the oil separates from the mixture.\n- Mix in the cashew paste, cook for 2-3 minutes, then add chili powder, turmeric, coriander powder, and salt.\n- Add the paneer cubes and gently mix to coat with the sauce.\n- Pour in the milk or cream, if using, and let the curry simmer for 5 minutes.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and stir well.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh cream and coriander leaves before serving.\n- Serve hot with naan or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('309','High-Protein Besan Chilla','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup chickpea flour (besan)\n- 1/4 cup plain yogurt (can substitute with plant-based yogurt)\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1 small tomato, finely chopped\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- Salt to taste\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil or ghee for cooking\n\n## Optional Additions\n- 1/4 cup grated carrots\n- 1/4 cup chopped spinach\n- 1 tablespoon flaxseeds or chia seeds','## Prepare the Batter\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine besan, yogurt, and water to make a smooth batter.\n- Add chopped onion, tomato, green chili, coriander leaves, turmeric, cumin seeds, salt, and black pepper to the batter. Mix well.\n- Stir in any optional additions like carrots, spinach, or seeds for extra nutrition.\n\n## Cook the Chilla\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and add a few drops of oil or ghee.\n- Pour a ladleful of batter onto the pan and spread it into a thin circle, similar to a pancake.\n- Cook for 2-3 minutes on one side until golden brown, then flip and cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Repeat with the remaining batter, adding a bit of oil or ghee as needed.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('310','Pesarattu','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup green gram (whole moong dal)\n- 1/4 cup rice\n- 1 small piece of ginger\n- 2 green chilies\n- Salt to taste\n- Water as needed\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup chopped onions\n- 1/4 cup chopped coriander leaves\n- 1/4 cup grated carrot\n- Oil for cooking','## Preparation\n- Rinse the green gram and rice together several times.\n- Soak them in water for at least 4 hours or overnight.\n\n## Making the Pesarattu Batter\n- Drain the soaked green gram and rice, and add them to a blender.\n- Add ginger, green chilies, and salt.\n- Blend until smooth, adding water as needed to achieve a batter consistency similar to pancake batter.\n\n## Cooking Pesarattu\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and lightly grease it with oil.\n- Pour a ladleful of batter onto the skillet and spread it in a circular motion to form a thin pancake.\n- Drizzle a few drops of oil around the edges.\n- Cook until the edges start to lift slightly and the bottom is golden brown.\n- Optionally, sprinkle chopped onions, coriander leaves, and grated carrot on top, pressing them gently into the pesarattu.\n- Flip carefully and cook the other side for about a minute.\n- Remove from the skillet and serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('311','Anda Ghotala','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon ghee or oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt, to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n\n## For Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n- Onion rings','## Preparation\n- Boil 4 eggs until hard-boiled. Once cooled, peel and roughly chop them.\n- Beat the remaining 2 eggs in a separate bowl and set aside.\n\n## Cooking Instructions\n- Heat ghee or oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add finely chopped onion and green chili, sauté until onion becomes golden brown.\n- Stir in ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell disappears.\n- Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and oil starts separating.\n- Mix in turmeric, red chili powder, coriander powder, and salt. Cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Add the roughly chopped boiled eggs to the masala and mix well.\n- Pour in the beaten eggs and keep stirring until they cook and mix well with the masala.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and chopped coriander leaves. Stir to combine.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with additional coriander leaves, lemon wedges, and onion rings.\n- Serve hot with roti, bread, or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('312','Tandoori Chicken Wings','## Chicken Marinade\n- 2 lbs chicken wings\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons tandoori masala powder\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 tablespoon ground coriander\n- 1 tablespoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional, for extra heat)\n- 1 tablespoon minced garlic\n- 1 tablespoon minced ginger\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro (coriander leaves), chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine the Greek yogurt, lemon juice, olive oil, tandoori masala powder, cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, turmeric, cayenne pepper, garlic, ginger, and salt.\n- Mix well to form a smooth paste.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken Wings\n- Add the chicken wings to the marinade, ensuring they are fully coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight for best results.\n\n## Cook the Chicken Wings\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Line a baking sheet with foil and place a wire rack on top.\n- Arrange the marinated chicken wings on the wire rack.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, flipping halfway through, until the wings are cooked through and have a slight char.\n- For extra char and flavor, you can broil the wings for an additional 2-3 minutes on each side.\n\n## Serve\n- Transfer the wings to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with freshly chopped cilantro and serve with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('313','Kadai Paneer','## Main Ingredients\n- 250 grams paneer, cubed\n- 1 medium green bell pepper, diced\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 medium tomatoes, puréed\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Spice Mix\n- 1 tablespoon coriander seeds\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 2 dried red chilies\n- 1 teaspoon fennel seeds\n- 5 black peppercorns\n- 2 cloves\n\n## Additional Spices\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala','## Prepare the Spice Mix\n- Dry roast coriander seeds, cumin seeds, dried red chilies, fennel seeds, black peppercorns, and cloves in a pan until fragrant.\n- Cool and grind into a coarse powder. Set aside.\n\n## Cook the Vegetables and Paneer\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in ginger-garlic paste and sauté for another minute.\n- Add puréed tomatoes and cook until the oil separates.\n- Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt.\n- Stir in the prepared spice mix and cook for 2 minutes.\n- Add diced bell pepper and cook until slightly tender.\n- Add paneer cubes and mix well.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Sprinkle with garam masala and stir everything well.\n- Cook for another 2-3 minutes on low heat to allow flavors to meld.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves if desired.\n- Serve hot with roti, naan, or steamed rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('314','Soya Keema','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup soya granules\n- 2 tablespoons oil (olive or vegetable)\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, chopped\n- 1 large tomato, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 tablespoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped, for garnish\n\n## For Soaking\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 teaspoon salt','## Preparation\n- Soak the soya granules in 2 cups of water with 1 teaspoon of salt for about 15 minutes.\n- After soaking, drain the water and squeeze out excess moisture from the soya granules.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add finely chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Cook for 2 minutes until the raw smell disappears.\n- Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn soft.\n- Stir in turmeric powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and red chili powder. Cook the spices for a minute.\n- Add the soaked and drained soya granules to the pan. Mix well to coat with spices.\n- Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the soya is well cooked and blended with the spices.\n- Season with salt to taste.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('315','Chicken Keema Paratha','## For the Dough\n- 2 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon oil\n- Water as needed\n\n## For the Chicken Filling\n- 250 grams ground chicken\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped\n- 1 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## For Cooking\n- Oil or ghee for cooking','## Prepare the Dough\n- In a large bowl, mix the whole wheat flour and salt.\n- Add the oil and rub it into the flour.\n- Gradually add water to make a smooth, soft dough.\n- Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for 15-20 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Chicken Filling\n- Heat a tablespoon of oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add the ginger-garlic paste and green chili; sauté for another minute.\n- Add cumin powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder, and salt; cook for a minute.\n- Add the ground chicken and cook until it is no longer pink.\n- Stir in garam masala and cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and mix in the fresh cilantro.\n- Allow the filling to cool slightly.\n\n## Assemble the Paratha\n- Divide the dough into equal-sized balls.\n- Roll out each ball into a small circle on a floured surface.\n- Place some chicken filling in the center of the circle.\n- Fold the edges over the filling and pinch together to seal.\n- Gently roll out the stuffed dough into a larger circle, taking care not to let the filling spill out.\n\n## Cook the Paratha\n- Heat a tawa or skillet over medium heat.\n- Place the rolled paratha on the tawa.\n- Cook until small bubbles appear, then flip the paratha.\n- Drizzle a little oil or ghee around the edges.\n- Cook until both sides are golden brown and crispy.\n- Repeat for the remaining dough and filling.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('316','Kerala Style Fish Curry','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g firm white fish (like kingfish or tilapia), cut into pieces\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil\n- 1 teaspoon mustard seeds\n- 1 teaspoon fenugreek seeds\n- A sprig of curry leaves\n- 1 onion, finely sliced\n- 3 green chilies, slit\n- 2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 tablespoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 2 tablespoons coriander powder\n- 2 cups coconut milk\n- Salt to taste\n- 1-2 tablespoons tamarind paste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped','## Preparation\n- Clean and cut the fish into pieces, and set aside.\n- Extract the coconut milk (or use canned), and mix the tamarind paste in a small bowl with a little water to make it easier to add later.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat coconut oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add mustard seeds and let them crackle. Then add fenugreek seeds and curry leaves.\n- Saute onion until golden brown. Add green chilies and ginger-garlic paste, and saute until the raw smell disappears.\n- Add red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, and salt. Stir well to combine the spices.\n- Pour in the coconut milk and bring to a gentle boil.\n- Add the tamarind paste and stir to mix thoroughly.\n- Gently add the fish pieces to the curry, ensuring they are covered in the sauce.\n- Cover and simmer on low heat for about 10-15 minutes until the fish is cooked through.\n- Check the seasoning and adjust salt if necessary.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('317','Hara Bhara Kabab with Paneer','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup spinach leaves (blanched)\n- 1/2 cup green peas (boiled)\n- 1/2 cup paneer (crumbled)\n- 1 large potato (boiled and mashed)\n- 1/4 cup coriander leaves\n- 1 green chili (chopped)\n- 1 inch ginger (grated)\n\n## Spices and Seasoning\n- 1/2 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/4 teaspoon chaat masala\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste\n\n## Binding and Coating\n- 1/4 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1 tablespoon cornflour\n- 2 tablespoons oil (for shallow frying)','## Preparation\n- Blanch the spinach leaves in boiling water for 2 minutes, then drain and rinse under cold water.\n- In a blender, combine spinach, green peas, coriander leaves, green chili, and ginger. Blend to a coarse paste.\n\n## Mixing the Kabab\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the spinach-pea paste with crumbled paneer and mashed potato.\n- Add cumin powder, garam masala, chaat masala, salt, and black pepper. Mix well.\n- Add breadcrumbs for binding and mix until the mixture is firm and holds shape.\n\n## Shaping and Cooking\n- Divide the mixture into equal portions and shape them into patties.\n- In a shallow bowl, mix cornflour with a bit of water to form a slurry.\n- Dip each patty into the cornflour slurry and coat evenly.\n- Heat oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat.\n- Shallow fry the patties on each side until golden brown and crispy, about 3-4 minutes per side.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot with mint chutney or yogurt dip.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('318','Bhuna Chicken','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 2 medium onions, finely sliced\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 green chili, chopped\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Spice Mix\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- In a bowl, mix the chicken pieces with salt and set aside.\n- Prepare the spice mix: in a small bowl, combine cumin seeds, coriander powder, garam masala, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and black pepper.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add sliced onions and fry until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\n- Stir in the tomatoes and green chili, cooking until the tomatoes soften.\n- Add the prepared spice mix and cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring well.\n- Increase the heat to high and add the chicken pieces.\n- Sauté the chicken until it’s well coated with the masala and starts to brown.\n- Reduce the heat to low, cover the skillet, and let it cook for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally until the chicken is fully cooked and tender.\n- Once the oil starts to separate from the masala, remove the lid and cook for an additional 5 minutes to let the moisture evaporate and the masala cling to the chicken pieces.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.\n- Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('319','Punjabi Dal Makhani','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup whole black lentils (urad dal)\n- 1/4 cup red kidney beans (rajma)\n- 3 cups water\n- 2 tablespoons ghee or oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 teaspoons ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 large tomatoes, pureed\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For Finishing\n- 1/2 cup cream (optional for richness)\n- 1 tablespoon butter\n- Fresh cilantro for garnish','## Preparation\n- Rinse the black lentils and kidney beans thoroughly.\n- Soak them in water overnight or for at least 8 hours.\n\n## Cooking the Dal\n- Drain and rinse the lentils and kidney beans again.\n- In a pressure cooker, add lentils, kidney beans, and 3 cups water.\n- Pressure cook for about 15-20 minutes or until soft.\n\n## Preparing the Masala\n- Heat ghee in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until fragrant.\n- Stir in tomato puree, red chili powder, turmeric, and salt.\n- Cook until the oil separates from the masala.\n\n## Combining and Simmering\n- Add the cooked lentils and kidney beans along with the water in which they were cooked to the masala.\n- Mix well and let it simmer on low heat for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n- Add garam masala and butter, mixing well.\n- Optionally, stir in cream for a richer taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Serve hot with naan or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('320','Malabar Egg Roast','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 hard-boiled eggs\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil\n- 2 large onions, thinly sliced\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 1 sprig curry leaves\n- 1 teaspoon ginger paste\n- 1 teaspoon garlic paste\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Cilantro for garnish\n\n## Spices for Egg Marinade\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste','## Prepare Eggs\n- Peel the hard-boiled eggs and make shallow slits on them.\n- Marinate eggs with turmeric, red chili powder, and salt.\n\n## Cook\n- Heat coconut oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add the marinated eggs and sauté until golden brown. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add sliced onions and sauté until they are golden brown.\n- Add green chilies, curry leaves, ginger paste, and garlic paste. Sauté until the raw smell disappears.\n- Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn soft.\n- Add turmeric, red chili, and coriander powder. Cook until oil separates from the masala.\n- Add salt to taste and return the eggs to the pan.\n- Gently coat the eggs with the masala and simmer for a few minutes.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.\n- Serve hot with rice, chapati, or appam.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('321','Mutton Keema','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g minced mutton\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\n- 2 green chilies, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup green peas\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice','## Preparation\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them crackle for a few seconds.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste and cook for 1-2 minutes until the raw smell disappears.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate.\n- Add green chilies, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and coriander powder. Stir well.\n- Add minced mutton and salt, mix thoroughly ensuring the spices coat the meat evenly.\n- Cover and cook on low heat until the mutton is fully cooked, stirring occasionally (about 20-25 minutes).\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Optional: Add green peas and cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Adjust seasoning if necessary and add lemon juice for extra flavor.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('322','Protein-Rich Khichdi','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 1/2 cup yellow mung dal (split yellow lentils)\n- 2 tablespoons ghee or olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- 5 cups water\n\n## Vegetables\n- 1 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1/2 cup green peas (fresh or frozen)\n- 1 carrot, diced\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Rinse the quinoa and yellow mung dal in cold water until the water runs clear. Drain and set aside.\n- Chop all the vegetables and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat ghee or olive oil in a large pressure cooker or a heavy-bottomed pot over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them sizzle.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\n- Add the ginger-garlic paste and sauté for a minute until the raw smell disappears.\n- Stir in the tomatoes, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Cook until the tomatoes become soft and mushy.\n- Add the chopped spinach, green peas, and diced carrots. Cook for a few minutes until the vegetables are slightly tender.\n- Add the rinsed quinoa and mung dal to the pot. Stir well to combine with the spices and vegetables.\n- Pour in the water and mix everything thoroughly.\n- Close the pressure cooker lid and cook for 3 whistles or cook on a pot until the quinoa and dal are fully cooked and the mixture is thick and creamy, about 25-30 minutes on low heat.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Once cooked, open the lid and check the consistency. Adjust seasoning and add more water if necessary.\n- Sprinkle garam masala and mix well.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('323','Paneer Stuffed Paratha','## Dough\n- 2 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon oil\n- Water as needed\n\n## Paneer Filling\n- 200 grams paneer, grated\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1-2 green chilies, finely chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh coriander, chopped\n\n## Cooking\n- Oil or ghee for cooking','## Prepare Dough\n- In a mixing bowl, combine whole wheat flour and salt.\n- Add oil and mix well.\n- Gradually add water while kneading to form a smooth, soft dough.\n- Cover and let it rest for 20 minutes.\n\n## Prepare Paneer Filling\n- In a bowl, mix grated paneer, chopped onion, green chilies, cumin seeds, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt.\n- Add fresh coriander and mix well.\n\n## Assemble Parathas\n- Divide the dough into equal-sized balls.\n- Roll out one ball into a small circle using a rolling pin.\n- Place a spoonful of paneer filling in the center.\n- Bring the edges together to seal and form a ball.\n- Gently flatten and roll out again to form a paratha.\n\n## Cook Parathas\n- Heat a tawa or skillet over medium heat.\n- Place the rolled paratha on the tawa.\n- Cook for 1-2 minutes until bubbles start forming, then flip.\n- Apply oil or ghee on both sides while cooking until golden brown and crisp.\n- Repeat with remaining dough and filling.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('324','Coconut Shrimp Curry','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon ginger, grated\n- 2 tablespoons curry powder\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 can (14 oz) coconut milk\n- 1 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1 tablespoon fish sauce\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lime wedges','## Preparation\n- In a large pan, heat coconut oil over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onions and sauté until translucent.\n- Stir in the minced garlic and grated ginger, cooking until fragrant.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the curry powder and turmeric, stirring for about 1 minute.\n- Pour in the coconut milk, diced tomatoes, and fish sauce.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n- Bring to a simmer and cook for about 10 minutes to thicken slightly.\n- Add the shrimp and cook until pink and opaque, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro and lime wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('325','Black Eyed Peas Curry','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup dried black-eyed peas\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 inch ginger, grated\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 cup coconut milk\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh cilantro, for garnish\n\n## For Serving\n- Cooked brown rice or quinoa','## Preparation\n- Rinse and soak black-eyed peas in water for at least 4 hours or overnight. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cooking Base\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them sizzle for a few seconds.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in garlic, ginger, and green chili. Cook for another minute.\n\n## Curry\n- Add turmeric, ground coriander, garam masala, and red chili powder to the pot. Stir well.\n- Add diced tomatoes and cook until the mixture thickens.\n- Stir in soaked black-eyed peas, coconut milk, and salt.\n- Add enough water to cover the peas, then bring to a boil.\n- Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 40-45 minutes or until the peas are tender.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Check for seasoning and adjust salt if necessary.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot over cooked brown rice or quinoa for a wholesome meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('326','Grilled Fish with Spices','## Fish and Marinade\n- 4 fish fillets (such as salmon, tilapia, or cod)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish and Serving\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh cilantro (optional)','## Marinate the Fish\n- In a small bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, ground cumin, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper to create a marinade.\n- Place the fish fillets in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over them, ensuring each fillet is well coated.\n- Cover the dish and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Grill the Fish\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the fish from the marinade and place it on the grill.\n- Grill the fish for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until it is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Serve\n- Transfer the grilled fish to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon wedges.\n- Sprinkle with chopped cilantro if using.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('327','Amritsari Macchi','## For the Marinade\n- 500g fish fillets (preferably sole or cod)\n- 2 tablespoons gram flour (besan)\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon carom seeds (ajwain)\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For Frying\n- Oil for frying\n- Lemon wedges for serving\n- Fresh coriander for garnish','## Marinate the Fish\n- Clean and pat dry the fish fillets.\n- In a bowl, mix gram flour, ginger-garlic paste, lemon juice, carom seeds, red chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, and salt.\n- Coat the fish fillets thoroughly with the marinade and let them rest for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Fry the Fish\n- Heat oil in a deep frying pan over medium heat.\n- Once the oil is hot, carefully place the marinated fish fillets in the pan.\n- Fry the fish until they are golden brown and crispy on both sides, about 4-5 minutes per side.\n- Remove the fish from the oil and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the Amritsari Macchi hot, garnished with fresh coriander and lemon wedges.\n- Enjoy it as an appetizer or with your preferred side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('328','Soyabean Sabzi','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup dried soybeans (or 2 cups cooked soybeans)\n- 2 tablespoons oil (preferably olive or canola oil)\n- 1 large onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, chopped (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 1 teaspoon garam masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon asafoetida (hing)\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon','## Preparation\n- If using dried soybeans, soak them overnight and cook until soft, or use canned/cooked soybeans.\n\n## Cooking Instructions\n- Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add asafoetida, then onions, and sauté until golden brown.\n- Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies; sauté for 2 minutes.\n- Add tomatoes and cook until soft.\n- Add turmeric powder, coriander powder, red chili powder, and salt. Mix well.\n- Add the cooked soybeans and mix to coat with the masala.\n- Cover and let it simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.\n- Add garam masala and lemon juice, stir well.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('329','Chana Chaat with Yogurt','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 large tomato, chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1 cucumber, chopped\n- 1 green chili, finely chopped (optional)\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon chaat masala\n- 1/2 teaspoon roasted cumin powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n\n## Yogurt Topping\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black salt (optional)\n- 1/4 teaspoon roasted cumin powder\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Sev or crushed papdi\n- Pomegranate seeds\n- Mint leaves','## Prepare Chana Chaat\n- In a large bowl, combine chickpeas, chopped tomato, onion, cucumber, and green chili.\n- Add chopped cilantro, chaat masala, roasted cumin powder, salt, and lemon juice.\n- Mix well until all the ingredients are fully incorporated.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste, adding more salt or lemon juice if needed.\n\n## Prepare Yogurt Topping\n- In a separate bowl, whisk the Greek yogurt until smooth.\n- Add black salt and roasted cumin powder to the yogurt and mix well.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Assemble the Chaat\n- Divide the chana chaat into serving bowls.\n- Top each with a generous dollop of the seasoned yogurt.\n- Garnish with sev, pomegranate seeds, and mint leaves if desired.\n- Serve immediately to enjoy the fresh flavors.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('330','Chicken 65','## Marinade\n- 500g boneless chicken, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- Salt to taste\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n\n## Coating & Frying\n- 1/4 cup cornflour\n- 1/4 cup rice flour\n- Oil for frying\n\n## Temper & Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 1 teaspoon mustard seeds\n- 8-10 curry leaves\n- 3-4 green chilies, slit\n- 1 tablespoon chopped garlic\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh coriander leaves for garnish','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, mix the Greek yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, salt, and lemon juice.\n- Add the chicken pieces and mix well until evenly coated.\n- Let it marinate for at least 1 hour in the refrigerator.\n\n## Coat and Fry the Chicken\n- Mix cornflour and rice flour in a bowl.\n- Take each marinated chicken piece and lightly coat it with the flour mixture.\n- Heat oil in a deep pan over medium heat.\n- Fry the chicken pieces in batches until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n## Temper and Serve\n- In a separate pan, heat 2 tablespoons of oil.\n- Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add the curry leaves, green chilies, and chopped garlic, sauté until fragrant.\n- Sprinkle red chili powder and salt.\n- Add the fried chicken pieces, toss well to coat with spices.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('331','Tandoori Mushroom Skewers','## Main Ingredients\n- 500g button mushrooms\n- 1 large red onion\n- 1 large green bell pepper\n\n## Marinade\n- 200g Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 tablespoon tandoori masala powder\n- 1 teaspoon cumin powder\n- 1 teaspoon coriander powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Garnish and Serving\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Clean the mushrooms and pat them dry.\n- Cut the onion and bell pepper into chunks similar in size to the mushrooms.\n\n## Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, lemon juice, ginger-garlic paste, tandoori masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, garam masala, salt, and olive oil.\n- Mix well to create a smooth marinade.\n- Add the mushrooms, onion chunks, and bell pepper chunks to the marinade.\n- Coat everything evenly and let it marinate for at least 30 minutes in the refrigerator.\n\n## Cooking\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread marinated mushrooms, onions, and bell peppers onto skewers, alternating between each.\n- Place the skewers on the grill and cook for 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally until the mushrooms are cooked through and slightly charred.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve with lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('332','Masala Oats with Paneer','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 200 grams paneer, cubed\n- 1 tablespoon oil or ghee\n- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tomato, chopped\n- 1 green chili, chopped\n- 1/2 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n\n## Spices\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 2 cups water\n- 2 tablespoons peas (optional)\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped (for garnish)','## Preparation Steps\n- In a pan, heat oil or ghee over medium heat.\n- Add cumin seeds and allow them to sizzle.\n- Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.\n- Stir in ginger-garlic paste and chopped green chili.\n- Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they soften.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Mix well.\n- Add cubed paneer and sauté for 2-3 minutes.\n- Add rolled oats and mix well with the spices.\n- Pour in 2 cups of water and add peas, if using. Stir to combine.\n- Cover and cook on low heat for 5-7 minutes until oats are cooked.\n- Stir in garam masala and adjust salt as per taste.\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('333','Boiled Egg Fry','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon mustard seeds\n- 1 medium onion, finely sliced\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2 green chilies, slit\n- 10-12 curry leaves\n\n## Spices\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\n- 1 teaspoon red chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon garam masala\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh coriander leaves, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Place the eggs in a saucepan and cover them with water. Bring to a boil and let them cook for about 10 minutes.\n- Remove the eggs from heat, drain, and place them in cold water. Peel the shells off and set the eggs aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat the vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.\n- Add the sliced onions and sauté until they are golden brown.\n- Stir in the ginger-garlic paste, green chilies, and curry leaves. Sauté for another 2 minutes.\n- Add the turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for another minute.\n- Slice the boiled eggs in half and add them to the mixture. Gently stir to coat the eggs with the spice mixture.\n- Cook for another 2-3 minutes, ensuring the eggs are well-coated and heated through.\n- Remove from heat.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.\n- Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('334','Balsamic Glazed Chicken','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Balsamic Glaze\n- 1/2 cup balsamic vinegar\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme','## Preparing the Chicken\n- Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper on both sides.\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Add the chicken breasts to the skillet, cooking for about 6-7 minutes on each side or until cooked through and golden brown.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Making the Balsamic Glaze\n- In the same skillet, reduce the heat to medium and add the balsamic vinegar, honey, minced garlic, and Dijon mustard.\n- Stir the mixture, scraping up any brown bits from the bottom of the skillet.\n- Let the glaze simmer until it has reduced and thickened slightly, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the dried thyme.\n\n## Glazing the Chicken\n- Return the chicken to the skillet, turning to coat it in the glaze.\n- Cook for an additional 2 minutes, allowing the chicken to become fully coated and heated through.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the chicken hot, drizzling any remaining glaze over each piece.\n- Optional: Sprinkle with fresh herbs like parsley for garnish.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('335','Grilled Swordfish with Herbs','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 swordfish steaks (6 oz each)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Herb Marinade\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon fresh rosemary, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard','## Prepare the Swordfish\n- Rinse the swordfish steaks under cold water and pat dry with paper towels.\n- Brush both sides of the steaks with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Make the Herb Marinade\n- In a small bowl, combine minced garlic, lemon juice, rosemary, thyme, parsley, and Dijon mustard.\n- Mix well to form a thick paste.\n\n## Marinate the Swordfish\n- Rub the herb marinade mixture onto both sides of the swordfish steaks.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to let the flavors penetrate the fish.\n\n## Grill the Swordfish\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Oil the grill grates to prevent sticking.\n- Place the marinated swordfish steaks on the grill.\n- Grill for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until the fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.\n- Remove from the grill and let rest for a few minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('336','Tuna Stuffed Peppers','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers (any color)\n- 2 cans of tuna in water (5 oz each), drained\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup celery, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Toppings (optional)\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (e.g., cheddar, mozzarella)\n- Chopped fresh herbs for garnish','## Prepare Bell Peppers\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Slice the tops off the peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.\n- Place the peppers in a baking dish, cut side up.\n\n## Prepare Tuna Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine drained tuna, cooked quinoa, Greek yogurt, red onion, celery, parsley, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, and garlic powder.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well combined.\n\n## Stuff and Bake\n- Fill each pepper with the tuna mixture, pressing down slightly to pack it in.\n- If using, sprinkle shredded cheese on top of the stuffed peppers.\n- Cover the baking dish with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the peppers are tender.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove the stuffed peppers from the oven and allow them to cool for a few minutes.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh herbs if desired.\n- Serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('337','Turkey Bolognese','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1 medium carrot, finely chopped\n- 1 celery stalk, finely chopped\n- 1 bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 cup mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) crushed tomatoes\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n- Fresh basil or parsley for garnish (optional)\n\n## To Serve\n- 12 ounces whole grain or zucchini pasta','## Prepare the Sauce\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and garlic, sauté until soft and translucent, about 3 minutes.\n- Add the ground turkey, cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks, about 5-7 minutes.\n\n## Add Vegetables and Simmer\n- Add chopped carrot, celery, bell pepper, and mushrooms to the pan. Sauté for another 5 minutes until vegetables are slightly softened.\n- Stir in the crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n- Reduce the heat and let the sauce simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until it thickens.\n\n## Cook the Pasta\n- While the sauce is simmering, cook the whole grain or zucchini pasta according to package instructions.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Serve the turkey bolognese over the pasta.\n- Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and fresh herbs if desired.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('338','Chicken Pesto Zoodles','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium zucchini\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n\n## Pesto Sauce\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 cloves garlic\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare Zoodles\n- Using a spiralizer, create zucchini noodles from the zucchini set aside.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper.\n- Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add chicken breasts and cook for 6-7 minutes on each side until cooked through and golden brown.\n- Remove from skillet and allow to rest for 5 minutes before slicing into strips.\n\n## Make Pesto Sauce\n- In a food processor, combine basil leaves, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, and garlic. Pulse until finely chopped.\n- With the processor running, slowly add olive oil, blending until smooth.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Combine & Serve\n- In the same skillet used for the chicken, add the zucchini noodles and cherry tomatoes.\n- Sauté for 2-3 minutes until zoodles are slightly tender.\n- Add pesto sauce and sliced chicken to the skillet and toss to combine well.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('339','Italian Tuna Salad','## Base Ingredients\n- 2 cans of tuna in olive oil (5 oz each), drained\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup canned cannellini beans, rinsed and drained\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup black olives, sliced\n- 2 cups arugula or mixed greens\n\n## Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon capers, rinsed','## Prepare the Salad Base\n- In a large bowl, combine the drained tuna, cherry tomatoes, cannellini beans, red onion, black olives, and arugula or mixed greens.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, red wine vinegar, Dijon mustard, honey, minced garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- Pour the dressing over the salad ingredients.\n- Toss gently to combine all ingredients ensuring the dressing is evenly distributed.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Sprinkle chopped parsley and capers over the top of the salad.\n- Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 hours to let flavors meld before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('340','Prosciutto-Wrapped Asparagus','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound fresh asparagus (about 20 spears)\n- 10 slices of prosciutto\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Grated Parmesan cheese\n- Lemon zest','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Wash the asparagus and trim the woody ends.\n\n## Wrapping and Baking\n- Drizzle the asparagus with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Cut each prosciutto slice in half lengthwise.\n- Wrap each asparagus spear with a half slice of prosciutto, starting at the bottom and spiraling to the top.\n- Place the wrapped asparagus on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n\n## Cooking\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the prosciutto is crispy and the asparagus is tender.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and serve warm.\n- Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and lemon zest if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('341','Turkey & Mozzarella Stuffed Peppers','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1 cup marinara sauce\n- 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped fresh basil\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Prepare the Peppers\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove seeds and membranes.\n- Brush the outside of the peppers with olive oil and place them in a baking dish.\n\n## Cook the Filling\n- In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onion and minced garlic, sauté until the onion is translucent.\n- Add ground turkey, cook until browned and cooked through.\n- Stir in cooked quinoa, marinara sauce, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper. Mix well and let simmer for 5 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup of mozzarella cheese.\n\n## Stuff and Cook the Peppers\n- Fill each bell pepper with the turkey mixture.\n- Top each pepper with the remaining mozzarella cheese.\n- Cover the baking dish with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes or until the cheese is bubbly and golden.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly before serving.\n- Garnish with fresh basil and grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('342','Lentil and Sausage Stew','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 pound Italian sausage (turkey or chicken for a healthier option), sliced\n- 1 onion, diced\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper\n- 1 cup green or brown lentils, rinsed\n- 4 cups low-sodium chicken or vegetable broth\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 2 cups kale, chopped\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the sausage slices and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add onion, garlic, carrots, and celery. Sauté until the onion becomes translucent, roughly 5 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Stir in thyme, smoked paprika, and black pepper.\n- Add the lentils, broth, diced tomatoes, and browned sausage to the pot.\n- Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and cover. Simmer for 25-30 minutes or until lentils are tender.\n- Stir in the chopped kale and cook for an additional 5 minutes until the kale is wilted.\n- Taste and adjust salt as necessary.\n\n## Serving\n- Ladle the stew into bowls.\n- Garnish with chopped parsley and grated Parmesan cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('343','Grilled Chicken Panzanella','## For the Grilled Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n\n## For the Panzanella Salad\n- 4 cups rustic bread, cubed (preferably whole grain)\n- 2 large heirloom tomatoes, diced\n- 1 cucumber, sliced\n- 1 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil leaves, torn\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Grill the Chicken\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush the chicken breasts with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning.\n- Grill the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\n- Remove from the grill and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Prepare the Panzanella Salad\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Spread the cubed bread on a baking sheet and toast in the oven for 10-12 minutes, or until crispy and golden.\n- In a large bowl, combine the toasted bread, tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, bell pepper, and basil.\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil and red wine vinegar, then pour over the salad.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste and toss well to combine.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Slice the grilled chicken into strips and serve on top of the panzanella salad.\n- Garnish with additional basil if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('344','Italian Chickpea & Spinach Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, washed\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup sundried tomatoes, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n- Fresh basil leaves (optional)\n- Crusty whole-grain bread (optional)','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the garlic and red onion, sauté until the onion becomes translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add the chickpeas to the skillet and sprinkle with Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5-7 minutes until the chickpeas are slightly crispy.\n- Add cherry tomatoes and sundried tomatoes to the skillet. Cook for another 2-3 minutes until the tomatoes soften.\n- Stir in the fresh spinach and cook until wilted, about 2 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Divide the mixture into bowls.\n- Top with grated Parmesan cheese and fresh basil leaves, if using.\n- Serve with crusty whole-grain bread on the side, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('345','Chicken Florentine','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon unsalted butter\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup chicken broth\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper on both sides.\n- In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken breasts and cook for about 5-7 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, reduce the heat to medium and add 1 tablespoon of butter.\n- Add the minced garlic and sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Pour in the chicken broth, scraping the bottom of the skillet to release any browned bits.\n- Stir in the heavy cream and bring to a gentle simmer.\n- Add the Parmesan cheese and lemon juice, stirring until the cheese melts and the sauce thickens slightly.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the chopped spinach to the sauce and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Return the chicken breasts to the skillet, spooning sauce over the top.\n- Allow the chicken to simmer in the sauce for 5 minutes to absorb the flavors.\n- Serve the Chicken Florentine hot with a side of your choice, such as pasta or rice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('346','Veal Marsala','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 veal cutlets (about 1 pound)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 1 cup sliced mushrooms\n- 1/2 cup Marsala wine\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley','## Preparation\n- Season the veal cutlets with salt and pepper.\n- Dredge the cutlets in flour, shaking off the excess.\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the veal cutlets and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove from skillet and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In the same skillet, add butter and let it melt.\n- Add the sliced mushrooms and sauté for about 5 minutes until they are browned and tender.\n- Pour in the Marsala wine, scraping up any brown bits from the bottom of the skillet.\n- Add the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a simmer.\n- Return the veal cutlets to the skillet, and cook for an additional 5 minutes, spooning some of the sauce over the veal until cooked through.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Transfer the veal cutlets to a serving platter.\n- Increase the heat to thicken the sauce slightly if necessary.\n- Pour the sauce and mushrooms over the veal cutlets.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('347','Shrimp Scampi Zucchini Noodles','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 4 medium zucchini\n- 4 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup chicken broth\n- 1/4 cup lemon juice\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Prepare the Zucchini Noodles\n- Use a spiralizer to cut the zucchini into noodles. Set aside.\n\n## Cook the Shrimp\n- Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add shrimp to the skillet and season with salt and pepper.\n- Cook for about 2-3 minutes on each side, or until shrimp are pink and opaque.\n- Remove shrimp from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Scampi Sauce\n- In the same skillet, add the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Pour in the chicken broth and lemon juice, scraping up any bits from the bottom of the skillet.\n- Stir in the red pepper flakes and let the sauce simmer for 2 minutes.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the zucchini noodles to the skillet and toss them gently in the sauce until slightly softened, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Return the cooked shrimp to the skillet and toss everything together to coat well.\n- Remove from heat, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and fresh parsley.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('348','White Bean & Tuna Salad','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cans (15 oz each) of white beans, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cans (5 oz each) of tuna in water, drained\n- 1 small red onion, finely chopped\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Ingredients\n- Drain and rinse the white beans.\n- Drain the tuna and break it into chunks.\n- Finely chop the red onion.\n- Halve the cherry tomatoes.\n- Dice the cucumber.\n- Chop the fresh parsley.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, minced garlic, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Combine the Salad\n- In a large salad bowl, combine the white beans, tuna, red onion, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and parsley.\n- Pour the dressing over the salad ingredients.\n- Gently toss to combine, ensuring everything is well coated with the dressing.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately, or refrigerate for 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('349','Chicken Marsala','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour (or almond flour for a low-carb version)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 8 ounces cremini mushrooms, sliced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup Marsala wine\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Pound the chicken breasts to even thickness (about 1/2 inch thick).\n- Season the chicken with salt and pepper.\n- Dredge the chicken in flour, shaking off the excess.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken breasts and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side, until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, add the mushrooms and cook for about 5 minutes, until browned and softened.\n- Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute.\n- Pour in the Marsala wine and chicken broth, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.\n- Allow the liquid to simmer and reduce by half, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Finish the Dish\n- Stir in the butter until melted and smooth.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet, turning to coat in the sauce.\n- Simmer for another 2-3 minutes to heat the chicken through.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('350','Broccoli Rabe with Sausage','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound broccoli rabe, trimmed\n- 1 pound Italian turkey sausage, casings removed\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Grated Parmesan cheese\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.\n- Add broccoli rabe and blanch for about 2 minutes until bright green and slightly tender.\n- Drain and immediately transfer to ice water to stop cooking.\n- Once cooled, drain and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes, sauté until fragrant (about 1 minute).\n- Add the sausage, breaking it into small pieces with a spoon.\n- Cook until the sausage is browned and cooked through (about 5-7 minutes).\n- Add the blanched broccoli rabe to the skillet.\n- Sauté together for an additional 3-5 minutes until thoroughly heated.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve warm, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese and lemon wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('351','Italian Sausage-Stuffed Zucchini','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 medium zucchinis\n- 1 lb (450g) Italian sausage (removed from casing)\n- 1/2 cup onion, finely chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup marinara sauce\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n\n## Seasonings\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Garnish (optional)\n- Fresh basil or parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Slice the zucchinis in half lengthwise and scoop out the centers using a spoon or melon baller, leaving about 1/4 inch of the shell. Reserve the scooped zucchini flesh.\n\n## Cooking the Filling\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion, bell pepper, and garlic, sauté for 3-4 minutes until softened.\n- Add the Italian sausage and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon.\n- Stir in the reserved zucchini flesh and cook for another 2 minutes.\n- Add marinara sauce, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.\n- Remove from heat and let it cool slightly.\n\n## Stuffing and Baking\n- Place the zucchini shells in a baking dish, brush with the remaining olive oil, and lightly season with salt and pepper.\n- Fill each zucchini half with the sausage mixture, pressing down gently.\n- Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the stuffed zucchinis.\n- Top with shredded mozzarella cheese.\n- Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake an additional 10 minutes, or until the zucchini is tender and the cheese is bubbly and golden.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and let them cool slightly.\n- Garnish with fresh basil or parsley if desired and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('352','Grilled Eggplant & Chicken Rollatini','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium eggplants, sliced lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, sliced horizontally into 4 thin cutlets\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/2 cup chopped fresh spinach\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 egg, beaten\n- 1 tablespoon fresh basil, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Olive oil for grilling\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n\n## Topping Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese','## Preparation\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush the eggplant slices with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Grill the eggplant slices for about 3-4 minutes on each side until tender. Remove and set aside.\n- Season the chicken cutlets with salt and pepper.\n- In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, spinach, garlic, egg, basil, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Assembly\n- Lay a grilled eggplant slice on a flat surface.\n- Place a chicken cutlet on top of the eggplant.\n- Spread a couple of tablespoons of the ricotta mixture over the chicken.\n- Roll up the eggplant and chicken together, securing with a toothpick if necessary.\n- Repeat with the remaining eggplant slices and chicken.\n\n## Cooking\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Spread half of the marinara sauce on the bottom of a baking dish.\n- Place the rollatini in the dish, seam side down.\n- Pour the remaining marinara sauce over the rollatini.\n- Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top.\n- Cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes.\n- Remove foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes until cheese is bubbly and golden.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly before serving.\n- Serve warm, optionally garnished with extra basil.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('353','Beef and Mushroom Ragù','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb lean ground beef\n- 8 oz mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (28 oz) crushed tomatoes\n- 2 tbsp tomato paste\n- 1/2 cup beef broth\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh parsley, chopped, for garnish\n\n## Optional Serving Ingredients\n- Cooked pasta or zucchini noodles\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onions and minced garlic. Sauté until onions are translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add ground beef to the pan. Cook until browned, breaking it apart with a spatula, about 5-7 minutes.\n\n## Cooking the Ragù\n- Add sliced mushrooms to the beef. Cook until mushrooms are softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in tomato paste, cooking for 1-2 minutes.\n- Pour in the crushed tomatoes and beef broth.\n- Add oregano, basil, salt, and pepper. Mix well.\n- Bring the mixture to a simmer. Reduce heat to low, cover, and let it cook for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.\n- Serve hot over cooked pasta or zucchini noodles.\n- Garnish with chopped parsley and grated Parmesan cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('354','Grilled Shrimp with Italian Herbs','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon lemon zest\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Marinade Preparation\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the olive oil, minced garlic, lemon juice, lemon zest, dried oregano, dried basil, dried thyme, salt, and black pepper.\n\n## Shrimp Preparation\n- Add the shrimp to the bowl with the marinade.\n- Toss to coat the shrimp evenly, then cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Grilling\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated shrimp onto skewers.\n- Grill the shrimp for about 2-3 minutes per side, until they are opaque and cooked through.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove the shrimp from the grill and place them on a serving platter.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and serve with lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('355','Chicken Piccata','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon unsalted butter\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 1/3 cup fresh lemon juice (about 2 lemons)\n- 1/4 cup capers, drained and rinsed\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- Lemon slices, for garnish','## Preparing the Chicken\n- Place chicken breasts between two pieces of plastic wrap and pound to about 1/2 inch thickness.\n- Season both sides of chicken with salt and pepper.\n- Dredge each breast in flour, shaking off the excess.\n\n## Cooking the Chicken\n- Heat olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken breasts to the skillet and cook until golden brown on both sides, about 4-5 minutes per side.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Preparing the Sauce\n- Using the same skillet, add chicken broth, lemon juice, and capers.\n- Bring to a simmer, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet, reduce heat to low, and simmer for about 5 minutes to allow the sauce to thicken slightly.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the chicken to plates and spoon the sauce over the top.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon slices, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('356','Italian Bean Salad with Tuna','## Salad\n- 1 can (15 oz) cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cans (5 oz each) tuna in olive oil, drained\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, red wine vinegar, Dijon mustard, minced garlic, salt, and pepper until well combined.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the cannellini beans, chickpeas, tuna, cherry tomatoes, red onion, olives, and parsley.\n- Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently to coat all ingredients evenly.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning with more salt and pepper if needed.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 hours to allow flavors to meld. Serve chilled or at room temperature.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('357','Tofu Parmigiana','## For the Tofu\n- 1 block (14 oz) firm tofu, pressed\n- 1 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Breading Station\n- 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 eggs, beaten\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (15 oz) tomato sauce\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Assembly\n- 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- Fresh basil leaves (optional)','## Prepare the Tofu\n- Press the tofu block for at least 20 minutes to remove excess moisture.\n- Slice the tofu into 1/2-inch thick slabs.\n\n## Prepare the Breading Station\n- Set up three shallow bowls: one with the flour, one with the beaten eggs, and one with a mixture of breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Bread the Tofu\n- Coat each tofu slab lightly in flour, then dip into the beaten eggs, and finally dredge them in the breadcrumb mixture, pressing to adhere.\n\n## Cook the Tofu\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Place the breaded tofu on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake for 20 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden and crispy.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce\n- In a pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Sauté the minced garlic until fragrant, about 1 minute.\n- Add the tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer for about 10 minutes.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Lower oven temperature to 375°F (190°C).\n- Spread a layer of tomato sauce on the bottom of a baking dish.\n- Arrange baked tofu slices on top, then spread more tomato sauce over them.\n- Sprinkle shredded mozzarella over the tofu.\n- Bake for additional 15 minutes until the cheese is melty and bubbly.\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish with fresh basil before serving (optional).','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('358','Baked Eggplant & Tofu Lasagna','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 large eggplants, sliced lengthwise into 1/4 inch thick slices\n- 16 oz firm tofu, drained and pressed\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 1 bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 zucchini, chopped\n- 1 cup mushrooms, sliced\n- 14 oz canned crushed tomatoes\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups fresh spinach\n- 9 oz no-boil lasagna noodles\n- 1 cup grated mozzarella cheese (or plant-based alternative)\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese (or plant-based alternative)\n\n## Tofu Ricotta\n- 16 oz firm tofu, crumbled\n- 2 tablespoons nutritional yeast\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Eggplants\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Brush the eggplant slices with olive oil and season with salt.\n- Place on a baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes, turning halfway through.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add garlic, onion, bell pepper, zucchini, and mushrooms.\n- Cook until vegetables are tender, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer for 15 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Tofu Ricotta\n- In a bowl, combine crumbled tofu, nutritional yeast, lemon juice, minced garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until well combined and resembles ricotta cheese.\n\n## Assemble the Lasagna\n- Reduce oven temperature to 375°F (190°C).\n- In a baking dish, spread a layer of sauce on the bottom.\n- Layer with lasagna noodles, roasted eggplant, tofu ricotta, spinach, and more sauce.\n- Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of sauce.\n- Top with mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.\n\n## Bake the Lasagna\n- Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.\n- Remove foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.\n- Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('359','Tuscan White Bean Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 carrots, diced\n- 2 celery stalks, diced\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 teaspoon dried rosemary\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 2 (15-ounce) cans cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 4 cups vegetable broth\n- 1 (14-ounce) can diced tomatoes, with juices\n- 2 cups kale, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Parmesan cheese, grated\n- Fresh parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add the onion, garlic, carrots, and celery. Sauté until the vegetables are tender, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the thyme, rosemary, and red pepper flakes. Cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the cannellini beans, vegetable broth, and diced tomatoes to the pot. Stir to combine.\n- Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.\n- Add the chopped kale and continue to simmer for another 10 minutes until the kale is tender.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the soup hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese and fresh parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('360','Chicken Meatballs with Zoodles','## For the Chicken Meatballs\n- 450g ground chicken\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil (for frying)\n\n## For the Zoodles\n- 3 medium zucchinis, spiralized\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Tomato Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (400g) crushed tomatoes\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Chicken Meatballs\n- In a large bowl, combine ground chicken, Parmesan cheese, almond flour, egg, minced garlic, onion powder, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well incorporated.\n- Shape into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown and cooked through, about 7-10 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Zoodles\n- In another skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.\n- Add spiralized zucchini to the pan, sautéing for 3-4 minutes until tender but still crisp.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Prepare the Tomato Sauce\n- In a saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onion and garlic, sautéing until the onion becomes translucent.\n- Stir in crushed tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Let the sauce simmer for 10-15 minutes to allow flavors to meld.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Serve the chicken meatballs over the zoodles.\n- Drizzle with tomato sauce.\n- Garnish with fresh basil or parsley, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('361','Italian-Style Stuffed Cabbage Rolls','## Cabbage Rolls\n- 1 large head of cabbage\n- 1 cup quinoa, rinsed and drained\n- 1 pound lean ground turkey\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh basil\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Tomato Sauce\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (28 ounces) crushed tomatoes\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Cabbage Leaves\n- Bring a large pot of water to a boil.\n- Remove the core from the cabbage and carefully separate the leaves.\n- Blanch leaves in boiling water for 2-3 minutes until pliable, then drain and set aside.\n\n## Make the Filling\n- Cook quinoa according to package instructions and let cool.\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, ground turkey, ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, basil, parsley, garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until thoroughly combined.\n\n## Prepare the Tomato Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Sauté onions and garlic until translucent.\n- Add crushed tomatoes and oregano, and season with salt and pepper.\n- Simmer for 15-20 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Cabbage Rolls\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Place a cabbage leaf on a flat surface and add about 1/4 cup of filling.\n- Roll tightly and tuck in the sides.\n- Place in a baking dish seam-side down.\n\n## Bake the Cabbage Rolls\n- Pour tomato sauce over the cabbage rolls.\n- Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.\n- Uncover and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes until cooked through.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('362','Smoked Salmon Crostini','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 baguette, thinly sliced\n- 8 oz smoked salmon, thinly sliced\n- 4 oz cream cheese, softened\n- 2 tablespoons Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon lemon zest\n- 1 tablespoon capers, drained and rinsed\n- 2 tablespoons fresh dill, chopped\n- Freshly ground black pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh dill sprigs\n- Extra lemon zest\n- Black pepper','## Prepping the Crostini\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Arrange the baguette slices on a baking sheet.\n- Bake for 5-7 minutes until golden and crispy.\n\n## Making the Spread\n- In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, Greek yogurt, lemon juice, and lemon zest.\n- Mix until smooth.\n- Add chopped dill and a sprinkle of black pepper. Mix well.\n\n## Assembling the Crostini\n- Spread the cream cheese mixture over each toasted baguette slice.\n- Top with a slice of smoked salmon.\n- Add a few capers on top of the salmon.\n\n## Garnishing\n- Garnish each crostini with a small sprig of fresh dill, extra lemon zest, and a touch of freshly ground black pepper.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('363','Tomato Basil Chickpea Pasta','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz chickpea pasta\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup tomato paste\n- 1/4 tsp red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Herbs and Garnish\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 2 tbsp nutritional yeast or parmesan cheese (optional)','## Prepare Pasta\n- Cook chickpea pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Make Tomato Sauce\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato paste, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n- Let the sauce simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add cooked pasta to the skillet and toss with the tomato sauce.\n- Stir in chopped basil and parsley. Let it cook for another 2-3 minutes.\n- Serve hot, garnished with nutritional yeast or parmesan, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('364','Spaghetti Squash with Meat Sauce','## Spaghetti Squash\n- 1 large spaghetti squash\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Meat Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound lean ground beef or turkey\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 can (6 oz) tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional)','## Prepare Spaghetti Squash\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Cut the spaghetti squash in half lengthwise and scoop out the seeds.\n- Drizzle olive oil over the cut sides of the squash and season with salt and pepper.\n- Place the squash halves cut-side down on a baking sheet and roast for 30-40 minutes or until tender.\n- Once cooked, use a fork to scrape out the strands of squash into a bowl.\n\n## Prepare Meat Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the ground beef or turkey and cook until browned, breaking it into small pieces.\n- Add the chopped onion and garlic, and sauté until the onion is translucent.\n- Stir in the diced tomatoes (with juice), tomato paste, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer the sauce for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until it thickens.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Divide the spaghetti squash strands among plates.\n- Top each serving with meat sauce.\n- Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese, if using.\n- Serve hot and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('365','Gnocchi with Turkey Sausage','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound gnocchi\n- 1 pound turkey sausage, casings removed\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped\n\n## Garnish (Optional)\n- Freshly grated Parmesan cheese\n- Crushed red pepper flakes','## Preparation Steps\n- Cook the gnocchi according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add onion and garlic, sauté until onion becomes translucent (about 3-4 minutes).\n- Add turkey sausage, cook until browned and crumbled (about 5-7 minutes).\n- Stir in the red and yellow bell peppers, zucchini, and cherry tomatoes. Cook for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n- Add the cooked gnocchi to the skillet and stir to combine.\n- Season with oregano, salt, and pepper. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes to heat through.\n- Remove from heat and stir in fresh basil.\n\n## Serving Instructions\n- Serve hot, optionally topped with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and a sprinkle of crushed red pepper flakes for extra heat.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('366','Seared Scallops with Pesto Zoodles','## For the Scallops\n- 1 pound large sea scallops\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon unsalted butter\n\n## For the Pesto Zoodles\n- 2 medium zucchinis, spiralized\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts\n- 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice','## Prepare the Pesto\n- In a food processor, combine basil leaves, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, and garlic. Pulse until finely chopped.\n- Slowly add olive oil while the processor is running until smooth.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Zoodles\n- Spiralize the zucchinis to create noodles.\n- In a large pan, heat a little olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the zoodles and sauté for 2-3 minutes until just tender.\n- Remove from heat and toss with prepared pesto.\n\n## Sear the Scallops\n- Pat the scallops dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper.\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat until shimmering.\n- Add scallops and sear for 2-3 minutes on each side until a golden crust forms.\n- Add butter to the skillet, tilt the pan, and spoon melted butter over the scallops before removing them from the heat.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Divide the pesto zoodles onto serving plates.\n- Top with seared scallops.\n- Garnish with additional Parmesan and basil, if desired.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('367','Roasted Chicken with Herbs','## For the Chicken\n- 1 whole chicken (about 4 pounds)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n- 2 teaspoons garlic powder\n- 1 tablespoon dried thyme\n- 1 tablespoon dried rosemary\n- 1 tablespoon dried oregano\n- 1 lemon, quartered\n- 3 cloves garlic, crushed\n\n## Optional Glaze\n- 1/4 cup honey\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard','## Preparing the Chicken\n- Preheat your oven to 425°F (220°C).\n- Remove any giblets from the chicken cavity if present.\n- Pat the chicken dry with paper towels.\n\n## Seasoning\n- Rub the chicken with olive oil, salt, pepper, and garlic powder evenly.\n- Mix the dried thyme, rosemary, and oregano in a small bowl, then rub the mixture all over the chicken and inside the cavity.\n- Stuff the cavity with the lemon quarters and crushed garlic cloves.\n\n## Roasting\n- Place the chicken breast-side up on a roasting rack in a roasting pan.\n- Roast in the preheated oven for 1 to 1.5 hours, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C) when measured with a meat thermometer.\n\n## Optional Glaze\n- In a small saucepan, combine honey, lemon juice, and Dijon mustard.\n- Heat over low heat until the mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.\n- Brush the glaze over the chicken during the last 15 minutes of roasting for a sweet, tangy finish.\n\n## Serving\n- Let the chicken rest for 10-15 minutes before carving.\n- Serve with your favorite sides, such as roasted vegetables or a fresh salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('368','Zucchini Noodle Chicken Alfredo','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium zucchinis\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Alfredo Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon butter\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 2/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg (optional)\n\n## Garnish\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley\n- Extra grated Parmesan cheese','## Prepare Zucchini Noodles\n- Wash and trim the ends of the zucchinis.\n- Using a spiralizer, cut the zucchinis into noodle-like shapes.\n- Set aside.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook chicken breasts for about 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and no longer pink inside.\n- Remove from skillet and let rest for a few minutes before slicing into strips.\n\n## Make Alfredo Sauce\n- In the same skillet, melt butter over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in the heavy cream and bring to a gentle simmer.\n- Add Parmesan cheese and stir until the sauce is smooth and thickened.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and nutmeg.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Reduce heat to low and add the zucchini noodles to the sauce, tossing them gently until well coated.\n- Add the sliced chicken and gently mix to combine.\n- Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, allowing the noodles to soften slightly and everything to heat through.\n- Serve immediately, garnished with fresh parsley and extra Parmesan cheese.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('369','Ground Turkey Stuffed Eggplant','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium eggplants\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1 cup diced tomatoes (canned or fresh)\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup bell pepper, diced\n- 1 teaspoon dried Italian herbs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh basil leaves','## Preparing the Eggplant\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the eggplants in half lengthwise and scoop out the flesh, leaving about a 1/4-inch thick shell.\n- Dice the scooped-out eggplant flesh and set aside.\n\n## Cooking the Filling\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and garlic, and sauté until fragrant, about 2 minutes.\n- Add the diced bell pepper and diced eggplant flesh, cooking until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the ground turkey to the skillet, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until fully browned, about 7 minutes.\n- Stir in the diced tomatoes and Italian herbs, and season with salt and pepper.\n- Simmer the mixture for an additional 5 minutes to let the flavors meld together.\n\n## Stuffing and Baking the Eggplants\n- Place the eggplant shells on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Spoon the turkey mixture evenly into each eggplant shell.\n- Top each stuffed eggplant with shredded mozzarella cheese.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, until the eggplant shells are tender and the cheese is golden and bubbly.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly.\n- Garnish with fresh basil leaves, if desired.\n- Serve warm and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('370','Cannellini Bean & Tuna Crostini','## Crostini Base\n- 1 baguette, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Topping\n- 1 can (15 oz) cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (5 oz) tuna in olive oil, drained\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 1 tablespoon capers, rinsed and drained\n- Lemon zest','## Prepare the Crostini\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Brush the baguette slices lightly with olive oil on both sides.\n- Arrange on a baking sheet and bake for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until golden and crisp.\n\n## Make the Topping\n- In a bowl, combine the cannellini beans, tuna, lemon juice, garlic, and parsley.\n- Mash lightly with a fork until well mixed, but still chunky.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Crostini\n- Top each crostini with a generous spoonful of the bean and tuna mixture.\n- Garnish with capers and a pinch of lemon zest.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately while the crostini are still warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('371','Eggplant Ricotta Bake','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 large eggplants, sliced into 1/4-inch rounds\n- 2 cups ricotta cheese\n- 1 egg, beaten\n- 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Olive oil as needed\n\n## Herb Blend\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Lightly salt the eggplant slices and let them sit for 15 minutes, then pat them dry with a paper towel to remove excess moisture and bitterness.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Brush the eggplant slices with olive oil and place them on a baking sheet. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes, flipping the slices halfway through.\n- In a mixing bowl, combine ricotta cheese, beaten egg, half of the Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, and the herb blend.\n- Spread a thin layer of marinara sauce on the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.\n- Place a layer of sliced eggplant on top, followed by a layer of the ricotta mixture, a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese, and a thin layer of marinara sauce. Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used, finishing with a layer of marinara sauce.\n- Top with shredded mozzarella cheese and the remaining Parmesan cheese.\n- Cover with aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Then remove the foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown.\n- Let it rest for 10 minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('372','Italian Turkey Lettuce Wraps','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 zucchini, diced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh basil\n- 8 large lettuce leaves (such as romaine or iceberg)\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Red pepper flakes\n- Extra Parmesan cheese\n- Chopped fresh basil','## Preparing the Turkey Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat.\n- Add finely chopped onion and cook until softened, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Stir in minced garlic and cook for another 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add ground turkey and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in diced red bell pepper, zucchini, and halved cherry tomatoes.\n- Add tomato paste, dried oregano, and dried basil.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Cook until vegetables are tender and the mixture is well combined, about 5 minutes more.\n\n## Assembling the Wraps\n- Spoon the turkey mixture into the center of each lettuce leaf.\n- Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and chopped fresh basil.\n- Add optional toppings if desired, such as red pepper flakes or more Parmesan cheese.\n- Wrap the lettuce around the filling and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('373','Stuffed Artichokes with Quinoa','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large artichokes\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups vegetable broth\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup canned chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1/4 cup parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 lemon, zested and juiced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Steaming Artichokes\n- 4 cups water\n- 1 lemon, halved\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 tablespoon peppercorns','## Prepare the Artichokes\n- Trim the artichokes by cutting off the top third and snipping the tips of the leaves.\n- Rub the cut surfaces with lemon to prevent browning.\n- Remove the small, tough leaves at the bottom.\n\n## Steam the Artichokes\n- In a large pot, combine 4 cups of water, halved lemon, bay leaves, and peppercorns.\n- Place a steaming basket over the pot and arrange the artichokes in the basket, cut side down.\n- Cover and steam for about 20-25 minutes, or until the leaves pull away easily.\n- Once done, set aside to cool slightly.\n\n## Prepare the Stuffing\n- Rinse the quinoa in a fine-mesh sieve under cold water.\n- In a medium saucepan, bring the vegetable broth to a boil.\n- Add the quinoa, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.\n- Fluff quinoa with a fork and transfer to a large bowl.\n- Add cherry tomatoes, chickpeas, parsley, Parmesan cheese, garlic, lemon zest, 1 tablespoon of lemon juice, and 1 tablespoon of olive oil to the quinoa. Mix well.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Stuff and Bake the Artichokes\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Remove the choke (the fuzzy center) from each steamed artichoke with a spoon.\n- Spoon the quinoa mixture into the center of each artichoke and between the leaves.\n- Place the stuffed artichokes in a baking dish, drizzle with remaining olive oil, and cover with foil.\n- Bake for about 15-20 minutes or until heated through and slightly browned on top.\n- Serve warm, garnished with extra parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('374','Italian-Style Lentil Bowls','## Lentils\n- 1 cup green or brown lentils, rinsed\n- 3 cups water\n- 1 bay leaf\n- Salt, to taste\n\n## Vegetable Sauté\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 carrot, diced\n- 1 zucchini, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n\n## Assembly and Toppings\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 2 cups fresh spinach\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar','## Cook Lentils\n- In a medium saucepan, combine lentils, water, and bay leaf.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20-25 minutes until lentils are tender.\n- Drain excess water and season with salt.\n\n## Prepare Vegetable Sauté\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add onion and garlic, sauté for 2-3 minutes until fragrant.\n- Stir in carrot, zucchini, and red bell pepper.\n- Season with salt, pepper, oregano, and basil.\n- Cook for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n\n## Assemble Bowls\n- Divide cooked lentils among serving bowls.\n- Top with sautéed vegetables and fresh spinach.\n- Sprinkle with cherry tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.\n- Drizzle with balsamic vinegar before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('375','Baked Chicken with Mozzarella','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 8 oz fresh mozzarella cheese, sliced\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Seasoning and Herbs\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh basil leaves for garnish','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Pat the chicken breasts dry with paper towels and season with garlic powder, dried basil, dried oregano, salt, and pepper on both sides.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken breasts and sear each side for about 3-4 minutes until golden brown.\n- Remove the skillet from heat and pour the marinara sauce over the chicken breasts.\n- Top each chicken breast with slices of mozzarella cheese.\n- Sprinkle the grated Parmesan cheese over the mozzarella.\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven.\n\n## Baking and Serving\n- Bake for 20-25 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and the cheese is bubbly and golden.\n- Remove from the oven and let it rest for a few minutes.\n- Garnish with fresh basil leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('376','Chicken Sausage & White Bean Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 chicken sausages, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 can (15 oz) white beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups baby spinach\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Grated Parmesan cheese','## Preparation\n- Preheat a large skillet over medium heat and add olive oil.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the chicken sausage slices to the skillet and cook for 5-7 minutes, or until browned. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add the chopped onion and cook for 2-3 minutes until translucent.\n- Add the garlic and red bell pepper, cooking for another 2-3 minutes until soft.\n- Stir in the white beans, dried oregano, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes to heat through and blend flavors.\n- Return the chicken sausages to the skillet, mixing everything together. Cook for an additional 2 minutes.\n- Add the baby spinach to the skillet, stirring until wilted.\n- Finish by adding the lemon juice, stirring well.\n\n## Serve\n- Divide the mixture into four bowls.\n- Optional: Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and grated Parmesan cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('377','Lemon Herb Baked Cod','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 cod fillets (about 6 oz each)\n- 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon lemon zest\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Herb Mixture\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon fresh thyme, chopped\n\n## Garnish\n- Lemon wedges\n- Fresh parsley','## Marinate the Cod\n- In a small bowl, combine lemon juice, olive oil, minced garlic, lemon zest, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the cod fillets in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over them.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.\n\n## Prepare Herb Mixture\n- In a small bowl, mix together chopped parsley, dill, and thyme.\n\n## Bake the Cod\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it.\n- Place the marinated cod fillets on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Sprinkle the herb mixture evenly over the cod fillets.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Serve\n- Transfer the baked cod to serving plates.\n- Garnish with lemon wedges and fresh parsley.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('378','Polenta with Turkey Ragù','## Polenta\n- 1 cup coarse polenta\n- 4 cups water\n- 1 cup skim milk\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Turkey Ragù\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 carrot, finely chopped\n- 1 celery stalk, finely chopped\n- 1 can (14 ounces) crushed tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh parsley for garnish','## Prepare the Polenta\n- In a saucepan, bring water and milk to a boil.\n- Gradually whisk in polenta, reduce heat to low, and cook, stirring frequently, until thickened (about 30 minutes).\n- Stir in Parmesan cheese, season with salt and pepper, and keep warm.\n\n## Make the Turkey Ragù\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add ground turkey and cook until browned, breaking it apart with a spoon.\n- Add onion, garlic, carrot, and celery, cooking until softened.\n- Stir in crushed tomatoes, chicken broth, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer uncovered for 20-25 minutes until the sauce thickens.\n- Adjust seasonings to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Spoon the cooked polenta onto plates.\n- Top with turkey ragù.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('379','Grilled Portobello Mushrooms with Ricotta','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large portobello mushrooms\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Ricotta Filling\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh basil, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparing the Portobello Mushrooms\n- Remove the stems from the portobello mushrooms and wipe the caps clean with a damp cloth.\n- Brush both sides of the mushrooms with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Making the Ricotta Filling\n- In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, grated Parmesan, minced garlic, chopped basil, and chopped parsley.\n- Season the ricotta mixture with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Grilling the Mushrooms\n- Preheat the grill to medium heat.\n- Place the mushrooms, gill side down, on the grill.\n- Grill for about 5 minutes, or until they start to soften.\n- Flip the mushrooms and fill each with a generous amount of the ricotta mixture.\n- Continue grilling for another 5-7 minutes, until the cheese is heated through and the mushrooms are tender.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('380','Parmesan-Crusted Tilapia','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 tilapia fillets\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 lemon, cut into wedges\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon zest','## Prepare the Ingredients\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it with olive oil.\n- In a shallow bowl, combine the grated Parmesan cheese, breadcrumbs, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix well.\n\n## Coat the Tilapia\n- Rinse the tilapia fillets under cold water and pat them dry with a paper towel.\n- Brush each fillet lightly with olive oil, then press each side into the Parmesan mixture, ensuring an even coating.\n\n## Bake\n- Place the coated tilapia fillets on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork. The coating should be golden brown.\n\n## Serve and Garnish\n- Remove the fillets from the oven and transfer them to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with freshly chopped parsley and lemon zest, if desired.\n- Serve with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('381','Tofu & Spinach Stuffed Shells','## Stuffed Shells\n- 12 jumbo pasta shells\n- 14 oz firm tofu, drained and crumbled\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1/4 cup nutritional yeast\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Tomato Sauce\n- 2 cups tomato sauce\n- 1 teaspoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Toppings\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n- Fresh basil leaves for garnish','## Prepare the Pasta\n- Cook the jumbo pasta shells according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine the crumbled tofu, chopped spinach, nutritional yeast, minced garlic, lemon juice, dried basil, salt, and pepper. Mix well until thoroughly blended.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce\n- In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add tomato sauce, dried oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Stir well and simmer for 5 minutes.\n\n## Assemble\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce on the bottom of a baking dish.\n- Stuff each shell with the tofu and spinach mixture and place them in the dish.\n- Pour the remaining tomato sauce over the stuffed shells.\n- Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if using.\n\n## Bake\n- Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes until bubbly and golden.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('382','Italian-Style Baked Chicken Thighs','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 teaspoon dried rosemary\n- 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 lemon, sliced\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n\n## For Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Pat the chicken thighs dry with paper towels to remove excess moisture.\n\n## Seasoning the Chicken\n- In a small bowl, mix olive oil, minced garlic, oregano, basil, thyme, rosemary, crushed red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n- Rub the oil and herb mixture evenly over the chicken thighs, ensuring they are well-coated.\n\n## Baking\n- Arrange the chicken thighs on a baking sheet lined with foil or parchment paper, skin-side up.\n- Place lemon slices around and under the chicken thighs.\n- Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese evenly over the chicken.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 35-40 minutes, or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C) and the skin is golden and crispy.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Once done, remove the chicken from the oven and let it rest for about 5 minutes.\n- Garnish with freshly chopped parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('383','Ricotta & Turkey Baked Ziti','## Main Ingredients\n- 12 oz ziti pasta\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound lean ground turkey\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Sauce and Cheese\n- 2 cups marinara sauce\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cook the ziti according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Turkey\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the ground turkey and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the minced garlic, oregano, basil, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper. Cook for another 1-2 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- In a large bowl, combine the cooked ziti, turkey mixture, and marinara sauce. Mix well.\n- In a separate bowl, combine ricotta cheese and the egg. Mix until smooth.\n- In a baking dish, spread half of the ziti mixture.\n- Spread the ricotta mixture over the ziti.\n- Top with half of the mozzarella cheese.\n- Add the remaining ziti mixture, and top with the rest of the mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.\n\n## Bake\n- Cover with aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for another 10-15 minutes, or until the cheese is golden and bubbly.\n- Let it cool for a few minutes before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('384','Chickpea Pasta Primavera','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz chickpea pasta\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cup broccoli florets\n- 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 lemon, juiced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh basil, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese (optional)\n\n## Optional Protein Add-ins\n- 1 cup cooked chicken breast, sliced\n- 1 cup cooked shrimp','## Prepare the Pasta\n- Cook chickpea pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Vegetables\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Add sliced bell peppers, zucchini, and broccoli florets. Cook for 5-7 minutes until tender-crisp.\n- Stir in cherry tomatoes and Italian seasoning. Cook for an additional 2 minutes.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add cooked pasta to the vegetable mixture in the skillet. Toss to combine.\n- Drizzle with lemon juice and add chopped basil.\n- Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.\n- For additional protein, top with sliced chicken or cooked shrimp.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('385','Grilled Chicken Tostadas','## For the Grilled Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Tostadas\n- 8 corn tostada shells\n- 1 can refried black beans (15 oz)\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/2 cup queso fresco or crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges','## Prepare the Chicken\n- In a small bowl, mix olive oil, cumin, smoked paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Rub the mixture over the chicken breasts evenly.\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Grill the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\n- Remove from the grill and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing into thin strips.\n\n## Assemble the Tostadas\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Place tostada shells on a baking sheet and bake for 5 minutes until slightly crispy.\n- Heat the refried beans in a small saucepan over low heat until warm.\n- Spread a layer of refried beans on each tostada shell.\n- Top with sliced grilled chicken, shredded lettuce, cherry tomatoes, red onion, cilantro, avocado slices, and queso fresco.\n- Serve immediately with lime wedges for squeezing over the top.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('386','Bistec a lo Pobre','## Steak\n- 2 ribeye steaks (about 8 oz each)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Toppings\n- 2 large eggs\n- 2 ripe plantains\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil (for frying)\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Accompaniments\n- 4 cups cooked white rice\n- 2 large russet potatoes\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil (for frying)\n- Salt to taste','## Prepare the Steak\n- Season both sides of the steaks with salt and pepper.\n- Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the steaks for about 4-5 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.\n- Remove from skillet and let rest.\n\n## Fry the Plantains\n- Peel and slice the plantains into 1/2-inch thick slices.\n- Heat vegetable oil in a separate pan over medium heat.\n- Fry the plantain slices until golden brown on both sides, about 3-4 minutes per side.\n- Remove and season with salt.\n\n## Prepare the Fries\n- Peel and cut the potatoes into thick fries.\n- Heat vegetable oil in a deep pan or fryer to 350°F (175°C).\n- Fry the potato pieces until golden and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Remove and season with salt.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- In the same pan used for the steaks, fry the eggs sunny-side up or to desired doneness.\n\n## Assembly\n- Divide the cooked rice between two plates.\n- Top each with a cooked steak.\n- Add the fried plantains and fries on the side.\n- Top with a fried egg.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('387','Peruvian Grilled Chicken','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup lime juice\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 tablespoon paprika\n- 1 tablespoon oregano\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Chicken\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts (about 2 lbs total)\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Lime wedges\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a medium bowl, whisk together olive oil, soy sauce, lime juice, garlic, cumin, paprika, oregano, honey, salt, and black pepper until well combined.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken\n- Place chicken breasts in a large resealable plastic bag or shallow dish.\n- Pour the marinade over the chicken, ensuring all pieces are well coated.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or overnight for best results.\n\n## Grill the Chicken\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the chicken from the marinade, allowing excess to drip off, and discard the marinade.\n- Place the chicken on the grill and cook for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C) and the chicken is golden brown and charred in spots.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove the chicken from the grill and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.\n- Serve with lime wedges and garnish with chopped fresh cilantro, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('388','Huevos Rancheros','## For the Ranchero Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and chopped\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## For the Huevos Rancheros\n- 4 large eggs\n- 4 corn tortillas\n- 1 cup black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup crumbled queso fresco or feta cheese\n- Fresh cilantro leaves, for garnish','## Make the Ranchero Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in garlic and jalapeño, cooking for another minute.\n- Add diced tomatoes and cumin, then simmer for 10-15 minutes until slightly thickened.\n- Season with salt and pepper, then stir in cilantro.\n\n## Cook the Huevos Rancheros\n- Warm black beans in a small pot over low heat.\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and lightly oil it.\n- Fry the eggs to your liking (sunny-side up is traditional).\n- In another pan, warm the corn tortillas until pliable.\n- Place each tortilla on a plate, and layer with black beans, an egg, ranchero sauce, avocado slices, and cheese.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and extra sauce, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('389','Pollo Guisado','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 lbs chicken thighs, bone-in and skinless\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 1/2 cups chicken broth\n- 1 can (15 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup tomato sauce\n- 2 teaspoons ground cumin\n- 2 teaspoons paprika\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 2 bay leaves\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Lime wedges\n- Fresh cilantro leaves','## Preparation\n- Season chicken thighs with salt and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat.\n\n## Cooking\n- Brown the chicken thighs on all sides, about 5-7 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add the onion and sauté until translucent.\n- Add red and green bell peppers and cook until softened, around 4-5 minutes.\n- Add garlic and sauté for another 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Stir in chicken broth, diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, cumin, paprika, oregano, and bay leaves.\n- Return the chicken to the pot and submerge in the sauce.\n- Bring to a boil, then lower the heat to a simmer.\n- Cover and cook for 30 minutes until the chicken is tender and cooked through.\n- Remove bay leaves. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper, if needed.\n- Stir in fresh cilantro before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot with lime wedges and additional cilantro leaves for garnish if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('390','High-Protein Carne Asada Bowl','## For the Carne Asada\n- 1 lb flank steak\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup lime juice\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Bowl\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1 cup black beans, canned or cooked\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 2 tbsp Greek yogurt\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges','## Prepare the Carne Asada\n- In a bowl, combine minced garlic, soy sauce, lime juice, olive oil, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the flank steak in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over it. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.\n- Preheat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Remove the steak from the marinade and grill for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until desired doneness is reached.\n- Let the steak rest for 5 minutes before slicing against the grain.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Divide the cooked quinoa among four bowls.\n- Top each bowl with sliced carne asada, black beans, cherry tomatoes, avocado slices, and red onion.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and a dollop of Greek yogurt.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('391','Cuban Mojo Pork','## Pork and Marinade\n- 4 lbs pork shoulder (boneless)\n- 8 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup fresh orange juice\n- 1/2 cup fresh lime juice\n- 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 2 teaspoons dried oregano\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 tablespoon salt\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 cup olive oil\n\n## Garnish and Serving\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Sliced red onions\n- Lime wedges','## Step 1: Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine minced garlic, orange juice, lime juice, lemon juice, dried oregano, ground cumin, salt, and pepper.\n- Slowly whisk in the olive oil until well combined.\n\n## Step 2: Marinate the Pork\n- Place the pork shoulder in a large resealable plastic bag or a deep dish.\n- Pour the marinade over the pork, making sure it is fully submerged or well-coated.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight for maximum flavor.\n\n## Step 3: Cook the Pork\n- Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).\n- Remove the pork from the marinade and place it in a roasting pan.\n- Roast in the oven for 30 minutes, then reduce the heat to 375°F (190°C).\n- Continue roasting for 2 hours, or until the internal temperature reaches 145°F (63°C).\n- Baste the pork with the marinade occasionally while roasting.\n\n## Step 4: Rest and Serve\n- Remove the pork from the oven and let it rest for 15 minutes.\n- Slice or shred the pork and transfer to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro, sliced red onions, and lime wedges before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('392','Arepas with Chicken and Avocado','## Arepas\n- 2 cups pre-cooked white cornmeal (harina PAN)\n- 2 1/2 cups warm water\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n\n## Chicken Filling\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Avocado Topping\n- 2 ripe avocados\n- 1 lime, juiced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional\n- Cilantro for garnish\n- Hot sauce for serving','## Prepare Arepas\n- In a bowl, mix the cornmeal, warm water, and salt until a dough forms.\n- Divide the dough into 8 portions and shape each into a disk about 1/2-inch thick.\n- Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook each arepa for 5 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and slightly crispy.\n- Transfer to an oven preheated to 350°F (175°C) for 10 more minutes to finish cooking.\n\n## Cook Chicken\n- Season chicken breasts with cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side until fully cooked and golden brown.\n- Let chicken rest for a few minutes before shredding it with two forks.\n\n## Prepare Avocado Topping\n- Mash avocados in a bowl and mix with lime juice, salt, and pepper.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste.\n\n## Assemble Arepas\n- Slice each arepa open and fill with shredded chicken.\n- Top with avocado mixture.\n- Garnish with cilantro and add hot sauce if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('393','Arroz con Pollo','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 1/2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs (cut into bite-sized pieces)\n- 1 cup long-grain white rice\n- 2 cups chicken broth\n- 1 cup bell peppers (mixed colors, diced)\n- 1 medium onion (diced)\n- 3 cloves garlic (minced)\n- 1 cup frozen peas\n- 1/2 cup tomato sauce\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1/2 tsp paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro (chopped)\n- Lime wedges','## Preparation\n- Season the chicken pieces with salt, pepper, cumin, and paprika.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet or pot over medium-high heat.\n- Add the chicken pieces and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the chicken and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add another tablespoon of olive oil and sauté the onions, garlic, and bell peppers until softened, about 4-5 minutes.\n- Stir in the rice, mixing well to coat it with the oil and vegetables.\n- Add the tomato sauce and chicken broth to the skillet and bring to a boil.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet, reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.\n- After 15 minutes, scatter the peas on top of the rice and chicken, cover, and continue cooking for the remaining 5 minutes or until the rice is tender and has absorbed the liquid.\n\n## Serving\n- Fluff the rice with a fork, garnish with chopped cilantro, and serve with lime wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('394','Steak Picado','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb flank steak, cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 1 bell pepper, diced (any color)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 Roma tomatoes, diced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup beef broth\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Lime wedges\n- Sliced avocado\n- Chopped scallions','## Preparation Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the steak pieces in batches, browning them on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add the onions and bell peppers. Sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the garlic, diced tomatoes, and jalapeño, and continue to cook for another 2 minutes, stirring frequently.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Return the steak to the pan, along with the cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Pour in the beef broth, stirring to combine.\n- Lower the heat to a simmer, cover, and cook for about 15 minutes, or until the steak is tender and cooked through.\n\n## Serving Steps\n- Sprinkle the chopped cilantro over the top before serving.\n- Serve hot with optional garnishes such as lime wedges, sliced avocado, and chopped scallions.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('395','Mexican Chicken Skillet','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast, diced\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup canned black beans, rinsed and drained\n- 1 cup canned corn, drained\n- 1 cup diced tomatoes (canned or fresh)\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheese (optional, use a high-protein cheese)','## Preparation\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the diced chicken to the skillet and season with salt and pepper. Cook for about 6-8 minutes until the chicken is browned and cooked through.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add the chopped onion, red bell pepper, and green bell pepper. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are soft.\n- Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.\n- Return the chicken to the skillet. \n- Stir in the black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, cumin, and chili powder.\n- Simmer for 5-7 minutes until everything is heated through and well combined.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro, sliced avocado, and lime wedges. Add shredded cheese if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('396','Huevos a la Mexicana','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 1 medium tomato, finely chopped\n- 1-2 jalapeño peppers, finely chopped (seeded for less heat)\n- Salt to taste\n- Pepper to taste\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped (optional)','## Preparation\n- Crack the eggs into a bowl and beat them lightly. Set aside.\n- Heat the olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add the chopped onion to the skillet and sauté for about 2-3 minutes until translucent.\n- Add the chopped tomato and jalapeño to the skillet and cook for another 2-3 minutes until the tomato softens.\n- Pour the beaten eggs over the vegetables. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Stir occasionally until the eggs are cooked to your desired consistency, about 3-4 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the huevos a la mexicana to a serving plate.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('397','Chipotle Chicken Stuffed Peppers','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers (any color)\n- 1 lb ground chicken\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, rinsed and drained\n- 1 cup corn kernels (fresh, frozen, or canned)\n- 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Mexican blend)\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons chipotle sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Sour cream\n- Sliced avocado\n- Lime wedges','## Preparing the Peppers\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.\n- Place the peppers in a baking dish, cut side up. Drizzle with a little olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Bake for about 10 minutes to slightly soften the peppers.\n\n## Cooking the Filling\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, add the olive oil.\n- Add the onion and garlic, sautéing until translucent, about 3 minutes.\n- Add the ground chicken, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until browned, about 6-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the chipotle sauce, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, and half of the cheese. Mix until well combined.\n\n## Stuffing and Baking the Peppers\n- Spoon the chicken and quinoa mixture into each bell pepper until full.\n- Top with the remaining cheese.\n- Bake in the oven for 15-20 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the peppers are tender.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.\n- Top with optional toppings like chopped cilantro, sour cream, sliced avocado, and lime wedges before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('398','Cuban Picadillo','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound lean ground beef\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (8 oz) tomato sauce\n- 1/4 cup dry white wine (optional)\n- 1/4 cup sliced green olives\n- 1/4 cup raisins\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## To Serve\n- Cooked white rice or quinoa (optional)','## Preparation\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onions and bell peppers; sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in garlic and cook for an additional minute.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add ground beef to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spoon, until browned and cooked through.\n- Stir in tomato sauce and wine (if using), mixing well.\n- Add olives, raisins, cumin, oregano, salt, pepper, and bay leaves.\n- Lower the heat to a simmer, cover, and let cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n- Remove bay leaves and stir in fresh cilantro before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot over cooked white rice or quinoa if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('399','Carne Guisada','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 lbs beef stew meat, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 cups beef broth\n- 1 cup water\n- 1 large green bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 large red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes with green chilies\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 tablespoon chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Thickening\n- 2 tablespoons cornstarch\n- 2 tablespoons water\n\n## Garnish (optional)\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lime wedges','## Preparation\n- Season the beef with salt and pepper.\n- In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat.\n- Brown the meat in batches, making sure not to overcrowd the pot.\n- Remove the meat and set aside.\n\n## Cooking\n- In the same pot, add the onion and garlic, saute until the onion is translucent.\n- Return the beef to the pot, and add beef broth, water, bell peppers, diced tomatoes, tomato paste, cumin, chili powder, and oregano.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 1.5 to 2 hours or until beef is tender.\n\n## Thickening\n- Mix cornstarch and water in a small bowl until smooth.\n- Add the cornstarch mixture to the pot, stirring well until the sauce is thickened.\n- Cook for an additional 5 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro and lime wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('400','Grilled Tilapia Tacos','## For the Tilapia Marinade\n- 4 tilapia fillets\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 lime, juiced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Tacos\n- 8 corn tortillas\n- 1 cup shredded cabbage or coleslaw mix\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta or queso fresco\n- Lime wedges for serving\n\n## For the Sauce\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 teaspoon hot sauce\n- 1 lime, juiced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Marinate the Tilapia\n- In a small bowl, combine olive oil, lime juice, garlic, cumin, chili powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the tilapia fillets in a resealable plastic bag or shallow dish and pour the marinade over them.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to 1 hour.\n\n## Grill the Tilapia\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Lightly oil the grill grates to prevent sticking.\n- Remove tilapia from the marinade and place on the grill.\n- Grill for 3-4 minutes on each side or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, hot sauce, lime juice, salt, and pepper.\n- Stir until well combined and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Tacos\n- Warm the corn tortillas on the grill for about 30 seconds on each side or until pliable.\n- Place a portion of grilled tilapia in each tortilla.\n- Top with shredded cabbage, cilantro, avocado slices, and crumbled cheese.\n- Drizzle with the prepared yogurt sauce.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('401','Chili Lime Shrimp Salad','## For the Shrimp\n- 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Juice of 1 lime\n\n## For the Salad\n- 4 cups mixed salad greens (e.g., romaine, spinach, arugula)\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## For the Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- Juice of 2 limes\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Shrimp\n- In a large bowl, combine shrimp, olive oil, chili powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, pepper, and lime juice.\n- Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add shrimp to the skillet and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until shrimp are opaque and cooked through.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lime juice, honey, garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large salad bowl, combine salad greens, cherry tomatoes, avocado, red onion, and cilantro.\n- Add the cooked shrimp on top of the salad.\n- Drizzle with dressing and toss gently to combine.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('402','Ensalada de Pollo (Chicken Salad)','## Salad Ingredients\n- 2 cups grilled chicken breast, diced\n- 4 cups mixed greens (such as romaine, spinach, and arugula)\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup cucumber, sliced\n- 1/4 cup almonds, toasted and chopped\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n\n## Dressing Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon white wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, white wine vinegar, Dijon mustard, and minced garlic.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the diced chicken breast, mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, red onion, and cucumber.\n- Toss gently to mix the ingredients well.\n\n## Dress the Salad\n- Drizzle the prepared dressing over the salad.\n- Toss the salad lightly to ensure even coating with the dressing.\n\n## Garnish and Serve\n- Sprinkle the top of the salad with toasted almonds and crumbled feta cheese.\n- Serve immediately for the freshest taste.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('403','Mexican Lentil Soup','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup green or brown lentils, rinsed and drained\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 carrot, diced\n- 1 celery stalk, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon chili powder\n- 6 cups vegetable broth\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh cilantro\n- Avocado slices\n- Lime wedges\n- Crumbled queso fresco','## Prepare Ingredients\n- Rinse and drain the lentils under cold water.\n- Chop the onion, carrot, celery, and red bell pepper.\n- Mince the garlic and jalapeño.\n\n## Cook the Soup\n- In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add onion, garlic, carrot, celery, red bell pepper, and jalapeño. Sauté for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are softened.\n- Stir in cumin, smoked paprika, oregano, and chili powder. Cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Add lentils, vegetable broth, and diced tomatoes with their juices.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 25-30 minutes until lentils are tender.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serve the Soup\n- Ladle soup into bowls.\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro, avocado slices, lime wedges, and crumbled queso fresco as desired.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('404','Albondigas Soup','## For the Meatballs\n- 1 lb lean ground beef or turkey\n- 1/4 cup uncooked rice\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n- 1/4 cup chopped onion\n- 1 egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n\n## For the Soup\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 carrots, sliced\n- 2 zucchinis, sliced\n- 1 bell pepper, chopped\n- 6 cups beef or chicken broth\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1/2 tsp dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Meatballs\n- In a large bowl, combine ground beef or turkey, rice, cilantro, onion, egg, garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until just combined; do not overwork.\n- Form into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.\n\n## Prepare the Soup\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add onion and garlic, and sauté until softened, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add carrots, zucchinis, and bell pepper, cooking for another 5 minutes.\n- Pour in broth and diced tomatoes. Stir in cilantro, cumin, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer.\n- Carefully add the meatballs to the soup.\n- Cover and let simmer for 25-30 minutes, until meatballs are cooked through and rice is tender.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary.\n- Serve hot, garnished with extra cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('405','Tofu Sofritas','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 block (14 oz) extra-firm tofu\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n\n## Sauce Ingredients\n- 1 chipotle pepper in adobo sauce\n- 1 tablespoon adobo sauce\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup vegetable broth\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Lime wedges\n- Avocado slices\n- Chopped green onions','## Prepare the Tofu\n- Press the tofu to remove excess moisture. Wrap the tofu block in a clean kitchen towel and place something heavy on top for at least 15 minutes.\n- After pressing, crumble the tofu into small pieces resembling ground meat.\n\n## Cook the Tofu\n- In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the crumbled tofu and cook until browned and slightly crispy, about 8-10 minutes. Stir occasionally.\n- Remove the tofu from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil.\n- Sauté the onions and red bell pepper until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.\n\n## Combine and Simmer\n- Add the chipotle pepper, adobo sauce, tomato paste, cumin, smoked paprika, coriander, soy sauce, maple syrup, and vegetable broth to the skillet.\n- Stir well to combine and bring to a simmer.\n- Return the cooked tofu to the skillet and stir to coat with the sauce.\n- Simmer for 5-7 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.\n\n## Serve\n- Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Serve the sofritas hot, garnished with cilantro, lime wedges, avocado slices, and green onions, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('406','Carne Mechada (Shredded Beef)','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 lbs beef chuck roast\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup beef broth\n- 1/2 cup tomato sauce\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 bay leaves\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Lime wedges','## Preparation\n- Season the beef chuck roast with salt, pepper, cumin, and paprika.\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Sear the beef on all sides until browned.\n\n## Cooking\n- Remove beef and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add chopped onions, red and green bell peppers, and garlic. Sauté until onions are translucent.\n- Return the beef to the pot. Add beef broth, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, and bay leaves.\n- Cover and simmer on low heat for 3-4 hours until beef is tender and easily shredded.\n\n## Shredding and Serving\n- Remove the beef from the pot and shred using two forks.\n- Return shredded beef to the pot and mix well with the sauce.\n- Cook for an additional 10 minutes to let the flavors meld.\n- Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro and lime wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('407','Chicken Arepas','## Arepa Ingredients\n- 2 cups pre-cooked cornmeal (masarepa)\n- 2 1/2 cups warm water\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon oil (vegetable or olive oil)\n\n## Chicken Filling Ingredients\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon pepper\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1 cup low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 bell pepper, diced\n- 1/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 lime, juiced\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Avocado slices\n- Diced tomatoes\n- Sour cream or Greek yogurt\n- Hot sauce','## Prepare the Arepas\n- In a large bowl, mix the cornmeal, warm water, and salt until a dough forms.\n- Let the dough rest for about 5 minutes.\n- Divide the dough into 8 equal portions and shape them into discs about 1/2 inch thick.\n- Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the arepas for about 5–7 minutes on each side until golden brown.\n- Place them on a baking sheet and finish cooking in a preheated oven at 350°F (175°C) for 10 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Chicken Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Season chicken with salt, pepper, cumin, and paprika.\n- Cook the chicken in the skillet for about 5 minutes per side until browned but not fully cooked.\n- Remove chicken and shred it using two forks.\n- In the same skillet, add onion, garlic, and bell pepper, and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Return the shredded chicken to the skillet.\n- Add chicken broth and simmer until most of the liquid is absorbed and the chicken is fully cooked, about 10 minutes.\n- Stir in cilantro and lime juice.\n\n## Assemble Arepas\n- Slice the cooked arepas open to create pockets.\n- Stuff each arepa with the chicken filling.\n- Add optional toppings such as avocado slices, diced tomatoes, or sour cream.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('408','Taco Stuffed Zucchini Boats','## Zucchini Boats\n- 4 medium zucchinis\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Taco Filling\n- 1 pound ground turkey or lean ground beef\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon oregano\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 cup canned black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup salsa\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese or Monterey Jack cheese\n- 2 green onions, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 jalapeño, sliced\n- Sour cream','## Prepare Zucchini Boats\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Slice zucchinis in half lengthwise and scoop out the seeds to create a boat shape.\n- Brush the inside with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Place the zucchini halves on a baking sheet, cut side up.\n\n## Cook Taco Filling\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the onion and bell pepper, sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.\n- Add ground turkey or beef and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon.\n- Stir in chili powder, cumin, paprika, oregano, and black pepper.\n- Add black beans and salsa, stir to combine and simmer for 5 minutes.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Spoon the taco filling evenly into each zucchini boat.\n- If desired, sprinkle cheese on top of each boat.\n- Cover the baking sheet with foil and bake for 20 minutes.\n- Uncover and bake for an additional 10 minutes, or until the zucchinis are tender.\n\n## Serve\n- Top with green onions, cilantro, jalapeño slices, and a dollop of sour cream, if desired.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('409','Spicy Black Bean Tofu Tacos','## Taco Filling\n- 14 oz (400g) extra-firm tofu\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 cup canned black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 small red onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Taco Assembly\n- 8 small corn tortillas\n- 1/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1/4 cup lime juice\n- 1 ripe avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup salsa of choice\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt','## Prepare the Tofu\n- Press the tofu to remove excess water, then crumble it into small pieces.\n\n## Cook the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion, garlic, and bell pepper. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until softened.\n- Stir in the crumbled tofu and cook for another 5 minutes until slightly golden.\n- Add black beans, soy sauce, chili powder, smoked paprika, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Cook for an additional 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until everything is well combined and heated through.\n\n## Assemble Tacos\n- Warm the corn tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave.\n- Divide the tofu mixture among the tortillas.\n- Top with fresh cilantro, avocado slices, a spoonful of salsa, and a dollop of Greek yogurt.\n- Drizzle with lime juice before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('410','Mexican Tofu Breakfast Scramble','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 block (14 oz) firm tofu, drained and crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeds removed and minced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Toppings and Garnish\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n- 2 tablespoons nutritional yeast (optional)','## Preparation Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add diced onion, bell pepper, and jalapeño to the skillet. Sauté for about 5 minutes until the vegetables are softened.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for another 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in cumin, turmeric, salt, and pepper.\n- Add crumbled tofu to the skillet and stir well to combine with the spices and vegetables.\n- Cook for about 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the tofu is heated through and slightly golden.\n\n## Serving Suggestion\n- Serve the scramble hot, topped with sliced avocado, fresh cilantro, and a squeeze of lime.\n- Add a dollop of salsa and sprinkle with nutritional yeast if using.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('411','Grilled Shrimp with Chimichurri','## Chimichurri Sauce\n- 1 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 cup olive oil\n\n## Grilled Shrimp\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper','## Prepare Chimichurri Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine parsley, cilantro, garlic, red wine vinegar, red pepper flakes, salt, and black pepper.\n- Slowly whisk in the olive oil until the mixture is well combined.\n- Set aside to let the flavors meld.\n\n## Prepare Shrimp\n- In a separate bowl, toss the shrimp with olive oil, lemon juice, paprika, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.\n- Let marinate for 15 minutes.\n\n## Grill Shrimp\n- Preheat an outdoor grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Thread the shrimp onto skewers for easy grilling.\n- Grill shrimp for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until pink and opaque.\n\n## Serve\n- Drizzle grilled shrimp with chimichurri sauce.\n- Serve immediately with extra chimichurri sauce on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('412','Ropa Vieja','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 lbs flank steak\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 green bell pepper, thinly sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, thinly sliced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 teaspoons ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 can (14 oz) crushed tomatoes\n- 1 cup beef broth\n- 1/2 cup green olives, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons capers\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## Serving Suggestion\n- Cooked brown rice','## Preparing the Beef\n- Season the flank steak with salt and pepper.\n- In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.\n- Brown the flank steak on both sides, then remove and set aside.\n\n## Cooking the Vegetables\n- In the same pot, add sliced onion, green and red bell peppers.\n- Cook for about 5 minutes until softened.\n- Add garlic, cumin, and oregano, cooking for another minute until fragrant.\n\n## Simmering the Dish\n- Return the flank steak to the pot.\n- Add crushed tomatoes, beef broth, olives, and capers.\n- Bring to a simmer, then cover and reduce heat to low.\n- Cook for 2 to 2.5 hours until the beef is tender and easily shreds with a fork.\n\n## Shredding and Serving\n- Remove the beef from the pot and shred using two forks.\n- Return the shredded beef to the pot and mix with the sauce.\n- Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.\n- Serve hot over cooked brown rice, garnished with fresh cilantro.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('413','Tostones with Garlic Shrimp','## For the Tostones\n- 2 large green plantains\n- Vegetable oil for frying\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For the Garlic Shrimp\n- 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Prepare the Tostones\n- Peel the plantains and cut them into 1-inch thick slices.\n- Heat the vegetable oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.\n- Fry the plantain slices for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until they start to get golden but not fully cooked.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels.\n- Using the bottom of a flat cup or a tostonera, flatten each slice to about half its original thickness.\n- Return the flattened plantains to the hot oil, frying for an additional 2-3 minutes on each side until golden brown and crispy.\n- Remove from oil and drain on paper towels again, then lightly salt.\n\n## Prepare the Garlic Shrimp\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the minced garlic, sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.\n- Add the shrimp to the skillet, season with salt, pepper, and paprika.\n- Cook the shrimp for about 2-3 minutes on each side until they turn pink and opaque.\n- Stir in the lemon juice and chopped parsley, cooking for an additional minute.\n\n## Assemble and Serve\n- Arrange the tostones on a serving platter.\n- Top each tostone with a spoonful of garlic shrimp.\n- Garnish with extra parsley if desired and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('414','White Fish Ceviche','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb white fish (such as snapper or halibut), skinless and deboned\n- 1 cup fresh lime juice\n- 1/2 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 1 small red onion, finely sliced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and finely chopped\n- 1 small cucumber, diced\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Salt and freshly ground pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 bunch radishes, thinly sliced\n- Tortilla chips or tostadas (optional)','## Preparation\n- Cut the white fish into small cubes, about 1/2 inch in size, and place in a glass or ceramic bowl.\n- Pour the lime and lemon juice over the fish, ensuring it is fully submerged. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15-20 minutes, or until the fish is opaque and ''cooked'' through by the citrus juice.\n\n## Mixing Ingredients\n- Remove the fish from the fridge and drain some of the excess citrus juice, leaving about half in the bowl.\n- Add the red onion, jalapeño, cucumber, avocado, and cilantro to the bowl with the fish.\n- Gently mix all ingredients together, being careful not to mash the avocado.\n\n## Final Touches and Serving\n- Season the ceviche with salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.\n- Garnish with cherry tomatoes and radish slices before serving.\n- Serve immediately with tortilla chips or tostadas if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('415','Chicken and Quinoa Bowl','## For the Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n\n## For the Quinoa\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water or chicken broth\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n## For the Bowl\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges for serving\n\n## For the Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat grill or stovetop grill pan over medium heat.\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and lemon juice.\n- Marinate chicken breasts in the mixture for at least 15 minutes.\n- Grill the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.\n- Allow chicken to rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Cook the Quinoa\n- Rinse quinoa under cold water.\n- In a saucepan, add quinoa, water or broth, and salt.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer, cover, and cook for 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.\n- Fluff with a fork.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, avocado, feta cheese, and parsley.\n- Slice the grilled chicken into thin strips.\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, salt, and pepper for the dressing.\n\n## Serve\n- Drizzle dressing over the quinoa mixture and toss gently to combine.\n- Divide the mixture into bowls, top with sliced chicken.\n- Garnish with lemon wedges and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('416','Pinto Bean & Egg Burritos','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 large eggs\n- 1 cup canned pinto beans, rinsed and drained\n- 1/2 cup diced onion\n- 1/2 cup diced bell pepper\n- 1 teaspoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or a Mexican blend)\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n- Hot sauce','## Preparation\n- In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs with salt, pepper, and ground cumin.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and bell pepper to the skillet, sauté until softened, about 4-5 minutes.\n- Add the pinto beans to the skillet and cook for another 2 minutes until heated through.\n- Push the vegetables to one side of the skillet and pour the eggs into the other side. Let them sit for a moment, then gently scramble until cooked through.\n- Mix the cooked eggs with the bean and vegetable mixture.\n\n## Assembly\n- Warm the tortillas in a microwave or on a skillet for a few seconds until pliable.\n- Divide the egg and bean mixture evenly among the tortillas.\n- If desired, sprinkle shredded cheese, add salsa, slices of avocado, cilantro, and hot sauce.\n- Roll up each tortilla tightly to enclose the filling.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('417','Pabellón Criollo','## Beef and Marinade\n- 1 lb flank steak\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tbsp vegetable oil\n\n## Black Beans\n- 1 cup dried black beans (or 1 can, drained)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 1 bay leaf\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Rice\n- 1 cup long-grain white rice\n- 2 cups water\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Plantains\n- 2 ripe plantains\n- Vegetable oil for frying','## Prepare the Beef\n- Mix garlic, cumin, oregano, salt, and pepper, and rub it over the flank steak.\n- Let marinate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Sear the steak on both sides until brown, about 4-5 minutes per side.\n- Remove from heat, let rest, then shred using two forks.\n\n## Cook the Black Beans\n- If using dried beans, soak them overnight. Drain and rinse.\n- In a pot, sauté garlic and onion until soft.\n- Add beans, bay leaf, salt, and enough water to cover beans by an inch.\n- Simmer until beans are fully cooked (approximately 1-2 hours if using dried beans).\n- Remove bay leaf before serving.\n\n## Prepare the Rice\n- Rinse rice under cold water.\n- Bring water to a boil in a pot.\n- Add rice and salt, cover, reduce to a simmer, and cook for 18-20 minutes.\n- Fluff with a fork before serving.\n\n## Fry the Plantains\n- Peel and slice plantains into thin slices.\n- Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat.\n- Fry plantains until golden brown on both sides, about 2-3 minutes per side.\n- Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Serve shredded beef alongside rice, black beans and fried plantains on a plate.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro or avocado if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('418','High-Protein Chicken Sancocho','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb chicken breast, cut into pieces\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 2 carrots, sliced\n- 2 ears corn, cut into chunks\n- 1 green plantain, sliced\n- 1 small yucca, peeled and cubed\n- 2 potatoes, peeled and cubed\n\n## Broth and Seasoning\n- 8 cups chicken broth\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add chicken pieces and brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same pot, add onion, garlic, green bell pepper, and red bell pepper. Sauté until soft.\n\n## Cooking\n- Return chicken to the pot.\n- Add chicken broth, cumin, oregano, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil.\n- Add carrots, corn, plantain, yucca, and potatoes.\n- Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.\n\n## Finishing Touch\n- Add lime juice and cilantro to the pot.\n- Stir well and adjust seasoning if needed.\n- Serve hot and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('419','Churrasco with Chimichurri Sauce','## For the Churrasco\n- 2 lbs skirt steak\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n\n## For the Chimichurri Sauce\n- 1 cup fresh parsley, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh oregano, finely chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup olive oil\n- 1/4 cup red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Chimichurri Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine parsley, oregano, and garlic.\n- Add olive oil, red wine vinegar, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well and adjust seasoning if needed. Set aside to allow flavors to meld.\n\n## Prepare the Churrasco\n- Preheat grill to medium-high heat.\n- Rub the skirt steak with olive oil, minced garlic, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Allow steak to sit at room temperature for about 15 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Steak\n- Place the skirt steak on the grill and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until desired doneness is reached.\n- Remove from grill and let rest for a few minutes before slicing.\n\n## Serve\n- Slice the steak against the grain into thin strips.\n- Serve with chimichurri sauce on the side or drizzled over the steak.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('420','Lomo Saltado','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb beef sirloin or tenderloin, cut into strips\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 large red onion, cut into wedges\n- 2 tomatoes, cut into wedges\n- 1 yellow chili pepper, sliced\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Cooked white rice\n- French fries','## Marinate the Beef\n- In a bowl, combine the beef strips with soy sauce, red wine vinegar, salt, and pepper.\n- Let marinate for at least 15 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Beef\n- Heat vegetable oil in a large pan over high heat.\n- Add the marinated beef and sear quickly until browned.\n- Remove from pan and set aside.\n\n## Stir Fry the Vegetables\n- In the same pan, add the minced garlic and yellow chili pepper. Stir fry for 1 minute.\n- Add onion and stir fry until slightly translucent.\n- Add tomato wedges and continue to stir fry until tomatoes are softened.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Return the beef to the pan and mix everything together.\n- Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes to combine the flavors.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro.\n- Serve with cooked white rice and French fries.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('421','Shrimp & Avocado Tostadas','## For the Shrimp\n- 1 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon cumin\n- 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Avocado Salsa\n- 2 ripe avocados, diced\n- 1/2 red onion, finely chopped\n- 1 jalapeno, seeded and minced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Juice of 2 limes\n- Salt to taste\n\n## For the Tostadas\n- 8 corn tortillas\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n\n## For Assembly\n- 1/4 cup sour cream or Greek yogurt (optional)\n- 1/4 cup crumbled queso fresco (optional)\n- Lime wedges for serving','## Prepare the Shrimp\n- In a large bowl, combine shrimp, olive oil, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and cook the shrimp for 2-3 minutes on each side until opaque and cooked through. Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Make the Avocado Salsa\n- In a medium bowl, gently combine diced avocados, red onion, jalapeno, cilantro, lime juice, and salt.\n- Set aside to let the flavors meld.\n\n## Prepare the Tostadas\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Brush corn tortillas with vegetable oil on both sides and place on a baking sheet.\n- Bake for 5-7 minutes on each side until crispy and golden brown.\n\n## Assemble the Tostadas\n- Spread a layer of avocado salsa on each tostada.\n- Top with cooked shrimp.\n- Add a dollop of sour cream or Greek yogurt if desired.\n- Sprinkle with crumbled queso fresco if using.\n- Serve with lime wedges and enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('422','Turkey Picadillo','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 green bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup tomato sauce\n- 1/4 cup green olives, sliced\n- 1/4 cup raisins\n- 1 tablespoon capers, rinsed\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- Cooked brown rice or quinoa\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped (optional)','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onion and minced garlic; sauté until the onion is translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Add ground turkey to the skillet. Cook until browned, breaking up the meat with a spoon, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in the chopped green and red bell peppers. Cook for an additional 4-5 minutes until peppers are slightly softened.\n- Add diced tomatoes (with juice), tomato sauce, olives, raisins, and capers.\n- Season with ground cumin, dried oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer the mixture for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened and flavors have melded together.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot over cooked brown rice or quinoa.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('423','High Protein Chicken Empanadas','## Dough\n- 2 cups whole wheat flour\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup cold water\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Filling\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound ground chicken breast\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 cup diced red bell pepper\n- 1/2 cup canned black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1/2 cup corn kernels\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese','## Prepare the Dough\n- In a large bowl, combine whole wheat flour and salt.\n- Add Greek yogurt, cold water, and olive oil; mix until the dough comes together.\n- Knead the dough on a floured surface for about 5 minutes until smooth.\n- Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add ground chicken and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add onion and garlic; sauté until onion is translucent.\n- Stir in cumin, paprika, chili powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Add red bell pepper, black beans, and corn; cook for another 3 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and stir in cilantro and feta cheese.\n- Let cool slightly before filling the empanadas.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Roll out the dough on a floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.\n- Cut out circles using a round cutter (about 4 inches in diameter).\n- Place about 1-2 tablespoons of filling in the center of each circle.\n- Fold the circles in half and press the edges with a fork to seal.\n- Place the empanadas on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Brush lightly with olive oil or egg wash.\n- Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('424','Grilled Fish Veracruz','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 fillets of firm white fish (e.g., snapper, cod, or halibut)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Veracruz Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, thinly sliced\n- 3 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes, drained\n- 1/2 cup green olives, sliced\n- 1/4 cup capers\n- 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and chopped\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped','## Grilling the Fish\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush both sides of the fish fillets with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Place the fish on the grill and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until the fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.\n- Remove from grill and set aside.\n\n## Preparing the Veracruz Sauce\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the onion and cook until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Stir in the garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.\n- Add the diced tomatoes, olives, capers, lime juice, jalapeño, oregano, and cumin.\n- Simmer for 7-10 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld together.\n- Stir in the chopped cilantro and remove the sauce from heat.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve each grilled fish fillet topped with generous spoonfuls of the Veracruz sauce.\n- Garnish with additional cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('425','Tofu Enchiladas','## For the Filling\n- 1 block (14 oz) extra firm tofu, drained and crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 bell pepper, diced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup corn kernels (fresh or frozen)\n- 2 tablespoons finely chopped cilantro\n\n## For the Enchiladas\n- 8 corn tortillas\n- 1 can (15 oz) red enchilada sauce\n- 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Mexican blend)\n\n## For Serving\n- Sliced avocado\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Lime wedges\n- Sour cream or Greek yogurt','## Prepare the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add onion and garlic, sauté until soft and fragrant.\n- Stir in bell pepper, cook for 2-3 minutes until softened.\n- Add crumbled tofu, ground cumin, smoked paprika, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Mix in black beans and corn, cook until heated through.\n- Remove from heat and stir in chopped cilantro. Set aside.\n\n## Assemble and Bake Enchiladas\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Spread a thin layer of enchilada sauce at the bottom of a baking dish.\n- Heat tortillas slightly to make them pliable.\n- Fill each tortilla with the tofu mixture, roll up, and place seam-side down in the baking dish.\n- Pour remaining enchilada sauce over the top of the enchiladas.\n- Sprinkle shredded cheese over the enchiladas.\n- Cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake for an additional 5-10 minutes, until cheese is bubbly and golden.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve hot, garnished with sliced avocado, chopped cilantro, lime wedges, and a dollop of sour cream or Greek yogurt.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('426','Beef Chile Relleno','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large poblano peppers\n- 1 lb ground beef\n- 1 cup chopped onion\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup corn kernels\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 1/2 cups shredded Monterey Jack cheese\n\n## For the Batter\n- 3 large eggs, separated\n- 1/4 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 2 tbsp vegetable oil\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped, for garnish','## Prepare Peppers\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Place the poblano peppers on a baking sheet and roast for 10-12 minutes until the skin is charred, turning occasionally.\n- Remove from oven, place in a bowl, and cover with plastic wrap for 10 minutes to steam.\n- Peel the skins off the peppers, then carefully slit to remove seeds without detaching the tops.\n\n## Prepare Filling\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, add the ground beef and cook until browned, about 7-8 minutes.\n- Add onion and garlic, cooking until softened, about 3 minutes.\n- Stir in black beans, corn, cumin, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Mix in 1 cup of shredded cheese until melted.\n\n## Stuff and Batter Peppers\n- Divide beef mixture evenly and stuff each pepper.\n- In a bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks and salt, then gently fold into the egg whites.\n- Dust stuffed peppers lightly with flour, then gently coat with egg mixture.\n\n## Cook Stuffed Peppers\n- In a large skillet, heat vegetable oil over medium heat.\n- Carefully place peppers in the hot oil, cooking until golden brown on each side, about 3 minutes per side.\n- Place cooked peppers in an oven-safe dish, top with remaining cheese, and bake at 400°F for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from oven and let cool for a few minutes.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('427','Mexican Quinoa & Black Bean Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa, rinsed\n- 2 cups water or vegetable broth\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 bell pepper (any color), diced\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (15 oz) corn kernels, drained\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheese (optional)\n- Sliced jalapeños (optional)','## Cooking Quinoa\n- In a medium saucepan, bring the water or vegetable broth to a boil.\n- Stir in the quinoa, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed and quinoa is fluffy.\n\n## Preparing the Vegetables\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Stir in the garlic and cook for another minute.\n- Add the bell pepper and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.\n\n## Combining Ingredients\n- Stir in the cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, ground cumin, and chili powder.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until everything is heated through.\n\n## Serving\n- Divide the mixture into bowls.\n- Top with avocado slices, cherry tomatoes, cilantro, lime wedges, shredded cheese, and jalapeños if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('428','Baked Chicken Taquitos','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups cooked chicken, shredded\n- 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Mexican blend)\n- 1/2 cup salsa\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon chili powder\n- 8 small whole wheat tortillas\n- Cooking spray\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Guacamole\n- Sour cream\n- Chopped cilantro\n- Diced tomatoes\n- Lime wedges','## Preheat Oven\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine the shredded chicken, cheese, salsa, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, and chili powder. Mix until well combined.\n\n## Assemble Taquitos\n- Spoon 2-3 tablespoons of the chicken mixture onto the lower third of each tortilla.\n- Roll the tortilla tightly around the filling and place seam-side down on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n\n## Bake Taquitos\n- Lightly spray the tops of the taquitos with cooking spray.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes or until the taquitos are crispy and golden brown.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately with optional garnishes like guacamole, sour cream, chopped cilantro, diced tomatoes, and lime wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('429','Carne Molida (Seasoned Ground Beef)','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 pound lean ground beef\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup tomato paste\n- 1/2 cup beef broth\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh cilantro\n- Diced avocado\n- Sliced green onions','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Stir in minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute until fragrant.\n\n## Cooking the Beef\n- Add the ground beef to the skillet. Cook while breaking it apart with a spoon until it is browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Drain excess fat if necessary.\n- Stir in the cumin, smoked paprika, chili powder, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the tomato paste and beef broth, stirring to combine.\n- Reduce heat to low and let it simmer for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the mixture is thick and well combined.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, optionally garnishing with chopped cilantro, diced avocado, and sliced green onions.\n- Enjoy with tortillas, rice, or a side salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('430','Chicken Pupusas','## For the Chicken Filling\n- 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/2 tsp black pepper\n- 1/2 tsp cumin\n- 1/2 tsp paprika\n- 1/2 cup diced onion\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n\n## For the Masa Dough\n- 2 cups masa harina (corn flour)\n- 1 1/2 cups warm water\n- 1/2 tsp salt','## Prepare the Chicken Filling\n- Preheat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, cumin, and paprika.\n- Cook the chicken breasts in the skillet for about 5-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and shred it using two forks.\n- In the same skillet, add diced onion and minced garlic; sauté for about 2-3 minutes until the onion is translucent.\n- Add the shredded chicken back to the skillet and mix well with the onions and garlic.\n- Remove from heat and let it cool slightly before mixing in the shredded mozzarella cheese.\n\n## Prepare the Masa Dough\n- In a large bowl, combine masa harina and salt.\n- Gradually add warm water while mixing until a soft dough forms.\n- Knead the dough for a couple of minutes until smooth and pliable.\n\n## Assemble the Pupusas\n- Divide the masa dough into 8 equal portions and roll each into a ball.\n- Flatten each ball into a disc, about 1/4 inch thick.\n- Place about 2 tablespoons of the chicken filling in the center of each disc.\n- Carefully fold and seal the edges to enclose the filling, reshaping into a ball.\n- Flatten each ball gently again to form a thick disc with the filling secured inside.\n\n## Cook the Pupusas\n- Heat a non-stick griddle or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook each pupusa for about 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown and cooked through.\n- Serve hot with salsa or curtido on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('431','Chipotle Chicken Lettuce Wraps','## Marinade and Chicken\n- 1 lb chicken breast, diced\n- 2 tbsp chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, minced\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/4 tsp black pepper\n- Juice of 1 lime\n\n## Wrap Assembly\n- 1 head of butter or romaine lettuce, leaves separated\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine chipotle peppers, olive oil, garlic, smoked paprika, cumin, salt, black pepper, and lime juice.\n- Add diced chicken and mix well to coat.\n- Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add the marinated chicken and cook for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cooked through.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Lay the lettuce leaves on a serving platter.\n- Spoon the cooked chicken into the center of each leaf.\n- Top with a dollop of Greek yogurt, diced avocado, red onion, and cilantro.\n- Serve with lime wedges on the side for extra zest.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('432','Chorizo & Veggie Frittata','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup milk\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 4 oz chorizo, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 green bell pepper, diced\n- 1 small red onion, diced\n- 1 cup baby spinach\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Cooking the Frittata\n- Heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chorizo and cook for 3-4 minutes until it begins to brown.\n- Add the red and green bell peppers and onion to the skillet. Cook for 4-5 minutes until softened.\n- Stir in the spinach and cherry tomatoes, cooking until the spinach wilts slightly.\n- Pour the egg mixture into the skillet, ensuring it evenly covers the ingredients.\n- Cook on the stovetop for 2-3 minutes until the edges start to set.\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven. Bake for 10-15 minutes until the frittata is fully set.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Remove the frittata from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes.\n- Sprinkle with feta cheese and parsley, if using.\n- Slice and serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('433','Salvadorean Grilled Steak','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup soy sauce\n- 1/4 cup fresh lime juice\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Steak\n- 2 pounds flank steak or skirt steak\n\n## To Serve\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lime wedges\n- Sliced onions','## Step 1: Prepare the Marinade\n- In a bowl, combine soy sauce, lime juice, minced garlic, ground cumin, paprika, black pepper, salt, and olive oil. Mix well to create a marinade.\n\n## Step 2: Marinate the Steak\n- Place the flank steak in a resealable plastic bag or a shallow dish.\n- Pour the marinade over the steak, ensuring it is well coated.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or overnight for best results.\n\n## Step 3: Prepare the Grill\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Oil the grill grates to prevent sticking.\n\n## Step 4: Grill the Steak\n- Remove the steak from the marinade, letting any excess drip off.\n- Place the steak on the hot grill.\n- Grill for about 4-6 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or longer if desired.\n- Use a meat thermometer to check the internal temperature, aiming for 130°F to 135°F for medium-rare.\n\n## Step 5: Rest and Serve\n- Remove the steak from the grill and let it rest for about 5 minutes before slicing.\n- Slice the steak thinly against the grain.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve with lime wedges and sliced onions.\n- Enjoy with sides like rice, beans, or a fresh salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('434','Black Bean & Tofu Arepas','## For the Arepas\n- 2 cups precooked white cornmeal (harina PAN)\n- 2 1/2 cups warm water\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## For the Filling\n- 1 block (14 oz) firm tofu, drained and crumbled\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped\n- Juice of 1 lime\n\n## For Serving\n- Avocado slices\n- Salsa or hot sauce\n- Chopped lettuce\n- Sliced tomatoes','## Prepare the Arepas\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine cornmeal and salt.\n- Gradually add warm water, stirring until a dough forms.\n- Let the dough rest for 5 minutes, then divide into 8 pieces.\n- Shape each piece into a disc about 1/2 inch thick.\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook arepas for 5-7 minutes on each side, until golden and slightly puffed up.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.\n- Add garlic and sauté until fragrant.\n- Stir in crumbled tofu, cooking for 2-3 minutes.\n- Add black beans, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook for another 5 minutes.\n- Remove from heat and stir in chopped cilantro and lime juice.\n\n## Assemble the Arepas\n- Slice each cooked arepa open, creating a pocket.\n- Fill each arepa with the tofu and black bean mixture.\n- Add avocado slices, salsa or hot sauce, chopped lettuce, and sliced tomatoes as desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('435','Peruvian Turkey Meatballs','## Meatballs\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1/4 cup quinoa, cooked and cooled\n- 1/4 cup onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 egg\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp aji amarillo paste (or substitute with 1 tsp cayenne and 1 tbsp bell pepper paste)\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/4 tsp black pepper\n- 1 tbsp olive oil for frying\n\n## Sauce\n- 1 cup low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1/2 cup tomato sauce\n- 1/4 cup aji amarillo paste (or substitute as above)\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1/4 cup green peas\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Meatballs\n- In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, cooked quinoa, finely chopped onion, minced garlic, egg, cilantro, aji amarillo paste, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well until the ingredients are evenly distributed.\n- Form the mixture into 1.5-inch meatballs.\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add meatballs to the skillet and cook until browned on all sides, about 8-10 minutes. Make sure they are cooked through. Remove from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce\n- In the same skillet, add olive oil and sliced bell pepper.\n- Sauté for 2-3 minutes until the peppers begin to soften.\n- Add the chicken broth, tomato sauce, aji amarillo paste, lime juice, and peas.\n- Simmer the sauce for 5 minutes, allowing it to thicken slightly.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Add the cooked meatballs back to the skillet with the sauce.\n- Gently stir to coat the meatballs with the sauce.\n- Simmer for an additional 5 minutes to heat through and meld flavors.\n- Serve hot, garnished with extra cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('436','Baked Cod with Tomatoes & Olives','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 cod fillets (about 6 oz each)\n- 2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cup pitted Kalamata olives, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n\n## Assembling the Dish\n- Place the cod fillets in a baking dish.\n- In a bowl, combine halved cherry tomatoes, sliced olives, olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, dried oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix the ingredients in the bowl, then spread the mixture over the cod fillets in the baking dish.\n\n## Baking\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes or until the cod is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.\n- Check for doneness after 15 minutes to avoid overcooking.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and let it sit for a few minutes.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('437','Mediterranean Chicken Skillet','## For the Chicken Marinade\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Skillet\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 red onion, sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried rosemary\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, mix olive oil, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n- Add chicken breasts and coat evenly with the marinade.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes or overnight for better flavor.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.\n- Add marinated chicken breasts and cook for 5-6 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.\n- Remove chicken from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Vegetables\n- In the same skillet, add a little more olive oil if needed.\n- Add the red onion, red and yellow bell peppers, zucchini, cherry tomatoes, Kalamata olives, and sun-dried tomatoes.\n- Sprinkle with dried basil, rosemary, salt, and pepper.\n- Sauté until the vegetables are tender, about 8-10 minutes.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Return the chicken to the skillet with the vegetables.\n- Sprinkle with feta cheese and let it warm through for a minute.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('438','Grilled Salmon with Herbed Couscous','## Salmon\n- 4 salmon fillets (about 6 oz each)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 lemon, sliced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n\n## Herbed Couscous\n- 1 cup couscous\n- 1 1/2 cups low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt to taste\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh mint\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh chives\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- 1/4 cup toasted sliced almonds (optional)','## Prepare Salmon\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush the salmon fillets with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and minced garlic.\n- Place lemon slices on top of each fillet.\n\n## Grill Salmon\n- Place salmon fillets on the grill, skin side down.\n- Grill for 4-5 minutes on each side or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.\n- Remove from grill and let rest for a few minutes.\n\n## Prepare Couscous\n- In a saucepan, bring chicken broth and olive oil to a boil.\n- Stir in couscous and a pinch of salt, then remove from heat and cover.\n- Let it sit for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.\n\n## Combine and Serve\n- Mix parsley, mint, chives, and lemon juice into the couscous.\n- Add sliced almonds if desired, and adjust seasoning to taste.\n- Serve each salmon fillet alongside a portion of herbed couscous.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('439','Harissa Grilled Chicken','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup harissa paste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Chicken\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro (optional)\n- Lemon wedges, for serving','## Marinating the Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine harissa paste, olive oil, minced garlic, lemon juice, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the chicken breasts in a zip-top bag or shallow dish and pour the marinade over them, ensuring they are well-coated.\n- Seal the bag or cover the dish and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or up to overnight for deeper flavor.\n\n## Grilling the Chicken\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Remove the chicken from the marinade, allowing excess to drip off, and place on the grill.\n- Grill the chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C) and juices run clear.\n- Remove chicken from the grill and let it rest for a few minutes before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with chopped cilantro, if desired.\n- Serve the chicken with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('440','Baked Falafel with Tahini Sauce','## Falafel\n- 1 cup dried chickpeas, soaked overnight\n- 1 small onion, roughly chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley leaves\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro leaves\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Tahini Sauce\n- 1/2 cup tahini\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 cup water (or more for desired consistency)','## Prepare the Falafel\n- Drain and rinse the soaked chickpeas.\n- In a food processor, combine the chickpeas, onion, garlic, parsley, cilantro, cumin, coriander, baking powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Pulse until the mixture is coarse and holds together when pressed.\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- Shape the falafel mixture into small balls or patties and place them on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Brush or spray lightly with olive oil.\n- Bake for 20-25 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden and crisp.\n\n## Make the Tahini Sauce\n- In a bowl, whisk together the tahini, lemon juice, garlic, salt, and water.\n- Adjust with more water for a thinner consistency if desired.\n- Set aside.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the baked falafel with the tahini sauce drizzled on top or on the side for dipping.\n- Optionally, serve with pita bread and salad for a complete meal.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('441','Greek Turkey Meatballs','## Meatballs\n- 1 pound ground turkey\n- 1/3 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/4 cup finely diced red onion\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Dipping Sauce (optional)\n- 1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Meatballs\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, breadcrumbs, feta cheese, parsley, red onion, garlic, egg, olive oil, lemon juice, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until ingredients are just combined, being careful not to overmix.\n- Shape the mixture into 1-inch meatballs and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n\n## Cook the Meatballs\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until the meatballs are golden brown and cooked through, reaching an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).\n\n## Make the Dipping Sauce (optional)\n- In a small bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, dill, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Serve the meatballs warm with the dipping sauce on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('442','Tuna Niçoise Salad','## Salad Ingredients\n- 8 ounces green beans, trimmed\n- 4 small red potatoes\n- 4 cups mixed salad greens\n- 2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 small red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup Kalamata olives\n- 2 hard-boiled eggs, quartered\n- 1 pound fresh tuna steak or 2 cans of tuna packed in water\n\n## Dressing Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Ingredients\n- Boil the green beans in salted water for 3 minutes until bright green and tender-crisp. Drain and immerse in ice water to stop cooking.\n- Boil the potatoes in salted water for 10-15 minutes until fork-tender. Cool slightly and cut into quarters.\n- Hard-boil eggs by placing in cold water, bringing to a boil, then covering and removing from heat for 9 minutes. Cool in ice water and peel.\n\n## Cook the Tuna\n- Season the tuna steak with salt and pepper. If using fresh tuna, sear it in a hot skillet with a little olive oil, about 2 minutes per side for medium-rare. Let it rest and then slice. If using canned tuna, simply drain and flake.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl or platter, arrange salad greens, green beans, potatoes, cherry tomatoes, onion slices, olives, and hard-boiled eggs.\n- Top with sliced or flaked tuna.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- Whisk together olive oil, mustard, vinegar, garlic, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.\n\n## Dress the Salad\n- Drizzle the dressing over the assembled salad.\n- Toss gently to combine, or serve with dressing on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('443','Eggplant & Chickpea Tagine','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 large eggplant, diced\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup dried apricots, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n- 1/4 cup vegetable broth\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Spices and Herbs\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)\n- 1 tablespoon fresh ginger, grated\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped (for garnish)','## Preparation\n- Dice the eggplant and set aside.\n- Chop the onion, garlic, and apricots. Mince the ginger.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot or tagine over medium heat.\n- Add the onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in garlic and ginger, cooking for another minute until fragrant.\n- Add the cumin, coriander, cinnamon, smoked paprika, and cayenne pepper. Stir for about 1 minute to toast the spices.\n- Add the eggplant, stirring to coat with the spice mixture.\n- Add the tomato paste and mix well, then add the diced tomatoes and vegetable broth.\n- Stir in the chickpeas and apricots. Season with salt and pepper.\n- Bring to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and cover.\n- Cook for about 25-30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant is tender.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('444','Mediterranean Tuna Wrap','## Wrap Ingredients\n- 2 large whole wheat tortillas\n- 1 can (5 oz) tuna packed in water, drained\n- 1/4 cup hummus\n- 1/4 cup diced cucumber\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup Kalamata olives, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- Fresh spinach leaves\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparation Steps\n- In a small bowl, combine the tuna, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Mix well to combine.\n- Lay the tortillas flat and spread evenly with hummus, leaving a small border around the edges.\n- Add a layer of fresh spinach leaves over the hummus.\n- Divide the tuna mixture evenly between the two tortillas, spreading it down the center of each.\n- Sprinkle the diced cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, and olives over the tuna.\n- Top with crumbled feta cheese.\n- Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll tightly from the bottom to secure the wrap.\n- Cut each wrap in half and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('445','Feta & Spinach Egg Muffins','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1 cup fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup red bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup onion, diced\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/4 cup milk or non-dairy milk (for extra creaminess)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lightly grease a 12-cup muffin tin with cooking spray or line with silicone muffin liners.\n\n## Mix Ingredients\n- In a large mixing bowl, whisk the eggs until well blended.\n- Stir in the chopped spinach, feta cheese, red bell pepper, onion, salt, and pepper.\n- If using, add garlic powder and milk, and mix well until all ingredients are combined.\n\n## Fill Muffin Tin\n- Pour the egg mixture evenly into the prepared muffin tin cups, filling each about 3/4 full.\n\n## Bake\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 18-20 minutes, or until the egg muffins are set and lightly golden on top.\n\n## Cool and Serve\n- Allow the muffins to cool in the tin for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack.\n- Serve immediately, or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. Reheat in the microwave or enjoy cold.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('446','Grilled Chicken Souvlaki','## Marinade\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Chicken\n- 1.5 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into 1-inch cubes\n\n## To Serve\n- 8 wooden skewers, soaked in water for 30 minutes\n- Whole wheat pita bread\n- Tzatziki sauce\n- Chopped tomatoes\n- Chopped cucumbers\n- Sliced red onion\n- Chopped fresh parsley','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the chicken cubes to the marinade and mix well to ensure the chicken is fully coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or overnight for best results.\n\n## Prepare the Skewers\n- Preheat grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated chicken pieces onto the soaked skewers.\n\n## Grill the Chicken\n- Place the skewers on the grill.\n- Cook for about 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and has grill marks.\n- Ensure the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165°F (75°C).\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the chicken souvlaki with whole wheat pita bread, tzatziki sauce, chopped tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion, and parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('447','Greek Chickpea Salad with Chicken','## Salad Ingredients\n- 1 (15 oz) can chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cups cooked chicken breast, diced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 medium cucumber, diced\n- 1/2 red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and halved\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Dressing Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, lemon juice, minced garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine chickpeas, cooked chicken, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, Kalamata olives, and feta cheese.\n\n## Mix and Serve\n- Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to combine.\n- Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('448','Mediterranean Sardine Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cans sardines in olive oil, drained\n- 1 cup quinoa, rinsed\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 2 tablespoons capers, drained\n- 2 cups baby spinach or arugula\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n\n## Dressing\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano','## Prepare Quinoa\n- In a medium saucepan, combine 1 cup quinoa and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil over medium heat.\n- Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes until the water is absorbed and the quinoa is tender.\n- Fluff with a fork and set aside to cool.\n\n## Prepare Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together 1/4 cup olive oil, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard, and 1 clove garlic.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and 1 teaspoon oregano.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, capers, and spinach.\n- Add sardines and gently toss with the dressing.\n- Divide the mixture into bowls.\n- Top with crumbled feta cheese.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('449','Grilled Halloumi with Chickpeas','## Main Ingredients\n- 250g halloumi cheese, sliced\n- 1 can (400g) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1/2 tsp smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Salad\n- 100g cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 small cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, finely sliced\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- Lemon wedges\n- Fresh mint leaves (optional)','## Prepare the Chickpeas\n- In a bowl, combine chickpeas, olive oil, ground cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well to coat the chickpeas with the spices.\n\n## Grill the Halloumi\n- Heat a grill pan over medium heat.\n- Add the halloumi slices and grill for 2-3 minutes on each side, until golden brown.\n\n## Cook the Chickpeas\n- In the same grill pan, add the seasoned chickpeas and cook for 5-6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they are crispy.\n\n## Prepare the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, and parsley.\n- Drizzle with lemon juice and olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.\n- Toss to combine.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- On a serving platter, arrange the grilled halloumi with crispy chickpeas.\n- Serve with the fresh salad on the side.\n- Garnish with lemon wedges and mint leaves if using.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('450','Spiced Lamb Meatballs with Yogurt Sauce','## Lamb Meatballs\n- 1 lb ground lamb\n- 1/4 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1 egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1 tsp ground coriander\n- 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n\n## Yogurt Sauce\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 2 tbsp fresh mint, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Meatballs\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine ground lamb, breadcrumbs, egg, minced garlic, chopped onion, parsley, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well combined.\n- Shape the mixture into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.\n\n## Cook the Meatballs\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add meatballs to the skillet, cooking in batches if necessary to avoid overcrowding.\n- Cook for about 8-10 minutes, turning frequently, until browned on all sides and cooked through.\n\n## Prepare the Yogurt Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine Greek yogurt, minced garlic, lemon juice, mint, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well until smooth.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve meatballs hot with the yogurt sauce on the side for dipping.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('451','Chickpea & Tuna Cakes','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (5 oz) tuna in water, drained\n- 1/2 cup breadcrumbs\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped red onion\n- 1 egg\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Greek yogurt or sour cream\n- Extra lemon wedges\n- Chopped fresh parsley','## Preparation\n- In a large bowl, mash the chickpeas with a fork until mostly smooth, leaving some chunks for texture.\n- Add the drained tuna, breadcrumbs, parsley, red onion, egg, garlic, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper to the bowl with the chickpeas.\n- Mix all the ingredients until well combined.\n\n## Shaping and Cooking\n- Form the mixture into 8 even-sized patties.\n- Heat olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the patties in the skillet for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and heated through.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the tuna cakes warm, topped with a dollop of Greek yogurt or sour cream, additional parsley, and a squeeze of fresh lemon juice.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('452','Frittata with Spinach and Feta','## Main Ingredients\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup milk\n- 1 cup fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup onion, finely chopped\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved\n- Fresh basil, chopped','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, and pepper until well combined.\n- Heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Add the chopped onions and sauté until they are translucent.\n- Add the chopped spinach to the skillet and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Pour the egg mixture over the spinach and onions in the skillet. Gently stir to combine the ingredients.\n- Sprinkle the crumbled feta cheese evenly over the top of the egg mixture.\n- Cook on the stovetop for about 5 minutes, or until the edges begin to set.\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the frittata is fully set and slightly golden on top.\n- Remove from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing.\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Garnish with halved cherry tomatoes and fresh basil if desired.\n- Serve warm as a main dish or a hearty side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('453','Chicken Artichoke Bake','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 can (14 oz) artichoke hearts, drained and quartered\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Seasoning Ingredients\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and black pepper to taste','## Preparation Steps\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Lightly grease a baking dish with olive oil.\n\n## Chicken and Artichoke\n- Place the chicken breasts in the prepared baking dish.\n- Season the chicken with garlic, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper.\n- Spread the artichoke hearts and cherry tomato halves evenly over the chicken breasts.\n\n## Topping\n- Drizzle olive oil over the chicken and vegetables.\n- Sprinkle the mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses over the top.\n\n## Bake\n- Place the dish in the preheated oven.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the cheese is golden and bubbly.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before serving.\n- Serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('454','Greek Salmon Salad','## Salmon\n- 4 (6-ounce) salmon fillets\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Salad\n- 1 large cucumber, diced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and halved\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 4 cups mixed salad greens\n\n## Dressing\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Salmon\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Place the salmon fillets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with dried oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Bake for 12-15 minutes until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Prepare the Salad Ingredients\n- While the salmon is baking, prepare the salad ingredients.\n- Dice the cucumber, halve the cherry tomatoes, thinly slice the red onion, and halve the Kalamata olives.\n- In a large bowl, combine the mixed salad greens, cucumber, tomatoes, red onion, olives, and crumbled feta cheese.\n\n## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, minced garlic, salt, and pepper to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- Once the salmon is done, let it cool slightly.\n- Top the mixed salad with the baked salmon fillets.\n- Drizzle the dressing over the top of the salad just before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('455','Mediterranean Quinoa Chicken Bowl','## Chicken Marinade\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Quinoa\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Toppings\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely diced\n- 1/4 cup kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine olive oil, garlic, oregano, basil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the chicken breasts to the marinade, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or up to overnight.\n\n## Cook the Quinoa\n- Rinse quinoa under cold water.\n- In a saucepan, combine quinoa, water, and a pinch of salt.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until water is absorbed.\n- Fluff with a fork and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Preheat grill or stovetop grill pan over medium-high heat.\n- Remove chicken from marinade and cook for 6-7 minutes per side, or until fully cooked.\n- Let rest for a few minutes, then slice into strips.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Divide cooked quinoa into four bowls.\n- Top with grilled chicken strips, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, and feta cheese.\n\n## Prepare the Dressing and Serve\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Drizzle the dressing over the bowls.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('456','Shrimp with Feta and Tomatoes','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 1 can (14 ounces) diced tomatoes, drained\n- 1/2 cup dry white wine\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh basil leaves\n- Crusty bread, for serving','## Preparation\n- Rinse and pat the shrimp dry with paper towels.\n\n## Cooking Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes. Sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in the drained diced tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes, allowing the mixture to thicken slightly.\n- Pour in the white wine and cook for another 3-4 minutes until the sauce reduces a bit.\n- Season the shrimp with salt and pepper, then add them to the skillet.\n- Cook the shrimp for 2-3 minutes on each side until they turn pink and opaque.\n- Sprinkle the crumbled feta over the shrimp and tomatoes.\n- Cover the skillet and let it cook for another 2 minutes, allowing the feta to soften slightly.\n- Remove from heat, drizzle with lemon juice, and sprinkle with fresh parsley.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the shrimp mixture hot, garnished with fresh basil leaves if desired.\n- Accompany with crusty bread for dipping in the sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('457','Grilled Swordfish with Lemon Herb Sauce','## Swordfish\n- 4 swordfish steaks, about 6 ounces each\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## Lemon Herb Sauce\n- 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper, to taste','## Grilling the Swordfish\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Brush both sides of the swordfish steaks with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Grill the swordfish for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until the fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Preparing the Lemon Herb Sauce\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, olive oil, parsley, basil, dill, and minced garlic.\n- Season the sauce with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the grilled swordfish to a serving platter.\n- Drizzle the lemon herb sauce over the top of the steaks before serving.\n- Garnish with additional herbs if desired and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('458','Mediterranean White Bean Chicken Stew','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes, undrained\n- 1 can (15 oz) white beans, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cups chicken broth\n- 1 zucchini, chopped\n- 1 red bell pepper, chopped\n- 1/2 cup kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Cooking Instructions\n- Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in minced garlic and cook for another minute.\n- Add chicken pieces, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper. Cook until the chicken is browned on all sides.\n- Pour in the diced tomatoes and chicken broth. Stir to combine.\n- Add beans, zucchini, and red bell pepper. Bring to a boil.\n- Reduce heat and let simmer for about 20 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and the chicken is cooked through.\n- Stir in olives and fresh parsley.\n- Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper if needed.\n- Serve hot garnished with extra parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('459','Tuna-Stuffed Peppers','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers (any color)\n- 2 cans of tuna in water, drained\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup chopped red onion\n- 1/4 cup chopped celery\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1/4 cup shredded mozzarella cheese\n- Chopped chives','## Prepare the Peppers\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Slice the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.\n- Place the peppers in a baking dish, standing upright.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine the drained tuna, cooked quinoa, Greek yogurt, red onion, celery, parsley, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until well combined.\n\n## Stuff the Peppers\n- Spoon the tuna mixture into each bell pepper, packing it lightly.\n- If using, sprinkle the tops with mozzarella cheese.\n\n## Bake\n- Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 5-10 minutes, until the peppers are tender and the cheese is bubbly.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.\n- Garnish with chopped chives if desired before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('460','Grilled Turkey Kofta','## Kofta Mixture\n- 500g ground turkey\n- 1 small onion, grated\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh mint, chopped\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## To Serve\n- Whole wheat pita bread\n- Greek yogurt\n- Sliced cucumbers\n- Chopped tomatoes\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Kofta Mixture\n- In a large bowl, combine the ground turkey, grated onion, minced garlic, parsley, mint, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well incorporated.\n\n## Shape the Kofta\n- Divide the mixture into 8 equal portions.\n- Shape each portion into an oval or cylindrical shape around a skewer.\n\n## Grill the Kofta\n- Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.\n- Place the kofta skewers on the grill and cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked through.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the grilled turkey kofta with whole wheat pita, a dollop of Greek yogurt, sliced cucumbers, chopped tomatoes, and lemon wedges.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('461','Chickpea & Spinach Scramble','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Crumbled feta cheese\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation Steps\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and garlic to the skillet, and sauté until the onion becomes translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add the ground cumin and paprika, stirring for 1 minute until the spices are fragrant.\n- Add the rinsed chickpeas to the skillet and cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they begin to brown and crisp up slightly.\n- Use a fork to gently mash some of the chickpeas for a varied texture.\n- Add the chopped spinach to the skillet and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Remove from heat and garnish with chopped fresh parsley, crumbled feta cheese, and lemon wedges if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('462','Chicken Spinach Power Bowl','## For the Chicken Marinade\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## For the Bowl\n- 4 cups fresh spinach\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup almonds, sliced\n\n## For the Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon honey\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Marinate the Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Add chicken breasts to the marinade and coat evenly.\n- Let it marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.\n- Remove from heat and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, honey, salt, and pepper.\n- Set aside for serving.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Divide the spinach between two bowls.\n- Top with cooked quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, feta cheese, and almonds.\n- Place sliced chicken on top of each bowl.\n\n## Serve\n- Drizzle the dressing over each bowl before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('463','Caper Lemon Baked Salmon','## Salmon and Marinade\n- 4 salmon fillets (6 oz each)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Topping\n- 2 tablespoons capers, drained\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1 lemon, thinly sliced','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, minced garlic, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.\n- Place the salmon fillets in a baking dish and pour the marinade over them, making sure each piece is well coated.\n- Allow the salmon to marinate for at least 15 minutes for enhanced flavor.\n\n## Baking\n- Arrange lemon slices on top of the marinated salmon fillets.\n- Sprinkle capers over the top of the fillets.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the salmon is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with freshly chopped parsley before serving.\n- Serve hot with a side of steamed vegetables or a fresh salad.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('464','Mediterranean Lentil Power Bowl','## Lentil Base\n- 1 cup green or brown lentils, rinsed\n- 2 cups water or vegetable broth\n- 1 bay leaf\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Vegetable and Protein Toppings\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 cup baby spinach\n- 1/2 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and halved\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1/2 cup hummus\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Cook Lentils\n- In a medium saucepan, combine lentils, water or broth, and bay leaf.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for about 20-25 minutes, or until lentils are tender.\n- Drain any excess liquid and remove the bay leaf.\n- Season with salt to taste and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, red wine vinegar, oregano, garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Set aside to let the flavors meld.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Divide cooked lentils between two bowls.\n- Arrange cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red bell pepper, red onion, spinach, olives, and feta cheese on top of the lentils.\n- Add a dollop of hummus to each bowl.\n- Drizzle the dressing evenly over the bowls.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately while the lentils are warm, or refrigerate and serve cold.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('465','Roasted Eggplant with Spiced Ground Turkey','## Eggplant and Turkey\n- 2 medium eggplants\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n\n## Sauce & Garnish\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- Salt to taste\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts (optional)\n- Chopped parsley for garnish','## Prepare the Eggplants\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Slice the eggplants in half lengthwise and score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern.\n- Brush the cut sides with 1 tablespoon olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n- Place eggplants cut side down on a baking sheet and roast for 25-30 minutes until tender and golden.\n\n## Cook the Turkey Mixture\n- While the eggplant is roasting, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add chopped onion and garlic, sauté until translucent.\n- Add ground turkey, breaking it apart with a spatula, and cook until browned.\n- Stir in red bell pepper, cumin, paprika, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.\n- Cook for an additional 5-7 minutes until the peppers are tender. Stir in chopped parsley.\n\n## Prepare the Sauce & Assemble\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, lemon juice, and a pinch of salt.\n- Once eggplants are done, remove from the oven and let cool slightly.\n- Spoon the turkey mixture onto the roasted eggplant halves.\n- Drizzle with yogurt sauce, garnish with pine nuts and chopped parsley, if desired.\n- Serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('466','Greek Chicken Salad Wrap','## Chicken Marinade\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Salad Ingredients\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 cups mixed greens\n\n## Yogurt Dressing\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Wraps\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas or wraps','## Marinate and Cook the Chicken\n- In a bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n- Add chicken breasts to the marinade, ensuring they are well coated.\n- Cover and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, or up to 4 hours.\n- Preheat grill or stovetop grill pan over medium heat.\n- Cook the chicken breasts for 6-7 minutes per side, or until fully cooked and golden brown.\n- Remove from heat and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing into strips.\n\n## Prepare the Salad and Dressing\n- In a large bowl, combine cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, feta cheese, and mixed greens.\n- In a smaller bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, olive oil, lemon juice, dill, salt, and pepper.\n- Pour dressing over the salad mixture and toss to coat evenly.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Lay each whole wheat tortilla flat.\n- Place a portion of the salad mixture in the center of each wrap.\n- Add slices of grilled chicken on top of the salad mixture.\n- Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll tightly to enclose the ingredients.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('467','Shawarma-Spiced Tofu Bowl','## Tofu and Marinade\n- 14 oz firm tofu, pressed and cubed\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 tbsp lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tbsp ground cumin\n- 1 tbsp ground coriander\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- 1/2 tsp ground turmeric\n- 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Bowl Ingredients\n- 2 cups quinoa, cooked\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup fresh mint, chopped\n\n## Tahini Dressing\n- 1/4 cup tahini\n- 2 tbsp lemon juice\n- 2 tbsp water\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare Tofu\n- Press tofu for at least 15 minutes to remove excess moisture.\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, coriander, paprika, turmeric, cinnamon, cayenne, salt, and pepper.\n- Add cubed tofu to the marinade and toss until well-coated.\n- Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes, ideally 1 hour, in the fridge.\n\n## Cook Tofu\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Spread marinated tofu cubes on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes, turning halfway through, until golden and slightly crispy on the edges.\n\n## Make Tahini Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together tahini, lemon juice, water, garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth.\n\n## Assemble Bowls\n- Divide cooked quinoa among bowls.\n- Top with roasted tofu, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, parsley, and mint.\n- Drizzle with tahini dressing before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('468','Mediterranean Chicken Pasta Salad','## Salad Ingredients\n- 2 cups cooked whole wheat pasta (such as rotini or penne)\n- 2 cups cooked chicken breast, diced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup kalamata olives, pitted and halved\n- 1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Dressing Ingredients\n- 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Pasta\n- Cook the whole wheat pasta according to package instructions. Drain and rinse under cold water to cool.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and a pinch of oregano.\n- Grill or pan-cook the chicken until fully cooked through and juices run clear.\n- Dice the cooked chicken into bite-sized pieces.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, red wine vinegar, minced garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the cooled pasta, diced chicken, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, and feta cheese.\n- Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('469','Lemon Dill Grilled Shrimp','## Shrimp Marinade\n- 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon lemon zest\n- 2 tablespoons fresh dill, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt to taste\n- Black pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish and Serving\n- Lemon wedges\n- Fresh dill sprigs','## Preparing the Marinade\n- In a mixing bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, chopped dill, minced garlic, salt, and black pepper.\n- Add the shrimp to the bowl and toss to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to marinate.\n\n## Grilling the Shrimp\n- Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n- Thread the marinated shrimp onto skewers for easy grilling.\n- Grill the shrimp for about 2-3 minutes on each side, until they are opaque and cooked through.\n- Remove the shrimp from the grill and let them rest for a couple of minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the grilled shrimp to a serving platter.\n- Garnish with fresh dill sprigs and lemon wedges.\n- Serve immediately while hot, alongside your choice of sides like a fresh salad or grilled vegetables.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('470','Greek Zucchini & Turkey Burgers','## Patties\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1 cup grated zucchini (squeeze out excess moisture)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 2 tbsp chopped fresh dill\n- 2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\n- 1 egg, beaten\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## To Serve\n- Whole grain buns or lettuce wraps\n- Sliced tomatoes\n- Sliced cucumbers\n- Tzatziki sauce','## Prepare the Patties\n- Preheat grill or stovetop pan over medium heat.\n- In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, grated zucchini, garlic, red onion, feta cheese, dill, parsley, oregano, egg, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well incorporated, but do not over-mix.\n- Divide the mixture into 4 equal portions and form each into a patty.\n\n## Cook the Patties\n- Lightly oil the grill or pan.\n- Cook patties for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked through and internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\n\n## Assemble and Serve\n- Place each patty on a whole grain bun or in a lettuce wrap.\n- Top with sliced tomatoes, cucumbers, and a dollop of tzatziki sauce.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('471','Greek Chickpea & Tuna Salad','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (5 oz) tuna, drained\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and halved\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped','## Preparation\n- In a large bowl, combine chickpeas, tuna, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, and feta cheese.\n\n## Making the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, red wine vinegar, oregano, salt, and pepper until well combined.\n\n## Combining Everything\n- Pour the dressing over the chickpea and tuna mixture and toss gently to coat all the ingredients evenly.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with freshly chopped parsley before serving.\n- Serve immediately or chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to let the flavors meld.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('472','Mediterranean Lamb Stuffed Peppers','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large bell peppers (red, yellow, or green)\n- 1 lb ground lamb\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1/4 cup chopped kalamata olives\n- 1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted\n- 1 small red onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp ground cumin\n- 1/2 tsp paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes, drained\n\n## For Serving (optional)\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges\n- Greek yogurt','## Prepare the Peppers\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.\n- Lightly brush the outsides of the peppers with olive oil and place them on a baking dish, open side up.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, add 2 tablespoons of olive oil.\n- Sauté the diced onion and minced garlic until they are translucent.\n- Add the ground lamb to the skillet, breaking it up with a wooden spoon, and cook until browned.\n- Stir in the cooked quinoa, drained tomatoes, crumbled feta, chopped olives, and pine nuts.\n- Season with oregano, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper, and combine everything well.\n\n## Stuff and Bake the Peppers\n- Spoon the lamb mixture evenly into each pepper.\n- Cover the dish with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.\n- Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes, until the peppers are tender and slightly charred on the edges.\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and serve with lemon wedges and a dollop of Greek yogurt, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('473','Roasted Chickpeas & Eggs Breakfast Bowl','## Chickpeas\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Bowls\n- 4 large eggs\n- 2 cups fresh spinach\n- 1 ripe avocado, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- Fresh parsley or cilantro, chopped (optional)','## Roasted Chickpeas\n- Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).\n- Pat the chickpeas dry with a paper towel.\n- In a bowl, toss chickpeas with olive oil, smoked paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n- Spread chickpeas on a baking sheet and roast for 20-25 minutes, until crispy, stirring halfway through.\n\n## Eggs\n- Bring a pot of water to a gentle simmer.\n- Carefully add the eggs and cook for 7 minutes for soft-boiled or 10 minutes for hard-boiled.\n- Remove eggs and place them in an ice bath to cool.\n- Peel and slice them when ready to serve.\n\n## Assembly\n- In a serving bowl, layer fresh spinach.\n- Add roasted chickpeas, sliced eggs, avocado slices, cherry tomatoes, and crumbled feta cheese.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley or cilantro if desired.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('474','Hummus Chicken Salad','## For the Salad\n- 2 cups cooked chicken breast, shredded or diced\n- 1 cup canned chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cup cucumber, diced\n- 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 2 cups mixed salad greens\n\n## For the Hummus Dressing\n- 1/2 cup plain hummus\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together hummus, olive oil, lemon juice, apple cider vinegar, and garlic powder.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine the shredded chicken, chickpeas, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, and parsley.\n- Pour the hummus dressing over the salad and toss to coat evenly.\n- Serve the salad over mixed greens.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('475','Herbed Chicken & Farro Bowl','## For the Herbed Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 teaspoon dried basil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Farro Bowl\n- 1 cup farro\n- 2 cups chicken broth or water\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Herbed Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, basil, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the chicken breasts to the marinade and coat well. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes.\n- Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Cook the chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked.\n- Remove from heat and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.\n\n## Cook the Farro\n- Rinse the farro under cold water.\n- In a medium pot, bring chicken broth or water to a boil.\n- Add farro, reduce heat to a simmer, and cover.\n- Cook for 25-30 minutes, or until farro is tender.\n- Drain any excess liquid and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Farro Bowl\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked farro, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, and parsley.\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, red wine vinegar, salt, and pepper.\n- Drizzle the dressing over the farro mixture and toss to coat.\n- Divide the farro salad into bowls.\n- Top each bowl with sliced herbed chicken and feta cheese.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('476','Spicy Mediterranean Tofu Wrap','## Tofu Marinade\n- 14 oz firm tofu, pressed and cubed\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 2 teaspoons smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Wrap Ingredients\n- 4 whole wheat wraps or tortillas\n- 1 cup hummus\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cucumber, sliced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/3 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and sliced\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n\n## Spicy Yogurt Sauce\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon harissa paste\n- 1 teaspoon lemon juice\n- Salt to taste','## Prepare the Tofu\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, smoked paprika, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Add the cubed tofu to the marinade and let it sit for 20-30 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Tofu\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat.\n- Add marinated tofu and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 8-10 minutes. Set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Spicy Yogurt Sauce\n- In a small bowl, combine Greek yogurt, harissa paste, lemon juice, and salt.\n- Mix well and adjust seasoning if needed.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Warm the wraps or tortillas in a dry pan or microwave.\n- Spread a layer of hummus on each wrap.\n- Top with cooked tofu, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, and feta cheese.\n- Drizzle with spicy yogurt sauce.\n- Sprinkle fresh parsley over the top.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('477','Mediterranean Egg Salad Lettuce Wraps','## Egg Salad\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons mayonnaise\n- 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard\n- 1/4 cup chopped kalamata olives\n- 1/4 cup diced cucumber\n- 1/4 cup chopped sun-dried tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup chopped red onion\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Wraps\n- Large romaine lettuce leaves\n- Crumbled feta cheese (optional)\n- Sliced avocado (optional)','## Prepare the Eggs\n- Place eggs in a pot and cover with cold water.\n- Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.\n- Once boiling, remove from heat, cover, and let sit for 10 minutes.\n- Transfer eggs to a bowl of ice water to cool, then peel and chop.\n\n## Make the Egg Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, mayonnaise, and Dijon mustard.\n- Add chopped eggs, kalamata olives, cucumber, sun-dried tomatoes, red onion, and parsley.\n- Mix until well combined.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Spoon egg salad into the center of each lettuce leaf.\n- Top with crumbled feta cheese and sliced avocado if using.\n- Fold the lettuce around the filling and enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('478','Lamb Pita with Cucumber Yogurt Sauce','## Lamb Filling\n- 500g ground lamb\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Cucumber Yogurt Sauce\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cucumber, grated and drained\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Pita and Assembly\n- 4 whole wheat pitas\n- 1 tomato, diced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1/2 cup lettuce, shredded','## Prepare the Lamb Filling\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, heat olive oil.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 30 seconds.\n- Add ground lamb and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon, about 8-10 minutes.\n- Stir in cumin, coriander, cinnamon, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper, and cook for 2 more minutes.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Make the Cucumber Yogurt Sauce\n- In a bowl, combine Greek yogurt, grated cucumber, minced garlic, lemon juice, fresh dill, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well and refrigerate until ready to use.\n\n## Assemble the Pitas\n- Warm the pitas in a dry skillet or oven until pliable.\n- Spread a generous amount of cucumber yogurt sauce inside each pita.\n- Fill with the cooked lamb mixture.\n- Top with diced tomato, sliced red onion, and shredded lettuce.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('479','Fava Bean & Egg Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup fava beans, shelled and cooked\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 cup spinach, washed and chopped\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 avocado, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1 tablespoon crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh herbs (such as parsley or cilantro)\n- Red pepper flakes','## Prepare Fava Beans\n- If using fresh fava beans, remove beans from their pods. Boil them in salted water for 2-3 minutes, then transfer to an ice bath. Once cool, peel off the skins.\n\n## Cook Eggs\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and add a bit of olive oil.\n- Crack the eggs into the skillet. Cook to your liking (soft, medium, or hard yolks). Season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Sauté Spinach and Tomatoes\n- In another pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add chopped spinach and cherry tomatoes. Sauté until the spinach is wilted and tomatoes are slightly blistered, about 2-3 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- In a serving bowl, layer the cooked fava beans at the bottom.\n- Add the sautéed spinach and tomatoes on top.\n- Gently place the cooked eggs over the vegetables.\n- Add sliced avocado around the bowl.\n- Sprinkle with optional toppings like feta cheese, fresh herbs, or red pepper flakes if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('480','Eggplant & Lentil Moussaka','## Eggplant Layer\n- 2 large eggplants, sliced into 1/4 inch rounds\n- Salt, for sprinkling\n\n## Lentil Filling\n- 1 cup dried green or brown lentils, rinsed\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 tablespoon tomato paste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Béchamel Sauce\n- 2 tablespoons butter or olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour (or whole wheat flour)\n- 2 cups milk (or plant-based milk)\n- 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Topping\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese (optional, for a non-vegan version)','## Prepare Eggplants\n- Sprinkle the eggplant slices with salt and let them sit for 30 minutes to draw out moisture. Rinse and pat dry.\n\n## Cook Lentils\n- In a pot, cover the lentils with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20-25 minutes until tender. Drain and set aside.\n\n## Make Lentil Filling\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add chopped onions and garlic, sauté until translucent.\n- Add cooked lentils, diced tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n- Simmer for 10-15 minutes until thickened.\n\n## Make Béchamel Sauce\n- In a saucepan, melt butter or heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Whisk in flour and cook for 1-2 minutes.\n- Gradually whisk in milk, stirring constantly until thickened.\n- Season with nutmeg, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Assemble Moussaka\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Lightly oil a baking dish.\n- Layer half of the eggplant slices on the bottom of the dish.\n- Spread the lentil mixture over the eggplants.\n- Layer the remaining eggplant slices on top.\n- Pour the béchamel sauce evenly over the top layer.\n- Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if using.\n\n## Bake\n- Bake in preheated oven for 30-35 minutes until the top is golden and bubbly.\n- Allow to cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('481','Spinach and Tuna Stuffed Pita','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 whole grain pitas\n- 1 can (5 oz) tuna, drained\n- 1 cup fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (plain, non-fat)\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup bell pepper, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Feta cheese\n- Chopped cucumber\n- Tomato slices','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a medium-sized bowl, combine the tuna, chopped spinach, Greek yogurt, red onion, bell pepper, lemon juice, and olive oil. Mix well.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Assembly\n- Cut the pitas in half to create pockets.\n- Stuff each pita half with the tuna and spinach mixture.\n- Place the stuffed pitas on a baking sheet.\n\n## Cooking\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes, or until the pitas are slightly crispy and the filling is warmed through.\n- Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve warm, optionally topped with feta cheese, chopped cucumber, or tomato slices.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('482','Seared Chicken with Lemon Tahini Sauce','## Chicken\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n\n## Lemon Tahini Sauce\n- 1/2 cup tahini\n- 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons water (more as needed)\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 garlic clove, minced\n- Salt to taste\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley (optional)\n\n## Garnish (optional)\n- Lemon slices\n- Chopped parsley','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Pat the chicken breasts dry with paper towels.\n- Season both sides with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika.\n- Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n\n## Sear the Chicken\n- Add the chicken breasts to the skillet, cooking in batches if necessary.\n- Sear each side for about 5-7 minutes until golden brown and cooked through (internal temperature should reach 165°F or 75°C).\n- Remove from the skillet and let them rest for a few minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Lemon Tahini Sauce\n- In a bowl, whisk together tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, minced garlic, and salt.\n- Add water gradually until the sauce reaches a creamy, pourable consistency.\n- Stir in fresh parsley for added flavor, if desired.\n\n## Serve\n- Slice the seared chicken breasts.\n- Drizzle the lemon tahini sauce over the chicken.\n- Garnish with lemon slices and chopped parsley, if using.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('483','Zucchini Noodles with Shrimp & Feta','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 medium zucchinis\n- 1 lb raw shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 4 oz feta cheese, crumbled\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 lemon, juiced and zested\n- 1/2 tsp red pepper flakes\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare the Zucchini Noodles\n- Use a spiralizer to cut the zucchinis into noodle-like strands.\n- Place the zucchini noodles in a colander, sprinkle with a pinch of salt, and let them sit for 15 minutes to drain excess moisture.\n\n## Cook the Shrimp\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add minced garlic and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Add the shrimp to the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook for about 2-3 minutes on each side until they are pink and opaque.\n- Remove shrimp from the skillet and set aside.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- In the same skillet, add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil.\n- Add zucchini noodles and sauté for 2-3 minutes until just tender.\n- Add lemon juice, zest, red pepper flakes, and cooked shrimp back into the skillet.\n- Toss everything together and cook for another minute or two until warmed through.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Remove the skillet from heat, and sprinkle crumbled feta cheese over the top.\n- Gently mix the feta into the noodles and shrimp.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley and serve with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('484','Yogurt-Marinated Chicken Skewers','## For the Marinade\n- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Skewers\n- 1.5 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into 1-inch cubes\n- 1 large red bell pepper, cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 1 large green bell pepper, cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 1 large red onion, cut into 1-inch pieces\n- 8-10 wooden or metal skewers','## Prepare the Marinade\n- In a large bowl, combine the Greek yogurt, olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, cumin, paprika, turmeric, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix until well blended.\n\n## Marinate the Chicken\n- Add the cubed chicken to the marinade, ensuring each piece is coated.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or overnight for best results.\n\n## Prepare the Skewers\n- If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for at least 30 minutes to prevent burning.\n- Remove marinated chicken from the refrigerator.\n- Alternately thread the chicken, bell peppers, and onion onto the skewers.\n\n## Cook the Skewers\n- Preheat a grill to medium-high heat.\n- Place skewers on the grill and cook for about 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.\n- Ensure chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from grill and let rest for a few minutes.\n- Serve with a fresh salad or whole-grain pita bread.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('485','Grilled Fish Gyro Wrap','## Fish Marinade\n- 4 fillets of white fish (such as tilapia or cod)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Yogurt Sauce\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Wrap Ingredients\n- 4 whole wheat flatbreads or pita breads\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup sliced cucumbers\n- 1/2 cup sliced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup red onion, thinly sliced','## Prepare the Fish\n- In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Coat fish fillets with the marinade and let them sit for at least 20 minutes.\n- Preheat grill to medium-high heat.\n- Grill fish fillets for 3-4 minutes on each side until cooked through.\n- Remove from the grill and set aside.\n\n## Make the Yogurt Sauce\n- In a small bowl, combine Greek yogurt, lemon juice, dill, minced garlic, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well and adjust seasoning to taste.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Warm the flatbreads on the grill or a pan for about 1 minute on each side.\n- Place a grilled fish fillet on each flatbread.\n- Top with shredded lettuce, cucumbers, tomatoes, and red onion.\n- Drizzle with the yogurt sauce.\n- Wrap tightly and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('486','Smoked Salmon Avocado Toast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices whole-grain or sourdough bread\n- 2 ripe avocados\n- 200g smoked salmon\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved\n- Capers\n- Radish slices\n- Microgreens or arugula\n- Red onion, thinly sliced\n- Sesame seeds','## Preparations\n- Toast the bread slices until golden brown and crispy.\n- While the bread is toasting, cut the avocados in half, remove the pits, and scoop the flesh into a bowl.\n- Add lemon juice, salt, and pepper to the avocado. Mash with a fork until smooth and creamy.\n\n## Assembly\n- Spread a generous amount of the mashed avocado on each slice of toasted bread.\n- Layer slices of smoked salmon on top of the avocado.\n- Add any optional toppings like cherry tomatoes, capers, radish slices, microgreens, or red onion as desired.\n- Sprinkle with sesame seeds for an extra crunch.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('487','Protein Chia Pudding with Whey','## Main Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons chia seeds\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- Fresh fruit, nuts, or seeds for topping','## Preparation Steps\n- In a medium-sized bowl, combine chia seeds and whey protein powder.\n- Add almond milk and vanilla extract to the bowl, stirring well to ensure there are no clumps.\n- If using sweetener, add honey or maple syrup and mix thoroughly.\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight for a thicker consistency.\n\n## Serving\n- Stir the pudding to break up any clumps and ensure even consistency.\n- Divide the chia pudding into two servings.\n- Top with fresh fruit, nuts, or seeds as desired before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('488','Turkey & Egg Breakfast Quesadilla','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 cup cooked turkey, shredded\n- 1/4 cup bell peppers, diced\n- 1/4 cup onion, diced\n- 1/4 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or Mexican blend)\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas\n\n## Seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder','## Preparation\n- Crack the eggs into a bowl, season with salt, pepper, paprika, and garlic powder, then whisk until well combined.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the diced bell peppers and onions to the skillet and sauté until they soften, about 3 minutes.\n- Add the spinach, followed by the shredded turkey. Stir and cook for 2 more minutes.\n- Pour the whisked eggs into the skillet, stirring occasionally until the eggs are fully cooked and scrambled with the vegetables and turkey. Remove the mixture from the skillet and set aside.\n- Wipe the skillet clean and place one tortilla in the skillet over medium heat.\n- Sprinkle a layer of cheese on one half of the tortilla. Place half the scrambled egg and turkey mixture over the cheese, then fold the tortilla in half.\n- Cook for 2 minutes on each side or until the cheese is melted and the tortilla is golden brown.\n- Repeat the process with the second tortilla.\n\n## Serving\n- Cut the quesadillas into wedges and serve hot.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('489','Quinoa Breakfast Bowl with Eggs','## For the Quinoa\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## For the Bowls\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 ripe avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika (optional)','## Cook the Quinoa\n- Rinse the quinoa under cold water using a fine mesh strainer.\n- In a medium saucepan, add the quinoa, water, and a pinch of salt.\n- Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.\n- Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes, or until the quinoa is tender and the water is absorbed.\n- Fluff the quinoa with a fork and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Eggs and Vegetables\n- In a large non-stick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.\n- Crack the eggs into the skillet and cook until the whites are set, but the yolks are still runny (about 3-4 minutes). For firmer yolks, cover the skillet with a lid for an extra minute. Season with salt, pepper, and paprika (if using).\n- Remove the eggs and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add the cherry tomatoes and cook for 2-3 minutes, just until they start to soften.\n\n## Assemble the Bowls\n- Divide the cooked quinoa among 4 bowls.\n- Top each bowl with a cooked egg, avocado slices, sautéed cherry tomatoes, and a sprinkle of feta cheese.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley, and add additional salt and pepper to taste.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('490','Chicken Sausage Breakfast Hash','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 pound chicken sausage, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 2 bell peppers (any color), diced\n- 2 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and cubed\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 4 eggs\n- Fresh parsley, chopped for garnish','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- In a large, oven-safe skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the sliced chicken sausage and cook until browned, about 5 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 3 minutes.\n- Add the bell peppers and sweet potatoes to the skillet. Season with salt, pepper, smoked paprika, and thyme if using.\n- Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sweet potatoes begin to soften.\n- Return the sausage to the skillet and mix well with the vegetables.\n- Make four wells in the hash and crack one egg into each well if using.\n\n## Baking\n- Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for about 15 minutes, or until the eggs are cooked to your liking and the sweet potatoes are tender.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.\n- Sprinkle with fresh parsley before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('491','Black Bean & Turkey Breakfast Tacos','## For the Tacos\n- 1 cup cooked black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1/2 pound ground turkey\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon taco seasoning\n- 4 corn tortillas\n- 4 large eggs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Toppings\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup chopped cilantro\n- 1/4 cup diced red onion\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta or cotija cheese (optional)\n- Lime wedges','## Prepare the Filling\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add ground turkey and season with taco seasoning, cooking until browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Add the black beans to the turkey mixture and stir to combine. Cook for another 2-3 minutes.\n- In a separate non-stick pan, scramble the eggs until just set. Season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Tacos\n- Warm the corn tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until pliable.\n- Divide the turkey and black bean mixture equally onto each tortilla.\n- Top each with a portion of scrambled eggs.\n\n## Add Toppings\n- Add diced tomatoes, red onion, and cilantro over the eggs.\n- Place avocado slices on top and sprinkle with cheese, if using.\n- Squeeze a lime wedge over each taco for extra freshness.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('492','Mushroom & Tofu Breakfast Stir-Fry','## Stir-Fry Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 200g firm tofu, drained and cubed\n- 150g mushrooms, sliced (e.g., shiitake, button, or cremini)\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 small onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 cups spinach leaves\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon sesame oil\n- 1 teaspoon ginger, grated\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons green onions, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- Fresh ground black pepper, to taste','## Preparation\n- Press tofu to remove excess water, then cut into cubes.\n- Prepare and slice all vegetables and mushrooms.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add tofu cubes and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Remove tofu from the pan and set aside.\n- In the same pan, add a bit more olive oil if needed, then add onions and garlic. Sauté until translucent, about 3 minutes.\n- Add mushrooms and red bell pepper. Stir-fry until softened, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in the ginger and soy sauce.\n- Return tofu to the pan and add spinach and sesame oil. Stir-fry until spinach is wilted and everything is well combined, about 2 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the stir-fry hot, garnished with chopped green onions, sesame seeds, and freshly ground black pepper.\n- Enjoy your healthy and protein-packed breakfast!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('493','Salmon & Cottage Cheese Toast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of whole-grain bread\n- 200g smoked salmon, thinly sliced\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- Handful of arugula or spinach\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved','## Prepare the Cottage Cheese Spread\n- In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese with lemon juice and chopped dill.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Mix well until the ingredients are combined.\n\n## Assemble the Toast\n- Toast the slices of whole-grain bread until golden brown.\n- Spread the cottage cheese mixture evenly over each slice of toast.\n- Lay slices of smoked salmon over the cottage cheese.\n\n## Add Optional Garnishes\n- Top with avocado slices, arugula, or spinach if desired.\n- Scatter halved cherry tomatoes for extra freshness and flavor.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut each toast in half, if preferred, and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('494','Smoked Tofu Breakfast Wrap','## Main Ingredients\n- 200g smoked tofu, sliced\n- 4 whole grain tortillas or wraps\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 small red onion, sliced\n- 1 cup baby spinach leaves\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheese (optional for extra protein, e.g., cheddar or mozzarella)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n## Spice Mix\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- Hot sauce or salsa (optional)\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped (optional)','## Prepare the Tofu and Vegetables\n- In a skillet over medium heat, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.\n- Add sliced red onion and red bell pepper. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until softened.\n- Add smoked tofu slices to the skillet.\n- Sprinkle the spice mix over the tofu and vegetables and stir to combine.\n- Cook for an additional 5-7 minutes until tofu is heated through and slightly crispy on the edges.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Warm the tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave for a few seconds until pliable.\n- Place a portion of spinach in the center of each tortilla.\n- Top with the tofu and vegetable mixture.\n- Sprinkle with cheese if using.\n- Add a drizzle of hot sauce or salsa if desired.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Fold in the sides of each tortilla, then roll up the wraps tightly.\n- Slice in half if desired and serve immediately, garnished with fresh cilantro if using.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('495','Protein-Packed Banana Egg Pancakes','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 ripe bananas\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 2 tablespoons protein powder (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1 pinch salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Greek yogurt\n- Fresh berries (e.g., blueberries, strawberries)\n- Honey or maple syrup\n- Chopped nuts (e.g., almonds, walnuts)','## Preparation\n- Mash the bananas in a large mixing bowl until smooth.\n- Crack the eggs into the mashed bananas and whisk until well combined.\n- Add almond flour, protein powder (if using), baking powder, and salt to the banana-egg mixture. Stir until a smooth batter forms.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat and lightly coat with cooking spray or a small amount of oil.\n- Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.\n- Cook pancakes for about 2-3 minutes, until bubbles form on the surface and the edges start to look dry.\n- Flip and cook for another 2 minutes, or until golden brown on the other side.\n- Transfer the pancakes to a plate and keep warm. Repeat with the remaining batter.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the pancakes warm with optional toppings like Greek yogurt, fresh berries, honey, maple syrup, or chopped nuts.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('496','Spicy Ground Beef & Eggs Breakfast Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb lean ground beef\n- 1 medium onion, diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 bell pepper, diced\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and minced\n- 2 cups fresh spinach\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Spices & Seasoning\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Red pepper flakes (optional, for extra heat)\n\n## Toppings & Garnishes\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lime wedges','## Prepare the Ground Beef Mixture\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add diced onion, garlic, bell pepper, and jalapeño. Sauté until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the ground beef to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spatula.\n- Cook until the beef is browned, about 7-10 minutes.\n- Stir in the chili powder, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. If you like extra heat, add some red pepper flakes.\n- Add black beans and spinach to the mixture and cook for another 3-5 minutes until the spinach is wilted.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- In a separate non-stick pan, cook the eggs to your preference—either scrambled or fried.\n- Season with a little salt and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Breakfast Bowls\n- Divide the beef and bean mixture into four bowls.\n- Top each bowl with an egg.\n- Add sliced avocado on the side.\n- Sprinkle with fresh cilantro and serve with a lime wedge.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('497','Almond Butter Protein Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 2 tablespoons almond butter\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1 medium banana\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Ice cubes (optional)\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Sliced almonds\n- Banana slices\n- A sprinkle of cinnamon','## Preparation Steps\n- In a blender, combine the almond milk, almond butter, vanilla protein powder, banana, chia seeds, and vanilla extract.\n- Blend on high until smooth and creamy. If a thicker consistency is desired, add a few ice cubes and blend again.\n- Taste and adjust sweetness if needed by adding a small amount of honey or maple syrup (optional).\n\n## Serving Suggestions\n- Pour the smoothie into a glass.\n- Garnish with sliced almonds, banana slices, and a sprinkle of cinnamon if desired.\n- Serve immediately while cold.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('498','Quinoa & Egg Protein Porridge','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n\n## Flavor and Garnish\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce or tamari (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon sesame oil\n- 2 green onions, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon sesame seeds\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1/2 cup steamed spinach or kale\n- 1/4 cup diced bell peppers\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh herbs (such as cilantro or parsley)','## Prepare Quinoa\n- Rinse the quinoa under cold water using a fine mesh strainer.\n- In a medium saucepan, bring the water and salt to a boil.\n- Add the quinoa, reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes or until the quinoa is tender and water is absorbed.\n- Fluff quinoa with a fork and set aside.\n\n## Cook Eggs\n- In a separate saucepan, bring water to a gentle simmer.\n- Crack eggs into a small bowl and gently slide into the simmering water.\n- Poach for 3-4 minutes, until whites are set but yolks remain runny.\n- Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Porridge\n- Divide the cooked quinoa into bowls.\n- If using, stir in soy sauce or tamari and sesame oil for flavor.\n- Top each serving with a poached egg.\n- Sprinkle with chopped green onions, sesame seeds, and any optional add-ins like spinach or bell peppers.\n- Season with additional salt and pepper as needed.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('499','Mediterranean Chicken Egg Wrap','## For the Chicken\n- 1 lb (450g) boneless, skinless chicken breast\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Wrap\n- 6 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons milk\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Non-stick cooking spray\n\n## For the Filling\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh mint\n- 1/2 cup diced cucumber\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1/4 cup sliced Kalamata olives','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Rub chicken breasts with olive oil, oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.\n- Place on a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until fully cooked.\n- Let the chicken cool slightly, then slice into thin strips.\n\n## Make the Egg Wraps\n- In a bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and spray with cooking spray.\n- Pour a portion of the egg mixture into the skillet to form a thin, even layer.\n- Cook for 1-2 minutes or until set, then carefully flip and cook the other side for 1 minute.\n- Repeat to make multiple wraps.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a small bowl, combine Greek yogurt and lemon juice to make a sauce.\n- Mix parsley, mint, cucumber, tomatoes, feta cheese, and olives in a bowl.\n- Toss the mixture with the yogurt sauce.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Take an egg wrap, layer slices of chicken, and spoon filling on top.\n- Roll up tightly and slice in half if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('500','Tempeh Breakfast Burrito','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 oz tempeh, crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric\n- 1 teaspoon cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 4 large whole wheat tortillas\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 cup fresh spinach leaves\n- 1/2 cup salsa\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (optional)\n- Hot sauce to taste (optional)','## Prepare Tempeh Scramble\n- In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add crumbled tempeh to the skillet and sauté for 3-4 minutes until it begins to brown.\n- Sprinkle turmeric, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper over the tempeh.\n- Continue to cook for another 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the tempeh is well-coated and heated through.\n\n## Assemble Burritos\n- Lay out a tortilla on a flat surface.\n- Place a portion of the cooked tempeh scramble in the center of the tortilla.\n- Add slices of avocado and a handful of fresh spinach leaves.\n- Top with a spoonful of salsa.\n- If using, sprinkle with shredded cheese and add hot sauce to taste.\n- Roll the tortilla tightly around the filling to form a burrito.\n\n## Serve and Enjoy\n- Serve immediately or wrap in foil for an on-the-go breakfast option.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('501','Cottage Cheese & Smoked Salmon Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 100g smoked salmon, sliced\n- 1/2 cucumber, thinly sliced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 tablespoon capers\n- 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 hard-boiled egg, sliced','## Prepare the Base\n- In a medium bowl, spread the cottage cheese as the base layer.\n\n## Add the Salmon and Vegetables\n- Evenly distribute the smoked salmon slices over the cottage cheese.\n- Top with cucumber, red onion, and capers.\n\n## Season and Garnish\n- Drizzle lemon juice over the bowl.\n- Sprinkle with fresh dill, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Add Optional Toppings\n- If desired, add slices of avocado, halved cherry tomatoes, or a hard-boiled egg for extra flavor and protein.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve immediately and enjoy this fresh, protein-packed meal!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('502','Breakfast Farro with Poached Egg & Chickpeas','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup farro\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, rinsed and drained\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley\n- Red pepper flakes to taste','## Cook Farro\n- Rinse 1 cup of farro under cold water.\n- In a medium saucepan, combine farro and 2 cups of water.\n- Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for about 20-25 minutes until tender.\n- Drain any excess water and set aside.\n\n## Prepare Chickpeas\n- Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add rinsed and drained chickpeas.\n- Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper.\n- Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chickpeas are slightly crispy.\n- Set aside.\n\n## Poach Eggs\n- Fill a shallow saucepan with about 2 inches of water and bring to a gentle simmer.\n- Crack an egg into a small bowl.\n- Create a gentle whirlpool in the water with a spoon and slowly pour the egg into the center.\n- Poach the egg for about 3-4 minutes for a runny yolk, or longer for a firmer yolk.\n- Carefully remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.\n- Repeat with the second egg.\n\n## Assemble\n- In serving bowls, layer the cooked farro and crispy chickpeas.\n- Top each serving with a poached egg.\n- Optionally, add sliced avocado, a squeeze of lemon juice, crumbled feta cheese, and fresh parsley.\n- Sprinkle with red pepper flakes for some heat, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('503','Breakfast Chicken Sausage Frittata Muffins','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 large eggs\n- 1/2 pound ground chicken sausage\n- 1/2 cup bell pepper, diced\n- 1/2 cup baby spinach, chopped\n- 1/4 cup onion, diced\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Sliced green onions\n- Hot sauce','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with olive oil or cooking spray.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the ground chicken sausage, onion, and bell pepper, cooking until the sausage is browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, salt, and pepper.\n- Stir in the cooked sausage mixture, baby spinach, and shredded cheddar cheese.\n- Divide the mixture evenly among the muffin cups, filling each about three-quarters full.\n\n## Baking\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until the egg is fully set and the tops are golden brown.\n- Remove from the oven and allow to cool for a few minutes before removing from the muffin tin.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve warm, garnished with sliced green onions and a dash of hot sauce if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('504','Savory Oatmeal with Egg & Turkey','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 2 cups water or low-sodium chicken broth\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 4 ounces ground turkey\n- 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 cup baby spinach, chopped\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce or tamari (optional)\n- 2 green onions, sliced\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped (optional)','## Prepare the Oatmeal\n- In a medium saucepan, bring 2 cups of water or low-sodium chicken broth to a boil.\n- Stir in 1 cup of rolled oats and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.\n- Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the oats are tender and the liquid is absorbed.\n\n## Cook the Turkey\n- In a skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil.\n- Add 4 ounces of ground turkey, 1/4 teaspoon of garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon of onion powder, and 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper.\n- Cook for about 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the turkey is browned and cooked through.\n- Stir in 1/2 cup of chopped baby spinach and cook until wilted, about 1-2 minutes.\n\n## Prepare the Eggs\n- In another pan, cook 2 large eggs according to your preference (fried, poached, or scrambled).\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Divide the cooked oatmeal into two bowls.\n- Top each serving with half of the turkey and spinach mixture.\n- Add a cooked egg to each bowl.\n- Drizzle with soy sauce or tamari if using.\n- Garnish with sliced green onions and chopped parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('505','Protein Matcha Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 frozen banana\n- 1 tablespoon matcha powder\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon almond butter\n- 1 teaspoon honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Chia seeds\n- Sliced almonds\n- Sliced strawberries','## Preparation\n- Add the unsweetened almond milk, frozen banana, matcha powder, vanilla protein powder, almond butter, honey or maple syrup (if using), and vanilla extract to a blender.\n- Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy. Taste and adjust the sweetness by adding more honey or maple syrup if needed.\n- Pour the smoothie into a glass and top with chia seeds, sliced almonds, or strawberries if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('506','Tuna & Egg Breakfast Wrap','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 whole wheat tortilla\n- 1 can tuna in water, drained\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon Greek yogurt\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or mozzarella)\n- 1/4 cup baby spinach leaves\n- 1 small tomato, diced\n\n## Optional Add-ons\n- Sliced avocado\n- Hot sauce\n- Chopped fresh herbs (parsley or chives)\n\n## Cooking Essentials\n- Non-stick skillet\n- Mixing bowl\n- Spatula','## Preparation\n- In a mixing bowl, combine drained tuna, Greek yogurt, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper. Mix well until combined.\n- Crack the eggs into another bowl, add a pinch of salt and pepper, and beat them until well mixed.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and add the beaten eggs. Scramble until just set, then remove from the pan and set aside.\n- In the same skillet, place the tortilla and warm for about 30 seconds on each side until soft and pliable.\n\n## Assembly\n- Lay the warm tortilla flat on a plate and spread the tuna mixture evenly over it.\n- Top with scrambled eggs, shredded cheese, baby spinach, and diced tomato.\n- Add optional add-ons like sliced avocado, hot sauce, or herbs if desired.\n\n## Final Steps\n- Roll the tortilla tightly into a wrap, slice in half, and serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('507','Turkey Bacon & Egg Casserole','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 slices turkey bacon\n- 10 large eggs\n- 1 cup low-fat milk\n- 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/2 cup chopped onions\n- 1/2 cup chopped bell peppers (any color)\n- 1 cup chopped spinach\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Sliced green onions','## Preparation Steps\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish with cooking spray or a small amount of oil.\n\n## Cooking Turkey Bacon\n- In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the turkey bacon until crispy.\n- Once cooked, remove the bacon and place on a paper towel-lined plate to drain excess fat.\n- Once cool, chop the turkey bacon into bite-sized pieces.\n\n## Combining Ingredients\n- In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper, and garlic powder until well combined.\n- Stir in the chopped onions, bell peppers, spinach, and half of the shredded cheddar cheese.\n- Add the chopped turkey bacon into the mixture and stir to combine.\n\n## Baking\n- Pour the egg mixture into the prepared baking dish and spread evenly.\n- Sprinkle the remaining cheddar cheese on top.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 35-40 minutes or until the eggs are set and the top is golden brown.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove the casserole from the oven and let it cool slightly before slicing.\n- Garnish with chopped parsley or sliced green onions if desired.\n- Serve warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('508','Cottage Cheese Breakfast Tacos','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 small corn tortillas\n- 1 cup cottage cheese\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 red onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- Hot sauce or salsa\n- Lime wedges','## Prepare Ingredients\n- Halve the cherry tomatoes.\n- Finely chop the red onion.\n- Drain and rinse the black beans.\n- Chop the fresh cilantro.\n\n## Cook Eggs\n- In a non-stick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.\n- Crack the eggs into the skillet and scramble them, cooking until just set, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Season the eggs with salt and pepper, then remove from heat.\n\n## Assemble Tacos\n- Warm the corn tortillas in a dry skillet over medium heat, about 30 seconds on each side, until pliable.\n- Divide the cottage cheese evenly among the tortillas.\n- Top each with scrambled eggs, black beans, cherry tomatoes, and red onion.\n- Sprinkle with fresh cilantro.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve with optional avocado slices, hot sauce or salsa, and lime wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('509','Middle Eastern Spiced Lentil Scramble','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup cooked green or brown lentils\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon ground coriander\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Sliced green onions\n- Crumbled feta cheese\n- Sliced avocado\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Cook the lentils according to package instructions if not already cooked. Drain and set aside.\n- In a bowl, beat the eggs and season with a pinch of salt and pepper.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes.\n- Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Stir in the cooked lentils, cumin, coriander, turmeric, and smoked paprika. Cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring frequently, until the spices are fragrant.\n- Pour the beaten eggs into the skillet and gently stir, integrating the lentils and spices into the eggs.\n- Continue to cook while stirring occasionally, until the eggs are set to your preference, about 3-5 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Transfer the scramble to plates and garnish with optional toppings like parsley, green onions, feta, avocado, or a squeeze of lemon as desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('510','Shrimp & Egg White Omelette Wrap','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 8 egg whites\n- 1/4 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1/4 cup red bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup green onions, thinly sliced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## Wrap and Garnish\n- 2 whole wheat tortillas\n- Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish)\n- Lemon wedges','## Prepare Ingredients\n- Rinse and pat dry the shrimp. Set aside.\n- Chop spinach, dice red bell pepper, and slice green onions.\n\n## Cook the Shrimp\n- Heat 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add shrimp to the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook until they turn pink, about 2-3 minutes per side.\n- Remove shrimp from skillet and set aside.\n\n## Make the Omelette\n- In a bowl, whisk the egg whites with a pinch of salt and pepper.\n- Heat the remaining 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil in the same skillet over medium-low heat.\n- Pour the egg whites into the skillet, swirling to coat the bottom evenly.\n- Cook for 2-3 minutes until the edges start to set.\n- Sprinkle the spinach, red bell pepper, and green onions over the egg whites.\n- Cook until the eggs are fully set, about 3 more minutes.\n\n## Assemble Wraps\n- Place the whole wheat tortillas on a flat surface.\n- Carefully slide the omelette onto one tortilla.\n- Arrange cooked shrimp over half of the omelette.\n- Fold the tortilla over the filling to create a wrap.\n- Repeat with the second tortilla and remaining ingredients.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut each wrap in half and serve with lemon wedges on the side.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('511','Peanut Butter Protein Overnight Oats','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 tablespoons natural peanut butter\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n\n## Protein Boost\n- 1 scoop vanilla or chocolate protein powder\n\n## Sweetener (optional)\n- 1-2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n\n## Toppings (optional, choose your favorites)\n- Sliced bananas\n- Fresh berries\n- Chopped nuts\n- Cacao nibs\n- Coconut flakes','## Preparation\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the rolled oats, almond milk, Greek yogurt, peanut butter, chia seeds, and protein powder.\n- If desired, add honey or maple syrup to taste for sweetness.\n- Mix all ingredients thoroughly until well combined.\n\n## Refrigeration\n- Transfer the mixture into a jar or airtight container.\n- Refrigerate overnight, or for at least 4 hours.\n\n## Serving\n- In the morning, stir the oats and add your choice of toppings.\n- Serve chilled and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('512','Smoked Mackerel & Spinach Toast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of whole-grain bread\n- 200g smoked mackerel fillets\n- 100g fresh spinach leaves\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 ripe avocado\n- 1 lemon\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Chili flakes (optional)\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh dill (optional)\n- Lemon wedges','## Preparation\n- Remove the skin from the smoked mackerel and flake it into bite-sized pieces.\n- Wash and dry the spinach leaves.\n- Cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a bowl. Mash it with a fork until smooth. Add a squeeze of lemon juice, salt, and pepper to taste.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the spinach and sauté until wilted. Add a pinch of salt and set aside.\n- Toast the whole-grain bread slices until golden brown.\n- Spread a generous layer of mashed avocado on each slice of toast.\n- Top the avocado with sautéed spinach, followed by flaked smoked mackerel.\n- Drizzle a little olive oil and a squeeze of lemon juice over each toast.\n\n## Serving\n- Sprinkle with chili flakes if desired.\n- Garnish with fresh dill and serve with lemon wedges on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('513','Baked Eggs with Chickpeas and Lamb','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\n- 200g ground lamb\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1 can (400g) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 can (400g) crushed tomatoes\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste\n- 4 large eggs\n- Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the onion and garlic, sautéing until soft and fragrant, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add the ground lamb, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until browned, about 5-6 minutes.\n- Stir in cumin, smoked paprika, and cinnamon, cooking for another minute.\n- Add the chickpeas, crushed tomatoes, salt, and pepper. Simmer for 10-12 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld and the sauce to thicken slightly.\n- Make four wells in the mixture and crack an egg into each well.\n- Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake until the eggs are set to your liking, about 10-12 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly. Garnish with fresh parsley.\n- Serve warm with crusty bread or a side salad if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('514','Power Green Breakfast Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup spinach leaves\n- 1/2 cup kale leaves\n- 1/2 avocado\n- 1 banana\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup almond milk\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 1 tablespoon almond butter\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1 teaspoon honey or maple syrup for sweetness (optional)\n- 1/2 teaspoon spirulina or matcha powder for extra nutrients (optional)\n\n## Toppings\n- Sliced almonds\n- Pumpkin seeds','## Preparation Steps\n- Wash and dry the spinach and kale leaves.\n- Peel the banana and avocado.\n- Add the spinach, kale, avocado, banana, Greek yogurt, almond milk, chia seeds, and almond butter into a blender.\n- Blend until smooth and creamy. Add more almond milk if needed to reach desired consistency.\n- Taste and add honey or maple syrup if additional sweetness is desired.\n- If using, add spirulina or matcha powder and blend briefly to incorporate.\n\n## Serving\n- Pour the smoothie into glasses.\n- Top with sliced almonds and pumpkin seeds as desired.\n- Serve immediately for best freshness and taste.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('515','Seitan Breakfast Stir Fry','## Main Ingredients\n- 200g seitan, sliced into strips\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 green bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 100g baby spinach\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Nutritional yeast','## Preparation\n- Slice the seitan into thin strips.\n- Chop the onion, slice the bell peppers, and mince the garlic.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the onions and garlic, sauté until translucent.\n- Add the bell peppers and cook until they begin to soften, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Add the seitan strips, soy sauce, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Stir well and cook for another 5-7 minutes.\n- Add the baby spinach and cook until wilted, about 2 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley and a sprinkle of nutritional yeast if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('516','Tofu & Avocado Protein Toast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices of whole grain bread\n- 200g firm tofu\n- 1 ripe avocado\n\n## Seasonings and Garnish\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon soy sauce\n- 2 tablespoons nutritional yeast\n- Fresh cilantro or parsley (optional)\n\n## Additional Toppings\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved\n- Red pepper flakes\n- Sesame seeds','## Preparing the Tofu\n- Press the tofu to remove excess moisture by wrapping it in a clean towel and placing a heavy object on top for about 15 minutes.\n- After pressing, cut the tofu into small cubes.\n- In a bowl, mix the olive oil, soy sauce, smoked paprika, and nutritional yeast. Add the tofu cubes and gently toss to coat them evenly.\n- Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and sauté the tofu for about 8-10 minutes until golden and slightly crispy.\n\n## Preparing the Avocado\n- While the tofu is cooking, cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a bowl.\n- Add lemon juice, salt, and pepper to the avocado. Mash with a fork until smooth but slightly chunky.\n\n## Assembling the Toasts\n- Toast the slices of whole grain bread until golden brown.\n- Spread the mashed avocado evenly over each slice of toast.\n- Top each toast with the sautéed tofu cubes.\n- Add optional toppings such as cherry tomatoes, red pepper flakes, sesame seeds, and fresh cilantro or parsley if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('517','Chicken & Avocado Egg Bake','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium avocados\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 cup cooked chicken breast, shredded\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, diced\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (cheddar or mozzarella)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes for heat\n- 1 tablespoon sour cream or Greek yogurt for topping\n- Lime wedges for serving','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Slice the avocados in half and remove the pits. Scoop out a bit of the flesh from the center to make more room for the eggs.\n- Place the avocado halves in a baking dish, ensuring they are stable. You can trim a small piece off the bottom to flatten them if needed.\n\n## Assembling\n- Fill the hollow of each avocado half with shredded chicken. \n- Crack an egg into each avocado half, placing it on top of the chicken. Some egg white might overflow depending on the size of the avocados. It''s okay!\n- Sprinkle diced cherry tomatoes and shredded cheese over each egg.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and optional red pepper flakes.\n\n## Baking\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the eggs are cooked to your liking.\n- Remove from oven and let it slightly cool.\n\n## Serving\n- Garnish with fresh chopped cilantro.\n- Serve with a dollop of sour cream or Greek yogurt on top if desired.\n- Add lime wedges on the side to squeeze over for extra flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('518','High-Protein Chocolate Mug Muffin','## Dry Ingredients\n- 3 tablespoons almond flour\n- 1 tablespoon cocoa powder\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder (whey or plant-based)\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 tablespoons milk of choice (dairy or non-dairy)\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup or honey\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1 tablespoon dark chocolate chips\n- 1 tablespoon chopped nuts','## Prepare the Batter\n- In a microwave-safe mug, mix together all the dry ingredients: almond flour, cocoa powder, protein powder, baking powder, and salt.\n- In a small bowl, whisk the egg, milk, maple syrup, and vanilla extract until well combined.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the mug with the dry ingredients and stir until the mixture is smooth and well combined.\n- Fold in any optional add-ins like chocolate chips or nuts, if using.\n\n## Cooking Instructions\n- Place the mug in the microwave and cook on high for 1 to 1.5 minutes, or until the muffin has risen and is set in the center. The cooking time may vary depending on the microwave.\n- Let the muffin cool for a minute before enjoying.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('519','Egg White & Quinoa Wrap','## For the Wrap\n- 1 cup cooked quinoa\n- 4 large egg whites\n- 1 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1/4 cup bell peppers, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, diced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 4 whole wheat tortillas\n\n## For the Sauce (optional)\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon hot sauce\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Quinoa\n- Cook quinoa according to package instructions. You''ll need about 1 cup of cooked quinoa for this recipe.\n\n## Cook the Egg Whites\n- In a non-stick skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the diced bell peppers and red onion, sauté for 2-3 minutes until softened.\n- Add the chopped spinach and cook for another minute until wilted.\n- Pour in the egg whites and scramble with the vegetables.\n- Add salt and pepper to taste, and cook until the egg whites are set.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Lay a whole wheat tortilla on a flat surface.\n- Spread about 1 tablespoon of the prepared sauce in the center of the tortilla (if using).\n- Spoon 1/4 cup of cooked quinoa onto each tortilla.\n- Add a portion of the scrambled egg white mixture on top of the quinoa.\n- Fold in the sides of the tortilla, then roll it up tightly.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve the wraps warm. Optionally, slice in half before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('520','Ricotta & Turkey Breakfast Rollups','## Main Ingredients\n- 8 large whole-grain tortillas\n- 1 cup low-fat ricotta cheese\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1/2 cup chopped spinach\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped fresh basil\n- Sliced cherry tomatoes\n- Hot sauce','## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large skillet, cook the ground turkey over medium heat until fully cooked, about 6-8 minutes. Drain any excess fat.\n- Season the cooked turkey with salt and pepper.\n- Stir in the chopped spinach and cook for another 2-3 minutes until wilted.\n- Remove from heat and let it cool slightly.\n- In a mixing bowl, combine the ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, and cooked turkey mixture.\n\n## Assemble the Rollups\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lay a tortilla on a flat surface and spread about 2 tablespoons of the ricotta-turkey mixture evenly over it.\n- Roll the tortilla tightly, then place seam side down on a baking sheet.\n- Repeat with remaining tortillas and filling.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes or until heated through.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove from oven and let cool slightly.\n- Slice each rollup in half and serve warm.\n- Optionally, garnish with fresh basil, sliced cherry tomatoes, and hot sauce.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('521','High-Protein Mocha Smoothie','## Smoothie Base\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon instant coffee or espresso powder\n- 1 tablespoon unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 banana, frozen\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon almond butter\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Ice cubes (optional, for thickness)\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Cacao nibs\n- Sliced almonds\n- Chia seeds','## Blend Ingredients\n- Add almond milk, protein powder, instant coffee, cocoa powder, frozen banana, Greek yogurt, almond butter, and vanilla extract into a high-speed blender.\n\n## Adjust Consistency\n- Blend on high until smooth and creamy.\n- Add ice cubes if desired for a thicker consistency and blend again.\n\n## Serve\n- Pour the smoothie into a glass.\n- Top with optional toppings like cacao nibs, sliced almonds, or chia seeds for added texture and nutrition.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('522','Kale, Egg & Cannellini Bean Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups kale, chopped\n- 1 cup canned cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 tablespoon feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n- Red pepper flakes, for garnish','## Preparation\n- Wash and chop the kale, removing any tough stems.\n- Drain and rinse the cannellini beans.\n- Mince the garlic.\n\n## Cooking\n- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the minced garlic and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n- Add the kale to the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 3-4 minutes until wilted.\n- Stir in the cannellini beans and cook for another 2-3 minutes until heated through.\n- Push the kale and beans to one side of the skillet.\n- Crack the eggs into the skillet on the empty side and cook to your desired level of doneness, about 3-4 minutes for sunny side up.\n- Remove from heat.\n\n## Serving\n- Divide the kale and bean mixture between two bowls.\n- Top each bowl with a cooked egg.\n- Add optional toppings like cherry tomatoes, feta cheese, a squeeze of lemon juice, and red pepper flakes if desired.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('523','Spinach, Tuna & Egg Toast','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 slices whole grain bread\n- 1 can tuna in water, drained\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 cup fresh spinach, chopped\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n\n## Seasoning & Sauce\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 tablespoon mayonnaise (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard','## Prepare the Tuna Mixture\n- In a bowl, combine drained tuna, mayonnaise (if using), lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.\n- Mix well until all ingredients are combined.\n\n## Cook the Spinach\n- Heat a pan over medium heat and add olive oil.\n- Add chopped spinach and sauté until wilted, about 2 minutes.\n- Season the spinach with a pinch of salt and pepper.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- In the same pan, fry eggs sunny-side up (or to your preference).\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Toast the Bread\n- While the eggs are cooking, toast the whole grain bread slices until golden brown.\n\n## Assemble the Toasts\n- Spread a layer of the tuna mixture on each toast.\n- Top each with sautéed spinach and avocado slices.\n- Place a fried egg on top of each toast.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('524','Baked Chicken & Veggie Omelette Cups','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup egg whites\n- 1 cup cooked chicken breast, diced\n- 1/2 cup bell peppers, diced (any color)\n- 1/2 cup spinach, chopped\n- 1/4 cup onions, finely chopped\n- 1/4 cup low-fat cheese, shredded\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped fresh parsley\n- Hot sauce','## Preparation\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lightly grease a muffin tin with cooking spray or olive oil.\n\n## Mixing\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs and egg whites until well combined.\n- Add in the diced chicken, bell peppers, spinach, onions, and cheese.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Mix everything until thoroughly combined.\n\n## Baking\n- Pour the egg mixture evenly into the prepared muffin tin, filling each cup about 3/4 full.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes, or until the omelette cups are set and lightly golden on top.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove the omelette cups from the oven and let them cool slightly before removing from the tin.\n- Garnish with chopped fresh parsley or a dash of hot sauce, if desired.\n- Serve warm or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('525','Seared Tempeh Breakfast Sandwich','## Tempeh Marinade\n- 1 block tempeh, sliced into 1/4 inch thick strips\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup\n- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder\n\n## Sandwich Assembly\n- 4 whole grain English muffins, split and toasted\n- 4 large eggs (or egg substitute)\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 medium tomato, sliced\n- 4 leaves of lettuce or spinach\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Condiments\n- Sriracha or hot sauce\n- Vegan mayo or regular mayo\n- Dijon mustard','## Prepare the Tempeh\n- In a shallow dish, combine soy sauce, maple syrup, apple cider vinegar, smoked paprika, garlic powder, and onion powder.\n- Add the sliced tempeh to the marinade, ensuring each piece is well coated. Marinate for at least 20 minutes.\n\n## Cook the Tempeh\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and add a little olive oil.\n- Place the marinated tempeh strips in the skillet and sear each side for about 3-4 minutes, until golden brown. Remove and set aside.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- In the same pan, add a bit more olive oil if needed.\n- Crack the eggs into the skillet and season with salt and pepper. Cook until the whites are set but the yolks are still runny, or to your desired level of doneness.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwiches\n- Spread optional condiments on the toasted English muffin halves.\n- Layer the bottom half with seared tempeh, avocado slices, a few tomato slices, a cooked egg, and finally a leaf of lettuce or spinach.\n- Top with the other half of the English muffin.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('526','Sweet Potato & Black Bean Protein Bowl','## For the Bowl\n- 2 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and cubed\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup quinoa, rinsed\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 avocado, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped\n\n## For the Dressing\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Sweet Potatoes\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Toss sweet potato cubes with 1 tablespoon olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n- Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 25-30 minutes until tender.\n\n## Cook the Quinoa\n- In a medium saucepan, bring 2 cups of water to a boil.\n- Add quinoa, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until water is absorbed.\n- Remove from heat and let sit, covered, for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lime juice, minced garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, roasted sweet potatoes, black beans, halved cherry tomatoes, and chopped cilantro.\n- Drizzle with dressing and toss to combine.\n- Top with sliced avocado before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('527','Greek Yogurt & Almond Butter Parfait','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 cups Greek yogurt (plain, non-fat or low-fat)\n- 1/2 cup almond butter\n- 1 cup granola (preferably low-sugar)\n- 1/2 cup sliced almonds\n- 1 cup mixed berries (e.g., blueberries, strawberries, raspberries)\n\n## Optional Sweetener\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup (optional)\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh mint leaves','## Preparation Steps\n- In a small bowl, mix the almond butter with one tablespoon of honey or maple syrup to make it easier to drizzle if desired.\n- In four glasses or bowls, add a generous spoonful of Greek yogurt to form the first layer.\n- Drizzle a layer of almond butter over the yogurt. Use the back of a spoon to spread it gently if needed.\n- Add a layer of granola on top, followed by a sprinkle of sliced almonds.\n- Add a layer of mixed berries over the almonds.\n- Repeat the layers until glasses or bowls are full, ending with a topping of berries and a sprinkle of almonds for garnish.\n- Optionally, drizzle a little more honey or maple syrup over the top and garnish with fresh mint leaves.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('528','Eggplant & Egg Breakfast Stack','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 medium eggplant, sliced into 1/2-inch rounds\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 cup baby spinach leaves\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n\n## Seasoning\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh basil leaves (optional)','## Prepare the Eggplant\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Arrange the eggplant slices on a baking sheet.\n- Brush both sides with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, oregano, and garlic powder.\n- Roast in the oven for 20 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden and tender.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- While the eggplant is roasting, heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat.\n- Add a touch of oil and fry the eggs until the whites are set and the yolks are cooked to your preference.\n\n## Assemble the Stack\n- Place roasted eggplant slices on plates.\n- Top with baby spinach, cherry tomatoes, and a fried egg.\n- Sprinkle with crumbled feta cheese.\n\n## Serve and Garnish\n- Garnish with fresh basil leaves if desired.\n- Season with additional salt and pepper to taste before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('529','Broccoli & Cheese High-Protein Muffins','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 3 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup milk (dairy or plant-based)\n\n## Add-ins\n- 1 cup chopped broccoli florets\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped green onions\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Extra shredded cheddar cheese for topping\n- Chopped parsley','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line or grease a muffin tin.\n- In a large bowl, mix together the oat flour, almond flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and black pepper.\n\n## Mix Wet Ingredients\n- In another bowl, whisk together the eggs, Greek yogurt, and milk until smooth.\n- Pour the wet mixture into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.\n\n## Add Mix-ins\n- Fold in the chopped broccoli, shredded cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese, and green onions until evenly distributed.\n\n## Bake\n- Divide the batter evenly among the muffin cups.\n- Top each muffin with additional cheddar cheese if desired.\n- Bake for 18-22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n- Allow the muffins to cool in the pan for about 5 minutes before transferring them to a cooling rack.\n\n## Serve\n- Garnish with chopped parsley before serving if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('530','Ground Turkey & Sweet Potato Hash','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 2 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and diced\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 small onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups baby spinach\n- Optional: 2-3 eggs\n\n## Garnish\n- Fresh parsley, chopped\n- Avocado slices\n- Hot sauce (optional)','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add the chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.\n- Stir in minced garlic and cook for another 30 seconds.\n\n## Cooking the Turkey\n- Add ground turkey to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spatula.\n- Cook until browned and cooked through, about 6-7 minutes.\n- Season with salt, pepper, cumin, and smoked paprika.\n\n## Cooking the Sweet Potatoes\n- While the turkey cooks, in a separate pan, heat a small amount of olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the diced sweet potatoes and bell pepper.\n- Cover the pan and let cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until sweet potatoes are tender.\n\n## Combine and Finish\n- Combine the cooked sweet potatoes and bell pepper mixture with the ground turkey in the skillet.\n- Stir in the baby spinach and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Check seasoning and adjust with salt and pepper if needed.\n\n## Optional Eggs\n- If using, push the hash to the sides of the skillet to create space for eggs.\n- Crack eggs directly into the pan, cover, and cook until whites are set, about 3 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Sprinkle with fresh parsley and top with avocado slices.\n- Serve hot with optional hot sauce on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('531','Chickpea & Ground Beef Breakfast Skillet','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 pound lean ground beef\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1 cup diced tomatoes (canned or fresh)\n- 1 cup baby spinach, packed\n- 4 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## Garnish\n- 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley\n- 1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese (optional)','## Preparation\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n- Add ground beef, cumin, smoked paprika, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Cook until beef is browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Stir in chickpeas and tomatoes. Cook for an additional 3-4 minutes to heat through.\n- Add spinach and cook until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Make four small wells in the mixture and crack an egg into each well.\n- Cover the skillet and cook until the egg whites are set but yolks are still runny, about 3-5 minutes.\n\n## Serving\n- Remove from heat and garnish with parsley and feta cheese, if using.\n- Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('532','Spiced Turkey & Veggie Wrap','## Spiced Turkey\n- 1 lb ground turkey\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Veggie Filling\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup shredded carrots\n- 1/2 cup thinly sliced bell peppers\n- 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro\n\n## Assembly\n- 4 whole wheat wraps\n- 1/2 cup hummus','## Prepare the Spiced Turkey\n- Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Add ground turkey and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.\n- Stir in smoked paprika, ground cumin, onion powder, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\n- Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until well blended and spices are fragrant.\n- Remove from heat and set aside.\n\n## Prepare the Veggie Filling\n- In a bowl, mix shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded carrots, sliced bell peppers, and chopped cilantro.\n\n## Assemble the Wraps\n- Spread 2 tablespoons of hummus on each whole wheat wrap.\n- Divide the spiced turkey mixture evenly among the wraps.\n- Top with the veggie filling mixture.\n- Roll each wrap tightly, tucking in the sides as you go.\n- Slice in half and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('533','Zucchini & Ricotta Mini Frittatas','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 medium zucchini, grated\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 6 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, grated\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Grease a muffin tin with olive oil or line with silicone muffin cups.\n\n## Cooking\n- In a large bowl, whisk the eggs thoroughly.\n- Add the ricotta cheese and mix until combined.\n- Stir in the grated zucchini, Parmesan cheese, and chopped basil.\n- Season the mixture with salt and pepper to taste.\n- Pour the egg mixture evenly into the prepared muffin tin, filling each cup about 3/4 full.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the frittatas are set and lightly golden on top.\n\n## Serving\n- Allow the frittatas to cool slightly before removing them from the muffin tin.\n- Serve warm or at room temperature.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('534','Egg & Salmon Grain Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa (or any preferred grain: brown rice, farro)\n- 2 eggs\n- 4 oz smoked salmon or cooked salmon fillet\n- 1 cup baby spinach\n- 1/2 avocado, sliced\n- 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n## For the Dressing\n- 2 tablespoons Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon dijon mustard\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 1 tablespoon capers\n- 1 tablespoon chopped fresh dill','## Prepare the Grain\n- Rinse and cook quinoa according to package instructions. Allow it to cool slightly.\n\n## Cook the Eggs\n- Boil eggs for 6-8 minutes for a soft yolk or 10 minutes for a hard yolk. Cool under cold water, peel, and set aside.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- In a large bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, baby spinach, and cherry tomatoes.\n- Place sliced avocado on one side and add the smoked or cooked salmon.\n- Cut the boiled eggs in half and arrange them in the bowl.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.\n- Drizzle the dressing over the assembled bowl.\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Garnish with capers and dill if using. Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('535','High Protein Chocolate Peanut Butter Smoothie','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons natural peanut butter\n- 1 banana, frozen\n- 1 tablespoon unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n\n## Optional for Serving\n- Ice cubes (if needed for thickness)\n- 1 teaspoon honey or maple syrup (for added sweetness)\n- 1 tablespoon cacao nibs or dark chocolate shavings','## Preparation\n- Add the almond milk, chocolate protein powder, peanut butter, frozen banana, cocoa powder, and chia seeds into a blender.\n\n## Blending\n- Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy. Add ice cubes if a thicker consistency is desired.\n- Taste and adjust sweetness with honey or maple syrup, if needed.\n\n## Serving\n- Pour into a glass and top with cacao nibs or dark chocolate shavings.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('536','Chocolate Protein Mousse','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh berries (e.g., strawberries, raspberries)\n- Dark chocolate shavings\n- Chopped nuts (e.g., almonds, hazelnuts)','## Prepare the Mousse\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine Greek yogurt, chocolate protein powder, unsweetened cocoa powder, honey (or maple syrup), vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt.\n- Using a whisk or an electric mixer, blend all ingredients until smooth and creamy. Make sure there are no lumps of protein powder or cocoa.\n\n## Chill the Mousse\n- Transfer the mousse mixture into serving cups or bowls.\n- Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to allow it to set and develop flavors.\n\n## Serve and Garnish\n- Before serving, top with fresh berries, dark chocolate shavings, or chopped nuts if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('537','Protein Tiramisu Cups','## Base Layer\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1/4 cup melted coconut oil\n- 3 tbsp maple syrup or honey\n- 1/2 tsp vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Cream Layer\n- 1 1/2 cups Greek yogurt (plain or vanilla)\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 2 tbsp maple syrup or honey\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\n## Coffee Soak\n- 1/2 cup strong brewed coffee (cooled)\n- 1 tbsp coffee liqueur (optional)\n\n## Topping\n- Unsweetened cocoa powder, for dusting\n- Dark chocolate shavings, for garnish (optional)','## Prepare Base Layer\n- In a bowl, combine almond flour, vanilla protein powder, unsweetened cocoa powder, and a pinch of salt.\n- Add melted coconut oil, maple syrup, and vanilla extract. Mix until a slightly sticky dough forms.\n- Divide the mixture evenly among serving cups and press firmly into the bottom.\n\n## Prepare Cream Layer\n- In a large bowl, combine Greek yogurt, vanilla protein powder, maple syrup, and vanilla extract.\n- Whisk until smooth and creamy. Adjust sweetness if needed.\n\n## Assemble Cups\n- Brush the base layer with the cooled brewed coffee and optional coffee liqueur.\n- Spoon the cream layer over the base until cups are nearly full.\n- Smooth the tops with the back of a spoon.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Refrigerate the cups for at least 2 hours or overnight to set.\n- Before serving, dust the tops with cocoa powder and garnish with chocolate shavings, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('538','Mocha Protein Ice Cream','## Base Ingredients\n- 2 cups Greek yogurt (plain, full-fat or low-fat)\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 2 scoops chocolate protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons instant coffee granules\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Dark chocolate shavings\n- Crushed nuts (e.g., almonds or pecans)\n- Fresh mint leaves','## Prepare the Mix\n- In a blender, combine Greek yogurt, almond milk, chocolate protein powder, cocoa powder, instant coffee granules, honey or maple syrup, vanilla extract, and salt.\n- Blend until smooth, making sure all ingredients are well combined.\n\n## Chill the Mixture\n- Pour the mixture into a container and cover it with a lid or plastic wrap.\n- Place in the freezer for about 1-2 hours until it begins to firm up but is still soft enough to stir.\n\n## Stir and Freeze Again\n- Remove the container from the freezer and stir the mixture to break up any ice crystals.\n- Return it to the freezer for another 2-3 hours or until it reaches the desired ice cream consistency.\n\n## Serve\n- Scoop the mocha protein ice cream into bowls.\n- Top with optional toppings such as dark chocolate shavings, crushed nuts, or fresh mint leaves for added texture and flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('539','Almond Butter Protein Balls','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup almond butter\n- 1/2 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup honey\n- 1/4 cup rolled oats\n- 1/4 cup chopped almonds\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips (optional)\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt','## Preparation Steps\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine almond butter, protein powder, honey, rolled oats, chopped almonds, chia seeds, vanilla extract, and salt.\n- Mix until all ingredients are well combined and form a firm dough. If the mixture is too dry, add a tablespoon of water or milk to reach the desired consistency.\n- Fold in the dark chocolate chips, if using.\n- Using your hands, roll the mixture into small balls, about 1 inch in diameter.\n- Place the protein balls on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to help them firm up before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('540','Protein Apple Crisp','## Filling\n- 4 medium apples, peeled, cored, and sliced\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup\n\n## Topping\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (e.g., almonds or walnuts)\n- 1/4 cup melted coconut oil or unsalted butter\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- Pinch of salt','## Prepare the Filling\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a mixing bowl, toss the sliced apples with lemon juice, cinnamon, and honey or maple syrup.\n- Spread the apple mixture evenly in a lightly greased baking dish.\n\n## Prepare the Topping\n- In a separate bowl, combine the oats, almond flour, protein powder, chopped nuts, cinnamon, and salt.\n- Stir in the melted coconut oil or butter and honey or maple syrup until the mixture is crumbly and well combined.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Spread the topping evenly over the apple mixture in the baking dish.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 30-35 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the apples are tender.\n- Allow to cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('541','Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Bars','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup natural peanut butter\n- 1/2 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 2 cups rolled oats\n- 1/4 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/4 cup milk or almond milk\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips\n\n## Optional Ingredients\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (almonds, walnuts)\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened shredded coconut\n- 1/4 cup chia seeds or flaxseeds','## Preparation\n- Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper.\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine peanut butter and honey or maple syrup. Microwave for about 30 seconds to 1 minute until warm and easily mixable. Stir until smooth.\n\n## Mixing\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine protein powder, rolled oats, and cocoa powder. Stir well.\n- Pour the warm peanut butter and honey mixture into the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly until well combined.\n- Add milk or almond milk slowly while stirring to reach a slightly sticky, dough-like consistency.\n- Fold in dark chocolate chips and any optional ingredients such as chopped nuts or seeds.\n\n## Shaping and Cooling\n- Press the mixture evenly into the prepared baking dish.\n- Refrigerate for at least 1-2 hours until firm enough to cut.\n- Once set, remove from the dish using the parchment paper and cut into bars.\n\n## Storage\n- Store the bars in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to one week, or freeze for longer storage.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('542','Strawberry Protein Shortcake','## Shortcake Base\n- 1 1/2 cups almond flour\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup coconut flour\n- 2 tablespoons baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/4 cup honey or agave syrup\n- 1/4 cup melted coconut oil\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 large eggs\n\n## Strawberry Topping\n- 2 cups fresh strawberries, hulled and sliced\n- 1 tablespoon honey or agave syrup\n\n## Whipped Topping\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt (or dairy-free alternative)\n- 1 tablespoon honey or agave syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare the Shortcake\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- In a large bowl, combine almond flour, protein powder, coconut flour, baking powder, and salt.\n- In another bowl, whisk almond milk, honey, melted coconut oil, vanilla extract, and eggs until smooth.\n- Gradually mix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients until a dough forms.\n- Scoop 1/4 cup portions of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, flattening them slightly.\n- Bake for 15-18 minutes, or until lightly golden and firm to the touch.\n- Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack.\n\n## Prepare the Strawberries\n- While the shortcakes are baking, combine sliced strawberries and honey in a medium bowl. Toss to coat. Set aside to macerate.\n\n## Prepare the Whipped Topping\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, honey, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Shortcake\n- Once the shortcakes have cooled, slice them in half horizontally.\n- Place the bottom half of a shortcake on a plate, top with a spoonful of the strawberry mixture, and a dollop of the yogurt topping.\n- Place the other half of the shortcake on top and add additional strawberries and yogurt if desired.\n- Repeat with remaining shortcakes. Serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('543','High-Protein Mocha Mug Cake','## Dry Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons protein powder (chocolate or mocha flavor)\n- 1 tablespoon cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons almond flour\n- 1 tablespoon instant coffee\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 tablespoons unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 tablespoon melted coconut oil\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup or honey\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Preparation\n- In a microwave-safe mug, mix all the dry ingredients (protein powder, cocoa powder, almond flour, instant coffee, baking powder, and salt).\n- In a separate bowl, whisk together the wet ingredients (egg, almond milk, melted coconut oil, maple syrup or honey, and vanilla extract).\n\n## Combining Ingredients\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the mug with the dry ingredients.\n- Stir until all the ingredients are well combined and smooth.\n- Make sure to scrape the bottom to mix all the dry ingredients.\n\n## Cooking\n- Microwave the mug on high for 1 to 2 minutes, or until the cake has risen and is firm to the touch.\n- Be careful not to overcook, as microwaves vary in power.\n\n## Serving\n- Let the mug cake cool for a minute before eating.\n- Optionally, top with a spoonful of Greek yogurt, a sprinkle of cocoa powder, or a few chocolate chips for extra flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('544','Vanilla Protein Pudding','## Pudding\n- 2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup chia seeds\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- Fresh berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries)\n- Sliced almonds\n- Coconut flakes','## Prepare the Pudding\n- In a medium-sized mixing bowl, whisk together the almond milk, vanilla protein powder, honey or maple syrup, and vanilla extract until well combined.\n- Stir in the chia seeds and mix thoroughly.\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight, to allow the pudding to thicken.\n\n## Serve\n- Stir the pudding before serving to ensure it''s well mixed.\n- Divide into serving bowls.\n- Top with fresh berries, sliced almonds, or coconut flakes if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('545','Chocolate Almond Chia Protein Pudding','## Main Ingredients\n- 1/4 cup chia seeds\n- 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 scoop chocolate protein powder (preferably plant-based)\n- 1 1/2 cups almond milk (unsweetened)\n- 2 tablespoons almond butter\n- 1-2 tablespoons maple syrup or honey (optional, to taste)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- Sliced almonds\n- Dark chocolate shavings\n- Fresh berries\n- Coconut flakes','## Mix Ingredients\n- In a medium bowl, whisk together the chia seeds, cocoa powder, and protein powder.\n\n## Combine Wet Ingredients\n- Add the almond milk, almond butter, maple syrup (or honey), vanilla extract, and salt to the bowl.\n- Whisk until the mixture is smooth and all ingredients are well incorporated.\n\n## Refrigerate\n- Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight, until the chia seeds have absorbed the liquid and the mixture has thickened to a pudding consistency.\n\n## Serve\n- Stir the pudding before serving.\n- Divide into serving bowls and top with optional toppings such as sliced almonds, dark chocolate shavings, fresh berries, or coconut flakes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('546','High-Protein Tofu Chocolate Mousse','## Main Ingredients\n- Silken tofu (400g, drained)\n- Dark chocolate (70% cocoa or higher, 150g)\n- Unsweetened cocoa powder (2 tablespoons)\n- Maple syrup or agave nectar (2 tablespoons)\n- Vanilla extract (1 teaspoon)\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh berries (e.g., raspberries, strawberries)\n- Chopped nuts (e.g., almonds, hazelnuts)\n- Shaved dark chocolate','## Prepare Chocolate\n- Break the dark chocolate into small pieces and melt using a double boiler or microwave until smooth.\n\n## Blend Mousse\n- In a blender or food processor, combine the silken tofu, melted chocolate, cocoa powder, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt.\n- Blend until the mixture is smooth and creamy.\n\n## Chill Mousse\n- Scoop the mousse into serving dishes.\n- Cover and refrigerate for at least 1-2 hours to set.\n\n## Serve\n- Before serving, top with optional toppings like fresh berries, chopped nuts, or shaved dark chocolate if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('547','Matcha Protein Ice Cream','## Base Ingredients\n- 2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons matcha powder\n\n## Sweetener and Flavor\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare the Mix\n- In a blender, combine the unsweetened almond milk, Greek yogurt, vanilla protein powder, matcha powder, honey (or maple syrup), and vanilla extract.\n- Blend until the mixture is smooth and all ingredients are well incorporated.\n\n## Freeze the Mixture\n- Pour the blended mixture into an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer''s instructions, usually about 20-25 minutes.\n- If you don’t have an ice cream maker, pour the mixture into a shallow container and place it in the freezer.\n- Stir the mixture every 30 minutes to break up ice crystals until it reaches your desired consistency, usually 3-4 hours.\n\n## Serve\n- Scoop the ice cream into bowls.\n- Optional: Top with a sprinkle of matcha powder or fresh fruit for garnish.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('548','Peanut Butter Protein Cookies','## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 cup natural creamy peanut butter\n- 1/2 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Optional Mix-ins\n- 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 1/4 cup chopped peanuts','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n\n## Mix Wet Ingredients\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the peanut butter, honey (or maple syrup), eggs, and vanilla extract. Whisk until smooth and well combined.\n\n## Combine Dry Ingredients\n- In another bowl, whisk together the protein powder, baking soda, and salt.\n\n## Mix Ingredients Together\n- Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. If using, fold in the chocolate chips and chopped peanuts.\n\n## Shape Cookies\n- Scoop tablespoon-sized amounts of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart. Flatten each cookie slightly with a fork, making a crisscross pattern.\n\n## Bake Cookies\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the edges are golden. Avoid overbaking to keep the cookies soft.\n\n## Cool and Serve\n- Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('549','Cinnamon Roll Protein Cake','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 tbsp almond milk\n- 1 large egg\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 2 tbsp maple syrup\n\n## Cinnamon Swirl\n- 2 tbsp maple syrup\n- 1 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder (optional)\n\n## Topping\n- 2 tbsp cream cheese, softened\n- 1 tbsp Greek yogurt\n- 1 tbsp maple syrup\n- 1/4 tsp vanilla extract','## Prepare the Batter\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and lightly grease a 6-inch round cake pan.\n- In a large bowl, mix together the oat flour, protein powder, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.\n- In another bowl, whisk the applesauce, Greek yogurt, almond milk, egg, vanilla extract, and maple syrup until smooth.\n- Gradually add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, mixing until well combined.\n\n## Make the Cinnamon Swirl\n- In a small bowl, mix the maple syrup and cinnamon (add cocoa powder if using) to create a swirl mixture.\n- Pour half of the batter into the prepared cake pan, then drop spoonfuls of the cinnamon swirl mixture over the batter.\n- Add the remaining batter and swirl the top gently with a knife.\n\n## Bake the Cake\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n- Allow the cake to cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n## Prepare the Topping\n- While the cake cools, mix the softened cream cheese, Greek yogurt, maple syrup, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Once the cake is cool, spread the cream cheese topping over the top before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('550','High-Protein Brownie Bites','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup almond butter\n- 1 large egg\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Optional Add-Ins\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (e.g., walnuts or almonds)','## Preparation Steps\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a mini muffin pan with paper liners or lightly grease it.\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the almond flour, chocolate protein powder, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt.\n\n## Mixing Wet Ingredients\n- In another bowl, mix the applesauce, honey or maple syrup, almond butter, egg, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.\n\n## Adding Optional Ingredients\n- Fold in dark chocolate chips and chopped nuts if using.\n\n## Baking\n- Spoon the batter evenly into the prepared mini muffin pan, filling each cup about three-quarters full.\n- Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out mostly clean.\n- Let the brownie bites cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('551','Vanilla Bean Protein Custard','## Custard Ingredients\n- 2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 vanilla bean, split and seeds scraped\n- 3 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 4 large egg yolks\n- 2 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- Pinch of salt','## Custard Preparation\n- In a medium saucepan, combine the almond milk, vanilla bean seeds, and pod. Heat over medium heat until it comes to a simmer, then remove from heat. Let it sit for 10 minutes to infuse the vanilla.\n- In a mixing bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, honey, vanilla protein powder, cornstarch, and salt until smooth.\n- Remove the vanilla pod from the almond milk. Slowly whisk the warm almond milk into the egg yolk mixture, a little at a time, to temper the eggs.\n- Return the mixture to the saucepan and cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon or spatula until the custard thickens, about 5–7 minutes. Do not let it boil.\n- Once thickened, pour the custard through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl to remove any lumps.\n- Cover the surface with plastic wrap to prevent a skin from forming and let it cool in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve chilled, in small bowls or cups. Garnish with fresh berries or a mint leaf if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('552','Protein-Fortified Bread Pudding','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 cups whole grain bread, cubed\n- 3 large eggs\n- 2 cups almond milk (or any milk of choice)\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 cup raisins (optional)\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (such as almonds or walnuts)\n\n## For Serving\n- Greek yogurt or cottage cheese\n- Fresh berries (optional)\n- Drizzle of honey (optional)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Grease an 8x8 inch baking dish with a little oil or butter.\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, almond milk, vanilla protein powder, honey or maple syrup, vanilla extract, and ground cinnamon until smooth.\n\n## Assembly\n- Place the bread cubes into the prepared baking dish.\n- Pour the egg mixture over the bread, pressing down gently to ensure the bread is soaked in the liquid.\n- Sprinkle the raisins and chopped nuts evenly over the top.\n\n## Baking\n- Let the mixture sit for about 10 minutes to absorb the liquid.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 30-35 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the center is set.\n\n## Serving\n- Allow to cool slightly before serving.\n- Top with a dollop of Greek yogurt or cottage cheese and fresh berries, if using.\n- Drizzle with honey if desired for extra sweetness.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('553','Protein Churro Bites','## Churro Bites\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Cinnamon Sugar Coating\n- 1/4 cup granulated sweetener (like erythritol or coconut sugar)\n- 1 tablespoon ground cinnamon','## Make the Dough\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- In a mixing bowl, combine oat flour, protein powder, baking powder, and salt.\n- In another bowl, mix almond milk, Greek yogurt, melted coconut oil, honey, and vanilla extract until well combined.\n- Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until a dough forms.\n\n## Shape and Bake\n- Scoop small portions of the dough (about a tablespoon each) and roll into bite-sized balls.\n- Place dough balls on the prepared baking sheet.\n- Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly golden and firm to the touch.\n\n## Coat the Churro Bites\n- While the bites are baking, mix the granulated sweetener and ground cinnamon in a shallow dish.\n- Once baked, lightly spray or brush the bites with a bit of water or coconut oil.\n- Roll the bites in the cinnamon-sugar mixture until fully coated.\n\n## Serve\n- Serve warm as a delightful protein-rich snack or dessert.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('554','Greek Yogurt Chocolate Bark','## Greek Yogurt Base\n- 2 cups Greek yogurt (preferably full-fat or 2% for creaminess)\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n\n## Toppings\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips or chopped dark chocolate\n- 2 tablespoons chopped nuts (almonds, walnuts, or pecans)\n- 2 tablespoons dried fruit (such as cranberries or raisins)\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 1 tablespoon shredded coconut (optional)','## Prepare the Greek Yogurt Base\n- In a mixing bowl, combine Greek yogurt and honey (or maple syrup). Stir until well mixed and smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Bark\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- Spread the Greek yogurt mixture evenly over the parchment paper to about 1/4 inch thick.\n- Sprinkle the dark chocolate chips evenly over the yogurt.\n- Distribute the chopped nuts, dried fruit, chia seeds, and shredded coconut (if using) over the top.\n\n## Freeze the Bark\n- Place the baking sheet in the freezer and freeze for at least 3 hours, or until the yogurt is firm.\n- Once frozen, remove from the freezer and break the bark into pieces.\n\n## Serve and Store\n- Serve immediately, or store in an airtight container in the freezer until ready to enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('555','Protein Carrot Cake','## Cake Ingredients\n- 3/4 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup coconut flour\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup grated carrots\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup maple syrup or honey\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/4 cup chopped walnuts (optional)\n\n## Frosting Ingredients\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup or honey\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare the Cake\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Grease an 8x8 inch baking pan.\n- In a large bowl, mix almond flour, coconut flour, protein powder, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.\n- In another bowl, combine grated carrots, applesauce, maple syrup, eggs, and vanilla extract.\n- Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until well combined.\n- Fold in the walnuts if using.\n- Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread evenly.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n\n## Prepare the Frosting\n- In a small bowl, mix Greek yogurt, maple syrup, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Once the cake is cool, spread the frosting evenly over the top.\n\n## Serve\n- Cut the cake into 9 squares.\n- Serve and enjoy.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('556','Chocolate Hazelnut Protein Tart','## Crust\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted\n- 2 tablespoons maple syrup\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Filling\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt (or dairy-free yogurt)\n- 1/2 cup chocolate hazelnut protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Topping\n- 1/4 cup chopped hazelnuts\n- 2 ounces dark chocolate, melted','## Crust\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a mixing bowl, combine almond flour, cocoa powder, melted coconut oil, maple syrup, and salt.\n- Press the mixture into the bottom of a tart pan to form an even layer.\n- Bake for 10-12 minutes until set. Let it cool completely.\n\n## Filling\n- In a blender or bowl, combine Greek yogurt, chocolate hazelnut protein powder, cocoa powder, honey, and vanilla extract.\n- Blend or mix until smooth and creamy.\n- Spread the filling evenly over the cooled crust.\n\n## Topping\n- Sprinkle chopped hazelnuts over the filling.\n- Drizzle melted dark chocolate on top.\n- Refrigerate the tart for at least 1 hour before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('557','Mango Coconut Protein Pudding','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 ripe mango, peeled and diced\n- 1 cup coconut milk (preferably light)\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons chia seeds\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh mango slices\n- Toasted coconut flakes\n- Chopped nuts (such as almonds or pistachios)','## Prepare the Pudding\n- In a blender, combine the diced mango, coconut milk, Greek yogurt, and vanilla protein powder.\n- Blend until smooth and creamy.\n- Stir in the chia seeds until well mixed.\n\n## Chill and Set\n- Pour the mixture into serving bowls or containers.\n- Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight to allow the chia seeds to expand and thicken the pudding.\n\n## Serve\n- Before serving, give the pudding a good stir.\n- Top with fresh mango slices, toasted coconut flakes, or chopped nuts, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('558','Chocolate Chickpea Blondies','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed\n- 1/2 cup almond butter\n- 1/3 cup maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup oats\n- 2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/8 teaspoon salt\n\n## Add-ins\n- 1/3 cup chocolate chips','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper or lightly grease it.\n\n## Blend Ingredients\n- In a food processor, combine chickpeas, almond butter, maple syrup, oats, vanilla extract, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n- Blend until the mixture is smooth and creamy.\n- Fold in the chocolate chips using a spatula.\n\n## Bake\n- Spread the mixture evenly in the prepared baking dish.\n- Sprinkle a few extra chocolate chips on top for added texture and flavor.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out mostly clean.\n\n## Cool and Serve\n- Allow the blondies to cool in the pan for at least 10 minutes.\n- Cut into squares and serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('559','Raspberry Protein Muffins','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 1/2 cups almond flour\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 1/2 tsp baking soda\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup almond milk\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\n## Add-ins\n- 1 cup fresh or frozen raspberries','## Prepare Dry Ingredients\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Line a muffin tin with paper liners or lightly coat with cooking spray.\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the almond flour, oat flour, protein powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n\n## Prepare Wet Ingredients\n- In a separate bowl, beat the eggs.\n- Add the applesauce, almond milk, honey, and vanilla extract to the eggs and mix well.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.\n- Gently fold in the raspberries.\n\n## Bake Muffins\n- Divide the batter evenly among the muffin cups.\n- Bake for 18-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean.\n- Allow the muffins to cool in the tin for a few minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('560','Chocolate Protein-Covered Strawberries','## Main Ingredients\n- 12 large fresh strawberries\n- 1 cup dark chocolate chips (at least 70% cacao)\n- 2 tablespoons chocolate or vanilla protein powder (whey or plant-based)\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil','## Preparation\n- Wash the strawberries thoroughly and pat them dry with a paper towel, leaving the stems on for easy dipping.\n\n## Chocolate Coating\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil.\n- Microwave in 30-second intervals, stirring after each until the chocolate is fully melted and smooth.\n- Add the protein powder to the melted chocolate and stir until fully combined and smooth.\n\n## Dipping Strawberries\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- Hold each strawberry by the stem and dip it into the chocolate-protein mixture, ensuring it''s thoroughly coated.\n- Shake off excess chocolate and place the strawberry on the parchment paper.\n- Repeat with all strawberries.\n\n## Chilling\n- Place the baking sheet in the refrigerator for about 15 minutes or until the chocolate is set.\n\n## Serving\n- Once set, remove the strawberries from the refrigerator and serve immediately.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('561','Protein Mocha Truffles','## Truffle Mixture\n- 1 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1/4 cup instant coffee granules\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup almond butter\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Coating\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon instant coffee granules','## Prepare the Truffle Mixture\n- In a large bowl, mix together the chocolate protein powder, unsweetened cocoa powder, instant coffee granules, and almond flour until well combined.\n- Add the almond milk, honey or maple syrup, almond butter, and vanilla extract to the dry ingredients. Mix until a thick dough forms. If the mixture is too dry, add a bit more almond milk, one tablespoon at a time.\n\n## Shape the Truffles\n- Using your hands, roll small portions of the mixture into bite-sized balls. This should make about 20 truffles.\n- Place the truffles on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n\n## Coat the Truffles\n- In a small bowl, combine the unsweetened cocoa powder and instant coffee granules for the coating.\n- Roll each truffle in the coating mixture until fully covered.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Place the coated truffles in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour to set.\n- Serve chilled. Store any leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('562','Spiced Protein Rice Pudding','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup cooked brown rice\n- 2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 scoop vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup raisins\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- 1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\n- 1/8 teaspoon ground cardamom\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Garnish\n- Sliced almonds\n- Fresh berries (e.g., blueberries, raspberries)','## Prepare the Base\n- In a medium-sized saucepan, combine the almond milk, honey, vanilla extract, cinnamon, nutmeg, cardamom, and salt over medium heat. Stir until well combined.\n\n## Cook the Pudding\n- Add the cooked brown rice and raisins to the saucepan.\n- Bring the mixture to a gentle simmer, stirring occasionally.\n- Let it simmer for about 15 minutes, or until the mixture thickens and becomes creamy.\n\n## Add Protein\n- Remove the saucepan from heat.\n- Stir in the vanilla protein powder until fully incorporated and smooth.\n\n## Serve\n- Divide the rice pudding into serving bowls.\n- Top with sliced almonds and fresh berries.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('563','Baked Protein Donuts','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 1/2 cup granulated erythritol or sweetener of choice\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 1/2 tsp baking soda\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 2 tbsp coconut oil, melted\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- 2 tbsp almond butter\n- 2 tbsp Greek yogurt\n- Berries for garnish','## Prepare the Batter\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a large bowl, whisk together the oat flour, protein powder, almond flour, erythritol, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n- In a separate bowl, mix together the eggs, applesauce, almond milk, melted coconut oil, and vanilla extract until well combined.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Do not overmix.\n\n## Bake the Donuts\n- Lightly grease a donut pan with cooking spray or coconut oil.\n- Fill each donut cavity about 3/4 full with batter.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into a donut comes out clean.\n- Allow the donuts to cool in the pan for a few minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n## Add Toppings\n- Once cooled, drizzle with almond butter or Greek yogurt for additional flavor.\n- Top with berries if desired for extra texture and taste.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('564','Chocolate-Covered Protein Figs','## Main Ingredients\n- 12 dried figs\n- 1 cup dark chocolate chips (70% cacao or higher)\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil\n\n## Protein Powder Coating\n- 2 tablespoons protein powder (vanilla or chocolate)\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Crushed nuts (e.g., almonds, pistachios)\n- Coconut flakes\n- Sea salt flakes','## Preparation\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set it aside.\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave in 20-second intervals, stirring each time, until smooth and fully melted.\n- Let the chocolate cool slightly before proceeding.\n\n## Assembling\n- Dip each fig into the melted chocolate, using a fork to fully coat the fig.\n- Let excess chocolate drip off before placing each chocolate-covered fig onto the prepared baking sheet.\n- Dust or roll each chocolate-covered fig in the protein powder to coat lightly.\n- Add optional toppings such as crushed nuts, coconut flakes, or a sprinkle of sea salt if desired.\n\n## Setting\n- Place the baking sheet in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes, allowing the chocolate to firm up.\n- Once set, store the chocolate-covered protein figs in an airtight container in the refrigerator until ready to serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('565','Lemon Ricotta Protein Bars','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 1 cup ricotta cheese\n- 1/3 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 large eggs\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare Ingredients\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper.\n- In a large bowl, combine oat flour, vanilla protein powder, almond flour, baking soda, and salt. Mix well.\n\n## Mix Wet Ingredients\n- In another bowl, whisk together ricotta cheese, honey or maple syrup, Greek yogurt, eggs, lemon juice, lemon zest, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n\n## Combine and Bake\n- Slowly add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, mixing gently until just combined.\n- Pour the batter into the prepared baking dish and smooth out the top with a spatula.\n- Bake for 20-25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n\n## Cool and Serve\n- Allow the bars to cool in the pan for about 10 minutes, then transfer them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n- Once cool, cut into bars and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('566','Coconut Almond Protein Cups','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 cup unsweetened shredded coconut\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup whey protein powder (vanilla flavor)\n- 1/4 cup almond butter\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil (melted)\n- 2 tablespoons maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Topping Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 2 teaspoons coconut oil\n\n## Optional Garnish\n- Chopped almonds\n- Extra shredded coconut','## Prepare the Base\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the shredded coconut, almond flour, and whey protein powder.\n- Add the almond butter, melted coconut oil, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and salt to the dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly until well combined.\n\n## Form the Cups\n- Line a muffin tin with paper or silicone liners.\n- Divide the mixture evenly into the muffin cups, pressing it down firmly to form a compact base.\n\n## Make the Topping\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine dark chocolate chips and coconut oil.\n- Microwave in 20-second intervals, stirring in between, until the chocolate is fully melted and smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Cups\n- Spoon the melted chocolate over the pressed mixture in the muffin cups, spreading it evenly.\n- Optional: Sprinkle chopped almonds or extra shredded coconut on top for garnish.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Place the muffin tin in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, or until the cups are set and firm.\n- Once set, remove from the tin and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('567','Cinnamon Protein Pancake Bites','## Dry Ingredients\n- 1 cup oat flour\n- 1 scoop (about 30g) vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon ground cinnamon\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- Cooking spray or a small amount of coconut oil for greasing\n- Optional toppings: Greek yogurt, fresh berries, or a drizzle of maple syrup','## Prepare the Batter\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients: oat flour, protein powder, cinnamon, baking powder, and salt. Mix well.\n- In another bowl, whisk together the wet ingredients: eggs, almond milk, vanilla extract, and honey until smooth.\n- Gradually add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, stirring until just combined. Avoid over-mixing to keep the batter light.\n\n## Cook the Pancake Bites\n- Preheat a mini muffin pan in the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Lightly grease the mini muffin pan with cooking spray or coconut oil.\n- Fill each muffin cup about 3/4 full with the batter.\n- Bake in the oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the pancake bites are golden brown and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.\n\n## Serve\n- Allow the pancake bites to cool slightly in the pan, then transfer to a wire rack.\n- Serve warm with your choice of toppings, such as Greek yogurt, fresh berries, or a drizzle of maple syrup.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('568','Protein Pecan Pie Cups','## Crust\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1 egg white\n\n## Filling\n- 1 cup pecans, chopped\n- 1/2 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup coconut sugar\n- 1/4 cup maple syrup\n- 2 tablespoons almond milk\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 2 eggs','## Prepare the Crust\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a mixing bowl, combine almond flour, melted coconut oil, honey, and egg white.\n- Mix until a dough forms.\n- Divide the dough into a greased muffin tin, pressing it down to form cups.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, combine chopped pecans and protein powder.\n- In another bowl, whisk together coconut sugar, maple syrup, almond milk, vanilla extract, salt, and eggs until smooth.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until well combined.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Fill each crust cup with the pecan mixture evenly.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes or until the filling is set and the crust is golden brown.\n- Allow to cool slightly before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('569','High-Protein Matcha Cheesecake Bars','## Crust\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n\n## Filling\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 8 oz cream cheese, softened\n- 1/2 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 2 tablespoons matcha powder\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract','## Prepare the Crust\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a bowl, mix almond flour, melted coconut oil, and honey.\n- Press the mixture into the bottom of an 8x8 inch baking pan lined with parchment paper.\n- Bake for 10 minutes, then set aside to cool.\n\n## Prepare the Filling\n- In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.\n- Add Greek yogurt, protein powder, matcha powder, honey, and vanilla extract. Mix until well combined.\n- Beat in the eggs one at a time until the mixture is smooth and creamy.\n\n## Assemble and Bake\n- Pour the filling over the baked crust and spread evenly.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the center is set and edges are slightly golden.\n- Remove from oven and let it cool to room temperature.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Refrigerate the bars for at least 2 hours, or until firm.\n- Cut into 12 bars and serve chilled.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('570','Apple Cinnamon Protein Bread','## Dry Ingredients\n- 2 cups oat flour\n- 1 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1 tablespoon cinnamon\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Add-ins\n- 1 cup grated apple (about 1 large apple)\n- 1/4 cup chopped walnuts (optional)','## Preparation\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan or line it with parchment paper.\n\n## Mix Dry Ingredients\n- In a large bowl, combine the oat flour, protein powder, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.\n\n## Mix Wet Ingredients\n- In another bowl, whisk together the eggs, applesauce, Greek yogurt, honey (or maple syrup), and vanilla extract.\n\n## Combine Ingredients\n- Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.\n- Fold in the grated apple and walnuts (if using).\n\n## Bake\n- Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan.\n- Bake for 40-45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n\n## Cool and Serve\n- Allow the bread to cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n- Slice and serve or store in an airtight container.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('571','Peanut Butter Protein Mug Cake','## Dry Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour or almond flour\n- 1 tablespoon powdered peanut butter\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Wet Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons natural peanut butter\n- 1 tablespoon maple syrup or honey\n- 3 tablespoons milk (dairy or nut milk)\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Sliced bananas\n- Chopped nuts\n- Dark chocolate chips','## Preparation\n- In a microwave-safe mug, whisk together all the dry ingredients: protein powder, flour, powdered peanut butter, baking powder, and salt.\n- In a separate bowl, mix the wet ingredients: peanut butter, maple syrup, milk, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the mug with the dry ingredients. Stir until you have a smooth batter.\n- Ensure there are no lumps and the ingredients are well combined.\n\n## Cooking\n- Place the mug in the microwave and cook on high for about 60-90 seconds. Watch closely to avoid overcooking.\n- Check if the cake is done by inserting a toothpick into the center. It should come out mostly clean.\n- If necessary, microwave for an additional 10 seconds each time until cooked.\n\n## Serving\n- Allow the mug cake to cool slightly before serving.\n- Top with optional toppings like sliced bananas, chopped nuts, or dark chocolate chips if desired.\n- Enjoy as a quick, high-protein snack or dessert.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('572','Chocolate Avocado Protein Mousse','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 ripe avocados\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1/4 cup protein powder (chocolate or vanilla)\n- 1/4 cup almond milk\n- 1/4 cup maple syrup or honey\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Fresh berries\n- Cacao nibs\n- Chopped nuts\n- Mint leaves','## Prepare the Ingredients\n- Cut the avocados in half, remove the pits, and scoop the flesh into a blender or food processor.\n\n## Blend the Mousse\n- Add the cocoa powder, protein powder, almond milk, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and salt to the blender.\n- Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides as needed.\n\n## Chill the Mousse\n- Transfer the mousse into serving bowls or ramekins.\n- Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld and the texture to firm up.\n\n## Serve\n- Top with optional toppings like fresh berries, cacao nibs, chopped nuts, or mint leaves before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('573','High-Protein Mocha Granita','## Base Ingredients\n- 2 cups strong brewed coffee (cooled)\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/4 cup protein powder (chocolate or vanilla)\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon\n\n## Topping Options (optional)\n- Whipped cream or coconut cream\n- Dark chocolate shavings\n- Cacao nibs\n- Chopped nuts (e.g., almonds, hazelnuts)','## Prepare the Mixture\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the cooled brewed coffee, almond milk, protein powder, cocoa powder, honey or maple syrup, vanilla extract, and cinnamon.\n- Whisk the ingredients together until the protein powder and cocoa powder are fully dissolved and the mixture is smooth.\n\n## Freeze and Scrape\n- Pour the mixture into a shallow baking dish.\n- Place the dish in the freezer for 1 hour.\n- After 1 hour, use a fork to scrape and stir the icy edges into the center. Return the dish to the freezer.\n- Repeat scraping and stirring every 30 minutes for 2 to 3 hours, until the granita has a fluffy, crystalline texture.\n\n## Serve\n- Spoon the granita into serving glasses or bowls.\n- Optionally, top with whipped cream, chocolate shavings, cacao nibs, or chopped nuts.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('574','Pistachio Protein Balls','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup unsalted pistachio nuts, shelled\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup almond butter\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Coating (Optional)\n- 1/4 cup finely chopped pistachios\n- 1 tablespoon unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon unsweetened shredded coconut','## Prepare Pistachio Mixture\n- In a food processor, pulse the pistachios until they are finely ground.\n- Add almond flour, protein powder, honey, almond butter, vanilla extract, and salt to the food processor.\n- Blend until the mixture is well combined and forms a sticky dough.\n\n## Form Balls\n- Using a small scoop or your hands, form the mixture into 1-inch balls.\n- If desired, roll each ball in finely chopped pistachios, cocoa powder, or shredded coconut for coating.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Place the protein balls on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to set.\n- Enjoy immediately or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to a week.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('575','Chocolate Protein Rice Cakes','## Rice Cakes\n- 2 cups puffed rice cereal\n- 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1/4 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/4 cup honey or agave syrup\n- 1/2 cup nut butter (like almond or peanut butter)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 tablespoons chia seeds\n\n## Chocolate Coating (Optional)\n- 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil','## Prepare the Rice Cakes\n- In a large bowl, mix together the puffed rice cereal, chocolate protein powder, cocoa powder, and chia seeds.\n- In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the honey, nut butter, and vanilla extract. Stir constantly until the mixture is smooth and well combined.\n- Pour the wet mixture over the dry ingredients in the bowl and stir until everything is uniformly coated.\n\n## Form the Rice Cakes\n- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n- Scoop portions of the mixture onto the parchment paper, shaping them into disc-like cakes using your hands or a mold for uniform size.\n- Let them set at room temperature or place in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes until firm.\n\n## Optional Chocolate Coating\n- Melt the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil in a microwave-safe bowl or over a double boiler until smooth.\n- Dip each rice cake into the melted chocolate or drizzle the chocolate over the top.\n- Allow the chocolate to set by refrigerating the cakes for an additional 15 minutes.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('576','Protein Caramel Banana Pops','## Main Ingredients\n- 3 ripe bananas\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt (plain, unsweetened)\n- 2 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup almond butter\n\n## Toppings\n- 1/4 cup crushed nuts (almonds, pistachios, or peanuts)\n- 2 tablespoons sugar-free caramel sauce\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips','## Preparation Steps\n- Peel the bananas and cut each into halves.\n- Insert a popsicle stick into each banana half.\n- In a bowl, mix Greek yogurt and protein powder until smooth.\n\n## Assembly\n- Dip each banana half into the yogurt mixture, ensuring even coverage.\n- Place the dipped bananas on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\n- Drizzle almond butter over each banana pop.\n\n## Toppings and Finishing\n- Sprinkle crushed nuts over the top of the banana pops.\n- Drizzle with sugar-free caramel sauce.\n- Melt dark chocolate chips in the microwave in 20-second intervals, stirring in between, until smooth.\n- Drizzle melted chocolate over the banana pops.\n\n## Freezing\n- Freeze the banana pops for at least 2 hours or until solid.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('577','Tofu Peanut Butter Cups','## Tofu Filling\n- 1/2 cup silken tofu, drained\n- 1/2 cup natural peanut butter\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Chocolate Coating\n- 1 cup dark chocolate chips or chopped dark chocolate\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil\n\n## Optional Garnishes\n- Chopped peanuts\n- Sea salt flakes','## Prepare the Tofu Filling\n- In a blender or food processor, combine the silken tofu, peanut butter, honey or maple syrup, and vanilla extract.\n- Blend until smooth and creamy. Taste and adjust sweetness if needed.\n- Set aside the tofu filling.\n\n## Prepare the Chocolate Coating\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the dark chocolate and coconut oil.\n- Microwave in 30-second intervals, stirring each time, until fully melted and smooth.\n\n## Assemble the Peanut Butter Cups\n- Line a muffin tin with paper liners.\n- Spoon a tablespoon of melted chocolate into the bottom of each liner and spread it evenly.\n- Place the muffin tin in the freezer for about 5 minutes to set the chocolate.\n- Divide the tofu filling evenly among the cups, gently spreading it over the set chocolate layer.\n- Cover the tofu filling with another tablespoon of melted chocolate, ensuring it''s completely covered.\n- Sprinkle with optional garnishes like chopped peanuts or sea salt flakes.\n\n## Set and Serve\n- Place the muffin tin back in the freezer for at least 30 minutes to set completely.\n- Once set, remove the cups from the liners.\n- Store the peanut butter cups in the refrigerator until ready to serve.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('578','Coconut Cashew Protein Squares','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 cup raw cashews\n- 1 cup unsweetened shredded coconut\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup coconut oil, melted\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- 2 tbsp dark chocolate chips (melted)\n- 1 tbsp chopped cashews\n- 1 tbsp shredded coconut','## Instructions\n- Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper.\n- In a food processor, combine the cashews and shredded coconut. Pulse until finely ground.\n- Add the protein powder, honey or maple syrup, melted coconut oil, vanilla extract, and salt to the food processor. Blend until the mixture is well combined and forms a sticky dough.\n- Press the mixture evenly into the prepared baking dish.\n- If using, drizzle melted dark chocolate over the top, and sprinkle with chopped cashews and additional shredded coconut.\n- Refrigerate the mixture for at least 2 hours, or until firm.\n- Once set, remove from the dish and cut into squares.\n- Store in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to one week.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('579','Chocolate Protein Lava Cake','## Main Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1/4 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 2 tablespoons coconut sugar\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 2 tablespoons coconut oil (melted)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Filling\n- 2 squares dark chocolate (70% cocoa or higher)','## Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Grease four ramekins with a light coat of coconut oil or nonstick spray.\n\n## Mixing the Batter\n- In a bowl, mix together the chocolate protein powder, almond flour, unsweetened cocoa powder, coconut sugar, baking powder, and salt.\n- In another bowl, whisk the eggs, almond milk, melted coconut oil, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n- Combine the wet ingredients with the dry ingredients and mix until well combined.\n\n## Assembling the Cakes\n- Spoon a small amount of the batter into each ramekin to cover the bottom.\n- Place a square of dark chocolate in the center of each ramekin.\n- Cover the chocolate square with the remaining batter, dividing it evenly among the ramekins.\n\n## Baking\n- Place the ramekins on a baking sheet and bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes. The edges should be firm, but the center should remain soft.\n\n## Serving\n- Allow the cakes to cool for a minute or two after removing them from the oven.\n- Carefully invert each ramekin onto a plate to release the cake.\n- Serve immediately for a gooey, molten center.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('580','Sweet Potato Protein Brownies','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 medium sweet potatoes\n- 1/2 cup almond butter\n- 1/3 cup maple syrup\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 1/2 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips (optional)\n\n## Toppings (Optional)\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts\n- 1/4 cup shredded coconut','## Sweet Potato Preparation\n- Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Peel the sweet potatoes and cut them into cubes.\n- Boil or steam until they are tender, about 10-15 minutes.\n- Mash the sweet potatoes until smooth and let them cool.\n\n## Brownie Batter\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine the mashed sweet potatoes, almond butter, maple syrup, and vanilla extract. Mix well until smooth.\n- Add the cocoa powder, chocolate protein powder, baking powder, and salt to the wet mixture.\n- Stir until all ingredients are fully incorporated into a batter.\n- Fold in the dark chocolate chips, if using.\n\n## Baking\n- Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper.\n- Pour the brownie batter into the prepared dish, smoothing the top with a spatula.\n- Optional: Sprinkle chopped nuts or shredded coconut on top.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out mostly clean.\n- Remove from oven and let cool in the pan for 10 minutes.\n- Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before slicing into 12 squares.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('581','Almond Joy Protein Bars','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 cup almond butter\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/2 cup almond flour\n- 1/4 cup coconut flour\n- 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened shredded coconut\n- 1/2 cup chopped almonds\n\n## Coating Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 1 tablespoon coconut oil','## Prepare the Base\n- In a large mixing bowl, combine almond butter, honey or maple syrup, cocoa powder, and vanilla extract. Mix until smooth.\n- Add almond flour, coconut flour, chocolate protein powder, shredded coconut, and chopped almonds. Stir until fully combined and a thick dough forms.\n\n## Shape the Bars\n- Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper.\n- Press the mixture evenly into the prepared dish, smoothing the top with a spatula.\n\n## Coat with Chocolate\n- In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil.\n- Microwave in 30-second intervals, stirring between each, until fully melted.\n- Pour the melted chocolate over the pressed mixture in the baking dish, spreading evenly to coat the top.\n\n## Set and Serve\n- Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until the bars are firm.\n- Once set, lift the bars out of the dish using the parchment paper. Cut into 12 equal pieces.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('582','Baked Protein Pears with Greek Yogurt','## Main Ingredients\n- 4 ripe pears\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\n\n## Protein Boost\n- 1/4 cup protein powder (vanilla or unflavored)\n\n## Serving\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (e.g., almonds or walnuts)\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds (optional)\n- Fresh mint leaves (for garnish)','## Prepare Pears\n- Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Wash and halve the pears, scooping out the seeds with a spoon.\n- Place pears cut-side up in a baking dish.\n\n## Mix Toppings\n- In a small bowl, combine honey, cinnamon, lemon juice, and protein powder to form a smooth paste.\n- Drizzle the mixture over the pear halves evenly.\n\n## Bake Pears\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until pears are tender and slightly caramelized.\n\n## Serve\n- Remove pears from oven and let cool slightly.\n- Serve each pear half with a dollop of Greek yogurt.\n- Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chia seeds.\n- Garnish with fresh mint leaves if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('583','Chocolate Protein Waffles','## Waffle Batter\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 2 scoops chocolate protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n- 1 tablespoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup Greek yogurt\n\n## Optional Toppings\n- Sliced bananas\n- Fresh berries\n- Greek yogurt\n- Nut butter\n- Chopped nuts\n- Dark chocolate chips','## Prepare the Batter\n- Blend rolled oats in a blender until they become a fine flour texture.\n- In a large mixing bowl, whisk together oat flour, chocolate protein powder, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt.\n- In a separate bowl, whisk eggs, almond milk, vanilla extract, honey, and Greek yogurt until well combined.\n- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.\n\n## Cook the Waffles\n- Preheat your waffle iron according to the manufacturer''s instructions.\n- Lightly grease the waffle iron with cooking spray or a small amount of oil.\n- Pour the batter onto the center of the preheated waffle iron and close the lid.\n- Cook for 4-5 minutes or until the waffles are cooked through and slightly crispy.\n- Carefully remove the waffles and repeat with remaining batter.\n\n## Serve and Enjoy\n- Serve the waffles warm.\n- Top with your choice of sliced bananas, fresh berries, Greek yogurt, nut butter, chopped nuts, or a sprinkle of dark chocolate chips.\n- Enjoy your healthy, high-protein chocolate waffles!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('584','Mango Lassi Protein Popsicles','## Popsicle Mixture\n- 2 ripe mangoes, peeled and diced\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt (unsweetened)\n- 1/2 cup vanilla protein powder\n- 1 cup milk (dairy or almond)\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- 1/4 teaspoon cardamom powder','## Preparation\n- In a blender, combine the diced mangoes, Greek yogurt, protein powder, milk, honey or maple syrup, and cardamom powder.\n- Blend until smooth and creamy.\n- Taste the mixture and adjust sweetness if necessary by adding more honey or sweetener of choice.\n\n## Freezing\n- Pour the mixture evenly into popsicle molds, leaving a small gap at the top for expansion.\n- Insert sticks into each mold.\n- Place in the freezer and freeze for at least 4 hours or until solid.\n\n## Serving\n- To remove the popsicles from the molds, run warm water over the outsides of the molds for a few seconds, then gently pull out each popsicle.\n- Enjoy immediately!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('585','Espresso Protein Cheesecake Cups','## Crust\n- 1 cup almond flour\n- 2 tablespoons melted coconut oil\n- 2 tablespoons honey or maple syrup\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Cheesecake Filling\n- 1 cup low-fat cream cheese\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 2 scoops vanilla protein powder\n- 2 tablespoons espresso or strong brewed coffee\n- 1 tablespoon honey or another sweetener\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Topping\n- Cocoa powder, for dusting\n- Espresso beans, optional, for garnish','## Prepare the Crust\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- In a bowl, mix the almond flour, melted coconut oil, honey or maple syrup, and vanilla extract until combined.\n- Press about 1 tablespoon of the mixture into the bottom of each muffin cup, lined with muffin liners.\n- Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until lightly golden.\n- Remove from the oven and let cool.\n\n## Make the Cheesecake Filling\n- In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth.\n- Add Greek yogurt, vanilla protein powder, espresso, honey, and vanilla extract.\n- Mix until the filling is creamy and smooth.\n\n## Assemble and Chill\n- Spoon the cheesecake filling over the cooled crusts in the muffin cups, filling almost to the top.\n- Smooth the tops with a spoon or spatula.\n\n## Chill and Serve\n- Refrigerate the cheesecake cups for at least 2 hours, or until set.\n- Before serving, dust with cocoa powder and optionally garnish with espresso beans.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('586','Black Bean Brownie Protein Muffins','## Muffin Base\n- 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed\n- 3 large eggs\n- 1/2 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/2 cup protein powder (chocolate or unflavored)\n- 1/4 cup honey or maple syrup\n- 1/4 cup almond butter or peanut butter\n- 2 tablespoons melted coconut oil\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Optional Add-ins\n- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips\n- 1/4 cup chopped nuts (e.g., walnuts, almonds)','## Prepare the Batter\n- Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).\n- Line a muffin tin with paper liners or grease lightly with cooking spray.\n- In a blender or food processor, combine black beans, eggs, cocoa powder, protein powder, honey, almond butter, coconut oil, vanilla extract, baking powder, and salt.\n- Blend until completely smooth and well combined.\n- Fold in dark chocolate chips and chopped nuts if using.\n\n## Bake the Muffins\n- Pour the batter into the prepared muffin tin, filling each cup about 3/4 full.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 18-22 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out mostly clean.\n- Allow muffins to cool in the tin for about 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('587','High-Protein Tri-Tip Steak Bowl with Turmeric Rice and Vegetables','## Main Ingredients\n- 1.5 lbs Tri-Tip Steak\n- 1 bunch Kale, chopped\n- 1 cup Basmati Rice\n- 1 tbsp Butter or Coconut Oil (for turmeric rice)\n- 1/4 Onion, finely diced (for turmeric rice)\n- 1 clove Garlic, minced (for turmeric rice)\n- 1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder (for turmeric rice)\n- 1 1/2 cups Beef Broth (for turmeric rice)\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n- 1 lb Brussel Sprouts, trimmed and halved\n- 2 medium Sweet Potatoes, peeled and cubed\n- 2 tbsp Olive Oil (for roasting sweet potatoes and brussel sprouts)\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n- Microgreens for garnish\n\n## Mushroom and Peppercorn Madeira Sauce\n- 1 tbsp Olive Oil\n- 1/2 cup Mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 tbsp Fresh Ground Peppercorns\n- 1/2 cup Madeira Wine\n- 1/2 cup Beef Broth\n- 1 tbsp Butter\n- 1 tsp Fresh Thyme, chopped\n- 1 tbsp Heavy Cream (optional for richness)','## Turmeric Rice\n- Melt the butter or coconut oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and minced garlic, sautéing for 2-3 minutes until aromatic.\n- Mix in the turmeric powder, cooking for another minute to release the spice''s flavors.\n- Add the basmati rice, beef broth, salt, and pepper, bringing the mixture to a boil.\n- Lower the heat, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes until the rice is cooked and all the liquid is absorbed.\n- Fluff the rice with a fork and set it aside.\n\n## Roasted Brussels Sprouts\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Combine the halved brussels sprouts with olive oil, salt, and pepper, ensuring an even coating.\n- Spread them on a baking sheet and roast for 20-25 minutes, stirring halfway through, until they''re crispy on the edges and tender inside.\n\n## Baked Sweet Potato Bites\n- Ensure the oven is set to 400°F (200°C) if not already.\n- Mix the cubed sweet potatoes with olive oil, salt, and pepper, laying them out on a baking sheet.\n- Roast for 20-25 minutes, turning halfway, until they are golden and soft.\n\n## Tri-Tip Steak\n- Heat a grill or cast-iron skillet to medium-high.\n- Season the tri-tip steak thoroughly with salt and pepper.\n- Cook the steak for 4-6 minutes on each side, depending on thickness, until achieving your preferred doneness (medium-rare is an internal temperature of about 130-135°F or 55-57°C).\n- Allow the steak to rest for 5-10 minutes, then slice it against the grain.\n\n## Mushroom and Peppercorn Madeira Sauce\n- Warm olive oil in a pan over medium heat, adding the sliced mushrooms.\n- Sauté for 5-7 minutes until they start to release moisture and turn golden brown.\n- Add the ground peppercorns, cooking for an additional minute.\n- Pour in the Madeira wine and let it reduce to half, about 5 minutes.\n- Stir in the beef broth, fresh thyme, and butter, allowing the sauce to thicken. For a richer flavor, incorporate the heavy cream.\n- Simmer for a few more minutes until reaching your desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper as needed.\n\n## Assembling the Bowl\n- In each serving bowl, layer the turmeric rice, chopped kale, roasted brussels sprouts, and baked sweet potato bites.\n- Slice the tri-tip steak and arrange on top of each bowl.\n- Drizzle the mushroom and peppercorn Madeira sauce over the steak.\n- Garnish with microgreens for a fresh finish.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('588','High-Protein Veggie Bowl with Peanut Dressing','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 bunch Kale, chopped\n- 1 cup Almond Wild Rice (or regular wild rice with a handful of almonds, chopped)\n- 1 block Firm Tofu, pressed and cubed\n- 1/2 Red Cabbage, shredded\n- 1 head Broccoli, cut into florets\n\n## Walnut Pesto Mushrooms\n- 1/4 cup Walnuts, chopped\n- 1/2 cup Mushrooms, sliced\n- 1/4 cup Fresh Basil\n- 1/4 cup Olive Oil\n- 1 tbsp Lemon Juice\n- 1 Garlic Clove\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n\n## Mango Salsa\n- 1/2 Mango, diced\n- 1/4 Red Onion, finely diced\n- 1 tbsp Cilantro, chopped\n- 1 tbsp Lime Juice\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Peanut Dressing\n- 3 tbsp Peanut Butter\n- 1 tbsp Soy Sauce or Tamari (for gluten-free)\n- 1 tbsp Lime Juice\n- 1 tbsp Honey or Maple Syrup\n- 1 tsp Sesame Oil\n- 1-2 tbsp Water (to thin, as needed)\n- 1/2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1/4 tsp Ginger Powder\n\n## Toppings\n- Microgreens','## Almond Wild Rice\n- Rinse the wild rice under cold water until the water runs clear.\n- Combine the rice, 2 cups of water, and a pinch of salt in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.\n- Lower the heat to a simmer, cover, and cook for 40-45 minutes until tender with all water absorbed.\n- Once cooked, mix in chopped almonds and set aside.\n\n## Roasted Broccoli\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Coat the broccoli florets in olive oil, salt, and pepper, then arrange on a baking sheet.\n- Roast for 20-25 minutes, turning halfway, until the broccoli reaches a crisp-tender state.\n\n## Walnut Pesto Mushrooms\n- Warm a skillet with olive oil over medium heat.\n- Add the sliced mushrooms and sauté for 5-7 minutes until browned and tender.\n- Incorporate chopped walnuts, cooking for an additional 2-3 minutes, seasoning with salt and pepper.\n- Blend basil, olive oil, lemon juice, and garlic in a processor for a smooth pesto, and mix it with the mushrooms.\n\n## Tofu\n- Press the tofu to drain excess moisture and cut it into cubes.\n- Heat a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat, adding a small amount of oil.\n- Sauté the tofu cubes, stirring occasionally, for 8-10 minutes until uniformly golden and crispy.\n- Season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Mango Salsa\n- Combine diced mango, red onion, cilantro, and lime juice in a bowl.\n- Season with salt and mix thoroughly.\n\n## Peanut Dressing\n- Whisk peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, honey, sesame oil, garlic powder, and ginger powder together in a small bowl.\n- Gradually incorporate water until you reach the desired consistency.\n\n## Assembling the Bowl\n- Layer almond wild rice, kale, roasted broccoli, walnut pesto mushrooms, and tofu in each serving bowl.\n- Add a substantial scoop of mango salsa and drizzle with peanut dressing.\n- Garnish with microgreens for added freshness and flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('589','Protein-Packed Quinoa and Salmon Bowl','## Quinoa\n- 1 cup Quinoa\n- 2 cups Water\n- Pinch of Salt\n\n## Roasted Cauliflower\n- 1 head Cauliflower, cut into florets\n- 1 tbsp Olive Oil\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n\n## Walnut Pesto Mushrooms\n- 1/2 cup Mushrooms, sliced\n- 1/4 cup Walnuts, chopped\n- 1/4 cup Fresh Basil\n- 1 Garlic Clove\n- 1/4 cup Olive Oil\n- 1 tbsp Lemon Juice\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n\n## Wild Salmon\n- 2 Wild Salmon Fillets\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n\n## Mango Salsa\n- 1/2 Mango, diced\n- 1/4 Red Onion, finely diced\n- 1 tbsp Cilantro, chopped\n- 1 tbsp Lime Juice\n- Salt, to taste\n\n## Cashew Cilantro Lime Dressing\n- 1/4 cup Cashews, soaked for at least 2 hours\n- 1/4 cup Fresh Cilantro\n- 2 tbsp Lime Juice\n- 1 tbsp Olive Oil\n- 1-2 tbsp Water\n- 1/4 tsp Salt\n- 1/4 tsp Garlic Powder\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 1 bunch Kale, chopped\n- 1/2 Red Cabbage, shredded\n- Microgreens','## Quinoa\n- Thoroughly rinse the quinoa under cold water until clear.\n- Add quinoa to a medium saucepan with 2 cups of water and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to low heat, cover, and let simmer for 12-15 minutes until the water is absorbed.\n- Fluff with a fork and set aside.\n\n## Roasted Cauliflower\n- Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Toss cauliflower florets in olive oil, salt, and pepper, and spread evenly on a baking sheet.\n- Roast for 20-25 minutes until golden and tender, flipping halfway through.\n\n## Walnut Pesto Mushrooms\n- In a skillet over medium heat, warm olive oil.\n- Add mushrooms, sautéing for 5-7 minutes until browned.\n- Stir in walnuts and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes. Add basil, lemon juice, and a minced garlic clove, then season with salt and pepper.\n\n## Wild Salmon\n- Preheat a grill or skillet to medium-high heat.\n- Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper.\n- Cook for 4-5 minutes per side until the fish flakes with a fork.\n- Let rest briefly before breaking into bite-sized pieces.\n\n## Mango Salsa\n- Combine diced mango, red onion, cilantro, and lime juice in a bowl.\n- Season with salt and mix well.\n\n## Cashew Cilantro Lime Dressing\n- In a blender or food processor, combine soaked cashews, cilantro, lime juice, olive oil, water, salt, and garlic powder.\n- Blend until smooth, adjusting with more water if necessary.\n\n## Assembling the Bowl\n- In each bowl, layer quinoa, kale, shredded red cabbage, roasted cauliflower, mushrooms, and salmon.\n- Top generously with mango salsa and drizzle with cashew cilantro lime dressing.\n- Garnish with microgreens and extra cilantro if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('590','High Protein Thai Chicken Rice Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 1 bunch Kale, chopped\n- 1 cup Basmati Rice\n- 1 tbsp Butter or Coconut Oil\n- 1/4 Onion, finely diced\n- 1 clove Garlic, minced\n- 1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder\n- 1 1/2 cups Chicken Broth\n- Salt & Pepper, to taste\n- 2 Chicken Breasts\n- 1 Red Bell Pepper, sliced\n- 1 Yellow Bell Pepper, sliced\n- 1 head Broccoli, cut into florets\n- 1 medium Red Onion, sliced\n- 2 tbsp Olive Oil\n- 1/4 cup Cashews, chopped\n- Microgreens for topping\n- 1 Carrot, shaved or julienned\n- Fresh Cilantro, for garnish\n\n## Thai Sauce\n- 1/4 cup Coconut Milk\n- 2 tbsp Soy Sauce or Tamari (for gluten-free)\n- 1 tbsp Lime Juice\n- 1 tbsp Honey or Maple Syrup\n- 1 tsp Fish Sauce (optional)\n- 1 tsp Sesame Oil\n- 1/2 tsp Garlic Powder\n- 1/2 tsp Ginger Powder\n- 1 tbsp Water (optional for thinning)','## Turmeric Rice\n- Melt the butter or coconut oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.\n- Sauté the diced onion and minced garlic for 2-3 minutes until they become fragrant.\n- Mix in the turmeric powder and cook for an additional minute to enhance the flavors.\n- Pour in the basmati rice, chicken broth, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil.\n- Lower the heat, cover, and let it simmer for 15-20 minutes until the rice is fully cooked and the liquid is absorbed.\n- Fluff with a fork and keep aside.\n\n## Roasted Veggies\n- Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Combine the broccoli florets, sliced bell peppers, and onion on a baking sheet with olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n- Roast for 20-25 minutes, turning halfway, until they are tender and slightly caramelized.\n\n## Chicken\n- Meanwhile, season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and your preferred additional spices.\n- In a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat, cook the chicken breasts for 5-6 minutes on each side until they reach an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).\n- Remove from heat and allow to rest before slicing.\n\n## Thai Sauce\n- Whisk together the coconut milk, soy sauce, lime juice, honey, fish sauce (if using), sesame oil, garlic powder, ginger powder, and water in a small bowl.\n- Taste and adjust seasoning as needed, adding more lime juice or honey for balance.\n\n## Assembling the Bowl\n- Layer the turmeric rice, kale, roasted broccoli, roasted onions, roasted bell peppers, and sliced chicken in a bowl.\n- Drizzle with the Thai sauce.\n- Finish by topping with chopped cashews, shaved carrot, fresh cilantro, and microgreens.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('591','High-Protein Chicken and Turmeric Rice Bowl','## Chicken\n- 2 chicken breasts\n- Paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, and pepper\n\n## Turmeric Rice\n- 1 tbsp butter or coconut oil\n- 1/4 onion, finely diced\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1/2 tsp turmeric powder\n- 1 cup basmati rice\n- 1 1/2 cups chicken broth\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## Dressing\n- 1/4 cup cashews (soaked for at least 2 hours)\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro\n- 1 jalapeño, seeded and chopped\n- 2 tbsp lime juice\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1-2 tbsp water (for desired consistency)\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n- 1/4 tsp garlic powder\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 1 can black beans, drained and rinsed\n- Microgreens\n- 1 bell pepper, sliced\n- Seasoned kale\n- Hummus','## Chicken\n- Heat your oven to 375°F (190°C).\n- Rub the paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, and pepper onto the chicken breasts evenly.\n- Position the chicken breasts on a baking sheet covered with parchment paper or foil.\n- Bake for 25-30 minutes until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\n- Once done, take the chicken out of the oven and let it rest for a few minutes before cutting into slices.\n\n## Turmeric Rice\n- Melt the butter or heat the coconut oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.\n- Add the diced onion and minced garlic, sautéing until they''re fragrant, about 2-3 minutes.\n- Stir in the turmeric powder and heat for an additional minute to release the spice''s aroma.\n- Introduce the basmati rice, chicken broth, and season with salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a boil.\n- Lower the heat to a simmer, cover the saucepan, and cook for 15-20 minutes until the rice is tender and the broth is absorbed.\n- Use a fork to fluff the rice once it''s cooked and put aside.\n\n## Dressing\n- Add the soaked cashews, fresh cilantro, jalapeño, lime juice, olive oil, water, salt, and garlic powder to a blender or food processor.\n- Blend until the mixture is smooth, adding more water if needed to reach the preferred consistency.\n- Sample the dressing and adjust the seasoning if necessary.\n\n## Assembling the Bowl\n- In a serving bowl, arrange layers of turmeric rice, black beans, sliced bell pepper, microgreens, seasoned kale, and the sliced chicken.\n- Pour the cilantro-jalapeño cashew lime dressing over the top.\n- Serve alongside a scoop of hummus for extra flavor.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('592','Quinoa, Kale, and Falafel Protein Bowl','## For the Quinoa\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n\n## For the Kale\n- 1 cup kale (chopped)\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## For the Falafel\n- 6-8 baked falafel balls\n\n## For the Toppings\n- 2 tablespoons hummus or baba ghanoush\n- 1/2 cup microgreens\n- 1/2 cup red cabbage (shredded)','## Cook the Quinoa\n- Rinse the quinoa under cold water.\n- Combine 1 cup of quinoa with 2 cups of water in a pot and bring to a boil.\n- Reduce the heat, cover, and let it simmer for about 15 minutes until the water is absorbed and the quinoa is fluffy.\n\n## Prepare the Kale\n- In a pan over medium heat, warm the olive oil.\n- Add chopped kale, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Sauté for 3-5 minutes until the kale becomes tender yet retains its color.\n\n## Bake the Falafel\n- Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n- Arrange the falafel on a baking sheet and bake as per package directions or until they''re golden brown and crispy, about 20 minutes.\n\n## Assemble the Bowl\n- Start by placing a serving of quinoa at the base of your bowl.\n- Layer on the sautéed kale beside the quinoa.\n- Arrange the baked falafel either on top or next to the kale.\n- Add a hearty spoonful of hummus or baba ghanoush.\n- Top with shredded red cabbage and a handful of microgreens.\n\n## Serve & Enjoy\n- Drizzle with extra olive oil or your preferred dressing, if you like.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy your nutritious, protein-rich bowl!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('593','High-Protein Chicken and Almond Wild Rice Bowl','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 chicken breasts\n- 1 bunch kale\n- 1 cup almond wild rice\n- 1 cup broccoli florets\n- 1 cup cauliflower florets\n- 2 sweet potatoes\n- Handful of microgreens\n\n## Dressing\n- 1 cup fresh cilantro (packed)\n- 1/2 cup raw cashews (soaked 15–30 minutes in hot water if needed)\n- 1 jalapeño (deseeded for less heat)\n- 1 garlic clove\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil (optional)','## Prepare the ingredients\n- First, cook the chicken until it''s thoroughly done, then transfer it to a plate and set aside.\n- Rinse and coarsely chop the kale, discarding any hardy stems.\n- Prepare the almond wild rice by following the package directions.\n- For the vegetables, preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Roast the broccoli and cauliflower on a baking sheet until they’re tender, which takes about 20-25 minutes.\n- Peel and cube the sweet potatoes, then roast them on another baking sheet at the same temperature until they are soft and slightly caramelized, roughly 25-30 minutes.\n\n## Make the dressing\n- Combine the cilantro, soaked cashews, jalapeño, garlic, lime juice, salt, and cumin in a blender or food processor.\n- Add 1/2 cup of water and blend until the mixture is smooth. If you prefer a thinner dressing, add more water as needed.\n- For a richer taste, add the olive oil and blend until everything is well combined.\n\n## Assemble the bowl\n- Begin with a layer of almond wild rice as the base in a bowl.\n- Arrange pieces of chicken, chopped kale, roasted broccoli, cauliflower, and sweet potato cubes over the rice.\n- Pour some of the cilantro cashew dressing over the top.\n\n## Finish with microgreens\n- Sprinkle a handful of fresh microgreens over the dish to add a fresh flavor and nutritional boost.\n\n## Serve\n- Enjoy the bowl immediately while fresh.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('594','Grilled Pita Pockets with Cashew and Avocado','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 whole wheat pita breads (halved or whole, depending on size)\n- 1/2 cup cashew cream (recipe below)\n- 2 tbsp spicy cashew dressing (recipe below)\n- 1 ripe avocado, sliced\n- 1 cup fresh spinach\n- 1/2 cup grilled onions (sautéed or grilled)\n- 1/2 cup housemade pesto mushrooms (recipe below)\n- 2 tbsp lime tomato vinaigrette (recipe below)\n- Fresh basil leaves for garnish\n- Avocado jalapeño dressing (for drizzling)\n\n## Cashew Cream\n- 1/2 cup cashews (soaked in water for at least 2 hours)\n- 1/4 cup water\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n\n## Spicy Cashew Dressing\n- 1/4 cup cashew cream\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- 1 tsp chili flakes (or more for extra heat)\n- 1 garlic clove\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Housemade Pesto Mushrooms\n- 1 cup sliced mushrooms\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 tbsp pesto\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Lime Tomato Vinaigrette\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes (packed in oil, drained)\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- 1 small garlic clove\n- Salt & pepper to taste','## Prepare the Pita\n- If using whole pita rounds, slice them in half to create pockets. Alternatively, leave them whole and slice open after grilling.\n\n## Assemble the Pita\n- Inside the pita, spread a layer of cashew cream. Add grilled onions, spinach, pesto mushrooms, and avocado slices.\n\n## Add Dressing\n- Drizzle with lime tomato vinaigrette and a bit of spicy cashew dressing.\n\n## Grill the Pita\n- Preheat a skillet or panini press to medium heat. Lightly brush the pita with olive oil and grill until crispy and golden brown.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Drizzle with avocado jalapeño dressing and garnish with fresh basil leaves.\n\n## Enjoy\n- Serve immediately and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('595','Grilled Tri-Tip Pita Melt','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 pita breads (halved or whole, depending on size)\n- 1 lb grilled tri-tip, sliced thinly\n- 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella\n- 2 tbsp tomato vinaigrette\n- Cashew cilantro jalapeño dressing (for drizzling)\n- Olive oil for grilling\n- Fresh herbs for garnish (optional: cilantro or parsley)\n\n## Tomato Vinaigrette\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes (packed in oil, drained)\n- 1 tbsp red wine vinegar\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 small garlic clove\n- 1/2 tsp honey\n- Salt & pepper to taste','## Prepare the Pita\n- Slice the pita in half to create pockets, or keep it whole and cut open after grilling.\n\n## Assemble the Melt\n- Spread tomato vinaigrette inside the pita.\n- Add the grilled tri-tip slices and mozzarella cheese.\n- Drizzle with cashew cilantro jalapeño dressing.\n\n## Grill the Melt\n- Warm a skillet or panini press over medium heat.\n- Brush pita with olive oil and grill each side until crispy, golden, and the cheese is melted.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Add extra dressing and garnish with fresh cilantro or parsley for added flavor.\n- Serve immediately and enjoy!\n\n## Tomato Vinaigrette Preparation\n- Blend sun-dried tomatoes, red wine vinegar, olive oil, garlic, honey, salt, and pepper until smooth and emulsified.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('596','Chicken Pesto Pita Melts','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 pita breads (halved or whole, depending on size)\n- 1 cup cooked chicken, shredded or sliced\n- 1/2 cup shredded or sliced fresh mozzarella\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 2 tbsp homemade pesto\n- 2 tbsp tomato vinaigrette\n- Cashew cilantro jalapeño dressing (for drizzling)\n\n## Homemade Pesto\n- 1 cup fresh basil leaves\n- 1/4 cup toasted cashews or pine nuts\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan\n- 1 garlic clove\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Tomato Vinaigrette\n- 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes (packed in oil, drained)\n- 1 tbsp red wine vinegar\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 small garlic clove\n- 1/2 tsp honey\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Pita\n- If using whole pita rounds, cut them in half to form pockets, or keep them whole and slice open after melting the cheese.\n\n## Build the Melt\n- Spread pesto inside each pita piece.\n- Layer with chicken, mozzarella, fresh basil, and a spoonful of tomato vinaigrette.\n\n## Cook the Melt\n- Preheat a skillet or panini press over medium heat.\n- Lightly brush the outside of the pita with olive oil.\n- Toast each side until the bread turns golden and crispy, and the cheese is fully melted.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Drizzle with cashew cilantro jalapeño dressing.\n- Garnish with additional basil or a sprinkle of chili flakes, if desired.\n- Serve hot and enjoy!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('597','Chicken and Goat Cheese Sandwich with Muhammara','## Main Sandwich Ingredients\n- 2 pieces of cooked chicken (grilled, roasted, or pan-seared)\n- 1/4 cup muhammara (roasted red pepper and walnut spread)\n- 2 oz goat cheese, crumbled\n- 1 handful mesclun greens (or baby arugula)\n- 2 slices of sourdough bread (or your preferred bread)\n- Olive oil for toasting\n- Optional: A drizzle of balsamic glaze for added sweetness\n\n## Muhammara Ingredients\n- 1 cup roasted red peppers (jarred or homemade)\n- 1/4 cup walnuts, toasted\n- 1 clove garlic\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp lemon juice\n- 1/2 tsp cumin\n- Salt & pepper to taste','## Make the Muhammara\n- In a blender or food processor, combine the roasted red peppers, toasted walnuts, garlic, olive oil, lemon juice, and cumin.\n- Blend until you achieve a smooth and creamy texture.\n- Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n## Toast the Bread\n- Drizzle olive oil into a skillet and warm it over medium heat.\n- Toast the sourdough slices on each side until they are golden and crispy.\n\n## Assemble the Sandwich\n- Spread muhammara generously on one slice of the toasted bread.\n- Layer the chicken on top, followed by the crumbled goat cheese and mesclun greens.\n- For a sweet and tangy touch, you can drizzle balsamic glaze over the greens if desired.\n\n## Finish and Serve\n- Place the second slice of bread on top to complete the sandwich.\n- Cut the sandwich in half for easier handling.\n- Serve immediately while warm.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('598','Grilled Lime Chicken Salad with Mango and Arugula','## Salad\n- 2 cups arugula\n- 1/2 cup shredded red cabbage\n- 1 mango, peeled and sliced\n- 1 cup grape tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cup goat cheese crumbles\n- 1/4 cup slivered almonds\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil leaves\n\n## Dressing\n- 3 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp honey\n- 1 tbsp lime juice\n- 1 tsp Dijon mustard\n- 1 clove garlic, finely grated\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n- Optional: Pinch of chili flakes\n\n## Chicken\n- 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- Zest of 1 lime\n- Juice of 1 lime\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp honey\n- 1/2 tsp chili powder\n- 1/4 tsp smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste','## Prepare the Chicken\n- In a bowl, mix lime zest, lime juice, olive oil, honey, chili powder, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Add chicken breasts to the marinade and ensure they are well coated. Allow to marinate for at least 20 minutes or up to 2 hours for enhanced flavor.\n\n## Cook the Chicken\n- Heat a grill or skillet over medium heat.\n- Cook the chicken until golden brown and cooked through, about 6-7 minutes per side.\n- Let the chicken rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n## Make the Dressing\n- In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, honey, lime juice, Dijon mustard, and garlic.\n- Season with salt, pepper, and chili flakes, if desired.\n\n## Assemble the Salad\n- In a large bowl, combine arugula, red cabbage, mango slices, grape tomatoes, goat cheese, and almonds.\n- Add sliced chicken and basil leaves.\n- Drizzle with the dressing and toss gently to combine.\n\n## Serve\n- Plate the salad and enjoy your meal!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('599','Grilled Chicken Salad with Cashew-Cilantro Dressing','## Main Ingredients\n- Mesclun greens\n- Kale\n- 2 boneless skinless chicken breasts\n- 1 hard-boiled egg\n- 1 avocado\n- Parmesan crisps\n- Grape tomatoes\n- Red onion\n\n## Dressing\n- 1 cup fresh cilantro (packed, stems are fine)\n- 1/2 cup raw cashews (soaked 15–30 mins in hot water if not using a high-powered blender)\n- 1 jalapeño (remove seeds for less heat, leave them in for spice)\n- 1 garlic clove\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice (1 lime)\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt (or to taste)\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin (optional, adds earthiness)\n- 1/2 cup water (adjust for thickness)\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil (optional, for extra richness)\n\n## Chicken Seasoning\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika\n- 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- Juice of 1/2 lime','## Chicken Preparation\n- Pat the chicken dry and gently pound it to ensure an even thickness.\n- In a bowl, combine olive oil, garlic powder, smoked paprika, cumin, salt, pepper, and lime juice.\n- Coat the chicken thoroughly with the spice mixture and let it marinate for at least 15 minutes or up to overnight.\n- Preheat a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat.\n- Grill the chicken for 5–6 minutes on each side until fully cooked and the internal temperature is 165°F (74°C).\n- Allow the chicken to rest for 5 minutes, then slice it thinly against the grain.\n\n## Dressing Preparation\n- If you''re not using a high-speed blender, soak the cashews in hot water for 15-30 minutes and drain.\n- Place all dressing ingredients into a blender or food processor and blend until completely smooth.\n- If the dressing is too thick, incorporate additional water, one tablespoon at a time.\n- Taste and refine the seasoning, adding more salt or lime juice if necessary.\n\n## Salad Assembly\n- In a large bowl, combine mesclun greens, kale, sliced chicken, chopped hard-boiled egg, diced avocado, Parmesan crisps, halved grape tomatoes, and sliced red onion.\n- Drizzle the cashew-cilantro dressing over the ingredients and toss gently to combine.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve the salad on plates and enjoy your flavorful, high-protein meal!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('600','Creamy White Chicken Chili','## Base Ingredients\n- 1 small yellow onion, diced\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 (14.5 oz) cans chicken broth\n- 1 (7 oz) can diced green chilies\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1/2 tsp paprika\n- 1/2 tsp dried oregano\n- 1/2 tsp ground coriander\n- 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper\n- Salt & freshly ground pepper, to taste\n\n## Additional Ingredients\n- 1 (8 oz) package light cream cheese, cut into cubes\n- 1 can corn, drained and rinsed\n- 2 cans cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 1 tbsp fresh lime juice\n- 2 tbsp chopped cilantro\n\n## For Serving\n- Tortilla chips\n- Monterrey jack cheese\n- Avocado\n\n## Protein Component\n- 1 Rotisserie Chicken, shredded','## Preparation\n- Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Sauté the diced onion for about 4 minutes until soft, then add the minced garlic and sauté for an additional 30 seconds.\n\n## Simmering\n- Stir in the chicken broth, diced green chilies, cumin, paprika, oregano, coriander, cayenne pepper, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a gentle boil, then lower the heat to medium-low and let it simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.\n\n## Blending\n- Drain and rinse the beans and corn. Transfer one can of beans to a food processor or blender with about 1/2 cup of the broth from the pot. Blend until smooth.\n\n## Final Cooking\n- Add the cream cheese, corn, remaining whole beans, and the blended bean mixture to the pot. Let everything simmer together for about 5 minutes until the cream cheese is melted and the chili is creamy.\n\n## Finishing Touches\n- Stir in the lime juice and chopped cilantro. Gently fold in the shredded rotisserie chicken.\n\n## Serving\n- Serve hot, garnished with tortilla chips, Monterrey jack cheese, and avocado slices on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('601','High-Protein Beef and Bean Chili','## Main Ingredients\n- 2 tbsp canola oil\n- 1 large yellow onion, finely diced\n- 1.5 lb extra lean hamburger meat or seitan\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 2 small zucchinis, diced\n- 1 can corn kernels, drained\n- 1 can black beans, drained\n- 1 can pinto beans, drained\n- 1 (28 oz) can diced tomatoes with juices\n- 1 (14 oz) can diced tomatoes with juices\n- 1/2 cup water (more if desired)\n- 1/4 cup dark brown sugar\n- 2 heaping tsp fajita spice\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper\n- 1/8 tsp cinnamon\n\n## For Serving\n- Cheddar cheese, grated\n- Sour cream\n- Cilantro, chopped\n- Tortilla chip strips\n- Avocado, diced','## Preparation\n- Heat the canola oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the diced onion and sauté until it''s translucent and begins to brown slightly, about 5 minutes.\n- Incorporate the ground hamburger or seitan into the pot and cook until it''s lightly browned, roughly 8-10 minutes.\n\n## Cooking\n- Mix in the diced red bell pepper and zucchini, cooking them for an additional 5 minutes.\n- Stir in the corn kernels, black beans, pinto beans, diced tomatoes along with their juices, water, and dark brown sugar.\n- Add the fajita spice, cumin, cayenne pepper, and cinnamon, stirring everything together until well combined.\n- Lower the heat to a simmer, partially cover the pot, and let it cook for 20-25 minutes or until the mixture becomes thick and soupy. Cook longer if softer vegetables are preferred.\n\n## Serving\n- Optionally, garnish with grated cheddar cheese and fresh cilantro before serving.\n- Serve with sour cream, tortilla chip strips, and diced avocado if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('602','Grilled Salmon with Black Beans and Mango Mustard Sauce','## Black Beans\n- 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, undrained\n- 1/2 cup chopped red or green bell pepper\n- 2 teaspoons instant minced onion\n- 2 teaspoons ground cumin\n- 1 teaspoon chili powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n## Mango Mustard Sauce\n- 1 cup sliced mango\n- 1 1/2 tablespoons cider vinegar\n- 1 1/2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 1/8 teaspoon garlic powder\n- Dash of salt and pepper\n\n## Salmon\n- 4 salmon fillets\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n## For Serving\n- 3 cups cooked white sticky rice','## Prepare the Salmon\n- Season the salmon fillets with salt and pepper.\n- Grill or bake in a preheated oven at 425°F (218°C) for approximately 10 minutes per inch of thickness, or until the salmon flakes easily with a fork.\n- Keep the fillets warm once done.\n\n## Prepare the Black Beans\n- Drain the black beans, reserving 1/3 cup of the liquid from the can.\n- Combine the beans, reserved liquid, bell pepper, minced onion, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, and salt in a saucepan.\n- Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n## Prepare the Mango Mustard Sauce\n- Blend the mango, cider vinegar, Dijon mustard, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a food processor until smooth or slightly chunky, depending on your preference.\n- Transfer the mixture to a microwave-safe dish and heat in the microwave for 1-2 minutes until the sauce is warm.\n\n## Assemble the Dish\n- Place a portion of the black beans on each plate.\n- Position a salmon fillet on top of the beans.\n- Drizzle the warm mango mustard sauce over the salmon.\n- Serve with the white sticky rice on the side.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('603','Halibut in Curry Sauce','## Curry Sauce\n- 12 green onions\n- 1/4 cup minced garlic\n- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro (packed)\n- 4 kaffir lime leaves\n- 4 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 3 tablespoons red curry paste\n- 1 tablespoon paprika\n- 1 (13.5-ounce) can coconut milk\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 2 tablespoons fish sauce\n\n## Fish Packets\n- 6 halibut fillets\n- Juice of one lemon\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 6 sections of banana leaves (found in the frozen section of Asian markets)\n- Aluminum foil','## Prepare the Curry Sauce\n- Trim the woody centers from the kaffir lime leaves.\n- In a food processor, combine green onions, garlic, cilantro, and lime leaves; blend into a smooth paste.\n- Heat the vegetable oil in a sauté pan over medium-high heat, then add the paste; cook for several minutes until it becomes aromatic.\n- Mix in the red curry paste and paprika; cook for an additional two minutes.\n- Open the can of coconut milk, scoop out the thick cream on top, and add it to the pan, keeping the remaining liquid aside.\n- Add the sugar and fish sauce; bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until it thickens slightly.\n\n## Prepare the Fish Packets\n- Rinse the halibut fillets under cold water, then pat them dry with paper towels.\n- Place each fillet on a banana leaf section positioned over a piece of aluminum foil.\n- Season the fish with salt, pepper, and a good squeeze of lemon juice.\n- Generously spoon the curry sauce over each fillet, ensuring they are well-coated.\n- Fold the banana leaves over the fish, then wrap tightly with aluminum foil to form a sealed packet.\n- Allow the packets to sit and marinate for a minimum of 30 minutes, up to 4 hours, in the refrigerator.\n\n## Cook the Fish\n- Preheat your oven to 450°F (232°C).\n- Position the foil-wrapped packets on a baking sheet.\n- Bake in the preheated oven for 14 minutes; increase the baking time slightly if using thicker fillets.\n\n## Serve\n- Carefully unwrap the packets and place the fish over a serving of hot steamed rice.\n- Drizzle additional curry sauce over the top before serving.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('604','No-Bake Protein Energy Balls','## Main Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup peanut butter\n- 1/4 cup honey (or date syrup or coconut syrup)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/3 cup protein powder\n- 1/3 cup flaxseed meal\n- 1/2 cup rolled oats\n- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n- 1 tablespoon mini chocolate chips\n- Optional: 1/4 cup shredded coconut','## Using a Food Processor\n- In the food processor bowl, combine peanut butter, honey, vanilla extract, protein powder, flaxseed meal, oats, cinnamon, and chia seeds.\n- Pulse until the mixture is well combined.\n- Add chocolate chips and coconut, if using, and pulse a few more times.\n- Use a medium cookie scoop or your hands to form the mixture into 10 balls.\n- Place the balls in an airtight container.\n\n## Without a Food Processor\n- Mix the wet ingredients in a medium bowl until blended.\n- Stir in the dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly until a dough forms.\n- Use your hands to work the dough if necessary.\n- If the dough is too dry, incorporate more nut butter or sweetener until it holds together.\n- Roll into 10 balls and place in an airtight container.\n\n## Storage and Serving\n- Refrigerate for up to 1 week, or freeze for up to 2 months.\n- Enjoy as a quick, protein-packed snack!','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('605','Vodka Sauce Pasta with Grilled Chicken','## Pasta and Sauce\n- 8 oz rotini pasta (reserve 1 cup pasta water)\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 small onion, diced\n- 1 tbsp minced garlic\n- 1 tsp red pepper flakes\n- 1 tbsp tomato paste\n- 1 tbsp butter\n- 1 tbsp vodka\n- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n- 1/2 cup shredded Parmesan cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh basil for garnish\n\n## Chicken\n- 1 large chicken breast\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1 tsp paprika\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp butter','## Prepare the Chicken\n- Season both sides of the chicken breast with garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.\n- Heat a cast iron skillet over medium-high heat and add olive oil and butter.\n- Cook the chicken breast for about 5-7 minutes on each side, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).\n- Remove the chicken from the skillet and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.\n\n## Prepare the Pasta and Sauce\n- Cook the rotini pasta according to package instructions. Reserve 1 cup of pasta water, then drain the pasta and set aside.\n- In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, red pepper flakes, and minced garlic, sautéing until they become fragrant and the onion becomes translucent.\n- Stir in the tomato paste, butter, vodka, and heavy cream. Cook continuously for 2-3 minutes, stirring, and adjust the heat if needed to prevent burning.\n- Gradually incorporate the shredded Parmesan, stirring until melted. If the sauce is too thick, slowly add reserved pasta water until the desired consistency is reached.\n- Reduce heat to low-medium and simmer for 5 minutes to allow the flavors to meld, adding salt and pepper to taste.\n- Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and toss to coat evenly.\n\n## Serve\n- Plate the pasta and top with sliced chicken breast.\n- Garnish with fresh basil and additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.','default_thumbnail.jpg',NULL,NULL,'created_on');
